reviews.comment:
We visited The Melt with a group of friends and had a pretty good experience overall. The place has limited seating and is self-serve only, so be prepared for a casual, no-frills dining setup.

The Three Cheese Grilled Sandwich and Tomato Soup were definitely the highlights—rich, flavorful, and exactly what you’d want from a classic comfort food combo. The Garlic Parmesan Fries were decent but didn’t stand out, and the Spicy Chicken Sandwich was okay but not particularly memorable.

If you’re craving a solid grilled cheese and soup, this spot is worth a visit.

The food is above average for the price, and the ambient was surpsingly quiet and chill.  The burgers are simple but balanced. The meat is very good and cooked to a perfect medium-well, though you can order a well done optionally.

This place is generous on the cheese and lean on the sauce, which means their bread doesn't get very soggy. The ingredients overall are good.

The soda is a local craft alternative that is very good, and on its own a huge plus.

Overall, it is not necessarily special or fancy, and it is priced as an intermediate fast food place at what should be a bit over 15-20$ per person. But it is far preferable compared to The Habit, Five Guys, or Inn N Out.

We went for lunch and it's definitely worth checking out. However, service was very slow, the restaurant is very expensive and as it was a very cold day and they had their garage doors open, it was freezing inside. We ordered a lot of dishes as everything is shareable and the sizes of the dishes vary a lot. Some of the dishes have the same flavors like the sauce on the green beans and the loaded fries, as well as the chutney and salad. The chicken with lettuce cups was very bland. Our favorite was the poke salad.

So excited to try Chef Izard’s latest restaurant and it did not disappoint! We went for brunch on a Sat and the place was 3/4 full at noon. We ordered the Crispy Quinoa Tuna Poke Salad, Pork Belly Biscuit, Yolk-Onomiyaki, Potato Crepe, and House Maple Sausage.  Everything was well seasoned and played beautifully.  A special treat to see Chef Izard in the kitchen training the goats.  🐐 Can’t wait to check out dinner (especially the green beans!)

name: Metro City Restaurant & Bar
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
It is always nice checking out local spots while traveling, so one of the nights we were in town we decided to stop by Metro City. We went later in the evening on a Sunday so there wasn't a ton of people inside which was nice. Our server was friendly & quick to take our orders and get our drinks out to us.

The food was delicious! We tried the Brotatoes as an appetizer which were so good. We all enjoyed the main dishes we picked out as well, everything was cooked exactly how we wanted it and everything was packed full of flavor. The California pasta I picked out was a zhuge hit for me! The flavors were on point. I would stop by again if I were to be in the area again.

The location was cute, it is in a historic area of town and is along side many other local restaurants & businesses in an easily walkable street.

Ordered the Philly cheese steak sandwich with fries, and the chicken & waffles.

Philly cheese steak sandwich was really bland. And the meat tasted like it had been microwaved. The sandwich could've also used more cheese.

The chicken and waffles were also bland. This dish should be sweet and savory, but the waffle had no flavor, the syrup was not good, and the chicken strips were missing seasoning.

Maybe we would've had better luck ordering something else. But if you're going to try either of these two, keep in mind they're bland. If you like bland, then these are the dishes for you!

Our waitress was very kind. I believe her name was Wendy.

Lots of veggie/vegan options. Very tasty and nice vibe. Slightly on the expensive end though.
The horchata latte was delicious!

Excellent small plate south American flavor restaurant. The service was quick and the taste of the food was well balanced. There are outside seating arrangements available and also large groups of people can be seated. A good quick bite place worth visiting.

Delicious Food and Great Service!
Hunan House is a hidden gem in the Bay Area! The food is consistently flavorful, with bold and authentic Hunan-style dishes. The spicy dishes, like the preserved eggs with eggplant and hunan style sautéed pork are an absolute must-try if you love heat.

The service is attentive and friendly, and the staff is happy to recommend dishes if you’re unsure. The atmosphere is cozy and perfect for a casual meal with friends or family.

If you’re in the area and craving delicious Chinese food with a spicy kick, Hunan House is definitely worth a visit!

Would you like me to include anything more specific about the restaurant?

This place serves spicy and flavorful Chinese food at reasonable prices, with great service. The dishes I tried were perfectly seasoned, striking the right balance of spice and flavor. Highly recommend!

Feels Like We Got Sea Breeze!

Frankly, this place delivers a pleasant, airy vibe.

The staff is genuinely nice, and the cleanliness is adequate.

What impressed me was the authentic Japanese menu. They don't cut corners – using proper sumeshi is a clear sign of quality.

The food, drinks, and overall atmosphere were enjoyable.

No frills, just a solid experience. Recommended.

Good selection of food options - portions are adequate and seafood tasted fresh. The ceviche appetizer was not great but the Pupu platter, edamame, crudely sprout and corn sides were great, double rainbow roll, miso blackened cod, ceviche bowls, were nicely put together (a little more sashimi would have been better balanced)

I ordered the Chimichurri Steak and Tomato Basil soup. The steak was very good, but more on the well done side vs the picture that sold me which is a nice medium rare. The soup was thick and creamy. Delicious.  And the sides were great. I would go again.

Really enjoyed my lunch here, as did the rest of my family. The service was great and the person doing the ordering was super helpful. Drink selection was also great. I have nothing but good things to say.  Definitely would go back.
Very nice restaurant. We enjoyed Chicken shawarma hummus, it is best for 2-3 people. The bar is beautifully decorated. Falafel is okay too. Will try again sometime.

Yummy Yummy. Great portion sizes and even better flavor. This is the kind of place where I wanna go and try the entire menu 😋.. ok I'm being a fatty.. but i will surely will be back. Good cozy atmosphere , our waitress could have been a bit more attentive that is the only meh thing. Overall 5 stars

name: Delhi to Kathmandu, Restaurant & Bar
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
We went to this Indo-Chinese restaurant on Murphy Avenue in Sunnyvale on a Saturday evening. Visually, with its grand chandeliers and knocker back chairs, the place sets the mood for a great dining experience. Now, onto the experience.
The service was painfully slow. To be fair, Jenito did warn us about the delay, and given it was a Saturday night, we tried to be patient. But the wait to be seated and served felt excessive, even with the heads-up. The chicken soup came with an unexpected punch of coriander, but we were given vinegar and hot sauce right away when we asked for some. The chicken fried rice had a strange boiled rice aroma , and came with bits of coated chicken, which didn’t quite hit the mark. The malai kebabs seemed overcooked. The chilli chicken was perfectly spicy and saucy. Honestly, their Indian menu might be the safer bet.  That said, Jenito stood out for being kind and attentive, checking in with another staff member about our food which we appreciated.

Lovely new place in Downtown Sunnyvale (Murphy) Their veggie appetizers- beetroot kebabs, paneer 65 and tandoori momos were especially delicious. Sweeden - our server was very friendly and gave some good recommendations. He even accommodated birthday celebrations which was sweet! Had a pleasant experience here, highly recommend!

There are many restaurants on the street. We picked this one to try something new. We are not disappointed.  We recommend the tea leaves salad, with a unique taste unlike other salads. We also like the egg plant dish with yummy sauce, best served with rice. We would come back to try other dishes

The decoration in the restaurant is relatively old. Service is good, food is okay.

We ordered plata with chicken curry dip and it came REALLY quick. Tasted ok but I feel the taste of curry could have gone stronger.

We also got eggplant shrimp and chili beef. Both were good but definitely not the best we had.

We were comparing Burma Taste with other Burma food in the Bay Area, and we thought other Burma restaurant probably had better atmosphere and better tasting food. This place is ok and we’ll prob go somewhere else.

For drinks, we really recommend Burma Dream cocktail! Very interesting mixture of mango flavor

What a wonder owner Julie is. She had the perfect venue for my friends daughter birthday 🎂. Plenty of eating, dance floor and room for a mechanical bull. 2 bathrooms which was a plus. I plan to keep her place in mind for future events.

You must try the Momos. They tasted good with the orange sauce. I ordered Chicken Chowmein and Chicken Fried Rice as well. I felt the vegetables were a bit undercooked, and there was less soy sauce in these dishes. Overall, the food was average, but this place has a good ambiance. It was nice and quiet. Service was also good.

This Turkish feels like upscale Turkish restaurant with white table cloths. The service is excellent. However, I think we ordered lamb chops but I almost think our food was kebab. Anyway, it tasted good.
Definitely will be back in the future.

Had a great experience having dinner with my colleagues. We all did the $89 meal that included a large selection of their cold and hot appetizers, multiple entrees and desserts.
Our server was attentive and courteous, took her time explaining the dishes, names and descriptions. Great selection of drinks and overall great atmosphere. They had veggie, fish and meat options and were very accommodating to dietary needs
A bit on the expensive side but was a great dining experience overall.
Recommended!

Had a great time here enjoying the food and the ambience.Met a friend after 2 decades and he suggested this place. Food is authentic and very tasty. Lots of parking places nearby. It was not crowded since it was a weekday. Service was excellent.

Ended up going to this place as we wanted a restaurant that serves both Spring Rolls and Gobi Manchurian, to satisfy all the cravings of our party. It wasn’t crowded for a Thursday dinner. Needless to say, we ordered their Spring Rolls and Gobi Manchurian.
Spring Rolls were crispy on the outside but the inside was indiscernible, no distinguishable veggies, just one paste/goo, probably potato. This is a 2/5.
Gobi Manchurian was a 3/5. The Gobi was crispy on the outside, just how it should be, but the sauce was a huge let down. It was very very ketchup-y.
We also ordered Veg Chowmein which was alright, but definitely not worth $16. No veggies of note, nothing expensive like broccoli or snap peas or anything. 3/5 for the taste, 2/5 for the price.
The only dish of note was the Nepalese Veg Thukpa which is soupy noodles, like Ramen. The soup was tasty although the turmeric in it was a bit overpowering. The noodles was the same as the one in chowmein. Good quantity. 4/5.
Didn’t try the momos.
In summary, I think Everest Cuisine is a better option for taste and definitely on the price, and the number of options. Or, there’s always Inchin’s Bamboo garden or Red Hot Chilli Pepper. Similarly priced but better taste and overall experience.

name: Fibbar MaGees
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Ate lunch here recently and the food is really very good and filling. We had fish & chips and the Shepherds pie. If you like fish & chips or Shepherds pie this is the place to get either of them. We've eaten here many times over the years and it's never disappointed. There's both indoor and outdoor seating.

Love this place.  Cool Irish pub. Great beer selection on tap.  Service is always good.  Food I have had is OK.  Reminds me of my years overseas.  And, unlike most places around here they can still poor a black-n-tan.

Wow, I was very impressed with the chicken teriyaki bowl! Was able to enjoy their grand opening promotion and tried to maintain low expectations but they far exceeded them! The big thick and juicy chicken was grilled perfectly and the vegetables were still hot and crunchy. Rice was moist and fluffy. Sauce wasn't overly sweet-a perfect compliment for the meal. A meal just like how I would make at home! I think I'll have to include this place in my usual lineup of weekly restaurants. I hope they will maintain these excellent standards.
Only been here twice so far as it just opened but in general service was friendly and food quality/taste was solid. Prices are decent, makes for a nice neighborhood option as a go to

A couple pints and some finger foods ... all of it was pretty good. In particular, the mushroom empanadas were very tasty. The chicken wings were also good but they are basted in that thick, sticky, sweet sauce, so you gotta like that. Fried calamari was light and fluffy. Beers on tap of several varieties.

Service was fast to start, but we ordered the calamari in the "second batch" and they took 20+ minutes. Not cool. But this has a real brew pub atmosphere and there are games on the tv's. Pretty cool hangout spot.

It was a pretty big location and in an excellent spot.  The beer menu wasn't super large, but it did have a bunch of style options. I ordered their Hazy IPA and it was fine, kinda sweet for me though I think.  I'd probably go back to try some food if in the area, but wouldn't make it a destination trip.

name: Bonchon Sunnyvale
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment:
The soy garlic chicken strips are the best chicken I've had in my entire life. No exaggeration... This is literally the most delicious crispy, slightly sweet, yet savory chicken dish I've ever had in my entire lifetime.  Mic drop.  I can't wrap my head around why anyone would give this less than five stars.

This is the best single meal I've had in over a year (and I've eaten in at least 50 restaurants in the last year).

Used to love this Korean chicken store a lot. However, I feel recently the flavor changed. The chicken wings are not seasoned well, not juicy and flavorful anymore. Disappointed. The soy garlic sauce flavor changed as well, I only tasted salty flavor.
Good thing is they could do half and half.

If you’re seeking an exceptional Persian dining experience in the Bay Area, Chelokababi in Sunnyvale is a must-visit. During our recent visit, we indulged in the Shish Kabab—a delightful skewer of marinated filet mignon, bell peppers, and onions, grilled to perfection over charcoal. The meat was incredibly juicy and tender, bursting with authentic flavors that transported us straight to the heart of Persia. Accompanied by fragrant saffron basmati rice and barbecued tomatoes, the dish was a harmonious blend of taste and tradition.  ￼ ￼

We also sampled a variety of other meat dishes, including the Kabab Koobideh and Joojeh Kabab. Each was expertly prepared, showcasing the restaurant’s commitment to quality and authenticity. The Kabab Koobideh, made from marinated lean ground beef, was flavorful and succulent, while the Joojeh Kabab featured tender chicken fillet pieces, marinated and garnished with saffron—a true Persian delicacy.  ￼ ￼

The ambiance of Chelokababi is warm and inviting, with elegant decor that enhances the dining experience. The staff were attentive and knowledgeable, providing excellent service throughout our meal. It’s evident that Chelokababi takes pride in offering authentic Persian cuisine, making it a standout choice for anyone craving traditional flavors in the Bay Area.

Whether you’re a connoisseur of Persian food or new to the cuisine, Chelokababi offers a memorable dining experience that delights the senses. Highly recommended!

Excellent Persian food. High quality, huge portions and very flavourful. I get the beef koobideh and chicken koobideh plate and my husband loves the shish kabob. The meat is sooooo tender it’s quite amazing. Rice is fluffy. Masto mooser is thick and creamy. They often have Tahdig if you ask for it. I love this place!

We visited on a weekday with a group of 11 adults and four children to celebrate a birthday.

Our party was seated in the upstairs area, which I believe serves as the venue’s party hall. Unfortunately, the ambiance left much to be desired-there was little atmosphere, the speakers were uncomfortably loud, and the temperature was quite warm, especially given the hot weather outside.

The drinks were underwhelming, and the appetizers were just average. The only standout dish was the chili chicken, which had some genuinely good flavor.

On a positive note, the service was excellent. Allwyn took great care of our group and was always attentive and responsive. His service was, in fact, the highlight of our evening.

The total bill came to about $40 per person. For that price, the experience felt far from upscale, and there are definitely better dining options available in the Bay Area at a similar cost.

Went for my Birthday Brunch Buffet at 12pm on a weekend. Surprisingly, we were the only people at that time. As vegetarians, we were delighted to find so many veg options both in appetizers and main course. Desserts were okayish.
There were dahi kebab, crispy baby corn, paneer bakalava, paneer tikka wrap, samosa chaat, aloo tikki chaat and also live pani puri counter with 3 different pani (imli, pudina and orange) options. Veg main course included aloo poori, choley bhaturey, idli sambhar vada, paneer tikka, yellow dal tadka, veg pulav, hakka noodles and paneer manchurian.
They even served freshly made bhaturey, bedmi poori, aloo paratha and butter nan.

All in all it was worth $24 per person.

Stongly recommend!!

Went there because I heard them for a very long time. Their meat was fresh at the service was pretty good. I definitely felt like they were trying very hard to give us service to get tips and they are not very attentive. The environment was very cute and very modern. I liked their display of cocktail by the door when you walked in. I think overall consider their price. It’s a little bit overrated. Also, they didn’t provide us a bag when we asked for a box for takeout. It’s not a big deal, but consider their price tag. I would say their service was not OK.

The food was delicious. Maybe even more so because we waited so long to finally get seated. Be prepared for a bit of a wait. The side dishes were good and the meat was great. This is a spot where they do the cooking for you. The bibimbap and japchae is good too. The vibe was nice and service was on point.

name: Craft House
cuisine: Bar, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Small hangout establishment. The menu on Google is 4 years old so is not relevant anymore.

They have completely different menu right now (11.19.2024), definitely no shishito or edamame or salad anymore.

Drinks and foods have different payment systems. You will have to pay separately.

Drinks price around $9ish.
Foods is definitely overpriced. 1 (ONE) TACO priced for $6++-7++. Chicken bowl priced starting $15++. Burger alone is around $18++ (without fries).

Total food (3 tacos) and 1 drink will cost you around $35.

Ambience: quiet, cozy, good to play cards with a group of friends.

Bathroom: 1 (one) unisex, clean, well maintained.

Parking: free street parking.

Great spot to grab a drink and grab some food from the ABVE the Basics in the back!
Chicharones and a paloma pictured

name: Madras Café
cuisine: Cafe, Store, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Madras Café is a go-to spot for authentic South Indian food in Sunnyvale. The menu is purely vegetarian and packed with classic options—from masala dosa to pongal to filter coffee that’s strong and satisfying.

The place can get very busy, especially on weekends, so expect a bit of a wait. It’s more of a no-frills, fast-casual experience—don’t go in expecting fancy ambiance, but the food more than makes up for it.

Everything is flavorful, fresh, and reasonably priced. Their chutneys and sambar are standout, and they’re generous with portions too. Definitely a favorite for South Indian comfort food in the Bay Area.

Visiting San Francisco and this place is very well known for their South Indian vegetarian dishes. Food was delicious and came out really fast. Quick service. The place could use an update, the atmosphere needs a better vibe, had random music on, would recommend to sticking to Indian theme. All in all, I do recommend this restaurant for South Indian cravings. Filter coffee was nice and strong, yum.

It was my family’s first time eating at Gumba’s and we had the most amazing experience. They’re service was top notch! They were so kind, generous and welcoming.  The food was absolutely delicious. We sat outside, very nice patio seating. We look forward to coming back soon :)

A bit overpriced. My fettuccine carbonara was tasty, but the included salad looked like they didn’t put in any effort to make it presentable - it was just a pile of barely cut vegetables. The Calzone Dijon had too much mustard, which made it hard to eat, and the tiramisu was more like a cake, lacking the creamy texture and moisture.
It would be better if they worked on the presentation of their dishes and adjusted the amount of ingredients they use.

After trying a sandwich from another sourdough bread company location in Sacramento, I was excited to find out that there was a location close by to where I live. I've had sandwiches from all the major chains, and these sandwiches have been the best by far. They don't skimp on meats like many other chains have been doing lately. I came here close to their closing time, and they still accommodated me with extremely friendly service. I got the garlic pesto turkey sandwich and it was large and delicious. I'd definitely recommend this place to anyone in the area. TL;DR - kind service and amazing sandwiches (better than any other local option)

Was looking to grab some quick lunch before getting groceries, and saw there was a new place opened up so had to try it!
The place is bright and inviting, and the servers were extremely friendly and helpful! I had to order the sourdough bread bowl with the clam chowder for my first visit, but so many of their options were sounding very tempting!
Food came out very quickly and both the bread bowl and soup were piping hot! The sourdough has a nice crunchy texture and is clearly freshly baked, the soup is also very tasty! As you can see in the picture they do not skimp on the soup either!
Was a very satisfying lunch, will definitely come back again and try one of their other dishes. The French dip sandwich, for one, is calling out to me already!

name: The Oxford Kitchen and Gastropub
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
The menu suggests there is London as an influence (Britain, UK) but they have strayed a bit from this.

Don’t get me wrong, it’s not bad at all, and I think they have done well to keep the menu size down. They could just be a little more authentic.

Scotch eggs: These were good. Could take a little more salt and pepper but tasty. They are ground lamb scotch eggs, which is not the traditional variety from the UK. Ground pork is the traditional coating around the egg. Great to see the eggs not rock hard inside. Just cooked nicely. And beautifully presented. I would suggest add a small fork to the serving platter if it is being shared. As a group, nobody wanted to use their own “used” fork to take some coleslaw from the platter.

Fish and chips: In the UK fish and chips is served with a piece of fish, typically a fillet or half fillet from the side of the fish. However, here as with most US fried fish presentation, there are rectangular pieces of fish battered and fried. I don’t know why they do this. It is not British though 😆.. There is a side of mushy peas for an extra $2. Don’t waste your money!! They are just the Birds Eye frozen peas (or similar brand), mashed up with a fork. Not mushy peas at all. We did give the feedback but they still charged for them. If you are serving fish and chips and offering mushy peas, have the mushy peas available. Mushy peas are marrowfat peas, not frozen garden peas. A good brand to buy is Bachelors. They are available in tins or dried (if using dried: soak, add bicarb and salt and boil - google the recipe and really make them authentic!)

Bangers & Mash (Sausages): Very good. The sausages were good, the mash very good, and kale went well and not over cooked. If this establishment gets proper mushy peas, they could offer them as a kale alternative, as this would also be British in style.

Service was pretty good, though the bangers and mash took significantly longer to arrive while everyone politely waited to start eating.

Would I go back? Yes.

I came here to celebrate my father's birthday.

Upon arrival, we were greeted and there was plenty of seating for my party. All the main entrees on the menu were pretty expensive and did not strike me as very appetizing.

Upon ordering, the food took forever (20-30 minutes) to arrive at my table, despite the business not looking very busy on a Saturday night.

I ordered the Fish and Chips which I assumed was the safe option but turned out to be a mistake. The fish was extremely bland and I had to nearly force myself to finish once I exhausted the small portion of dipping sauce that accompanied the dish. The chips were decent. Overall I enjoyed the appetizer the most which was a deep-fried Macaroni and Cheese plate.

To the restaurants credit, they did provide my father a complimentary dessert which he seemed to enjoy.

Overall, my party did not enjoy the food or experience enough to be keen on returning for a 2nd time in the near future.

Ordered a small boneless honey garlic chicken and cheese fries. The cheese fries were a fun twist on fries. They were long fries coated in a cheese powder with a spicy almost gochujang like sauce. The chicken was nice and crispy, the meat was the right amount of firm inside. Overall the flavor coating on the chicken was a good pick, definitely does not make you feel over-sauced at the end. Place gets busy during the dinner rush. Otherwise, very chill place to grab a bite and chitchat. Service was fast and enough parking outside in the plaza.
It was so good! Chicken was fried and served hot, while the customer service was pretty good. You can sit down and enjoy the food whenever you want buy online order or via a kiosk.

name: Bawarchi Biryanis Sunnyvale
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
We went to Bawarchi today, and it was amazing! The food was super tasty, and the service was so warm and welcoming. We absolutely loved the place! The prices are quite reasonable, but the quality of the food is top-notch. And the cherry on top? Dessert! ‘Double Ka Meetha’ was an absolute game-changer. It just melts in your mouth! A must-try for sure. Also, a big shoutout to the owner, Mr. Vishnu -such a charming and kind person who made sure we were comfortable the whole time. Definitely our new favorite spot for fresh and comforting food!

Oh, and we just found out they’re starting a live Pani Puri counter soon—can’t wait to try it!

Finally, a slice of Hyderabad right here in Sunnyvale! From the very first bite of their Chicken 555, I felt transported back to the streets of Hyderabad. Perfectly crispy, spicy, and bursting with flavor—it’s everything you’d expect and more. Their Hyderabad Chicken Dum Biryani is a masterpiece, capturing the authentic aroma and taste that only true Hyderabadi biryani can deliver. The Gongura Mutton Biryani is a delightful reminder of home, with the tangy gongura perfectly complementing the tender mutton.

And let’s talk about the Kalakand—so fresh and buttery, it melts in your mouth like a sweet dream. Pairing all this with a chilled Thumbs Up made the experience complete.

This place has truly brought a piece of Hyderabad to Sunnyvale, and I can’t wait to go back for more! A must-visit for anyone craving that irreplaceable Hyderabadi love in every bite.

First time visiting this restaurant and enjoyed their carnitas burrito which was the perfect size. Beans and rice were served on the side which is exactly the way I like it. It was served topped with sauce and set up to be eaten with a fork and knife.  My friend ordered an enchilada, taco, and chilli rellenos (sp?). Everything was great. Place was clean. Noise level comfortable. Service was excellent. Will visit again.

Really like their vegetarian selection. We ordered the nachos, the veggie burrito, and the combination plate with two enchiladas. All dishes had a variety of veggies in them — carrots, broccoli, etc, instead of just cheese or bell peppers alone.

The spicy salsas were given on the side; small kids were able to handle the baseline spice level of the food.

Attentive staff and well lit casual space make it a fun lunch spot.

Worst food you can ask for sadly. Mostly no protein all veggies. Very underwhelming taste. The chicken curry tasted like water boiled chicken. And the Mongolian beef had almost three pieces of meat and the rest was vegetables. Again no taste at all. ZERO flavor. Zipppp flavor. Very very disappointed

Old school Chinese American food.

I came for the Chinese chicken salad that they’ve been known for forever.  It’s good, but I’ve had better.

The wonton soup is an odd thicker dark brown soup.  Strange but they said that’s how they’ve been making it for 50 years.  I like a clear wonton broth.

Lunch specials are a good deal.  They range from about $14-$20.  Not bad these days.

Service was better than I expected.
Clean and updated inside.

This place never disappoints. It is perhaps the only good, proper sit-down Mexican restaurant within a 2-3 mile radius. Keep coming back here for the food. I’ve not seen it to be fully packed ever, neither during lunch nor dinner. The service isn’t the fastest but absolutely love everything that we order. Of course, I have no semblance to what “authentic” Mexican is, but the food is tasty, served hot, loaded with veggies. The house hot sauce is one of the best I’ve tried. Good amount of options for veggies. Veggie quesadilla is very tasty and filling. The Chile Relleno de Vegetales was good (it is deep fried in egg batter). Enchiladas Verdes is really good too. Chile en Nogada is very different, with fruits and nuts, enjoyable though. Overall, a place that consistently delivers.

I love this place! It’s the best Mexican restaurant I’ve ever tried. I absolutely love the Swiss enchiladas—I could eat them every day and never get tired of them. My kids love coming here too. Plus, the service from Davy and andrea makes you fall in love with the place even more—they’re incredibly kind and attentive.

name: Merit Vegan Restaurant
cuisine: Bakery, Meal Takeaway, Store, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Been here a couple times already and yeah if you’re vegetarian or vegan, this place is the one. Like, stop scrolling, this is it.

Tons of variety. Like, the kind of menu where you stare at it for 10 minutes thinking, am I hungry or just emotionally unprepared to make a decision?

Had the spicy noodle soup before fantastic. Fresh spring rolls? Honestly hard to beat. But this time I went for the house special rice clay pot and it blew me away. Full of flavor, perfectly balanced, and straight-up comfort food for the soul.

Also tried the BBQ gluten vermicelli refreshing and super flavorful. Doesn’t even feel like “vegetarian food,” it just tastes good.

Showed up on a Saturday around 2pm thinking I could sneak in between the lunch rush…absolutely wrong. The place was packed. But for good reason.

This is definitely one of those spots you keep coming back to just to explore the menu. Every dish feels like a new main character.

I was thrilled to find a vegan restaurant around the southern Bay Area, and this one was at a convenient location. After visiting here, I would definitely recommend it as an economical option for anyone that wants to enjoy decent southeast Asian vegan food! Almost every dish was below $15 which made it really affordable, on top of what I had being extremely tasty!

The establishment's slogan about promoting vegan dining is very clear, and as much as I am not vegan myself, I love it when veganism is available as an option. As a result, I ordered the eggplant tofu clay pot, which was amazingly delicious. While I was not sure what house special sauce they had used, it definitely tasted a bit like there was garlic sauce included, which made the eggplant tasty. One can pour some of the sauce on top of the given rice, which I ended up picking brown rice, and it would make the whole thing super tasty. Either way, I very much enjoyed it. In terms of the spring rolls, they tasted as good as I imagined it to be, because the peanut sauce carried the main flavor when dipping the rolls in it. Mint leaves, tofu, vegetables altogether allowed a mixture of different flavors that made it a pleasant culinary experience. The tom kha tasted  more sour than sweet, most likely because it didn't have enough coconut milk, which wasn't a bad thing and would be dependent on different people's tastes.

Overall I think this establishment is one that anyone can easily trust to create good, quick, and cheap food. While I don't live around the area, I would recommend it to anyone who does.

By far one of the best vegetarian Indian restaurants. The quality, taste and aroma are unbelievable. Just the right amount of spices, makes every bite an explosion of flavors.
Lakhvir Singh is wonderful, polite and very kind.

I visited Chat Bhavan for some chaat and had a great experience! I tried their sev puri and bhel puri—both were good, but the bhel was my favorite. The flavors were well-balanced, and the crunch was just right. I also had their cutting chai, which was decent. They have an extensive menu with plenty of options to explore, so I’ll definitely be back to try more. A great spot for chaat lovers!

An unassuming building at the end of a residential road houses this interesting eatery. The decor is simple and the interiors reminded me of an old Pakistani college canteen.

We went around dinner time so there were a bit of a crowd, but we quickly found place to sit and ordered a number of things. The appetizers are good, especially dahi puri was presented well and tasted good.

The zinger burger was ok, and I wished it had more zing in it than just deep fried breaded chicken. The anday wala burger aka bun kabob took the cake. It was very nicely done. The texture and flavor were excellent. The sauce tangy and nice. Overall a great item to eat here.

We also tried the paratha chicken roll which was at par.

Service is good and they kept the place clean and good. The outside seating area was rained out when we visited but could make for a good place to eat.

Overall, a good experience.

We ordered the Zinger Burger with Crazy Curry Fries, the Bomb Kebob with Masala Fries, and a Mango Lassi. Everything was delicious, especially the Crazy Curry Fries.
Although I really enjoyed the food, it might be a bit strong in terms of spice for some people. For example, the Crazy Curry Fries contain cilantro, so if you're not a fan, be cautious. As for the Bomb Kebob, while I liked it and found it flavorful, the spice level was somewhat strong, so keep that in mind.

Wow! I liked the flavor, portion size and variety of options at this restaurant. I would definitely come back again. I cannot believe how much I enjoyed their organic chicken soup. It was so delicious and the basil in there hit the mark.  I squeezed in some of the lime after using it on the grilled chicken.  So darn tasty. The pupusa was also very delicious.  I could pass on the corn tortilla but that's only because I didn't grow up with this staple.  The quality of the food was really good and the service was very kind.

Order: Lunch special #1, plato tipico, and horchata Salvadoreño

This place hit the mark on several things when it comes to authentic taste. It's definitely better than a place I visited a few weeks back. I would say this will be a good option for me when craving MY food. Will absolutely save me miles from going to San Francisco for pupusas.

You order at register, and then it's open seating. They have pretty good indoor and outdoor seating. Depending on the time of your visit, this may or may not vary.

I ordered the plato tipico because I wanted to taste multiple items in 1 visit. The curtido and salsa were missing some of the authentic flavor for me, but it was still delicious.

The service could use a little improvement. We waited a while as the cashier took calls. Food took a while to come out. We were not checked on, and I had to call the waitress over when anything was needed, but they were not rude.

It's not a 1 hit wonder, so when that craving hits, I have an option to visit.

We just got back from our trip to Greece. My wife and I were craving good Healthy food. This is a slice of Greece in our homeland. Wonderful place to eat. The Gyro salad & wrap was absolutely delicious.

One of the best outdoor seating areas in the city. Nothing extravagant but yet so beautiful in spring.

Delicious food and warm service! Highly recommended.

name: Fuego Sports Bar and Club
cuisine: Night Club, Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Jody and Taylor were so nice.  They make amazing drinks.  The food was delicious and they offer ufc fights and after the fight the place turns into a club

I have been to Fuego twice and had a great time both times. I enjoy the music and the two dance floors are both pretty lively starting at about 10:30pm.

This time the air was very smoky. Maybe better ventilation would help?

name: Laughing Monk Brewing and Gastropub
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: It took us a long time to get seated despite the space being pretty empty! They were able to seat our party of 6 without a reservation though at 6pm on a Friday. The beers are good and they have a solid selection of cocktails, but limited mocktail options and no non alcoholic beers.  We love the pizza here! So many fun flavors.

There is a show stopping pretzel in the world and it lives here in full suspension and ready to be devoured. I say get a second sweet mustard because you’re going to want to re-dip that thing on repeat. The Salmon / Mediterranean bowl is the way to go for those of us who want to stay snatched and I’d say a solid round of red wines and cava to round out the night if beer is not your thing. Our server was awesome! Juan! And the Laughing Monk should be lucky to have him as this was a packed night but he nailed this crazy packed section with ease and grace sans was the best and just as upbeat and fun as this restaurant. We entered laughing and exited laughing knowing all monks would be proud!

This place is amazing. Been living in the area for so long, I wish I found this place sooner! Everything was so delicious and the portions are very generous. Love that they have many vegetarian options. Will be coming often!

I was very surprised! So nice place and so delicious food! We ordered chicken soup and traditional soup and we ordered small portions, but it was so big bowl!!! Highly recommended this place, because it’s a good deal about portion-delicious-price. Also I want say thanks for smoothies 💕 I lover mango smoothie and it was the best which I tried ever!

Had a great dinner at Fashion Wok in Sunnyvale. We ordered Tsing Tao beers, Sichuan High Wok, Chicken Pork Wonton Soup, and a Beef Wrap. Everything was flavorful and fresh. The Sichuan dish had the perfect amount of spice, and the wonton soup was comforting and rich. Portions were generous, and the prices were very reasonable—our total was just under $62. Friendly service from Cindy made the experience even better. Highly recommend for casual, delicious Chinese food!

Amazing food, great price. The staff was very polite and food came in super quick. Lots of parking space nearby.

Their combination fried rice is a must try.

I order from here regularly. But ate at the restaurant for the first time. Lot of vegetarian and gluten free options. Food is good 😋 especially the variety of Bao 💯
Love the burn garlic fried rice! Service was also great 😊
Loved the decor and service. Wish there were more salads or veggie dishes without soy protein. Quality is ok, definitely not fine dining. Orange chicken was good.

name: The Stand - American Classics Redefined
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: I was really impressed by the stand and I wasn’t expecting to be! First there gluten-free bread is really stellar great taste and they grill it very nicely. I tried the French dip burger, and the soup dip was fantastic with great salted flavor was very really an good grilled onions. My boyfriend also enjoyed His burger on sourdough and pickles.

We are vegetarians and this time did not have a good experience. We ordered 3 different burgers and all replacing beef with veggie option. The veggie burger is very similar to veggie black bean burger available at Costco, if not the same. Second they made prepared one burger with sliced cheese and wax paper of that cheese slice as well. When we showed this to restaurant we had to state what burger it was. We got a replacement veggie burger with bacon on it. Other burger we got had a fried egg included, but by the time it was at table the egg was broken and yolk was seeping through the wrapper. This total experience was a fiasco and the staff seems clueless.
Amazing ambiance. The food is good, but make sure you communicate well with the waiter about the customization of the order. My veg pasta came with only cauliflower.

My wife and I had a wonderful last-minute meal on the patio while visiting Sunnyvale. Arjan (I hope I’m spelling his name correctly) was an amazing server and really made our whole experience. He had great wine recommendations and was very kind and professional. The gnocchi was our favorite dish (it was half-devoured before I thought to take a picture), but it was all delicious. Ask for Arjan as your server and you’ll have a great time.

The food was really good! I got the Beef Birria Tacos the flavor was good but they were on non toasted corn tortillas if there were crispy it would’ve been even better. The service here is good the staff is super nice. It’s really clean here. They have inside and outside sitting.

We celebrated our daughter 18th Birthday and selected the  buffet option for out event. The food was very good specially the mashed potatoes and the ribs. The drinks were great too, the service was outstanding from the moment I contacted Bruce (the manager) , he was prompt in his responses, shared lots of information  helping us make the best decision about our celebration. Once we arrived to the event with our decorations Bruce and  his staff (three waiters) were all hand on,  the tables were already set up as well as multiple heaters because I was concerned we were going to be cold in the patio (we were not cold at all). They help us to set up the  flower arraignments and  ballons we had brought, they also  made sure the fire pits were ready as well as the different games they have four out teen guest, the "water pong" was an all time  favorite given my teens a "college like experience". In addition  Bruce allow us to  play our own music making our event feel completely personalize.  The party was a great success, our guest were happy, we were  very comfortable  with the bill. Clara's Junction is going to be our to go place for  events. I highly recommend them. The facilities, the manager, the staff, the food and the cost is amazing. Great value.  I am glad their are the new addition to our North Santa Clara neighborhood.

Tried for the first time with my colleagues for lunch and was pleasantly surprised. Classic dishes you would expect from any Italian restaurant, but not find them available as easily. Good value for money and family owned restaurant vibe. Will try lasagna next time. My colleagues commented how their seafood pasta’s shrimps have a stronger fishy taste than expected; however, my prawns in my pasta were fine.

Although it was a corporate event. The food, service and atmosphere was amazing.
From starters to mains was wonderful!
A good compliment was the Kendal-Jackson cab sav!
Had the baked penne with sausage and was delicious!
Even the chicken parmesan looked amazing.

name: Holder’s Mission City Grill
cuisine: Cafe, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment: Friendly welcoming service. Coffee immediately available at sit down and all through meal. Positive attentive staff. Food arrived hot and cooked to order. Clean modern bathroom. Sports memberiblia lined the way to the bathrooms. Definitely a place to return to for a comforting dining experience.

Food was very good. We ordered steak and avocado eggs Benedict and California eggs Benedict with sub Canadian bacon for regular bacon both coming with a side of hash browns (the eggs were cook perfectly) and sure coffee ☕️. Portions are normal for a Benedict and price is competitive with similar restaurants.
Our waitress Magdalena C was very friendly, attentive and professional and gave to us a few tips about when it’s a good time to go in weekend and weeks days.
For a dinner style restaurant it’s very nice decor and ambiance.
Definitely I’ll be back to try other dishes, because they have lunch, dinner and breakfast all day
Thank you very much, was a pleasant experience.

Very vibrant and professional service. Attentive waiters, the scene was nice and comfortable. Dishes were well prepared, except the steak salad under cooked and portion sizes decent. They presented a uniformed discount awesome! I would go back.

Came again and had the poke dish, it was phenomenal. The fish taco plate lacked seasoning though.

This place has mixed reviews but we decided to try it because it was late and not much was open. We're glad we did.  We tried the eureka salad with steak, the Asian salad and the truffle fries.
The steak was great. The veggies were crisp and fresh, the dressings were not overpowering flavors. The truffle fries were amazing. Warm and just the right amount of crispy. We did ent have any drinks but they had tons of options. Our server Taylor was really nice and attentive. Patient with us when we ordered and knowledgeable.

Fresh and tasty food, clean environment, fast and good service, good parking.  It is not easy to find such good restaurant, in terms of portion and price, like this one.  I have been its Cupertino location and happy with it food.  This is 2nd time to visit its Santa Clara location.  It is good, too.  Highly recommend this restaurant 😊

Hopefully it will not increase its prices soon 🙏

This is one of my favourite place of Chinese food. Came there 2 days in a raw. I love really spicy food, I used to live in China back in the days. So in the second time chef came to my table and asked if my food is spicy enough. Food was good and not expensive 🥩🥩🔥🔥🔥

I had the pleasure of dining at JOEY Restaurant at Valley Fair in Santa Clara, and I must say—this is a welcome addition to the culinary scene near Santana Row. From the moment I entered, I was struck by the sophisticated yet approachable ambiance. The space is modern, well-appointed, and thoughtfully designed to balance lively energy with comfort, ideal for both casual lunches and special gatherings.

We began our experience with a selection of starters. The Sushi Cone was a standout—featuring tempura shrimp wrapped in a crisp seaweed shell with avocado, spicy mayo, and a delicate pop of tobiko. It delivered a balanced bite of texture and umami that lingered pleasantly.

The Scallop & Shrimp Ceviche brought bright flavors to the table with avocado, red onion, cilantro, mint, and a lemongrass-pineapple dressing. While I appreciated the creativity and tropical flair, I found the lemongrass slightly overpowering and might have preferred a version that leaned more toward a classic Peruvian-style ceviche. That said, the seafood was fresh and expertly prepared, and the housemade yellow corn tortilla chips offered a great vehicle for each bite.

Next came the Spicy Crab Dip, served warm with grilled artisan sourdough. The dip itself was decadent and filled with sweet lump crab meat—clearly the star of the dish. My only note would be the ratio of bread to dip; a bit less bread or a thinner cut might allow the dip to shine more prominently.

For mains, the Sake Glazed Chilean Seabass was nothing short of exceptional. The fish was cooked to a perfect flake, with the richness of the seabass beautifully complemented by the savory-sweet glaze. Accompanied by wok-fired vegetables, gold potatoes, and immersed in a dashi broth, this dish delivered depth and warmth—a comforting yet refined plate.

The JOEY Classic Steak—a 7 oz prime top sirloin—was also a success. Cooked precisely to temperature, it was well-seasoned and juicy, and the real surprise came in the form of their fully loaded crispy mashed potatoes. These were unlike any I’ve had before—creamy inside, crisp on the outside, and topped with an indulgent array of toppings. We paired this dish with a bottle of Daou from Paso Robles, a red that offered bold fruit and elegant structure, enhancing the richness of the steak.

Service throughout was professional, attentive, and genuinely warm. Our server was knowledgeable about the menu and offered insightful wine pairings without being intrusive.

In conclusion, JOEY Valley Fair is a restaurant that balances culinary ambition with crowd-pleasing appeal. While a few minor tweaks could elevate certain dishes, the overall experience was polished, satisfying, and thoughtfully curated. I look forward to returning and exploring more of the menu. This is a strong contender for one of the best upscale-casual dining spots in Santa Clara.

Bravo to the team—and welcome to the neighborhood!

Soft opening for Joey Valley Fair. The vibe of the place is gorgeous; Casablanca meets California. We were seated on the second floor that high open ceilings that closed as the night chill came. All the staff were friendly and helpful. Every table was full so service was a bit slow but we munched on our chicken lettuce wraps and miso mushrooms both tasty so didn’t mind the wait. For entrees we ordered Baja tacos, steak and lobster and steak and sushi. My steak was a little cold but had a good flavor. Sushi was not traditional looking but tasty. Others tried the crème brulee cheesecake which they enjoyed.  Overall great experience and impressed for first night.

I was here on a weekday for lunch with friends and the service was swift and on point. We tried the Shakarkandi/sweet potato chaat, paani puri - both good appetizers but the gobi manchurian look alike was a bomb! The paneer biryani bowl was only satisfactory, sadly because of the overpowering cardamom and the dal could have used a little more salt. Both, the pineapple and mango mojito mocktails were refreshing! Definitely going back to try more.

This is an upscale restaurant with an interesting take on Indian food. Some of their starter dishes are pretty good. They have quite a good selection of vegetarian options. The ambience of the restaurant is great and perfect for a date night or a large group. However prices are pretty expensive and not everything lives up to the hype.
Great healthy seafood options with generous portions. The staff are friendly, the outdoor seating area is great. Very recommended 👌🏼👌🏼👌🏼

Loved this place. Everything about it is so good. We were a large group and the staff manager everything so well.

Ordered - coconut shrimp, East coast lobster roll with sweet potato, grilled lobster tail roll, surf and turf lobster roll, pick a fresh fish with sides, mexican salad bowl, wagyu burger.

Must try - East coast lobster roll with sweet potato, pick a fresh fish with sides, blood orange sprinkling water

Puesto absolutely delivers! From the moment we walked in, the vibe was spot-on—upscale and trendy with an almost Amazonian feel, lush and vibrant. The bar is stunning and sets the tone for a fun, elevated dining experience.

We started with the chips & molcajete salsa and the classic guac—both super fresh and packed with flavor. Then came the passion fruit & mango shrimp ceviche and yellowfin tuna crudo… just wow. So refreshing, bright, and beautifully plated. The tamarindo shrimp tacos were a flavor bomb—sweet, tangy, and perfectly balanced.

But what really made the night was the bartender. We sat at the bar and got completely spoiled with tequila tastings—he walked us through flavor profiles, suggested perfect pairings, and made us feel like VIPs. You can tell they take pride in the experience just as much as the food.

Can’t wait to come back—Puesto is a whole vibe.

Had such an amazing time at Puesto thanks to the incredible team behind the bar—Mario, Miguel, and Hernan. These guys truly made us feel like VIPs from the moment we walked in. Their energy, attentiveness, and kindness made our night unforgettable.

They were not only sweet and fun, but they also went above and beyond to make sure we had a great time—even more attentive than our actual server at times! They offered thoughtful drink recommendations and made sure our experience was perfect from start to finish. Honestly, they were the life of the party and a big reason why I’d come back.

Huge shoutout to them for making our night so special. If you’re headed to Puesto, do yourself a favor and sit at the bar or near it—you’ll be in the best hands!

Get the Yummy Yummy sauce, it’s the best. Came with my family and ordered the combo with Yummy Yummy sauce and it did not disappoint! Seafood was fresh and service was great! We will definitely come back and try other things on the menu!

Excited to bring our family of 5 here for the first time and it was so disappointing we walked right out. Upon entry, My husband and I stood around with our 3 children for 15 minutes with not even so much as an approach or Acknowledgement to seat us. (The restaurant wasn't packed at all) Finally, they got someone to seat us in the corner. And walked away immediately after seating us. No utensils. No waters. No, 'a server will be with you guys shortly' nothing. We sat there another 15min with absolutely no one to approaching us, I accounted it to being short of staff but then people were being sat down after us & served drinks immediately. At that point, with 3 anxious children 3, 5 & 9yrs old- we just got up & walked out.

Customer service was poor- only because we didn't recieve absolutely any service at all.
Can't comment on the food since we didn't even get a sip of water.
Just going to stick to boiling crab.

Walked right over next door to Pho Hoa, immediately was approached by staff, given waters right after we were seated & within the 1st 2 min. Another staff approached to take drink & food orders. Totally different vibe. Much more packed. & more of a vibrant atmosphere.

Roasted Crab was just so disappointing. 🙄
& we've been wanting to try this place out for a LONG time now since we only go to Boiling Crab.

Ordered through doordash - for a kids grilled cheese with fries, onion rings, and a treat yourself dessert. No onion rings, so fries were substituted, which were less than the onion rings cost. The dessert also looks nothing like the picture and I'm pretty sure it didn't come with pound cake, but a French toast style bread with a broken up piece of cheesecake stacked inside.

Decently OKAY food. But $15 for a sandwich I can make at home? No.

What made this place a hell hole is how the person coordinating orders is so damn rude. Literally told me, everyone's prices are increasing with inflation and that I "didn't have to eat there". Damn right I don't, so I had them return my money. Keep your overpriced dry turkey sandwich. Actual reality is this: everyone's prices are increasing because it's trickle down price gouging from suppliers.

Are you really going to try and rationalize $15 for couple layers of turkey, a slice of tomato, bread and cheese? Get real.

Food was pretty good, however it wasn't as exceptional to give 5 stars. The place has a nice vibe but the wait for a table was extremely long. Would recommend coming early or late.
We had the croissant French Toast which was very heavy and the jumbo crab bene was pretty good. They don't have cappuccino or latte which was a bummer, but they do serve regular coffee.

Pleasantly surprised with the quality of food! Great little place for brunch. We had to wait for about 30 minutes for our table, so be prepared if you're super hungry. Parking was a bit hard to find since it was super busy. We had to circle the lot a few times and wait for some people to leave. We sat outside, and there were some space heaters so it wasn't too cold. The sandwiches are definitely worth it.

name: Eataly
cuisine: Grocery Or Supermarket, Store, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Overall concept of an integrated food store and restaurant was appealing. Ambience and service was excellent but food was a let down. Ingredients were fresh but the food lacked any real distinct flavor. Solidly cooked standard fare. Mozzarella cheese to start with was excellent but accompanying bread was borderline stale in its chewiness. Chicken kebab was fine as was ravioli, nothing that would draw you back

Eataly is a food lover’s paradise! It has a gelato station, patisserie, and deli.
The variety of authentic Italian dishes and gourmet products is impressive. Everything is top-notch, from freshly made pasta to delicious pizzas and decadent desserts to fresh product, cheese, and wine collection. The ambiance is vibrant, and the staff is knowledgeable and friendly. A must-visit spot for anyone craving authentic Italian flavors!

The most beautiful restaurant I have ever seen. I fell in love with it ... Great architecture, interiors and ambience. Service and food were excellent and the staff is friendly and hard working. Highly recommend this place if you are in San Jose, California

We went there for the very first time and being vegetarians we did not have much options. There has been only 4-5 options in veg that we could order for main course.The name of appetizers were quite interesting but sadly the taste was not great. However I did order pina colada which tasted like cold milk but the server saw me not liking the drink and he came forward and got me another drink called billionaire which was good .The ambience is great there and food quality is good . The overall service was also good so
I am definitely going there again and cheers to festive season with wonderful decoration.we ordered churros in the end which was quite disappointing too but due to their service I would
Like to give them 3.5 stars.

Very delicious Korean food - our go to spot. If you order the noodles, rice, or meat dishes, it can be enough for two people. The stone bowl bibimbap is my favorite here, I order with tofu and vegetables. Many side dishes provided. The Korean bbq meats can be a bit expensive. Like every Korean bbq, you have to order two meat dishes, which can come out to at least $100 bucks. That’s a bit much on my end, but my wife says the meat quality is fantastic. The service is fantastic - the ladies always do a great job here. We keep coming back with friends.

Came here for team lunch. It took a while for the server to come by and take our order. Also took a while to get our food

We ordered a few appetizers and some entrees. Food tasted great. Good portion size for the price

name: Fleming’s Prime Steakhouse & Wine Bar
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Fleming’s offers top-tier steaks, great service, and a classy vibe. A bit crowded even on weekdays, so reservations are a must. Sides are limited  and wine list are excellent. Perfect for special occasions or a refined night out. Highly recommend!

We had a company dinner at Fleming’s Prime Steakhouse & Wine Bar. While the atmosphere looked upscale, my experience was a bit frustrating. I was seated right next to a private room, and the door kept opening and hitting my chair throughout the evening—really distracting and annoying.

The waitstaff were friendly overall, but some of the service felt rushed—at one point, utensils were dropped onto the table rather than placed properly. As for the food, the steaks had good flavor but were a bit too tough, with a lot of tendon that made them hard to chew.

Unfortunately, I wouldn’t recommend this location for a company gathering. For the price and setting, I expected a more comfortable and polished experience.

First time here but planning to come back often. I really enjoyed their Damascus style lamb shawarma. The toasted bread really makes the difference. Plus the lamb has really good flavor, especially coupled with the hot sauce. I wasn’t a big fan of the driving radish, or whatever the crunchy, purple vegetable was in there but I admit it does add a different taste kick. And the fries were perfectly crispy! Sounds weird, but I really liked those. I couldn’t resist and got a chocolate, hazelnut Turkish delight for dessert. So. Good. Really friendly restaurant manager.

Delightful Mediterranean restaurant, serving delicious shawarma, falafel, and baklava. They offer different regional styles, such as Syrian, Jordanian, and Lebanese. Everything tasted homemade with fresh ingredients. Fast and friendly service. Large free parking lot with plenty of parking spots.
Clean and very nice ambiance with great food selections, something for everyone. Customer service from Serena was exceptional. Loved the lamb Osso and hearty seafood chowder. Delicious as always.

1st time visiting.  Thank you Ganby for our recommendations and friendly help. The food was super good. Got the Braised beef with mashed potatoes and double burger. Definitely would recommend & revisit for other options!

name: RH Rooftop Restaurant at RH Palo Alto

reviews.comment:
Our experience at RH Rooftop in Palo Alto was truly exceptional, and were so glad we chose to celebrate our special anniversary there, despite our initial skepticism after reading mixed reviews. From the moment we arrived, we were greeted warmly by the hostess with a heartfelt "Happy Anniversary," setting a wonderful tone for the lunch.

We were seated in a semi-private area, away from the crowd, which made our celebration feel even more intimate. Our waiter, Andrew, immediately greeted us with another "Happy Anniversary," and from that moment on, he made our dining experience unforgettable. He expertly guided us through the menu, suggesting some of his personal favorites while allowing us ample time to make our selections.

When it was time to order, Andrew surprised us with complimentary RH Bellinis to kick off the celebration-such a thoughtful touch. We decided on crispy artichokes, truffle fries, and the Chinese chicken salad. My husband opted for the thinly shaved ribeye French dip, while I went for the lobster roll, topped with caviar per Andrew's recommendation.

The French dip was melt-in-your-mouth tender, and my lobster roll was overflowing with fresh lobster--absolutely delicious. The Chinese chicken salad was another standout: the chicken was incredibly juicy, and the crispy fried noodles added the perfect crunch.

For dessert, we kept it simple with coffee and decided we would just share a chocolate chip cookie. To our surprise, Andrew brought out not one, but three warm cookies, telling us they were "on the house" to celebrate our anniversary.

Andrew, your attention to detail and dedication to making our day special truly made all the difference. We will always remember your kindness and can't wait to return to RH Rooftop, becuase of YOU. Thank you for making our anniversary unforgettable!

Walking in, we had the expectations bar set quite low - thanks to the other reviews warning us about “meh” food. But we mostly came for the vibes and the view, so no biggie. Well, joke’s on us because the food was fantastic!
From the creamy burrata to the fancy lobster rolls with caviar, from the delicate blini also with caviar, to the warm shrimp salad, and finally, the perfectly grilled branzino - we devoured everything like we hadn’t seen food in weeks. Every bite was a love story.
Now, was the service a bit slow? Yes. Did we contemplate aging gracefully while waiting for our next dish? Also yes. And sure, the prices made our wallets shed a tear. But at the end of the day, with that view, that food, and that experience—we left full, happy, and only slightly financially wounded. Worth it!

name: Nola
cuisine: Night Club, Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Expansive menu with flavorful options! I enjoyed a pina colada slushie, cup of gumbo, and a wedge salad with shrimp. For dessert, I had the chocolate cake. It was enough to share between three people. Very cute atmosphere in a walkable area - great for any occasion. Highly recommend.

This is a gem! The cocktails were great, complemented by the appetizers… cajun fries and chicken starters etc items are good! Highly recommend their Blood + Fire cocktail which is spicy margarita- definitely one of the best I had! Great atmosphere!

I don’t quite understand the hype around this place. The food was underwhelming and didn’t live up to expectations. Many dishes, like the skewers and the mushrooms in the quail appetizer, leaned heavily on overly sweet flavors, which didn’t suit my taste. To top it off, they forgot to include cheese on my son’s burger—an oversight we only realized after seeing photos of the same dish from other reviewers when we got back home. My son found the burger too dry and complained, though to their credit, the restaurant didn’t charge us for it. Overall, I found it to be overpriced, and the experience left much to be desired.

Overpriced, noisy and underwhelming in terms of food! Service was okay.
They have one vegan starter, one vegan salad and a vegan side. Ordered asparagus from the sides and mushroom tempura from the starter. There were high on salt and had not much flavor. The tempura was excessively crispy.  Very disappointed.

Visited this trendy Spanish restaurant and had a pretty good time. Ordered their popular paella—the seafood was fresh, though the portion wasn’t huge. The place was a bit noisy, but the service was excellent. Overall, a nice dining experience. Be sure to make a reservation in advance！

The restaurant was quite noisy with all the guests talking loudly.  It was difficult to chat with others in our group due to the noise level.  The service was friendly and efficient.  The food overall was good but most dishes were we ordered were quite salty.  We would have enjoyed the food even more if they were less salty.

Visited for a meetup and the food was excellent though they can improve tad bit on the service. The atmosphere was nice and we enjoyed the time out there. Tried indoors but will look to try outdoor seating as well. Highly recommend the lamb chops and the Bronzino Fish.

We hosted our wedding reception at Taverna and could not have asked for better food, people, and ambience. Our guests raved about the food all night and the servers/managers were so kind with everyone from adults to kids at our reception. Sound system was great. Was the perfect intimate venue for our small reception and we will definitely be coming back for the food! Derya was our coordinator and was so kind, patient, and calm throughout all our interactions!

name: Bevri - Palo Alto
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Had such a lovely lunch here with my girlfriends—and my baby! The atmosphere is warm and welcoming, the service is fantastic, and everything we tried was absolutely delicious. The khachapuri and khinkali were incredible, and the Napoleon cake was the perfect sweet finish. Even my little one enjoyed it—there was something for everyone. Can’t wait to come back!

The best restaurant I've ever been to in California. All the food and drinks were delicious, the quality of the products was top notch, the designer presentation and combination of flavors is the mastery of this place. European hospitality deserves special thanks. The service is very professional, pleasant. I wish this restaurant chain was all over America.
The people who work there really make this place great. Thanks to manager Olga, bartender Ilkhom, waiters Kirill and Rene for the pleasant experience.

Fantastic Food and Great Service!
We absolutely loved our meal here! The chicken momos were flavorful and perfectly cooked, and the lamb shank was tender and rich in flavor. The paneer paratha was generously stuffed, delicious, and even got our toddler’s seal of approval! The ambience was warm and inviting, and the service was attentive and friendly. We’ll definitely be back!

An awesome spot that lives up to the reviews and high rating.  Highly recommend and plan to come back.  Great flavors in all dishes.

We ordered many different dishes and ate family style.  They are very accommodating to gluten free. Service was wonderful and appeared the owner or manager was highly involved and invested. Parking was very easy and accessible.

name: Sundance The Steakhouse
cuisine: Night Club, Bar, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment:
I recently dined at Sundance The Steakhouse, and while the experience was overall enjoyable, there were some aspects that could be improved.

The prime rib was very good—tender and flavorful—but it didn’t quite live up to the comparisons with House of Prime Rib in San Francisco. The quality was there, but the experience didn’t feel the same. That said, I’d still recommend it.

The highlight of the meal was definitely the sides. I had either the garlic fries or truffle fries (can’t quite remember), but they were absolutely amazing—crispy, flavorful, and perfectly cooked. Their deep-fried items are surprisingly excellent, with the tempura shrimp standing out as one of the best I’ve had. The strawberry arugula salad was also phenomenal, fresh, and well-balanced.

Service was just okay. Our server wasn’t bad, but they didn’t really engage much, and the interaction felt a little dry. It wasn’t a bad experience, but it didn’t enhance the meal either.

Overall, I’d give this place four stars, but it’s almost a three. The food, especially the deep-fried options and salad, pushes it up, but service and the prime rib experience could use some improvements. I’d still recommend it, but with a few caveats.

Our experience at this restaurant was disappointing, especially considering the price. We ordered the Prime Rib medium, but it arrived medium well and was very dry. The sea bass ($49.95) lacked flavor unless eaten with the sauce. On a positive note, the bread, lobster bisque, and baked potato were great, and our waiter was very nice.

However, the overall service left much to be desired. I had booked this reservation to celebrate a birthday, yet instead of offering anything special, they canceled it because of late arrival without notice. We were late due to a full parking lot and limited street parking, and we found that our reservation was already canceled, even though the restaurant never mentioned a late-arrival policy during the booking process. Despite plenty of available seats, the front desk staff gave us an attitude. While we were eventually seated, we were told we had only 1 hour and 15 minutes to dine because of upcoming reservations.

I wouldn’t visit again. For a similar price, I’d recommend House of Prime Rib, where both the service and food quality are significantly better.

Good combination of traditional and a bit more adventuresome options. Desserts made in house. I had a delicious autumn salad and very tasty pasta dish with sun dried tomatoes. It was easy to have a conversation and the waitress was very observant and attentive without being in the way. Wonderful food and atmosphere. I was concerned about parking, but there was a lot conveniently just across the street, and a passenger loading zone right in front for anyone who can’t walk far.

Solid place.

Red vongole is interesting and surprisingly I love it when paired with a nice red! Tangy and refreshing. Clams are huge and fresh.

Tiramisu is pretty good would rate it 4/5.

Calamari steak is interesting!

Flan is unique but not to my liking.

Disappointing, and a such waste of money and time.

I can’t imagine anyone coming back here after dining once. The food was tasteless - the wings were half as good as what I could make myself, $18 for some measly portions that were not even prepared right. The burger was empty of any taste, like any. The other dishes all the same. Food is not the attraction here, it’s the ambience and location, but you could find that many other places and get a nice dinner while you’re at it

Also the hours are posted as midnight but they closed shop at 10:30 and pushed us all out. Not surprised at all the way this place is run.

It's so great to discover a healthy, delicious and beautiful vibe restaurant in the Bay Area. I really enjoyed the bright, surrounded by the greenery plants and the natural light that shines in. The food was great, and they're mostly from local farmers. Lots of healthy options you can substitute and good portions (I had the omelette and it was is enough to feed two). The service is also great, our waitress not only was sweet but also very tentative. Definitely will come back soon to try out other items on the menus.

Please park in the garage on Bryant Street if you can't find street parking.

I would definitely say our new favorite Spanish tapas in the South Bay/peninsula! Service was top notch, drinks came out super fast which is always a plus. Pork paella was delicious, especially crispy. Eggplant chips are so unique and tasty. The Gambas al pil pil was delicious too.

I can’t decide if the food or the service in this restaurant are better as they are both truly amazing. It’s been a long time since a restaurant has blown my socks off but I have to say this restaurant is truly exceptional!  From the moment my party walked in the door the host was welcoming. The atmosphere was warm and cozy.  We were promptly seated by and brought drinks by our waitress Sylvia.  The drinks were delicious and kept refreshed throughout the meal.  Appetizers were incredible, tasty and plenty to share.  My main course the steak cooked perfectly and melts in my mouth with every bite!  Over all, best meal I have had in a long time. Thank you to the staff, Sylvia, David, the tall host and three gentlemen who helped with the table. Truly excellent service!  Will be visiting every time I visit San Francisco!!!

Had a wonderful, fresh breakfast and a nice dinner at the restaurant in The Westin in Palo Alto.   The breakfast I chose was the bar which included eggs, bacon, potatoes, and French toast. Cereal, coffee, OJ, and toast was available as well a 8 varieties of fruit.

For dinner, I started with the cheese plate and finished with the Soleil Burger with Gilroy fries.  Long Islands were outstanding. The cheese plate was excellent and served with toast. The burger was cooked to perfection with bacon and cheddar.

Very hit or miss. Bacon is thick and cooked properly, but super Smokey. One day the scrambled eggs are cooked in butter (yum) the next they’re cooked in seed oils (disgusting). Coffee is worse than Starbucks but the fruit is quite good.

name: Reposado
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Really good food and drinks. Had the Burrata with tomato starter, chile poblano, pollo parrilla mole sauce with tamarind margarita, mango margarita.
Drinks were good - not too sweet and made well.
Food was well made along with red and white rice. Very flavorful.
Got the salted caramel ice cream with upside down banana bread.

A nice, upscale restaurant offering Mexican cuisine. The service was friendly and the ambiance of the place is great. Good appetizers and desserts. The vegetarian selection for entrees was a bit limited, but still some good choices.

name: Dinah's Poolside Restaurant
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: We were staying at the hotel part of this restaurant and decided to have dinner when we booked in late. We made reservations, but the place had plenty of tables to go around. It was a little too chilly for the covered patio even tho it was a heated patio so we sat inside. It smelled like a greasy spoon with a strong burger smell. We were seated right away and given menus. The menu really does range from poolside items like popcorn, chicken to nicer fare like a petite fillet. We ordered truffle fries to start and they were pretty greasy, but otherwise good. We weren’t too confident at this point, but we ordered the salmon and the petite fillet anyways. When they arrived, they were absolutely beautiful, like a fine dining experience. They tasted very, very good! We were quite surprised and happy and finished everything on our plate. The next day I ordered veggie tempura for room service and it was greasy just like the french fries. It seems like if you stay away from the fried food, you’ll be good to go here. I can’t speak for the Drinks, but the service was super kind and warm and efficient. It’s not a fancy place, but they do have fancy food.

Love this place. The pool is lovely. Staff is friendly, welcoming and helpful.
The food selection is good.
The five stars tonight was the Brownie with cream. Swoon-worthy. My Wagu hamburger was juicy and red. The lettuce and tomatoes didn’t deserve it.

name: President's Terrace
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: We were going to Lou & Herbert's for lunch, and I was talking to the guy at the front desk of the Graduate. The Presidents Terrace wasn't open, but he told me that I could go up and look around which I did. The rooftop Terrace looks really good. There's a bar, fireplace and several places to sit. The views from the Terrace are wonderful. We'll be back when they're open!

We decided to make a pit stop at the President's Terrace for a couple of cocktails and light appetizers before our main dinner at Nobu. We were looking forward to a pleasant afternoon on the rooftop bar. Upon our arrival, we found that the staff seemed tired, likely from a busy happy hour rush.

I can't rave about the cocktails or food, as we only tried a couple of dishes, but the view, ambiance, and decor were undeniably appealing. We're definitely considering returning when the weather is more favorable.

Overall, the President's Terrace is an excellent spot for unwinding with friends or colleagues after work. It doesn’t seem to accommodate large parties with limited seating. It's also festive and charming, making it a great choice for a fun date as well.
