Super inflated prices, and the food options were pretty meh. I ordered the shrimp scampi and it came with 5 shrimp for $36. They were cooked perfectly and tasted good, but for an entree there was nothing else to complement the meal besides bread. It was more like an appetizer than an entree. The staff were very attentive and friendly. My drinks, although pricy at $20 each (a mere $2 mark up from the $18 mocktails), were delicious.

Delicious breakfast conveniently located right downstairs in the Citrine hotel. Server was very friendly and food came out quickly after I ordered. I recommend the custard dipped challah French toast.

⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

Definitely give the pollo toscano and fried calamari a try. The chicken was tender and the seasoning was just right. The fried calamari was quite perfect as it had a light and crispy coating, adding a satisfying crunch without overpowering the flavour of the squid.

The gnocchi was delicious, but a bit too saucy for my taste, which made the dish feel a bit heavy. I would have preferred a lighter coating to let the gnocchi shine more.

Overall, this is a lovely spot in Palo Alto as it offers a cozy and relaxed ambiance. I’d be
open to try different locations as well!

The picture should say enough but this was extremely bland.  If I wasn’t driving back to Marina I certainly would have asked for a refund. It was supposed to be my lunch for the following day but ended up in the basura.  I had the lasagna as well.  That I was able to stomach but I was not impressed by that either but the presentation was much nicer. Sorry no photo.

name: Sweet Maple
cuisine: Cafe, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: My husband loved his meal, and I wasn't impressed with the blueberry muffle. I like the Korean fried chicken we tried as an app, and the latte was good. I think next time I would stick to a more traditional meal. The service was good and I think the overall atmosphere was great.

The food is okay but not amazing. I’ve been back a couple of times and don’t understand why so many people love it. I’m guessing the appeal of this place for a lot of people is the beautiful presentation of the food or the setting. Or maybe the unique mochi waffle offering. But in my opinion, the food is just okay. Yes, even the mochi waffles are just okay. Nothing bad at all but it’s overrated.

This review is specifically for the private dining event we hosted at iTalico, and I can’t say enough good things about the experience.

From the start, the communication with the team (especially with Marcelino) was excellent—quick responses, clear details, and an overall sense that they truly cared about making our event special. We came in a week beforehand to sample and select wines and appetizers, which was extremely helpful, and they worked with us to customize the set menu and room setup exactly how we envisioned it for a milestone birthday celebration.

One of the standout aspects was how accommodating the staff was. They allowed us to arrive a few hours early to decorate, and they went above and beyond—even helping us take everything down at the end of the night, which we really appreciated because it was a lot! Every member of the staff and management (Antonio) was incredibly kind, helpful, and patient throughout the evening.

Our dedicated server was lovely—attentive and warm—making sure everyone was taken care of. Guests who wanted to take home their leftovers were easily able to do so because they serve excellent portions.

What really made the night extra special was that our party of 15 ppl had the private room for the entire evening. We came to set up at 3 pm and were one of the last groups to close it out. That kind of flexibility is rare and made the whole event feel unrushed and intimate.

The food? Outstanding. Every dish was delicious, and the wines were a hit across the board. As people who’ve worked and travel around Italy, we were genuinely impressed by the authenticity of the flavors—it brought us right back to the Tuscan countryside.

We’ve also dined in the main restaurant during regular service, and the vibe there is equally charming—casual yet elegant, with a warm, rustic Italian ambiance.

Huge kudos to the team at iTalico—you helped us create such a memorable evening. We’ll absolutely be back for more family gatherings, celebrations, and cozy date nights.

Quite enjoyed our meal here and was able to be seated as a party of 4 without reservations on a Monday evening but in the covered outdoor patio area which is decently well isolated from the winds and the cold. All the dishes we ordered were quite good from the lamb to the octopus and pizza. Desserts were delicious as well including the Tiramisu and Panna Cotta.

name: San Agus Cocina Urbana & Cocktails
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
I had stopped by to grab some food and drinks with my coworkers and it was honestly such a fun experience as the menu was unique and the drinks were really refreshing/paired well with the food.

The service was laid-back, which allowed us to enjoy each other's company and there's easy access to parking in the nearby streets. since we also stopped by at a fairly early time during the day, it wasn't as busy, but towards the end of our visit it did get busier. ambiance was relax and quite quaint.

We recently discovered this place and were blown away. So much better than the usual Mexican food in the Bay Area. Most places are either really generic or very expensive and out of reach. This is right in the sweet spot. Well priced for the portions and value. Insanely tasty - about as good as Mexico. We really enjoyed the birria, cochinita, ceviche, and guacamole. Recommend you get family style so everyone can try. Definitely will be back!

Top Notch service!!! Went to celebrate our Anniversary and we had Jennifer taking care of us. The steak was cooked to perfection—tender, juicy, and full of flavor. What really made the night special was the service. The team made sure everything was just right without being intrusive. We felt genuinely taken care of. Highly recommend this place if you’re looking for a top-tier steakhouse experience. We’ll definitely be back!

First time visiting this place. The atmosphere was cozy and inviting, and the service was excellent and great company. We ordered the dry-aged ribeye—the cowboy, requested medium rare, but it arrived rare and was even a bit cold in the center a perfect rare steak! We ate it anyway and didn’t mind too much and didn’t want to send it back! The potatoes were drenched in butter not my style.
One cool thing that they do is melt the compound butter table side, this makes it a nice presentation. I really wanted to love this place but it lacked flavor in my opinion. will keep exploring the area!

My favourite vegan restaurant in all of Bay areas. Not only are the dishes delicious,  they are also all healthier, made from unprocessed ingredients. Both the brunch and lunch menu are exquisite. And don't skip the skillet chocolate chip cookie with vanilla ice cream!

Overall, great experience. Enjoyed the food, it was light and healthy and we enjoyed it guilt free! The broccoli steak was my favorite, with a beautiful barbecue flavor. Enjoyed the brownie with ice cream for dessert. Highly recommend, especially for veggie lovers

name: La Bodeguita del Medio
cuisine: Night Club, Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: We tried the chicharrones de pollo and fried shrimp from their happy hour menu. The shrimp were juicy—maybe a bit on the oily side—but still delicious, and the chicken was super crispy and perfectly seasoned. We also had the Tierra y Mar, which came in a generous portion and was packed with flavor. The skirt steak was tender, juicy, and full of beefy goodness. The coconut shrimp were excellent—not overly sweet, just naturally so—and the asparagus was cooked perfectly. The whole place, including the bathrooms, was impeccably clean. Great experience overall!

I really enjoy coming here and this time was no different. Everything was solid. Came in for team dinner and it was a great meal. Only disappointment was that some of the vegetarian options couldn’t be made vegan despite being listed as such but overall everyone enjoyed the food.

name: Oklava Cafe
cuisine: Cafe, Bakery, Food, Point Of Interest, Store, Establishment

reviews.comment:
I've been wanting to try this place for a while, and finally, last week, I got to try their Turkish breakfast. Everything was delightful. In my opinion, the portions were just right; each flavor was individually enjoyable, and together, they formed a delightful combination. The bread was delicious, and from the moment it was brought to your table, it emitted a wonderful aroma (it's served hot).

The staff is friendly and helpful. Knowing it's a popular place, I went on a Thursday during lunchtime. I didn't have to wait for a table (although I got the last available one outside), and the food arrived promptly. Just as most reviews suggest, it's a lovely place to spend time and enjoy your meal without rushing.

4.8
They offered a variety of Turkish sweets and pastries. Recommended the Turkish breakfast plate and baklava.

The dough was really soft and buttery. Tasted great with all kinds of ingredients included in the plate. However, be prepared for limited seats and sometimes hard to find parking during weekends.

name: Palo Alto Creamery
cuisine: Bakery, Food, Store, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: A fantastic American diner with a charming retro interior and a great vibe! The all-day breakfast is a real treat—delicious, hearty, and served in generous portions. The milkshakes are thick, creamy, and absolutely worth trying. Service is friendly, and the atmosphere makes you feel like you’ve stepped back in time. Perfect spot for a classic diner experience!

It is a very classic traditional American dining all-day breakfast place 🍴
A variety of all-day breakfasts definitely makes you hungry. I'd like to come for breakfast next time.
We had just a regular black ice coffee, fresh grapefruit juice, and home-style potato. They were all good!
The customer service was excellent. I asked about the homemade potato or French fries, and then they brought me a piece of potato to try before ordering it! Great!! 😊

name: Lou & Herbert's
cuisine: Cafe, Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
We went to the Graduate by Hilton to eat at Lou & Herbert's for lunch. It's a nice little restaurant and bar with very nice decor, and it even has a nice fireplace. Our server,  Carolina was really nice and so was Tony the chef.
We had the Rigatoni Primavera, which was good and Katia's Shrimp Ceviche that was excellent and very craveable. We'll come back sometime for breakfast and dinner!

Cocktail tastes so so. What surprised me was there was a mouse crossed the hallway hidden under my chair. The restaurant didn’t take any action and just told me they contacted the maintenance group… Speechless experience…

Nice spot if you want to try multiple spots. Had the chicken and fries myself and it was definitely above average. Not so good but was more then passable.

Pricing is pretty fair for what it is, fun to visit and see what type of foods they have.
We love the food here! Super high quality! Sergio is the best!! He is always super friendly and knows everyone by their names!!

If you’re craving soul-satisfying, authentic Pakistani flavors, Zareen’s is an absolute gem. I ordered the Gola Kabab Sizzler and Paratha with a steaming cup of chai — and every bite transported me straight to the vibrant streets of Karachi. The kababs were smoky, juicy, and bursting with spices that danced on the tongue, perfectly paired with a buttery, flaky paratha. The chai was warm and fragrant, with just the right touch of cardamom — pure comfort in every sip.

And then came the mango soft serve. Mind-blowingly amazing. Bursting with the sweet, floral essence of real mangoes, it was like tasting summer in Karachi.

Zareen’s doesn’t just serve food — they serve memory, emotion, and love on a plate. I’ll definitely be back for their Friday biryani and nihari.

Had an awesome meal at Zareen’s. Food was fresh, delicious and fast, despite the massive line! Line moved fast, ordered and got seated super quickly, service was solicitous and lovely! The green chutney is the stuff of dreams, I could’ve drank it by the glass if I knew I could’ve gotten away with it!

An Unforgettable Culinary Experience at Nobu Palo Alto

My wife and I had the most incredible dinner at the bar last night at Nobu Palo Alto. From start to finish, everything was flawless. The chefs behind the bar weren’t just masters of their craft—they were passionate, engaging, and truly made our night memorable. Watching them prepare each dish with precision and pride added such a unique and intimate touch to the experience.

Every bite was exceptional—from the toro topped with caviar and gold leaf to the perfectly seared wagyu served sizzling on a hot stone. The hamachi jalapeño, crispy rice, salmon nigiri, and matcha dessert were standouts, both in flavor and presentation.

They even surprised us with a custom dessert to celebrate our special occasion—just one more reason why the service felt so warm and personal.

Dining at Nobu is more than just a meal—it’s an experience. If you're in Palo Alto, make sure to sit at the bar, trust the chefs, and enjoy the ride. We'll absolutely be back.

The service here was absolutely amazing and the food here was great. I didn’t capture pictures of everything but everything was amazing. The piña martini was amazing as it had a slight pineapple acidity and wasn’t too strong. The sake we had (Devil Killer) was absolutely amazing. Very smooth and has a slight spicy finish to it. My family got the prime filet tobonyaki and the black cod miso and they were both outstanding. The filet came out on a hot sizzling platter and the texture of the steak was buttery and perfect. Some of the best steak I’ve ever had. The black miso cod had this sweet glaze to it and flaked off perfectly. A slight salty taste to it that meshed well with the sweet glaze. The crab tempura was fried perfectly. It came with some sauce that was slightly sweet and paired very well with the crab. The tempura sushi roll I had was pretty good. Very straight forward. The snow crab nigiri, unagi nigiri and tuna nigiri were okay. I’m a bit harder on sushi as it’s hard to compare to Japan but it’s very good. The meat on the nigiri was a bit dry, taking away some of the flavor from it. The tuna was a bit fishy but the unagi was pretty good. The xurros had a lemon filling on the inside but it was very light and had subtle flavors. Great way to end the dinner. The coconut ice cream was also light and creamy with a slight crunch to it. The zen garden dessert was refreshing and the fruits and matcha all mixed together very well. Really good place to go to !

name: True Food Kitchen
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: After trying the plant-based burger, sweet potato hash, and chocolate chip cookie from True Food Kitchen in Palo Alto, I can say this meal stands out above similar spots like Tender Greens or Veggie Grill. The flavors are fresher, more inventive, and every bite feels thoughtfully prepared. The burger was hearty and satisfying, while the sweet potato hash had the perfect balance of smooth texture and natural sweetness. Unlike other fast-casual restaurants that sometimes feel generic, True Food’s menu feels chef-driven and genuinely nourishing, with vibrant ingredients. The service was prompt and friendly, making the takeout experience seamless. If you’re debating where to get your next healthy meal, True Food Kitchen is absolutely worth choosing over others for staff interaction, quality, and taste.

Decent restaurant option located in the Stanford Shopping Center. A lot of vegan and vegetarian choices, as well as seafood and meat options for the carnivores. Edamame dumplings were a highlight. Fast and friendly staff. Large free parking lot.

I came to State of Mind Slice House on the recommendation of a good friend who owns another pizzeria.  I got a slice of pepperoni and a slice of the heat and sweet. The crust had a great taste and was perfectly chewy and crunchy. Both slices were delicious.
The only downside was the service. Those slices were so delicious that I wanted to order a whole pizza to take home for my family. There were two workers at the front that were standing there talking behind the register. I was standing at the front of the register with my card out ready to order. They completely ignored me for two or three minutes. A group of people walked in and one of the workers slid over to his right to take their order. The pizza is good, so I will go back again, but hopefully those two workers are not there when I do.

No thank you. Pizza was terrible. Lot of new pizza places popping up everywhere this one really sucks. Lacks sauce and flavor, employees gave us their best seller a pepperoni and mushroom pizza, then we also got a plain pepperoni and 4 cheese. So we tried 3 different slices, lol they were all terrible. My friend blames the cooks I somewhat agree. Another pizza place we try that fails in are book. Service was a 1 for the dirty looks for asking for a plate I must have interrupted a very important conversation between the girl and the cook, and also for being recommended a soggy tasteless pizza. Nothing special here.

Love this place! Obviously their pizza is fantastic, but actually, everything on their menu is fantastic!! It is authentic. This place gets so extremely crowded every day of the week, not just weekends, so make a reservation. Great place for groups so you can order everything and share. Leaving for dessert!

The calamarta pasta was uninspiring, the low grade seafood was boiled and mixed into a basic tomato sauce. The pasta was barely cooked and chewy. It was a chore to attempt to finish, I ended up leaving the plate half full.
The pizza was plain, the sauce lacked flavour, not an ounce of spice in sight.
Not worth the high price tag, highly recommend you skip and find a different Italian restaurant to visit in the bay.

It was a very interesting experience. It was my first time eating Israeli food and it was delicious. Hummus was delicious and the atmosphere was modern. They also kindly recommended food. If you like a different experience, I recommend you to go.

All the hummus platters are delicious. The hummus is soo smooth and tasty- a true delight. All the vegetables are fresh and they are accommodating to special requests. Moroccan carrots are worth trying and so are the kabobs (beef and lamb). The mulled wine is flavorful and well balanced. Highly recommend especially for a late night dinner that’s light and nutritious.

We were happy to know there is no need to wait on Saturday night, however most of the tables were occupied.
The ordering process helps to focus on carefully choosing what you want without being rushed, there are tablets near each table to go through the menu and order more when needed.
The food is good overall, a good choice for different Japanese dishes, snacks and drinks, feels authentic.
Staff is good and polite.

Love this cute restaurant in Palo Alto! It’s a chain so you can find the same menu in their other locations. You can order food digitally from the table and get paid with the iPad. The menu offers wide range of dishes at economic price.

Had the mixed appetizer platter, veggie moussaka, falafel plate and truffle fries — all solid picks. The place is definitely on the pricier side, and I expected the service to match that. We went during a slow time with only one other group there, but the staff seemed pretty disengaged, mostly on their phones, and it took a few tries to get their attention. Great food, but the service definitely needs a little work to match the vibe and price.

I had a great dining experience at Anatolian Kitchen! We started with the eggplant purée, which was decent, and the lentil soup, which was flavorful and comforting. The octopus salad wasn’t my favorite, but the truffle fries were absolutely delicious—highly recommended.

For the main course, the shish kebab was unfortunately quite tough and hard to chew, but the Adana kebab was full of flavor and cooked perfectly. The real highlight of the meal was the branzino fish—fresh, tender, and beautifully prepared.

We ended the night with baklava and künefe paired with Turkish tea, and they were both amazing—perfectly sweet and satisfying.

The hospitality really stood out; our server was attentive, friendly, and made the experience even better. Overall, I had a good time and will definitely be coming back!

We really enjoy La Boheme, it's a rare spot of fresh European authenticity in a sea of Americanized cuisines. We eat here every week and enjoy their food. The portion sizes are also quite filling, really good value! Highly recommend eating here at least once and then you'll know its good!!!

Very cute neighborhood french restaurant. The bread and wine were absolutely delicious, and the ambiance is great. The main dishes, however, fell short of expectations. The mussels had an odd flavor that didn't taste very fresh, and the catch of the day tasted very uninspired. Pasta dish was decent but nothing special. Highlight of the meal was definitely the complimentary baguette.

name: Coconuts Caribbean Restaurant & Bar
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: From the moment we were greeted until the moment we left, the team here took great care of our party.   Located in a busy downtown area there was ample parking in the lot across the street in addition to the street.  Indoor and outdoor seating available.  The food is spicy, flavorful and yummy! Each person in our party enjoyed their selection.  Served at the perfect temperature, each entree exploded with flavors.  The oxtails? Divine.  Chef’s kiss.  This is definitely a new favorite.

Overall delicious food. Patty was good, The crispy pork appetizer with the guava sauce was unique and something special, and the goat curry & oxtail is hearty and flavorful. Skip the jerk wings though. And if you decide to order the ginger beer, know that it fights back.

The food and service were both excellent! We had a wonderful time celebrating a birthday here. We ordered a variety of dishes and definitely couldn't finish them all. Everything was delicious, with the standouts being the lamb chops and the antrikot rib eye. While the other dishes were good, they weren't necessarily worth the price.

The service was attentive, with our table consistently cleaned, water glasses refilled, and frequent check-ins from our server. However, our table's location near a high-traffic area resulted in frequent bumps from rushing servers and other diners. Despite the spaciousness of the restaurant, we were placed in a less than ideal spot. We moved our table ourselves, but the issue persisted.  Despite this, our server was fantastic, and we didn't let it ruin our evening. This was a one-time experience that we enjoyed overall!

Really enjoyed Valentines dinner here last evening. Make sure to make reservations. We got lucky with street parking but also make sure to be there early to park properly. We had the beets, rib eye, and pastry rolls. The bread is amazing and the ambiance will transport you to the Mediterranean. I can’t wait to come back

I mean 10/10 service! Yes, they really make your dining experience special. Food was great (didn’t like the mixed curry that much), tea leaf salad was great! Lettuce wraps were superb.
Atmosphere is so nice and you feel you will have a great experience the moment you step in. Hostess was friendly and fun. Coming back for sure.

The food was alright. We asked to make some of the dishes hot and medium spice but I think the waiter didn’t punch it in because the pad Thai was very sweet with almost zero spice.

They gave us a complimentary bowl of rice.

The tea leaf salad, however, was absolutely delicious and I highly recommend it.

Good gluten free options as well!

Ethel's fancy do be fancy. But also pretty casual with both indoor and outdoor dining. The food is new American with seasonal California flare and Japanese influence. This place is definitely going for the Michelin vibe which is no surprise given the chef's background. The service is impeccable and the ambience is perfect for the laid back yet sophisticated west coast vibe.

Keep in mind the menu changes constantly to highlight what's in season (and due to availability of fresh ingredients). So if you fall in love with something you see online, be prepared for some potentially bad news.

Overall, you can't really go wrong with Ethel if you are looking for more elevated seasonal flavors with a touch of Japanese fusion.

We have been dining here since December 2022. They opened in September 2022. Chef Scott has an impressive resume and always delivers a surprising menu with amazing flavors. The food here "Broke The Mouth" every time, bruddah! We recently had our holiday party here for 75 people max, and it was amazing! Joy coordinated everything with our team, and we highly recommend this restaurant for your event up to 75 people for a buy-out. We had a lunch buy-out. They allowed us to set up a photo booth outside upon entry and had two solo musicians rotating inside to really deliver an amazing company event. You can even book the private room for up to 16 people for smaller events. All of the staff is amazing and always helpful. This is a well oiled machine and I hope to see them anchored in Palo Alto for many more years to come so we can enjoy every new menu item chef creates. We just enjoyed the New Years Eve tasting menu and it did not disappoint. Enjoy the photos!

Orange square, more like Worange wuare. This place is the truth. Their bento boxes are sturdy and sustainable. No leaks at all. They have a label saying how long you can reheat safely. Dog even their plastic bag was sturdy as hell. The chicken leg was incredibly tender and fall off the bone. They don't skimp out on your protein portion. The vegetables were crisp and everything in general was well-flavored. Nothing was any bit close to being too salty. They have a great system going and are constantly pumping out bento boxes which are filling but not decadently so. You would think a place so dedicated to takeout wouldn't keep it's grounds clean but the tables and general area are pristine. Go here.

A good Taiwanese bento place. Even better on Wednesdays with the $9.99 chicken leg deal.

Employees are really nice and sweet and food is always consistently tasty. Big convenient parking lot. They also allow online ordering, which makes it a lot more convenient.

Great food at great prices. They run a weekly deal for $9.99 and several monthly deals for a reduced price. The portions are generous, it took me two lunches to finish my weekly special. Many things here are self-service and there's additional chili and the likes for your dishes in the middle of the establishment. The toilet was pretty clean. It's nothing revolutionary but they're really good at doing what they're doing. Go here for quick lunch if you're in the area.

Wow. At first, I wasn't expecting much when I walked in, but this place came highly recommended to us. We ordered the special and we were all really impressed! The service was amazing and the server intentionally made sure we had enough soup in the larger pot and that the temperature would stay perfect. The food was so delicious! Of course, we probably all over ate... But what a memorable evening! I highly recommend a visit and I hope to return again! I was very impressed with the service. I would give it 6 stars, if I could.

name: Lazy Dog Restaurant & Bar
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: We were a group of six and tried a variety of dishes. The food was average — nothing stood out — but the service was quite poor. Our server kept coming over to ask if we needed anything, but every time we asked them to clear the dirty plates, they would take just one and then disappear without returning. The table stayed messy for a long time, which really affected the overall experience. Not somewhere I’d be in a hurry to return to.

We came for the $1 wings and stayed for the Californian Burger and Reuben Sandwich. Fries are great texture but the sangrias could be a bit stronger. The kids Mac and cheese and corn doggies were satisfying with chocolate milk.
We went for an early lunch. My first  time and the experience was pleasant. Had smash burgers and garlic fries and a flight of beers . Friendly staff and nice lunch.

We had a wonderful dinner at Eureka on Main Street in Cupertino, and I just had to share how fantastic the experience was—especially thanks to Makayla! She was incredibly kind, patient, and professional while taking our order, and she was so friendly with the kids, which made the evening extra special.

My son was with his dad and godfather, and he felt so comfortable and happy—he even finished an entire bowl of mac and cheese (which never happens!). The food was amazing, and the atmosphere was warm, welcoming, and very family-friendly.

Makayla’s great attitude and attention to detail really stood out. She made us feel right at home. We’ll definitely be coming back!

name: Sweet Maple
cuisine: Cafe, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: A few weeks ago, we visited Sweet Maple in Cupertino for a weekend brunch, and it was buzzing! With no indoor tables available, we were seated outside, which was lively but a bit cold, making it less cozy. Parking was a hassle—had to park a few blocks away due to limited spots. The food was the star: I had the Chicken Croffle, a crispy, juicy chicken breast on a flaky croissant waffle, drizzled with spicy honey maple syrup that perfectly balanced sweet and savory. It was beautifully plated and absolutely delicious. My daughter ordered the Matcha Moffle, a vibrant, chewy matcha-infused moffle sitting on a pool of matcha lava, topped with fresh strawberries and a sprinkle of powdered sugar—a stunning, earthy-sweet treat that looked as incredible as it tasted. Service was okay, a bit rushed due to the busy crowd, but our server was friendly. A 20% tip was auto-added for our group of five. If you’re a foodie who loves creative brunch dishes like these, Sweet Maple’s Cupertino spot is a gem. Try visiting on a weekday for a less hectic experience, though you’ll still face tricky parking.

Such an nice experience! They have a limited (compared to some other places) but a very satisfying menu!

From the first interaction to the last the customer service was really good and friendly.

Food was amazing and the presentation was top notch as well.

They offer a range of egg preparations, burgers and other nice dishes as well. I didn’t tryout any beverages so can not vouch for those but the drinks menu looked pretty decent too

The food might be on the expensive side a bit but it is worth it. The waiting time can be a bit much depending on the day and time. For us it was just around 10 minutes.
Would not hesitate to go again!

I thought this was a cool concept! I liked it more than other "foodhalls" I've tried in the Bay Area.

Location is interesting, right on the corner so it's best to park in the small lot behind. I went on a Friday at 6pm and the lot was super full, but with people getting takeout. So if you want to eat inside, no problem!

I tried Proposition Chicken, the burger was super juicy and honestly good size for the price. My friend had one of the SOB Burgers which he also enjoyed, but said could've been a bit bigger.

You'd have to try all the offerings to get an accurate sense but my ratings are based on the experience I had. Will definitely be back to try more!
I come here at least 4times a week since my job is 3 min away. If I crave something different they usually have it. The staff and food have never been disappointed me.

I love udon and so I'm biased, but I'm a fan of Marugame! The service is great and the udon is good. Udon here vs Honolulu is a huge price difference. I ordered too much, but I finished it all! 🤣

I recommend this place and will be returning!

Note to self: don’t go 30 minutes before closing, not many tempura items available

If you have had Marugame in Oahu the Bay Area locations do not compare. Probably the reason why I’m a little disappointed with the Bay Area locations.

A huge difference I have seen is the size of the tempura especially the shrimp and squid. So much bigger in Hawaii. The shrimp at this location was so small. Smaller than the frozen Costco size.  Also both the shrimp and squid were on the soggy side and didn’t offer much crunch so I would like to try when they are freshly made. Remember price adds up when you add the tempura.

The Nikutama sauce was great! Worker gave us a little more since they were closing. I appreciate that service from the worker. But there is something different about the combination of free soup and eating hot crunchy tempura in Hawaii.

Location has lots of seats which is a plus and I like the counter that offers … water, to go cups, tempura sauce and etc. I’ll still go back but for some freshly made tempura!

Thursday night dine-in:(~6.30 pm)

- Ordered Baja Shrimp taco platter for entree and Chocolate Lava cake with Vanilla icecream(3$+)

- The Shrimp tacos were flavourful and crispy, the soft taco is not very intact and got messy, yummy though. The 2/3 taco platter comes with a side, I picked half and half fries, regular and chile lime option. The chile lime fries were better.

- The dessert was great, wish they’d put the vanilla on top instead of providing as a side option, it’d have been perfect. I skipped the seasonal berry.

- The tables were lil sticky, everything else was great, like the heaters etc. Also, the tipping starts at 18% when you pay, & the kinda waited on the side as we tip, so felt a little pressured to pick that 18%😏
Outdoor sitting, fresh food and service with smile, made a great combination for today’s lunch. This Cupertino location has the best service. Everyone is super nice. Carly is the best.

Salad plates are great. I liked the chicken (white meat) more than the steak as the latter was more tough. Balance of veggies to meat was better than the half chicken plate (or vice versa if you want more meat and fewer veggies). Fast service, clean dining area / bathroom.
I ordered lamb souvlaki wrap . Lamb pieces were dry , hard and so chewy to eat. Pita bread was fine . Will never order again .

The pork knuckle has a rich, savory flavor, and the skin is well-seasoned and melt in the mouth. The accompanying pickles are a great touch—tangy and refreshing, they complement the dish well. The rice is well cooked, too. However, the meat is a bit too dry, which takes away from an otherwise enjoyable experience. A little more juiciness would elevate the dish significantly.

So wonderful to have a Yunnan restaurant in Cupertino. The menu has dishes we don't see in other Chinese restaurants, and they are yum. We asked for a couple of dishes to be made vegetarian, and they obliged. There is a line, if you come in during normal lunch and dinner hours. The mushrooms with peppers was excellent, as were the sauteed veggies. The grilled fish, Cambodian style is a must have. The mushroom fried rice was excellent as well. Service is friendly.

name: Duke of Edinburgh
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: The place really does smell like an older British pub, which may be off-putting to some, but authentic enough. Sadly, the authenticity doesn't extend as far as their $24 "Bangers and Mash" which arrived with cold mashed potatoes and a tiny plastic pot of gravy on the side. It's certainly nostalgic if you're craving 1980s British school dinners, but that's probably not what you're here for at these prices. Avoid.

This was a delightful little find just next door to my hotel last weekend—had 3 meals there in 3 days. Stephen and Michelle were my bartenders, and service was impeccable on every visit. Quaint British pub with a vibrant bar crowd, darts games, the occasional sports on the TV, and quiet conversation. A nice place to go to unwind. Great wine selection. Must try the veggie burger or the bacon-wrapped filet! Also, they just put up some festive fall decor 🎃

I had an amazing experience at this seafood boil restaurant! Everything was absolutely top-notch—from the incredibly fresh seafood to the perfectly balanced seasoning. The staff was warm, attentive, and made us feel so welcome from the moment we walked in.

The portions were generous, and every bite was full of flavor. I especially loved how customizable everything was—it made the meal feel personal and fun. Plus, the location is super convenient, especially being so close to Apple Park.

This place is a gem! I’ll definitely be coming back again and again. Highly recommend to any seafood lover!

First visit to Cap’t Loui and it was a good experience! There was a line when we arrived, so we ordered takeout instead. We waited about 25 minutes for our food, so it might be a good idea to call ahead if you’re in a hurry.

The clams and crawfish were fresh and live. Head-off shrimp was good as well. The Cap’t Loui seasoning had a nice touch of sweetness and tasted great. The sides exceeded our expectations — both the Cajun fries and garlic noodles were delicious.

One thing to note: the price on the wall was for frozen crawfish. The menu didn’t clearly show the price for live crawfish, which ended up being more expensive, so that was a little confusing. Also, the crawfish itself was a bit plain and needed to be dipped in the sauce for more flavor.

Overall, a solid spot for Cajun seafood.

name: Aqui Cupertino
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: First time.  Glad we found this hidden spot in what seems to be China town. The atmosphere was clean, friendly staff.   Enchiladas and crab cake meal had soooo much flavor and came out scorching hot for a caferteria type pick up style.  Like the fact I can get my healthy alternatives in. My meal included zucchini and cherry tomatoes, soft and flavorful.   Brown rice was cooked perfectly. The portions were fulfilling.  Couldn't finish the appetizer black bean dip (delicious).  We tried half of the salsa bar sauces, all were delicious. The ghost sauce will creep up on you, oh and the drinks as well. Mai Tai and Carribean slushy premade drinks had a punch with lots of flavor.  Did the job 🙌.

I recently visited this restaurant again, and it was such a fantastic experience, never disappoints! vibe is great—lively, modern, and welcoming. As always, the food was amazing, with flavors that never disappoint. But the real standout for me was their industrial-grade drink totally unforgettable!

Highly recommend Aqui for anyone looking for great food, drinks, and a wonderful atmosphere.

We made a reservation online via Yelp, and the table was ready soon after we arrived. The service was very welcoming, and our host gave us some valuable recommendations. There is something for everyone, including the vegetarian option. If you are not going to ramen, you can order a different dish.

I love the San Francisco location but its so far, always crowded and a huge wait. I love that my favorite Ramen place opened up a location so close to my home! This location is also bigger and the interiors are quite pretty.

We went there on Saturday afternoon, and although there was a bit of a wait, it was much faster than SF. And there were other stores nearby so were easily able to spend time there. Bonus: Izumi Matcha is just across the street!

Coming to the food: we ordered our usual tonkutsu ramen, and it was pretty good. My husband ordered beer and that was amazing!

It’s my first time coming to this restaurant. I came for a birthday shindig. I’ve experienced the same type of Brazilian restaurant. I can’t complain the food was/is amazing. This place is an all you can eat of whatever type meal you choose.

Since I knew what I was to experience I decided to have the seafood and salad option. I know I cannot eat all the meat they’ll serve and I would get too full. I’m not saying you shouldn’t though. But the seafood and salad option is the same eat all you.

The service was great. The people I was with all had meat options and they just kept coming non-stop. They give you a token that when you want to take a break just flip the token and they’ll stop. Pretty cool right?!?

The ambiance is beautiful. Quite fancy. Good for a date night however it can get very loud. Now the food tastes great and all the meat you can eat is wonderful but in my opinion it’s a bit pricey. This is not a place I would do a big dinner party in.

Overall my second Brazilian steak house experience and I'll say it was better then the first.

All the meats were pretty good, nothing stood out too heavily from each other but that's fine.

Priced pretty competitively as well, for first timers I'd highly recommend this spot.
Oh and their tres leches cake was pretty nice.

Crazy fast & good service, delicious food, fair prices, easy parking. Their delivery service was non stop and the restaurant was packed at 4pm (which is a bit of a random time in between lunch/dinner) so we knew we were in the right spot.

Their Pad Thai is very authentic and exactly what I was looking for! Will come back!

The Papaya Salad is a must! Really fresh and huge plate that works to share.

We loved that they asked us for the level of desired spiciness on each plate. Be mindful of their spicy levels though as we went with medium and it was more like a “hot”. Mild is more like a true “medium”. Still very delicious as we love spicy foods but if you don’t, tell them zero spicy.

There’s many Thai restaurants around South Bay Area but not many that are great. This one will be on my repeat list.

Restaurant seemed clean other than the odd fish odor I couldn’t ignore.  The staff were polite enough.
The Food was not very impressive aside from the egg rolls.  They were delicious!  The curry was standard & the chicken fried rice was okay.  Last night ( Friday) they were beyond bustling.  The restaurant was packed, inside & out. There were other Asian cuisines as neighbors but they had most of the business.  The parking lot was at capacity.  People were parking illegally & using their hazards to pick up orders.  The most disappointing thing was that they didn’t have soy sauce & they didn’t give me napkins or cutlery in my to go order.  I’d be tempted to return for egg rolls but it’s not worth hassle. 3/5

Been coming here since they opened. Lemon slices with water is awesome but I do have one complaint is the recent change to their chicken sumac recipe changed and my kids can’t eat the new saltier and spiced up recipe. Even the chicken shawarma is kind of spicy now and unable to feed to children. I hope you can fix this.

When it comes to Mediterranean food , Dish n Dash never disappoints with the quality. Delicious Mansaf, Beriyani dejaj, Shawarmas are the best. Food portions are good. salads are always freshly made. Must try if you are around.

Whenever I crave Japanese tonkatsu, this is the place that comes to mind. The crispy tonkatsu, paired with the sauce and freshly ground sesame seeds, is incredibly fragrant and authentic. I’m really happy to have found such delicious tonkatsu here in the U.S.
As for the salmon don, it wasn’t as enjoyable—it had a strange bamboo-like taste that overpowered the freshness of the salmon. I’ll probably skip the salmon don next time, but I’ll definitely come back for the tonkatsu.

Had a hair in my food, you have order from a tablet, had no contact with server from the time I sat down to the time the food came.. so why 5 stars?  The food.  Absolutely amazing - perfect portions, presentation, preparation, flavor - HIGHLY recommend the Yayou Gozen.  Definitely will be back.

This is easily one of my favorite restaurants. The atmosphere is so beautiful and clean. Our server Nicole was so warm and welcoming, she was extremely knowledgeable about the menu and gave great recommendations. We had the garlic feta fries which were AMAZING, along with the Pita Chicken Falafel (which is my personal favorite) and for desert had the chocolate mousse which was a perfect combination of sweet but not over powering sweet. The manager Paloma (I believe her name was) came and checked in on us and was so kind! It was overall an amazing experience and tasty meal. I’m from Washington state here visiting family and every time I come down I always make sure to stop here. 10/10 recommend.

Had a lovely weekend lunch. The mimosa and strawberry lemonade were very tasty and refreshing. Beef lamb kebabs were delicious but a bit overcooked and firm. Falafel were crispy and well seasoned but were tiny. Roasted cauliflower was lightly seasoned and still crunchy. Shushuka was hot and spicy with lots of tomato sauce. But, The garlic feta fries were the best dish, to be honest, still crispy and moist topped with garlic and feta. Service was excellent and the ambience was relaxing and well appointed.

name: Alexander's Steakhouse
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
We went for a celebratory dinner. I didn’t have high expectations since the restaurant’s design didn’t seem particularly appealing in the photos. But when we arrived, everything looked absolutely wonderful in person. The lighting was perfectly dimmed, and the table settings were immaculate. The staff was highly professional, making the experience even more enjoyable.

And of course, the food—this was the best dry-aged steak I’ve ever had. Every other dish we tried was just as impressive.

I can’t wait to come back!

Top notch service and great quality! Went there for a private event and we're in a back room. Right from the ambience to prompt service and attention to detail, the place knocked if out of the park. The wait staff was extremely knowledgeable and accommodating. Great selection of steak and non steak items and customized to vegetarian options.  Pricey, but worth the experience.  The cotton candy at the end was a nice touch.

One of my favorite things about Koi Palace Contempo is that they serve dim sum later in the day! Very few places do that. We ordered Har Gow, Chicken Feet, Sesame Balls, Shanghai XLB, Crab Claws, Chicken Shui Mai, Poached Gailan, BBQ Pork Rice Crepe, and the Pineapple Bun. It looked like we hardly put a dent in the menu too, lots of good items, with some decent vegetarian options as well. All of it was excellent and I would recommend these items to my friends. The staff were friendly and welcoming and quick too! I was not expecting that. Henry was our server and he packaged up some of our left overs for us and gave us a complimentary pudding dessert.

The atmosphere was calm and well lit. Lots of space! They also have WiFi. I can say for sure that we will be coming back.

The fish here is incredibly fresh, with tender and juicy meat, absolutely delicious! The chicken feet are well-seasoned, soft, and full of flavor. The beef is crispy on the outside and tender on the inside, cooked to perfection. The service is also very attentive. Overall, a great experience, and I will definitely come back next time!

name: Dough Zone Dumpling House Cupertino
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Dough zone is a nice little find behind Cupertino Main St., though part of a larger chain. It has a nice ambiance and while not being a large venue has decent wait times, with the option to join the wait-list via Yelp.
The food is pretty tasty with a nice variety of dumplings and pot stickers. My favorites are the pan-fried pork dumplings and sweet and sour cucumber.
The only downsides here are the phone menu ordering in a building with bad reception and weak WiFi. It's taken me 10 minutes sometimes to get the page to load and be able to start placing orders. The staff is fairly attentive, but maybe due to the digital ordering system it feels like something is maybe missing from the sit down experience.
Overall a good find and we've visited a few times already, also the pricing is really good. I fed a family of 6 without holding back and we all left full for under $200. There's something that can't be understated about leaving with both a happy stomach and a happy wallet!

The prices here are very reasonable for a dumpling house. They served my beer with a chipped glass. You order online and they serve you but you cant cash out online, only with your wairess. The staff brought the food but no one checked on us until i flagged one of them down for my check

The food itself was middle of the road. The dumplings popped easy and soup got everywhere.  The potstickers had added batter that waffled out from the potstickers ( see photo) but were fresh and delicious.

I may go back because the prices were good but honestly there are much better dumpling spots.

The portions here are huge! We each ordered one, but couldn’t finish.

Pork Cutlet Curry: The cutlet was a bit thin, and it felt like a very traditional Japanese-style curry. It was tasty.

Beef Omurice Curry: The curry had a slightly tangy flavor, maybe from bell peppers — quite unique.

Second time at Curry Hyuga and it was just as delicious as the first time.
Corn soup is full of flavor, creamy, and just the right amount of croutons.
Potato salad is fresh and delicious. We LOVE the red pickled acoutremont.
The curry is thick and flavorful. The veggies are yummy. The pork/veggie katsu was big portions, fresh and crunchy.
We recommend getting there early as it does get busy quickly.

name: BJ's Restaurant & Brewhouse
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Very warm ambience and apt for a catch up with friends. The food is tasty. I loved the long island iced tea cocktail. Our server was very friendly. We ordered two mojitos with lite ice. But to fill up the glass extra lemonade was added that made it too sour. But our server replaced it promptly with a new one that was really good and didn't charge for the items at all in the bill to make up for it. It was really a good experience for us that he addressed it promptly and professionally.

Food is decent but really heavy, service is decent. I’d never come here on my own and only come with friends.

Pizookie (cookie pizza with ice cream) is a must and generally what they’re known for. Prime steak Sunday can be hit or miss. I liked the sides more than the steak. The food is ok.

name: La Pizzeria Cupertino - Italian Restaurant
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
We had made a reservation and the table was ready for us when we arrived. Note that it is a little bit of a walk from the parking to the restaurant. We ordered the vegetariana pizza as an appetizer as it looked appealing. I’m happy to report that it didn’t disappoint. With this we were excited for our order of Antonella gnocchi, pesto spaghetti, Alfredo pasta, and calzone (sub the vegan cheese for regular cheese). Of these, the gnocchi was the best. The spaghetti was a little dry and the calzone was ok. Food was actually a 3.5/5
Desserts-  Tiramisu and raspberry panna cotta were delicious!
The service was average but the ambiance was nice !!

Amazing food, rude service.

Ordered salad, focaccia, vegetarian pizza and pasta limone. Best lemon sauce pasta I have ever eaten. Loved the flavor. Dessert was amazing too. They have a vegan menu too.

I don't know why this place is so popular. The food tastes average but looks above average. The prices are very expensive. Best to make a reservation. Otherwise, you will get a seat with limited seating time

A delightful Japanese fusion tapas spot that truly exceeded my expectations. The food was excellent, with fresh, high-quality ingredients and thoughtful preparation. We tried the sashimi salad, hamachi (yellowtail) carpaccio, and salmon clay pot rice. While all were fantastic, the hamachi carpaccio was particularly delicate, flavorful, and beautifully balanced. The service was also very good, attentive without being intrusive, which made the experience even more enjoyable. We’ll definitely be back to explore more of the menu!

Our first time coming to this restaurant. The food is good. Just like other Japanese/Korean BBQ restaurants, grill it yourself and enjoy! They have a really good set of meat for larger party. By ordering the set is already fulfilling, and of course, always can add more for the sides. We came as party of 4 adult, and the set for 4 people (Yakiniku Party) is perfect for us!
Great japanese barbecue selection, we took a combo menu for six, the quality was great, especially the marinated beef. The quantity was perfect.We had a very nice evening among friends

Solid Taiwanese comfort food. The sesame and peanut noodles are delicious! The vegan pork belly is good.

The wonton noodle soup is so-so -- broth is blandish and the wonton has a dime sized filling. Go for the other soups. The beef noodle soup is quite flavorful.

For the noodle dishes, you can request for fresh/hand-pulled noodles.

For vegetarians and vegans, they have plenty of options. They even indicate in no meat dishes that lard/pork fat is used.

Downside is it's pricey.
Absolutely delicious. Breakfast is amazing, highly suggest eating in store for maximum crispiness. Salivating just with the thought of the delicious food. Wish they have breakfast on weekdays too!

The food here was superb. There's plenty of strong dishes here. I think the best for me was the pahadi paneer tikka. But none were weak, save the chicken malai soft shell quesadilla. The biryani are a great take on a classic disk. The drinks are presented well. I think the star of the show was the dessert. Everyone at the table adored the tutta futta paan for dessert. It has a wide-range of flavors with a good balance between aroma and sweetness. The rasmalai tres leaches was light, airy, and sweet. The place is kept clean and the service is alright but can be exceedingly lacking at times for a restaurant of this price point and with these goals in mind of tapas.

Really good food! Very creative presentations and the flavours were very unique! We’ve been to many upscale Indian restaurants in the Bay Area and this one was fantastic! Definitely one to add to your list!!

This place is ROBBING people! The food is horrendous and the prices are rocket high! Food comes out cold or lukewarm. Everything tastes like they were frozen food that's been reheated.

The worst dish was the garlic noodles! The noodles were soggy, as if it was for my grandma with no teeth to eat. The noodles were also cut into short 2in pieces for some reason.

There's a 5% extra charge added to every bill, for the waiters. The suggested tip starts from 18% which is wild for the horrendous food quality.

Everything we had was tasty. The mussels dish was our favorite. Garlic noodle was also really good. The salmon mousse, we couldn’t really taste the salmon in it but it tasted fine. We also ordered catch of the day dish (not shown in picture), the fish was light and crispy but the kimchi fried rice it came with was lacking; it tasted more like lightly seasoned fried rice—couldn’t taste the kimchi. Overall, the presentation was great and taste was enjoyable.

Stopped here for dinner to kill time during rush-hour and was pleasantly surprised. The burrito was solid. They’ve got a big salsa bar which is awesome, staff are friendly and the order was put together super fast.
No frills low key Mexican restaurant. Excellent New Mexican food at good prices. Favorite for the table was the special smoked Gouda quesadilla.

Famous taiwanese porridge in bay area. They serve bottom-up porridge with sweet potato. When they are busy, you have to put your name, and they will call you to be seated.
You ordered the side dishes  at the counter, and they will bring it to your table. There are plenty of items to choose from. If I am not mistaken, one plate is about $10. The food is good.  Lunch time you can order a plate with 3 side dishes.  After 8 pm, they also have 20% off the dishes.
Good quantity for the price. I enjoyed the eggplant. However, the ingredients didn’t taste very fresh, particularly the meat and we found multiple hairs in our food.

I recently visited Sizzling Lunch and was thoroughly impressed with the quality and presentation of the food. The dish I received was served in a hot iron skillet, which kept the food warm throughout my meal. The centerpiece was a mound of perfectly cooked white rice, topped with a creamy sauce, fresh green onions, sweet corn kernels, and a spicy condiment that added a delightful kick. Surrounding the rice were thin slices of beef that continued to cook on the hot skillet, ensuring each bite was tender and flavorful. The combination of textures and flavors was exceptional, and the sizzling presentation added an exciting element to the dining experience. Overall, Sizzling Lunch provided a delicious and memorable meal that I would highly recommend to anyone looking for a unique and satisfying dining experience.

As a family of five with kids aged 8-12, the fit was pretty decent for all of us. However, the sizzling plates lacked flavor, so be sure to use plenty of the sauces provided on the table. On the bright side, their fried chicken is a true gem.

Friendly service. Interesting food and decor. The fish looked great and tasted good but not as good as it looked. It was spicy but not excessively so. The cucumber with egg and wood ear mushrooms and the lotus root with wood ear mushrooms were both great. I look forward to trying their hotpot next time.

The food here was extremely tasty. A little salty but very delicious. My wife loved the dish (ma la xiang guo?) where she got to pick the ingredients of her own stir fry and it was priced by weight. Reminds us of restaurants in China.
Super duper nice people here! It's an added bonus to the yummy food! I can't believe I haven't written them a review yet! This place completely deserves every star! I will definitely be back!

I ordered the calamari and fish and chips, and overall, I was very happy with the meal. The tempura and fish were cooked perfectly crispy on the outside and super tender inside. While the fish was a little bland for my taste, the texture made up for it.

The calamari was very flavorful, though it did have a bit more breading than I prefer. Still, the seasoning made up for it, but I would have loved to taste more of the calamari itself. The fries that came with fish & chips were the only letdown, not quite up to par, but they didn’t detract too much from the overall experience. I'd definitely return!

Greeted with a big smile from the server Sofi, who has provided adequate service for our party of 4.  Ramen came out first and did not disappoint.  Spicy tuna over crispy rice is a must-try if you want a unique appetizer experience, so as the pork bun.  Will be back next time we are in the area.

Really good ramen. Been here twice with my wife and friends. We really like the vegetarian ramen… great flavorful soup broth. Can be enough for two, but I would recommend to get your own. The crispy rice with tuna is delicious - a bit of hot sauce can embellish the flavor if you dare! We tried the ramen with chicken broth but replace with tofu. It was good, but I still think the vegetarian ramen is better, IMHO. Edamame was ok, it had lemon or lime squirted in it - wasn’t my cup of tea, but my wife loves lemon, so a win for her. There is a 16% surcharge FYI. I would come back to try the crispy garlic chicken.

Many of my Taiwanese friends recommended it to me. This Boiled Fish with Pickled Cabbage and Chili is becoming increasingly popular.

It has a scallion and tomato flavor but is not spicy. I personally don’t think it’s anything special. The fish slices are very soft and the soup is a bit sour because the pickled cabbage, good to eaten with white rice.

Service is fast and friendly , but table so small and tiny .

Price is very reasonable, 2 people $38 , one appetizer - deep fried chicken , 2 drink , one pot of fish .

We arrived for an early dinner at 5:45 PM with easy seating and parking available. Was seated quickly and ordered via QR code. We ordered the Large Old Pot Sauerkraut Fish ($27), which came quickly and was piping hot. Fish was tender, vegetables and other ingredients cooked well, very flavorful. They have varying levels of spice for different palates, but the single chili pepper soup was just right for us. Pretty reasonable price for two people in the Bay Area.​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​ Would recommend!

Pretty good authentic braised food （卤味）. The owners are quite friendly.

We got the red oil chicken (口水鸡) takeout and it was really nice. Chicken is so tender (probably most tender chicken without too much grease) and the spicy sauce makes the chicken more tasty (real spicy that you can feel). Note the sauces are on the side (2 spicy sauce cups and 2 non spicy sauces) and you can control the spicy level by yourself. The sauce is so great that even the cucumbers and peanuts inside are tasty.

Also got some other braised food and they are vacuum packed and in the refrigerator which makes the food much safer, especially in the summer. See one of the pictures that shows the refrigerator. I haven’t tried them yet,  will update later. Update: they are super spicy, much spicier than the red oil chicken.

There’s more food I’d like to try in this place, such as Cold noodles and Liangpi（凉皮), braised beef shank（卤牛腱）and braised pork hock, bell shaped dumplings （钟水饺). Both pork hock and bell shaped dumplings are sold out this time.

The only complaint I have is about the parking place. Street parking available but limited, there’s a bit parking lot nearby but it was not designed for the store, not sure if I should park there.

Well it is a to-go place. So no dine in. I didn't know that at first. But the food were AMAZING! I will definitely be back for more! Very delicious! Love the Dandan noodle and the shredded chicken with chili oil.

name: One Pot Shabu Shabu
cuisine: Home Goods Store, Food, Point Of Interest, Store, Establishment

reviews.comment: It’s so satisfying to have a hot Shabu Shabu in a cold day. This shop offers high quality dishes, from meat to vegetables, broth to sauces. We had Ribeye and Kobe beef combo, with house special and sukiyaki broth. They pair very well. I especially loved the sesame sauce, so special and tasty - it made the meat and vegetables taste even better! We felt the quality of food from this restaurant in every dish they offered. We will definitely come back. Highly recommend!

🍵 One Pot Shabu Shabu – A Cozy Hot Pot Experience

My girlfriend and I love hot pot, so we had to try One Pot Shabu Shabu when we spotted it next to Daiso. It’s a small, intimate spot, with lighting that keeps the focus on what matters—the food!

🍲 Broths & Proteins

We ordered:

House Special Broth (Miso/Soymilk) – my pick

Garlic Miso Broth – my girlfriend’s choice

Both were flavorful and well-balanced. For meats, we had Kubota Pork Belly and American Kobe Beef, both top-tier in quality. Even the standard cuts were incredibly tender.

Each meal includes a generous veggie box 🥦 and a choice of rice or noodles. I chose clear noodles (harusame), while she went with rice.

☯️ The "One Pot" Twist

Instead of individual pots, they serve the broth yin-yang style, letting you share and swap flavors. Plus, there’s a temperature control knob so you’re not stuck with boiling-hot broth the entire time.

🥜 Dipping Sauces

They provide sesame sauce and ponzu sauce—mix and match to find your favorite combo. I liked a bit of both!

⭐ Final Thoughts

One Pot Shabu Shabu stands out with high-quality meats, flavorful broths, and thoughtful details. Whether you're a hot pot pro or a first-timer, this place is a must-try. We’ll definitely be back—maybe for the premium cuts next time! 😍🔥

It’s a pretty decent Thai restaurant!

I’ve sat outside a few times, but this was my first time dining inside. The service, atmosphere, and food were all great. Both the service and atmosphere were casual, but the food seemed to have more attention to detail than typical casual places, and the taste was noticeably better compared to others.

The Tom Yum Goong was great, and the Green Curry was delicious too!

Great restaurant with upscale vibes. Food tasted good too. Only downer being pad Thai had too much tamarind sauce and tasted over tangy. Smelt fish was crispy and great with their peanut dip. The pop star drink is very sweet. Definitely recommend their crab fried rice and summer rolls.

name: Holder's Country Inn Restaurant & Bar
cuisine: Bar, Bakery, Store, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Really enjoyed the fresh juicy salad. Chicken on the special menu was delicious, big shrimp with nicely cooked chicken, and artichoke! With good rice and veggies! Food portion is huge, great price, very good service - they were out of clam chowder when we ordered, but our waitress brought out an extra clam chowder for us when it was available again, really nice of her!

There is plenty sitting inside and outside. place is almost full during the brunch over the weekend. There is also a bar for drinks. Server was nice in helping is customize our food. Overall food tastes good.

name: The Blue Pheasant Restaurant
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
The view out the window was wonderful.

My Prime Rib was awesome and perfectly cooked!!! They have a good beer and wine menu. Service was outstanding.

The bar area was very lively.

I love the blue pheasant  go there all the time me and my wife of 14 year now . I love you dohar doe the like money that my wife. I get to see my friend's  love you guy. I love that place and the people.

We frequently visit Red Hot Wok next door but never ate here until recently. Our friends said it was their favorite restaurant hands down, so we tagged along with them. They’re from Hunan and so is my family, so I had high expectations which were let down.

For protein, we got a duck, frog, and tofu dish. They all had the same flavor profile—salty and oily—and way too much filler, not enough protein. The frog dish probably only had one frog. The only dish we completely finished was the hot and spicy shredded potato. The dishes also came out really slowly, maybe 15 minutes between each one, to the point we thought they had forgotten.

Patron bathroom was also out of order when we went, so you had to use the inside employee restroom.

Bench seating has this built-in wall, making it a bit awkward if you have a belly or are less mobile.

Small parking lot but plenty of street parking around. No wait on a Sunday night.

This is undoubtedly one of the best Chinese restaurants in the Bay Area. The menu offers a wide variety of dishes, and everything we order consistently exceeds expectations. The restaurant owner is super friendly, and the ambience is just great. I would definitely bring friends and coworkers here again.

As I was craving Pho, we visited this place with great reviews. Thankfully, despite the long lines, we managed to get a table in less than 10 minutes. We ordered
Pork Sausage Rolls
Grilled Pork Rolls
Sauteed Flank Steak Pho

We found it interesting that our starters came later after our Pho was served; perhaps we waited another 5 minutes. Wouldn't it be great to have the appetizers before our main dish? We felt it was fast moving chain of restaurant, it was great that our Pho came quickly but it wasn't hot - more of warm Pho. We enjoyed the rolls and the flavor of the Pho despite only having it warm.

Overall, we enjoyed the dishes that we ordered and were happy.

Fast service, delicious food.

We arrived around 12 noon, and the queue is about a full page long, maybe 20 ahead of us.   Went back to the car so we can get seated bec the waiting area indoors is full, and it's raining outside. After 25 mins, we got a call on my phone that our table was ready.  Went in and got seated immediately.

We were escorted to our table.  It was empty except for the paper cover and the menus.  When we got seated, another person brought the utnesils and glases of water.  We were told to call her when ready.

We ordered one beef Pho to share with my wife and one appetizer plus 2 appetizers to-go.  We were told there is a surcharge of 18% for dining in, so we will be charged separately for the to-go order - it makes sense, no problem.

It only took maybe 2 mins, and our hot Pho order arrived with one extra bowl so we can share. That was quick, considering the place is busy with a long queue.  Then, after 5 min, the crab appetizer came.

The Pho was really good.  It's not salty and tasted better than our favorite Pho place.  It came in a larger bowl, so immediately, we can say that we made the right decision to share it.  The beef peices are in cubes and they're cooked well and easy to chew and eat.  However, it didn't come with a lot of meat - or could be bec they're in thick cubes, instead of several thin slices.

My wife's favorite was the crab appetizer.  I liked it too, but I liked the Pho better.

Our to-go order were Pork Egg rolls and Goi Cuon.  I avoid reviewing to-go orders if we don't immediately eat them as soon as we get home, so I will not comment on these unless they are exceptionally still good even hours later.

A casual eatery for Japanese udon noodles. The menu was largely different types and styles of noodles. Service was quick. The udon noodles tasted fresh, and the broth was flavorful. I tried the Utsuke Udon Tsukemen, which had the noodles and broth served separately and then you add the noodles to the broth when eating. It was a solid dish. We also added a side green salad for some fiber and greens.

The tempura udon is very filling. The broth tastes great, be sure to get the tempura or it will be a bit bland.
The karaage looked delicious.
Service is wonderful, very friendly staff.

name: Bento Corner
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Pro: They take credit cards! 😎

This corner shop might not sell 'bento' boxes as stated in their name, but you definitely will find something yummy to eat.

The shop does not have a sit down area. Most of the items here are meant to be eaten cold or heat it up at the comfort of your home. You can walk in, grab what is in the fridge, pay, and leave.

The owner is very nice and answered all my questions since it is my first time here.  Support your local small businesses!

Food: I picked Dan Dan Noodles, Beef Combo, Green Bean Jelly, and Pork Intestines (for my hot pot 🤤). You can see the pork intestines are cleaned very well and filled with fat.  Most items are priced between $8 -$12 and good portion sizes.  I got all 4 dishes under $45 with tax.

They also have homemade beef jerky from sweet to spicy and other delicious looking food I haven't explore. I definitely will come back and give it a try!

Came from out of town for work. Randomly stumbled upon this little jam. The 滷肉拌麵 is so tasty I don't know how to describe it. You would have to try it yourself.  And it's only $10?! Where do you find cheap yummy food like this.

They take credit cards, but no AMEX. Take out only.

You need to make reservations before you go, specially over the weekend and Friday night!

Very cordial and efficient service, from the hostess to the waiter and waitress, to the chief who cooked our food, all seems very nice and friendly.

Everything cooked to our order and liking and make sure all our needs been taken care of.

Average cost per person is around $50 to $80 dollars if you not ordering lobster and A5 beef!

Meats are tender. Food is good.

Come here to celebrate birthday.
Each table has at least 1 person having birthday.

Both New York strip and filet are tender and tasty. Chicken breast is nice, I order it only for trying its taste.

Service is great.
But over all, this is an American-Japanese restaurant, not a Japanese restaurant.
Please correct your expectations.

I ordered a variety of dishes today, and perhaps because there were so many items, I realized that two of the same drinks were missing pearls. I contacted the store to report the issue, and they responded quickly, immediately refunding the cost of one of the drinks. Although they only refunded one drink, I could still feel the store's sincerity and attentiveness. Additionally, they informed me that I could get a free drink on my next visit. The food was also very delicious. Despite the small mistake, the store's swift handling left a great impression, and I look forward to coming back again!
We got the food from company group order. The package is nice! Small three side dishes and one entree. The tomatoes eggs are pretty sweet. The eels are very soft and heavily marinated.

Recommended by RedNote. Very authentic and definitely one of the my best Hainan Chicken rice in Bay Area. The chicken and chicken rice are both very flavorful. You can tell the ingredients are fresh and food is prepared carefully with heart. The food is in high quality and the price is very reasonable with its large portion. I’m surprised that such a fantastic restaurant is hidden in a small plaza. Will definitely come back again.
11/23/2024, build your own soup or order chef combo. You can change chef combo for additional cost. Tom Yum soup similar to Thai, very tasty.

We had our lunch 3-4 times here - dine-in & take out both. Fresh food, tastes good. I really like their Grilled Chicken wrap with mango slices in it - its really yummy! The other dish we had was Grilled Chicken Bowl.
Next time will try some other dishes too.
Ambience is simple. Service is quick & good. Full marks for cleanliness.

I love this place. I mainly order the house grilled tilapia with steamed veggies. I'd say it's one of my favorite fish dishes. Today the edges were a bit burned, But the rest was perfect as usual. Total cost of the meal was $19.63 after tax.

A nice deck overlooking the course makes this a decent stop for lunch even if you aren’t playing golf here.  The setup is a bit odd as you enter through the pro shop and the counter is shared between food and golf purchases.  While my patty melt was tasty, $18 seems a tad high
Good food, friendly staff, and great outdoor seating options makes this a stop worth making.

Nice place and delicious food. My daughter and I got in a good mood after having dinner here. Very nice staff. We liked that everything was fresh, the fish tasted amazing! We were also pleasantly surprised by the large portions and received a compliment from the establishment - free tea, which was very nice. By the way, the tea is very delicate and fragrant. And this is a quiet place where you can have a good chat with friends. We will definitely be back!

Azuma offers thoughtfully and skillfully prepared delicious Japanese food served with quiet simplicity and pride. We had four of their house specialties: Gindara Kasuzuke (broiled Alaskan black cod marinated in sake and miso), Chaean Mushi (steamed egg custard loaded with yummy umami proteins and veggies), Shimeji Mushroom Saute, and Kinpira Gobo (sauteed burdock root). These dishes are all worthy of your time and attention - all bursting with umami and delicately balanced in flavors. We also had one of the best Yakitori we have ever had. They served a generous portion of Ohitashi, a personal favorite. Finally, the saki and hamachi nigiri sushi they served were delicately delicious and perfect. Azuma is truly a gem! Highly recommended 👍🏼

Shanghai no 1 now known as Shanghai Bun Dynasty is so yummy! I loved coming here with my family. We ordered so many yummy dishes from dim sum to salt & pepper fish to fried rice, every dish was so good! My favorite would have to be the salt & pepper fish. Everything was seasoned well and the portions were huge! Service was quick and the dumplings were so yummy. You can watch at the window and see the dumplings get made. It was super cool! Will definitely be back again with my family!

This was my first time eating Shanghainese cuisine (with the exception of things I’ve eaten at a dim sum spot before) and I was able to try out a lot of new dishes here that my friend picked out. We got there on a Sunday afternoon, it wasn’t too busy and we got seated right away and had easy access to their menu using the QR code on the table. Ordering was super easy and food started coming out within 5-10 minutes.

蒜香四季豆 Stir-fried Garlic Flavored String Beans *Rating: 10/10* - Absolute fire!! You can’t go wrong with this dish in general and this place made it to perfection. I would’ve eaten all of it if I wasn’t so full.

牛肉卷饼 Beef Roll *Rating: 10/10* - Girllll I’ve never eaten anything like this before it was so delicious. I was skeptical about the cucumber at first, but the beef, the cucumber, the wrap– all of it together was heaven! I wish I could’ve ordered more of this.

鸡蓉玉米羹 Chicken & Cream Corn Chowder/Soup *Rating: 10/10*- I love me some soup, so when I saw this on the menu I begged my friend to order it for us. It was so delicious and soothed my throat. I saved some for the next day and enjoyed it one more time.

蟹粉小笼包 Crab Roe Soup Dumplings (XLB) *Rating: 10/10* - This was some standard crab roe soup dumplings, delicious and didn’t come out TOO hot like they usually do. I was a little sad that two came with the soup spilling out already but it was enjoyable otherwise.  生煎包 Pan-fried Buns *Rating: 10/10* - Loveeed these pan-fried buns. It was the perfect combination of crispy and the typical dumpling texture. The meat inside was savory and could give me a heart attack that’s how fire it was.

葱油拌面 Scallion-Oil Mixed Noodles *Rating: 8/10* - I liked these in general and they were good, but lacking a specific flavor I was personally looking for.  Still ate it up though!

糖醋小排 Shanghai Style Sweet and Sour Pork Ribs *Rating: 8/10* -  Okay before I say anything this is one of the new items I tried for the first time and they were good but I wouldn’t order it for myself. I’m glad my friend shared this with me. It is indeed sweet and sour.

红烧狮子头 Braised Pork Meatballs *Rating: 8/10* - This was pretty good but I also would not order this for myself personally. I think if the rice we got on the side was more fresh I would’ve enjoyed eating it with the meatballs more.

红烧肉鹌鹑蛋 Braised Pork Belly and Quail Eggs *Rating: 6.5/10* - I was really excited that we decided to order this one but once we got it, the flavor profile did not match what I was expecting is all. It was still good, the meat was delicious but it did have like a… ginger/cinnamon flavor to it that I wasn’t a fan of? Oh loved the quail eggs though.

It was my 2nd time coming here for lunch, and I am happy to say it was better than the first. We ordered the set menu for two, which was great. It included everything we wanted. Pickled cucumber appetizer, shrimp fried rice, braised beef shank and tendon noodle soup, fried pork chop, stir-fried vegetables and a four seasons green tea for two. All 5/5. We also added more appetizers. Fried fish cake and squid balls. If you are into Taiwanese food, check this place  out.
