It was busy despite coming right at opening on a weekend, but we were seated and served efficiently! Staff was very helpful with questions about the menu. All of the food was hot, fresh, and delicious. I really enjoyed the texture of the handmade noodles which were perfectly thick and chewy!

Had a wonderful and tasty dinner with friends. The ramen was excellent and the starters were great. Service was welcoming and hospitable. I'll come back to try more dishes from the menu. We had a great time.

Here’s a possible review:

Visited this place recently and tried the Akamaru Modern, Veggie Shiromaru Classic, Pork Bun, and Veggie Bun. The ramen flavors were some of the best I’ve had—rich, flavorful, and satisfying! The interior decor was really nice and added to the dining experience.

The service was excellent; the servers were kind, and everything was served quickly, which was great. However, I did find the portions a bit small—my ramen felt like half a bowl. For the price, which is on the higher side, a bit more quantity would make it perfect.

The parking could be an issue if you are looking to park in the complex, however there’s a multi level parking garage besides as well.

Overall, great flavors and atmosphere, just wish the portions matched the price!

The food and service are good, but the price may be a bit high, three courses + tip $80.

We love the iron plates seafood tofu , probably is the best in the Bay Area !

To me, the best dish was the vegetable tofu in brown sauce, because it was flavorful enough to enjoy various kinds of flavors. The establishment is clearly a Chinese restaurant that many would visit on a random basis, as it is located amongst a lot of stores that have Chinese on their titles or related to Chinese culture in an outlet format in Cupertino.

I thought the Kung Pao Chicken was pretty standard and was good enough to make myself full. The black mushroom with vegetables was unfortunately below my expectations as the mushrooms had strong flavor while the vegetables didn't have any, causing a flavor imbalance, while the dish itself didn't have enough juice or broth to allow some mushroom umami flavor to flavor up the vegetables. The sesame bread with green onion was pretty thick and I mostly used it to accompany my dishes instead of rice, and since it was flavorless itself, it worked out fine. However, if one was expecting it to taste like the scallion pancakes that are popular in China, then one could be disappointed.

Since there were other Chinese restaurants around the area, if I make it around the area again, I would most likely try another spot instead.

This place deserves more than 5 stars. I’ve been ordering from here since the pandemic and the quality has only gotten better. Peking duck is delicious and I genuinely believe they have the best Peking duck on the California coast.

First thing first… we tried to order the 6-7 set menu dinner which supposed to give 1.5 Peking Duck, but they said it’s either 1 or 2.   I felt we got ripped off because it's on the menu but they wouldn't honor it for whatever reason.

土豆 - is a local dish.  Vinegar stir fry potatoes.  It's ok. Acquired taste.

酸菜粉絲 - Actually not bad, sour but I enjoyed it.

大盤雞 - My favorite dish. The chicken and potatoes was flavorful.  The noodle was too soggy but taste good with the sauce.

Peking duck - It's actually very good.  Some of the skins were so crunchy it almost melt in your mouth but they're are other pieces more tough and the meat is a bit overcooked.

Sweet and sour pork - the batter was crunchy when it first came out.  Then get soggy.  It's not bad.

Kung Pao chicken - Good flavor, not bad.

Tofu - pretty plain. Sauce on the salty side.

I've to say I was disappointed when they couldn't give us the 1.5 duck. I assume they have a legitimate reason.   However, after a few dishes, I was pretty satisfied for the food is pretty good.  It's a Peking home style cooking.

One interesting aspect... No tips required.

I recently needed to celebrate birthday and miss Peking duck so I decided to come here. I felt imperial treasure is way overpriced and Beijing Duck House is closed on Tuesday so I came here.

But honestly I'm pleasantly surprised at how delicious some of the food has become. Maybe they improved their cooking but I decided to give them 4 stars instead of the typical 3 I would have given for food before.

The missing one star has a lot to do with how long it took for us to get our food. Maybe it's because they were busy but we wait over an hour for our food including the duck that we pre-ordered.

Otherwise I think their duck is really good deal because they gives you a lot of sauce and the wraps so you don't necessarily have to order extra wraps like other places do.

The other dishes are not bad either especially the boiling fish because it's really delicious. Even the cauliflower was well made. I think this place definitely deserves coming back more often because the quility of cooking went up.

The service can be slow because they are so busy and I like the availability of those semi private spaces.

Called the night before to reserve a Peking duck. It was very well made.
After the meat is sliced off you can ask them to make the leftover meat and bones into a seasoned dish or soup. I think the seasoned dish is good but ok to skip. I would like to try the soup next time.

Malatang noodle hotpot by weight with a pick-your-own-broth option is a fantastic dining experience for customization lovers. You select your ingredients—from fresh vegetables to proteins and noodles—pay by weight, and pair them with a broth of your choice. The broths are rich and flavorful, whether you prefer mild, spicy, or numbing Sichuan-style. It’s perfect for those who enjoy tailoring their meals to their tastes. Fresh ingredients, quick cooking, and a casual vibe make it a must-try for hotpot enthusiasts!

Came here for lunch on a Sunday with a friend and we got here early because we weren't sure how long the wait would be. Arrived at 11:45am because the place doesn't open until 11:30 am on Sunday and it was very easy for us to find parking. I've been to the Milpitas location and wanted to give this one a try since it's the same restaurant and I like it since it's a build your own noodle bowl and you even get to choose the broth base. I went with the tom yum soup base and it was delicious. I will also say that this location didn't seem to have a bottle of mala spice which I was a bit disappointed in.

The seating arrangement of the store has the tables really close to each other in the restaurant.

Food was delicious! Beyond the great food was the excellent service. My little one was being super fussy and the manager was so accommodating and understanding trying to console him as well and trying to give suggestions but he was super sleepy and wasn't having it but we really appreciated her support. Will definitely plan better and return. The braised pork was my favorite.

Bob Ross was right about happy little accidents!

My girlfriend and I were craving soup dumplings. We were at another restaurant across the street but realized it was the wrong place. It felt so cold and dark there. So we left and ended up at XLB Kitchen, a hole in the wall, and it was the best thing ever. The place is small but has an outdoor area. The vibe was very local Chinese—a Chinese grandpa was eating at a table next to me, reading his newspaper. Love it!

The hostess greeted us at the door and immediately gave us menus and tea. The menu is simple yet it had all the classic Chinese dishes. We ordered XLB, shanghai style rice cakes, and string beans. ALL DELICIOUS.

The XLB were HUGE! Thin skin yet SO juicy. Dare I say, better than Din Tai Fung!? The plate of rice cake was a pleasant surprise too. Very tasty, not too oily, included veggies too. The string beans were a classic, maybe a little pricey.

Overall, we cleaned everything off our plates and left with full stomachs and smiles. We will be back!!

name: Scratch
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Excellent restaurant with beautiful and tasty food, attentive service, and a modern decor. We had Ahi Poke Bites (loved the crisp nori chips), Little Gem Lettuce Salad w/ Salmon, Cider Glazed Pork Chop.

We came in at about 9pm on a Saturday night for drinks as a couple and sat in the bar. The kitchen was closing, and I think the bar closed at 9:30 so there was really only time for one drink at our pace. Seemed strange to close that early for a weekend night on Castro Street. Besides that the service was okay, and the drinks were pretty good. I really liked the atmosphere.

name: Doppio Zero Mountain View
cuisine: Meal Delivery, Meal Takeaway, Grocery Or Supermarket, Bar, Store, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment: Our favorite Italian restaurant in the Bay area. Neapolitan styled wood fired Pizzas are so thin and crispy. Mushroom Ravioli is super delicious. Tiramisu is amazing, so creamy and soft. I strongly recommend to check out this place. It’s advised to make reservations as this place is always busy.

The fettuccine wild boar was good--pasta was al dente and the meat was tender, though did taste quite like regular pork. The potato croquettes were AMAZING, melty on the inside and crisp on the outside. Place was a bit loud for regular conversation but the vibe and the servers were friendly!

Good spot for a burger. I think the only problem I really had was that our drinks came out after the entrees and we had to ask to follow up on them. Otherwise service was quick, the food was good, and the ambience was lively.

Was in town for an event and it seemed to be one of the few places that stayed open late. Had the nachos and a drink. The cheese and meat on the nachos were a bit cold. We also had the wings. My friend has the burger and fries, which to me was the best tasting plate from the table. Service was great. It's a bar atmosphere, so a bit noisy inside and if you sit closer to the outside, you have to regular street noise. There is outdoor seating if you prefer that. The drinks that were recommended to us were tasty and weren't too strong for the meals.

name: Cascal
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
It was a very nice atmosphere with a live band playing. The food is great. I thought the tapas would be small plates, but honestly those portions could be shared with four people. Got a go box home. The fresh burrata was amazing. Sangria was good but not particularly strong. The music is loud so if you want to have deep
Conversation it would be better to sit outside on  patio.

The food here tastes good. The meat is tender, the vegetables are so fresh, and so does the service. But it is not reasonable to charge 3% wage and welfare from the customers, it should be the owner’s responsibility instead of the customers. The tips are also charged based on the value of the after tax including 3% wage and welfare. You’d better pay close attention to your bills.

The food here is delicious and clearly made with fresh ingredients. We were seated right away without having reservations, although we had to sit outside because the indoor dining area was full even on a weekday.

The servers were very quick and helpful. I personally really liked the Fiesta Platter which allowed us to try a lot of the popular appetizers without getting too full. I would love to come back and try more dishes in the future!

First time being at this restaurant. We ordered a deep fried seafood (JALEA), a half rotisserie chicken, and a seafood paella (ARROZ CON MARISCOS) - The deep fried seafood tasted good and not too oily. The chicken thigh and drumstick were also delicious, but the breast was a bit too dry; The paella (they don't call it as such by the way) was good too, the portion isn't as big as you would see at other restaurant, but I would say it is enough for 2 - 4 adults if you intend to share all dishes.

We could find better taste of each individual dishes elsewhere, but to find them all in one restaurant is probably not that easy. All 3 dishes plus 2 drinks came in total $99+tax+gratuity, which isn't cheap for 2 people. We could've just ordered 2 dishes instead, but we thought we gave it a good try. Overall, the food is considered good, it is a solid 4 stars, but I won't give it 5 stars.

The waiter was super nice and friendly, the service should deserve 5 stars!! This restaurant is quite popular in the area, we were there without reservation, so we were given the choice of either at the bar or outdoor dining spot.

In summary, we have not yet found a good reason we would come back again any time soon. if we do, we probably would try out some other dishes and the seafood paella is probably the one we would order again.!!

I went to this place while on a work trip as we were craving some good German food. The sausages were absolutely fantastic. The beer selection was excellent and had something for everyone. I personally had the sausage bites appetizer and the cheese spaetzle dish. Both were extremely delicious and I can't wait to go back the next time I'm in the area.

We had an amazing dining experience! The food was absolutely delicious, and the service was top-notch. Everything we tried was fantastic, especially the sliders and the Bratwurstplatte (Sausage Sampler). The fries with cheese were a standout as well.

We’re already planning to come back soon to try the Wiener Schnitzel—it’s definitely on our list! Highly recommend this place to anyone looking for great food and an excellent atmosphere.

Whenever I visit the USA before heading home, I always look for good Italian food. This time, I found a new spot in the Mountain View area that serves quality Italian cuisine. The restaurant leans slightly upscale, thanks to its nice ambiance and well-prepared dishes.

We started with the grilled crispy octopus, which was cooked perfectly to the tenderness I prefer. The fried calamari with spicy dipping sauce was a great addition, especially when paired with a few glasses of wine. The classic burrata cheese with plenty of tomatoes was hearty, and I particularly enjoyed the soft, creamy texture of the burrata. The ahi tuna tartare, loaded with pickled vegetables, had a nice balance of flavors.

For my main course, I had the seafood fettuccine, which rounded out a satisfying meal. We finished with a trio of desserts—tiramisu, lava cake, and crème brûlée—bringing our lovely dinner to a sweet close. The service was great, though they did push high-end options like wine, liquor, and premium dishes. Just be mindful and check the prices before ordering.

Amazed to see a really good vegetarian menu. The food quality and taste is worth the price. Great ambience and the staff. 10/10 fine dining experience. We ordered a mushroom flatbread, ravioli and tiramisu.

Vegetarian reviewer:
Went to this restaurant on Valentine's Day. The restaurant is beautiful and sooo well lit. It looked aesthetic, and it was crowded (actually full).

We ordered:
1. Bruschette Assortite - This was the best dish amongst all our orders. There were 3- pesto cheese, mushroom, and one with tomato. All of them were great! I think $15 for this one still made sense.
2. App Gnocchi Gratinati - Super mediocre. Tasted kind of weird, and was pretty much a waste of $16.
3. Ravioli Zucca - Extremely oily. The gravy was mostly oil with some nuts and a couple of leaves. The nuts and leaves gave a nice flavor, but it couldn't cut it. Salt was less and it didn't justify a price of $28. This was actually our server's top recommendation.
4. Pizza Margherita - this was really underwhelming. $20.
5. Kick in Old Fashioned - My partner liked this drink, I liked it too. $15

The service wasn't great either. It took a long time and it is not the server's fault, but none of the suggestions worked great for us. Given the price point, I wouldn't recommend this place that much. I highly recommend going at a time when they have some happy hour/ offers for the try. I did read some people mentioning about it in reviews.

The server offered me a taste of a cocktail but never came back with it, maybe I was confused. But then I just skipped ordering one altogether.

Overall, it was a good experience--nothing fancy coz food wasn't top notch, but we loved the ambiance. We enjoyed our nice date night and made a memory for the next two weeks we were gonna live away!

Good Italian restaurant!! The appetizers are so delicious, especially the gnocchi and carpaccio. The calamari is very good as well. The rigatoni a la vodka sauce needs work though. Team of staff were attentive and service was great. The desserts are very good as well. Plenty of parking outside.

name: Roger Bar and Restaurant
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Love this hotel restaurant. We visit it so often for weekend brunch and stop by spontaneously for dinner as well. The staff are friendly and are generally quick. I love their Jazz night on Friday, which is a great opportunity for couples and friends to grab drinks together and chill. Their breakfast sandwich is so yummy.

Good solid basic hotel bar. The beer selection was extraordinary. Great cocktails too. Good for sharing and oh people watching too, like the business traveler types and a few locals.
Free Parking for 3 hours. Go, enjoy!

name: The Emerald Hour
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Modern, kinda swanky, hotel bar/restaurant with lots of seating options. More intimate comfy chairs and loveseats in the back. More informal high tables and TVs in front. Near the fireplace and/or out by the pool are nice too.

Consistently good craft cocktails. Small plates pricey, but delicious. Excellent service.

Highly recommend!
They opened recently. I am so happy to share their food.
Cocktails are so good, very tasty and high quality. Foods are also very good. They have a lot of small bites for drink but there’s dinner plate as well. (Steak, salmon and fish)
Cozy, clean, comfortable mood.
I want to visit again for drink and small bites!!

One of my go-to restaurants! We had a location nearby when we lived in Santa Clara, but I personally love this branch even more.

The food is always amazing and delicious. I especially prefer dining in rather than ordering delivery. When I last ordered from DoorDash, I found the portions to be smaller compared to the higher prices online. But when you dine in at the restaurant, that’s not the case—the food is served quickly, and the seafood is extremely fresh.

We’ve been here countless times, from casual evenings to birthday celebrations. I love how this place strikes the perfect balance between casual and fancy, making it great for any occasion. The ambiance is warm and inviting, and the service is always attentive, which adds to the overall experience. It’s definitely a spot we keep coming back to! (Apparently I cleared my phone form all other pics from this place perhaps I’ll finally them in storage discs later ). This one is from
Yesterday

We had a really good time sitting at the bar. The bartenders Shauna and Mark were really good and we enjoyed interacting with them. What we ate was also very good. We had the Sashimi trio and Japanese Wasabi original Ahi Poke bowl.
Latest update:
We've eaten here a couple of more times since my original review, and we were lucky that Shauna was our bartender! She's excellent and we have fun talking to her. We've had the sesame green beans and the Hawaiian Ahi Poke bowl, and both were very tasty. Yesterday, besides cocktails and wine we had the Guaca Poke followed by the Kanpachi and the East Coast Lobster roll, and both were so "Ono" For dessert we had the Macadamia nut gelato.

Came here for a Saturday brunch. The atmosphere was great! I loved the huevos rancheros - it was flavored very well! The french toast with 3 leches was also good but could have been a little more drenched. The mocha latte and matcha latte were a little underwhelming. Service was really good!

Came here with my parents and it was a super cute experience!

Good:
- There was a wall with hearts for Valentine's day (I think) and it was a great photo-op
- The food all came out pretty quickly, the coffee took longer than expected though
- I liked the horchata latte - it wasn't too sweet and tasted great
- The prosciutto avocado toast was amazing! It came with a sweet chili crisp that wasn't too spicy and added a ton of flavor

Bad:
- Super busy, when we left it was a 20 min wait time so we're lucky we came early enough!

Overall would come again, super cute ambiance and vibe.

name: Alexander's Patisserie
cuisine: Bakery, Cafe, Meal Takeaway, Food, Point Of Interest, Store, Establishment

reviews.comment: Located in the vibrant downtown, Mountain View with tons of other restaurant, it’s a great place to grab some quick coffee and pastry. On a lovely sunny day, we can sit outside and people watch while you enjoy your coffee. The selection was quite good, and everything looked very delicious, although a bit pricey. I settled with an almond croissant, which was very well done. I also got an iced latte, which again was a little bit expensive, but again very well made. Had it been a little more economical? I would have given this place a five star. Nevertheless, it’s a good choice if you want some pastries and coffee.

I've been to Alexander's Patisserie several times, and they truly are a good place to visit if you're looking for well-decorated and beautiful desserts. They taste good as well and are primarily mousse based which some people may prefer. The price is a bit steep, but you can see the quality and craftsmanship in their desserts so I don't think it's too expensive for what they sell.

Staff is helpful but has spilled several of our drinks when serving them at the table. The seating area is often full and crowded and can't accommodate large groups, but you could also try to sit outdoors. The indoor dining also is a bit messy as people are constantly coming in and out.

It's a classic spot for a hot drink and a dessert, and I definitely frequent Alexander's when I'm in the area!

This place has good vegetarian options. The chicken plate was fine for $15 but the okra plate was very good.

Yogurt w cucumbers very fresh. Hummus was good, but not like most restaurant hummus. it was more fatty and sour than creamy (if blended for longer, would have been more creamy) so it was good w rice instead of pita.

Chicken texture wasn't super tender but all food was hot and fresh.

Each plate came with 2 pieces of pita

Ambiance was fine, price was good for what you get esp for this area. Would come back.

10/18/2024

Mediterranean Grill House
650 Castro St Ste 110
Mountain View, CA 94041

I went there for lunch around noon on a Friday.  It's on Castro between Church and High School streets.  There is street parking and an underground lot behind the Wells Fargo shared with St. Joseph Church.  There is an order counter with a menu board above.  I ordered the Lamb Kebab, medium rare, plate with Hummus and Garlic Potatoes.  I was given a number stand to place at my table and waited a short time for my meal to be delivered along with 4 quarters of Pita bread and Tzatziki sauce.  It's a clean table and chair interior for about 30 people.  There is dining outside also.

My four large lamb cubes were mostly medium rare, lightly salted and with Mediterranean spices.  The long grain rice was very good, soft and moist.  The Hummus had good lemon and Tahini flavor and the garlic potatoes were soft and mildly flavored.  The Pita bread was warm and soft.

Everything was delicious, quality was very good and quantity also, I took most of the bread and Hummus home. Service was prompt and helpful.  Definitely repeatable.  Your clothes and hair will acquire the grilled meat odors, the grill and dining area are not separated, be warned.

name: Steins Beer Garden & Restaurant
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: One of my favorite places, and I’m at so thrilled that they are no longer closing! Everything from the ambiance, beer, service, to their made-from-scratch food is perfect for a weeknight meal or a gathering with friends. Can’t go wrong with anything from the menu. Thank you, Steins!
Finally got a chance to visit before they close. Got some decent beer going on, decent food. Very expensive though. Worth a shot before they're gone if you've ran out of restaurants around the area.

I went with my family for dinner on a Friday night. We did not have reservations but the friendly staff were able to get us a table in about 10 minutes as we chose to sit indoors. The outdoor seating looked rustic and inviting but it was a cold night and although they have heaters, I didn’t want to brave it.
We ordered off the vegetarian options on the menu.
We started with the minestrone soup and although it has chicken broth,  we were ok with that. The bread on the house was soft and delicious! But the soup was quite lacking in flavor.

We ordered a vegetable pizza and the fettuccine Alfredo. The vegetables on the pizza were like semi baked (zucchini) and the tomato slices on top were placed as garnish, which is a slightly different concept for me, but I’m not sure I’m a fan. It also lacked quite a bit in flavor IMO and tasted quite bland.
The pasta was ok; nothing to write home about.
The service was good and staff was pleasant but the food unfortunately was a little disappointing. Again this is the vegetarian part of the menu and that may be the reason

In the middle of El Camino Real in Mountain View is Giorgio’s Italian Grill and Pizzeria, a cute Italian joint with plenty of seating (outdoor as well) and free parking.

I got the complimentary bread bowl which you have to ask for. It comes with delicious subtle garlic butter and fresh sourdough. I got the chicken parmigiana. It was a large platter of breaded chicken, spaghetti with marinara sauce, and garlic spinach. The chicken was insanely tasty with melted mozzarella and fresh tomatoes on top. It was well breaded and extremely tender on the inside. They did not skimp on the chicken at all with 2 big cutlets of it. The spaghetti also tasted extremely fresh with marinara sauce. The garlic spinach was very oily though, but it did have a subtle garlic flavor. I didn’t like the spinach as much. The portions were extremely large and I got 2 meals from it!

OVERALL, Giorgio’s was a delicious spot with decent service and great ambiance. The dishes were quite affordable for its large portions. I definitely recommend Giorgio’s to others, especially those who come in large parties.

name: Seasons Noodles & Dumplings Garden
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
I ordered the braised beef noodle soup, and it was fantastic in every possible way! 🍜✨ The broth was rich and flavorful from the first sip, beautifully presented, and paired with fresh, perfectly cooked noodles. The beef was melt-in-your-mouth tender, and I couldn’t have been happier! 🤤🥢

I walked in during lunchtime and found plenty of seating, but since I was dining solo, I was seated at the front when I actually wanted a bigger booth. 😅 The place filled up quickly, creating a lively atmosphere with nice background music. 🎶

Great service and absolutely delicious food! Highly recommend! ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

I like this place. The noodles are awesome and the dumplings are great!

The service is pretty fast as well, but overall it’s a pretty chill spot.

Had dinner there and got both the noodles and dumpling, which came out hot and delicious. After that we also had the custard buns which were alright. I especially liked the tomato egg noodles out of everything we got.

It’s got yummy food and tasty dumplings, what more can you ask for? dipping them in the vinegar and chilli oil makes it even tastier though.

I really like the outside environment where the street was closed and well decorated for the holidays.

First the waitress placed some bread and oil based dipping on the table - I really liked it and had to stop my self a few times from filling up.

I tried their calamari as an appetizer, it was fresh and very tasty.

The breaded veal was fresh and delicious.  It was cooked just right and came with vegetable and mashed potatoes.  The whole dish was absolutely amazing.

The night ended with a chocolate cake - very tasty and what an awesome presentation.

The staff was very nice and very attentive - what a customer experience !!!

The food exceeded our expectations! The chicken was tender and flavorful, and the vegetables were perfectly cooked. The service was attentive, and the vibrant, colorful atmosphere made the dining experience even more enjoyable.

We were looking for a place with good crepes and finally found it here!
All the staff is kind and attentive, since the moment we entered they gave us the menus, counted us and began to prepare our table. Placing the order and paying was very quick, and the food didn’t take long to be served.
We had an omelette and sweet crepes, hot chocolate, cappuccino and coffee and everything was delicious. Portions have a good size, not too giant but big enough.
The place was also decorated with Christmas things, all looking great.
Restrooms are clean.
Overall a great experience.

What an amazing restaurant! I've visited it 3 times already and will be coming back many many more times.

Every time we walk in, there is always at least one table available as they have pretty of seats indoors and also outdoors. You walk in & order at the front desk, pay there, and thne you just wait for your food to be delivered to your table. Which happens very fast, their cooks are spectacular!

Now for the food... it's perfect. Never once have I nor anyone that aent there with me, had something wrong with the order. Everything I've ever eaten there was amazing, be that a breakfast food, the crepes, a sandwich, the best is the fries.

I'll definitely be ordering more new things from the menu.

It's also pet friendly! It's very nice to see so many dogs there :)

Burnt ends were tender and juicy!  Usually I find them like small nuggets not to soft!  They were nice here!  Beans were hot and flavorful!  Potato salad was so good!! Ribs were also amazing but on the smaller side! Overall great experience will definitely be back with others!

Cute little BBQ place in Mountain View, close to the 101 freeway. The brisket was moist and flavorful, and the Mac and cheese and bread were both delicious. However, the tri-tip was over cooked and not seasoned well. The parking lot is small and undergoing some construction, so limited parking spots.

The food was delicious! I loved the warm toasted bread with an earthy blend of herbs and olive oil, fresh flavors and textures of the strawberry spinach salad, and garlic crostini and seafood-infused tomato broth of the Bouillabaisse.

Our dishes came out fresh and quite soon after we ordered (~5 minutes or so) and the ambience was casual but elegant.

Flavorful food served with friendly service and hospitality in the hustle and bustle of downtown Mountain View. Excellent cocktails line up and wine selection to complement a nice menu.
Dishes were presented in creative ways with generous portions.  Our group had a wonderful meal.
My favorite was the grilled octopus, truffle fries, and duck breast. Highly recommend!

name: Olympus Caffe & Bakery
cuisine: Cafe, Bar, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment: Went in to try the viral Tres Leches cake and i was not disappointed. It was yumm! Delicious flavors and super moist, served dipped in condensed milk (i guess). We also tried the baklavas. They were great too! Would go back for savory dishes next time.

Nice place in downtown MV. Multi-cuisine restaurant. We went for Turkish breakfast. The food was okay. We also went for German beers in the evening. They have good collaboration of german beers. The pretzel was yummy with melted cheese.

name: Vaso Azzurro Restaurant
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
* Food: Solid, decent Italian. Nothing groundbreaking, but everything tasted good, including the basics like the olive oil and garlic.
* Menu: great choice for full course (4 mains, 2 desserts).
* Service: Staff was a definite plus – friendly and attentive.
* Atmosphere: Sounds like it's party-friendly.

* Overall: A reliable choice, especially for group gatherings. Not a culinary revelation, but you'll get a good meal and good service.

Had a lovely dinner at Vaso Azzurro! The Chicken Alfredo Pasta was creamy, rich, and perfectly cooked, with tender chicken and a well-balanced sauce. The Pesto Gnocchi was another highlight—light, pillowy gnocchi coated in a flavorful pesto sauce.

The ambiance was cozy and inviting, making it a great spot for a relaxed evening. Service was warm and attentive, though the food took a little longer than expected. That said, the quality made up for it!

Overall, a great Italian dining experience. Would definitely come back to try more dishes!

After my second visit, I can confidently say this has become a favorite spot in the Bay Area. As someone who recently moved from NYC, which has a lot of amazing Indian restaurants, this place has quickly become a top choice, hands down.

Everything I've had here has been solid. The staff and owner are very attentive and prices are very reasonable for the area.

A note for the spice junkies, "spicy" won't have you sweating, but it is a perfect amount of kick and flavor.

Helloooooo my spicy little chickpeas! Your queen Mother Masala is GAGGING over the flavor explosion I just experienced at Tandoori Junction! Four snaps in a Z-formation for this flavorful feast that had me living my best curry fantasy, hunty!

That Chicken 65 Biryani was serving BODY-ODY-ODY with its perfectly cooked rice and that chicken giving me all the seasoned drama I needed! Was it spicier than the backstage tea at a pageant? Absolutely! But mama didn't raise no seasoning-shy queen!

The Butter Chicken? DIVINE! Creamy, luxurious, and richer than my ex's new boyfriend. That sauce was so velvety I wanted to sew it into a gown and werk the runway!

Now the Palak Aloo threw some green realness that had me saying "Yes, spinach! Work that potato! Serve that nutrition!" It was giving healthy goddess while still bringing the flavor dance party!

That garlic naan? STUN-NING! Freshly baked, glistening with buttery goodness like my highlighter after a good setting spray. Though I had to get all diva and remind them I ordered it – don't make a queen wait for her carbs, darling!

The service? Well... let's just say it was more chaotic than my first time in five-inch platforms. A bit of confusion on the dance floor, if you know what I mean. Menus after ordering? A chai I didn't ask for? My Mango Lassi playing hide and seek? The drama!

Four stars, my lovelies! The flavors were IT, but the service needs a little choreography lesson. Might stick to takeout next time – this queen can't handle another encore of "where's my naan?"

XOXO,
Mother Masala 💋

name: Bonchon Mountain view
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Yangnyeom sauce still good but the soy flavor was way too salty.

Fast n quick services for Friday lunch time.
The new Yang yummm sauce is nice too.
Bimbimbap is nice n hot

Loved this spot! I got the Bulgogi stir fry that was really good ! Excellent service ❤️
🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟

Astoundingly delicious and gigantic Shrimp burrito (with generous shrimps!), perfectly hot and fresh thick-cut fries, and super friendly service. At $20 flat all-in with a drink, can’t beat the value. Yummy mild burrito side sauce too. Zero complaints, I’ll be going back!

A fun stop to share a crepe or beignet or a burrito. In this case, all three. The beignet came out first, it was airy bit not bready enough but the powdered sugar and chocolate spread made it tasty. The burrito was chicken and quite filling with rice, beans, lettuce and a side of chips with two salsas. The crepe was good with the banana and strawberry with whipped cream on the side. Service was nice, you eat outside with a couple of tables. We have seen this food truck, French and Mexican for awhile and we were curious. Next time, probably try their tacos or creme brulee.

name: Das Bierhauz
cuisine: Cafe, Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: It is a place that I am very pleased and enjoy every time I go. The food is very delicious, the beer is very good. The owners are very friendly and attentive. I think they are also very clean in terms of hygiene. I am excited every time I go and I will continue to go.

Great place, we made a reservation there on Saturday, great seating outside and the beer selection was great taste was awesome, we really enjoyed the bratwursts and also schnitzels were amazing too , definitely will try soon again

Ordered chicken tikka masala a la carte, lamb gosht a la carte, and rice. The chicken was a very good choice, I can see why this is a popular staple. The lamb gosht is also quite nice if you’re a fan of lamb. The rice was very fragrant and paired well with the curries. This meal was very great. We could not help wonder if the experience would have been better with in person dining. All orders are made online or via their QR code online. There is no in store seating, it's all pick up orders in to-go containers and paper plates. There is some seating outside and under a nearby tent but the experience is largely informal. Parking here is adequate, there are enough spaces to handle the lunch rush of customers.
We got zareen's thali to go. I got the palak gosht thali with naan, and the palak gosht was very flavorful and not too oily. The naan was also lightly fluffy and good to enjoy alongside the curry.

I really like this place. It's a funky, very narrow & long, easy to miss hole in the wall kind of place with really good food. We had the babaganoush, lamb moussaka and chicken, all delicious. The moussaka was loaded with meat, the chicken was tender - just a nice experience. Waiter was friendly, helpful and attentive. Recommended.

Have been here a couple of times and liked it. Pretty sure I had the Kayseri Manti the first time and loved the beef with the yogurt flavor. This time, I went for the octopus appetizer and my friend had the chicken kebab. They gave us two servings of the house pita, and we also had the kunefe for dessert. Everything was delicious. Will definitely go again to try other things on the menu. Staff is friendly and service is timely.

4.5 Stars
Visited Halal Street on a Sunday for lunch and went with the AYCE option at $24.95—such a great value! The buffet tables had an impressive variety, and everything was fresh and well-stocked. In addition to the usual hotpot ingredients, they even offered a solid selection of hot food items: the fried rice was very good, the chicken katsu was juicy, and the steamed buns, spring rolls, and sesame balls were all tasty and satisfying.

What really sets this place apart is the thoughtful extras: complimentary boba tea and fresh-churned Turkish-style ice cream were a fantastic bonus. Plus, there’s no time limit for the all-you-can-eat experience, which is a rare and welcome policy. It gave us the chance to enjoy our meal without feeling rushed, especially since it takes a little while for the hotpot broth to come to a boil.

The only downside was that some of the stoves weren’t working properly. One of our hotpots never boiled, and we had to switch tables mid-meal, which was a bit inconvenient. Hopefully, that gets resolved soon.

Still, overall a great spot for AYCE hotpot with excellent variety, fresh ingredients, and a relaxed atmosphere. Will definitely be back!

food was 10/10! we thought we overordered but ended up clearing every plate. everything was that good. the flavors are bold, ingredients are fresh, and overall just super satisfying. service was great too. everyone was kind and super efficient.

i saw a few reviews about the service, and as someone who’s eaten at a lot of authentic asian restaurants, it’s pretty standard not to have someone checking in every five minutes. personally, i prefer that—it lets me actually enjoy the food in peace.

you have to order the sautéed green beans, the spicy cumin fish, and the naan bread. my sister-in-law is also vegetarian and was able to enjoy a full meal here too. the garlic sautéed bok choy was also a favorite!

The food feels like home made food. We are here at least twice a week. The service is great, they are really nice. The food comes really fast. My kids love the sambar and chutney. The dollops of ghee in the Pongal gives an amazing flavor.  Go here and order anything, you won’t be disappointed.  Really glad to have this place in Mountain View.  It’s our default go to place for awesome South Indian food.

This is our go-to takeout spot, and we regularly pick up food from here. The service is great, with a friendly team at the front. The food quality is consistently excellent, and there’s a great variety of options to choose from. The coffee and breakfast dishes are among my favorites. The restaurant is always clean, and the seating is quite comfortable.

Pro tip: Weekday/ weekend  brunch is a must!

We celebrated my friend's birthday at this OH location. Their menu is the same as at the Palo Alto restaurant. Unfortunately they had black olives, not green ones which are much tastier with the pickles. Order a combo of small plates and appetizers 2 for $12 or 3 for $15. The rice bowl with veggies was good, however I would prefer more mushrooms on it. We liked that they substituted the pita with cut veggies for the hummus dip. Our server was very nice and helpful, chatty and polite.

Oren’s Hummus on Castro Street is a gem for Mediterranean food lovers! The hummus here is incredibly creamy and flavorful, served with warm, fluffy pita that’s perfect for dipping. They have a great selection of fresh salads, grilled meats, and veggie options, making it easy to find something for everyone. The casual, welcoming atmosphere and friendly staff add to the overall experience, making it a fantastic spot for a quick bite or a relaxed meal. Definitely worth a visit if you’re in the Castro area!

name: Mifen101 幺零幺(原花溪米粉王)

reviews.comment: This restaurant is absolutely amazing! From the moment you walk in, you’re greeted with a warm atmosphere and incredibly friendly service. The staff is attentive and makes you feel right at home. The menu offers a wide variety of dishes, each prepared with care and bursting with flavor. Their beef noodle is particularly outstanding—unique and unforgettable! The ambiance is cozy and beautifully designed, making it a perfect spot for a casual gathering with friends or a romantic date. The prices are very reasonable, offering excellent value for the quality. If you’re in the Mountain View area, I highly recommend giving this place a try!

A birthday celebration led us to noodles. We ordered different variations of beef, noodles and spice level. Very tasty and full of texture. We also ordered a fried bun and pork and cabbage dumplings. The servers were nice and welcoming. It is a small restaurant so it filled up quickly. The peanuts were a great bonus to go with the noodles.

name: Agave Mexican Bistro
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: A very nice place with a family friendly atmosphere! The Moxtil was called out as the best on the menu as it was a wonderful shrimp dish full of flavor.  The service was fast and friendly dry and the atmosphere was quiet enough with ample parking.  A local family favorite.

This place was really great! I live in San Antonio so I know good Mexican food and this place exceeded my expectations.
My chicken fajita skillet really impressed me! Typically I only get sautéed peppers and onions with my fajitas in San Antonio but these came with peppers, onions, mushrooms, carrots, broccoli, and some zucchini! Excellent!
The chicken was cooked perfectly and the tortillas were really good too.
Their free chips and salsa were also very fresh and crispy.
I started with a prickly pear margarita then tried the raspberry margarita and they're both really good also.  Only $12!!
Very happy with this place and I'll probably come back tomorrow night during my visit to the area 😆
They also have a huge selection of tequilas and other liquors with a very friendly and attentive staff.

2/21/25

Nick the Greek
298 Castro St
Mountain View, CA 94041

I went there for a late lunch on a Friday at 2:30 pm.  I ordered a Beef/Lamb Gyro from the menu board at the order counter and paid cash.  I gave my name and my gyro was brought to my table shortly.  The interior is a clean bench and table setup with contemporary diner furniture.  There is a large city free parking structure behind the restaurant.

My gyro was hefty with the meat slices, french fries, tomato, red onion and tzatziki sauce wrapped with a soft and thick pita.  The meat slices and fries were very noticeably salty although the overall flavor was good.

I thought it was a good value but it was way too salty for me so no repeat.

A welcome addition to DTMV, Nick the Greek is a solid choice for both takeout/dine-in. I always grab the beef/lamb gyro and recommend it. The combination of ingredients is consistently flavorful and delicious, and the value can't be beat (when it comes to eating out, anyway). Interior is clean and decently spacious.

The curry from the Katsu Curry Udon was good but the katsu was just okay, nothing special.

The soup from the Beef Sukiyaki Udon was delicious and I could of drank it as a beverage. The beef was so damn good I wish I had a second serving; there wasn't enough beef. I could do without the tempura pieces.

Udon here are pretty good but their standards seems to have drop since few years ago.

Some of their tempura are cold and hard but their prawns are still as good as ever. Probably that’s what most people order as well, allowing it to be more fresh.

Must try
Udon related dishes
Prawn tempura

Overall a great omakase experience with high-quality ingredients. I’ve been there twice, and the second time they intentionally changed the menu, which I really appreciated. The fish and other ingredients were fresh and seasonal. I especially like how the chef seasons the food just enough to let the natural flavors shine. The price is reasonable for the quality and experience you get.

I recently went to Katsu for my friend's birthday, and wow, what an amazing experience it was! Not only was the ambiance a beautiful, intimate atmosphere, but the staff and chefs exuded this wonderful, fun energy that made the dining experience that much more fun. The food itself was so delicious and so well thought out. From the conversation and observation of the chef's work, you can tell that each step is well thought out and intentional. Thinking about it now makes my mouth water - can't wait to come back again!!

10/10 would recommend for yall to stop by and experience this for yourself!

Hummus is one of our favorite places to eat in Mountain View!
We love the delicious food, the cozy atmosphere, and the kid-friendly menu.
We’ve tried many dishes, but our favorites are the appetizer sampler plate, lahmacun, beef sucuk pide, and köfte plate.
The staff is always very welcoming, special thanks to Aidana, who greets us with a bright smile every time :)
Highly recommend if you’re looking for a family-friendly spot with amazing food!

Very cute spot to grab a quick lunch and relax. The restaurant is so cute with light and airy room and beautiful interiors. It has lots of food seating spots and ones by the window are so cute.

They had the most amazing fresh made lemonade ever. Wow it was the best thing I
Had in my day. So refreshing and not overly sweet.
For lunch I had ordered a Falafel wrap. It was so tasty and light. It was made with fresh ingredients and came quickly. I would definitely recommend this place if you are looking for something healthy, light and quick to grab. Definitely will come back again.

They staff is so friendly and they help you too.

The staff was super kind and accommodating to allergies (I asked for the Banh Mi without sauces). I also tried their matcha boba, and it was good and affordable. The bread and the meat were warm and surprisingly tasty! (It tastes better than it looks). It is next to the station and they brought my food very fast. I recommend.

Great food - as in all of their other locations.

Fast service and good quality food. Was lovely to sit outside in the sun and watch people passing by outside.

name: St. Stephen's Green
cuisine: Night Club, Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Great pub along the main cafe strip from the station to city hall, with friendly staff.
Fusion menu with references to Irish origin and elements like soda and white/black pudding in between other options.
Similarly screens show NFL whilst one has RTE.
On NYE they had free champagne when Europe hit midnight and Guinness when Ireland hit midnight

The fish and chips were wonderful. It was a beautiful day and we got to sit on the patio overlooking Castro St. But unfortunately the sign for lunch specials out front is a lie, it’s more like a list of 5-6 appetizers.

New Small Plate Options: Affordable and Convenient for All!

Content:
I recently visited 3 Kingdoms Hot Pot with three friends—four grown men in total—and we were all impressed by their newly introduced “small plate” options. It’s a thoughtful and budget-friendly addition that worked perfectly for us!

With this new menu, the average per-person spending is now between $30 -$50 making it an excellent choice for casual gatherings, whether you’re dining solo or in a group. The small plates are especially ideal for lighter eaters or those looking to try more dishes without breaking the bank. Even with four of us, we were able to order a variety of dishes to share, and the portions were just right—plenty to enjoy without any waste.

This change not only adds flexibility to the dining experience but also makes it more accessible for everyone to enjoy delicious meals at great value. If you’re looking for a spot that offers both quality and affordability, I highly recommend checking out their small plates. Whether you’re dining alone or with friends, you’ll love this convenient and satisfying option!

The best hot pot I've ever had in the Bay Area. The soup base is very authentic and rich. The meat is very fresh and tender. The dining environment is very comfortable. The small ingredients are rich, and the watermelon sesame balls can fill you up. This time I also got two free cups of milk tea, which is so delicious! I will come again.

Quality and abundance for the price. I ordered snow crab legs as appetizer and mixed tofu soup for my entree.
The snow crab legs were crisp outside, tender inside, fresh and flavourful.  The tofu soup was rich, hearty and all the seafood was cooked perfectly.
I liked that the entree comes with rice and so much banchan! It was very filling and I couldn’t finish it all. I also enjoyed the authentic flavors of the food.
To top it all off, the restaurant is very thoughtfully designed, so you are immersed in an elegant dining experience.

I really liked their mixed tofu—it came with a lot of ingredients and tasted very authentic. Each dish came with a variety of side dishes, and the best part is they’re refillable! The spicy octopus bibimbap wasn’t as flavorful as I expected, and it didn’t have that crispy rice at the bottom. The service was excellent, although the atmosphere was a bit noisy. I also appreciated the takeout packaging—it was really nice. Overall, I had a great experience!

name: Chaat Bhavan Mountain View
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Chaat Bhavan in Mountain View is a decent option, but it doesn’t quite live up to the standards set by its Sunnyvale counterpart.

Food: The food is decent, with flavors that are satisfying but not particularly memorable. While the menu offers a variety of classic chaat and Indian dishes, the overall taste doesn’t quite match the richness and authenticity I’ve experienced at the Sunnyvale location. It’s good for a casual meal, but not a standout.

Service: The service is alright, but it feels less polished compared to Sunnyvale. While the staff are generally helpful, the attentiveness and efficiency could be improved to create a more welcoming dining experience.

Ambience: The ambience is simple and functional, but it doesn’t have the same vibrant, inviting feel as the Sunnyvale location. It’s a decent place to sit and enjoy a meal, but the atmosphere lacks the warmth and energy that makes the other location so enjoyable.

Overall, Chaat Bhavan in Mountain View offers a reasonable option for Indian food, but it falls short when compared to the Sunnyvale branch. If you’re nearby, it’s worth a try, but I’d recommend heading to Sunnyvale if you’re looking for the best experience.
A go to place for indian street food, and any north Indian vegetarian food. We love paneer Tikka, malai paneer, Bombay tava pulav, chat basket, chole bhature to name a few dish.

name: sweetgreen
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: I had an amazing experience at this restaurant! From the moment I walked in, I was impressed by how clean and well-maintained everything was. The space was bright, welcoming, and had a great atmosphere. The food looked incredibly fresh, and the presentation was top-notch. You could tell a lot of care went into preparing each dish. The customer service was outstanding – the staff was friendly, attentive, and made me feel right at home. I highly recommend this place to anyone who hasn't been here yet. If you're looking for great food and a wonderful dining experience, don't hesitate to give it a try!

Chicken Pesto Parm Salad is the one I ordered and it has a good serving size. I also got an Organic Lemonade. The service is excellent! All the staff is coordinated. I enjoyed the Salad! They have all sorts of choices. You can enjoy eating outside or dining in or to go.

I recently visited Chez TJ and, unfortunately, my experience did not live up to expectations, especially considering the reputation of the restaurant. Upon arrival, the service was not what I’d expect from a fine dining establishment. No one offered to take our coats, and I had to point out and ask multiple times before they understood it should be taken. The lack of attentiveness continued as we waited a long time for our order to be taken, which was frustrating.

That being said, the food was quite good, and I particularly enjoyed the smoked quail—it was delicious. However, the overall atmosphere and service left much to be desired, and I don’t think I’ll be returning in the future. While the food was tasty, the experience wasn’t worth the lack of warmth and attentiveness in the service.

It was actually a nice experience with the spring special menu. Tastes are balanced, not too salty sauce or too sweet for desserts. Especially love the starting bites, flavorful bonito dish, plate cleanser sorbet, wagyu (sauce is terrific) and the two dessert dishes (beautiful Sakura mousse and tasty coconut Paris Brest). 7-course portion is big for me. I will revisit for 4-course in the future if the menu online looks good.

name: Mantra India Mountain View
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: The only complaint I have is the seating -- the booth is not exactly comfortable.   But the quality/variety of food ... I have been to several Indian buffet places, this is one of the few that I would like to visit often.

Best Indian Buffett in the Bay Area. While the food is tasty, the amount of spices are so balanced. No heartburn afterwards and that is the biggest problem with Indian cuisine. The variety of dishes offered are very delicious. Naans are the best. I highly recommend this place.

Been here a few times, and my family and I like this place! It’s pricey but the foods are really good! I usually don’t like meat, but I like the grilled beef tongue here! Really juicy and fresh! We like the salad a lot and ordered twice a night! The fishes are good and fresh.
Just be aware that there’s an extra charge for bringing a cake here. But the fee is reasonable and they offer great service! Recommend for group meals!
The only shortcoming is - we don’t like the Japanese table setting: it’s not good for elder people since we can’t stretch our legs like a normal seats. But it shouldn’t be a problem for young people.

4.5/5 – Listed in order of my personal preference:
🍣 Sake Sashimi – The salmon is incredibly fresh with a smooth, almost jelly-like texture. Loved it.
🥗 Sakana Iroiro Salad – A nice Asian-fusion poke-style dish. The greens are especially flavorful, thanks to the creamy dressing.
🍚 Buta Meshi – Rich and tasty overall, though nothing particularly special. I’ve had Unagi before and found that more to my liking.
🍣 Hamachi Carpaccio – It’s definitely fresh and worth trying, though the flavor just didn’t click with me. Others might enjoy it more.
🍖 Gyutan Shioyaki – Very tough and hard to chew. Honestly not sure how people manage to eat it.
I’ve seen many recommendations to its pizza. Would probably try next time!

I recently visited this burger spot and had an amazing experience! I tried the Naughty Chicken Sandwich, and let me tell you—it was absolutely delicious! The spicy kick from the jalapeños paired perfectly with the crispy, perfectly-breaded chicken. Everything about it was spot on. For $15, including a side, the sandwich was HUGE—definitely too much for me to finish, which is saying a lot!

I opted for coleslaw as my side, while my husband had the seasoned fries. Both were fantastic, though I was bummed they were out of mac and cheese. The fact that the restaurant is halal is a huge plus for me, and the staff was really friendly, making the experience even better.

This place is definitely one I’ll recommend to others and would love to revisit! If you're in the area, don’t miss it!

Fried chicken is excellent! Super crispy batter and the meat just falls apart. I would recommend ordering just the chicken itself. The bun, veggies and cheese don't add much if you order the sandwich.

Location feels like it should just be a takeout spot, but I appreciate the seating.

Had the pleasure of experiencing the special valentines menu at Broma this year. This was my first time visiting this restaurant and I must say it was an amazing dine. The atmosphere was wonderful. We were seated comfortably, enjoying the ambiance next to the fireplace. The service and friendliness of the staff made me feel welcomed and special. The tasting menu was five stars. Each dish left my mouth more excited for the next. Elegant dining at its best. Thank you, Broma, for such a wonderful experience. I can't wait to come back.

Lovely place. A bit noisy. Food was interesting (antelope dumplings) and nicely presented. The mushroom pie was very good and so was the basque cheesecake with Meyer lemon compote. Would definitely come again.

Food is ok. Would have preferred the fish taco fried. Love the guac but the chips are slightly too hard for my liking

Service is good though!

This is absolutely the best veggie burrito place ever!  We are so grateful it's close to us in Mountain View!

People are super friendly, and the music always gets us to move!

Last night, my family and I went to Ramen Izakaya Yu-Gen in downtown Mountain View, and it was amazing! As soon as we walked in, I felt like we had stepped into a real Japanese ramen house. The atmosphere was warm and cozy, with wooden decor, lanterns, and Japanese art that made it feel super authentic.

For our appetizer, we had the Takoyaki, which are octopus dumpling balls. They were crispy on the outside, soft and gooey on the inside, and topped with a delicious sauce and bonito flakes that danced from the heat, so cool to watch!

For the main dish, I ordered the Tonkotsu DX Ramen, and it was hands-down one of the best bowls of ramen I’ve ever had! The broth was rich and creamy, full of deep flavors. The noodles were perfectly chewy, and all the toppings-chashu (braised pork), kakuni (slow-braised pork belly), bean sprouts, green onions, a soft-boiled egg, and dry seaweed made every bite incredible. I also got extra Kikurage mushrooms, which added a nice texture and earthy flavor.

The attention to detail in both the food and the decor really made the experience special. You can tell they put a lot of effort into making everything just right. I would definitely come back and recommend this place to anyone who loves real Japanese ramen!

Stopped by for lunch. The place looks nice and I like the decoration. It is like ramen shop in Japan. We ordered katsu curry, tan tan ramen, spicy tonkotsu ramen, veggi ramen and gyoza. I can say they highlight is tan tan ramen. The broth is very yummy. The tonkotsu broth is a bit on the light side. The noodle is cooked nicely. Gyoza is good and veggie soup is a bit back. The service is pretty good and the server is friendly.  I like the open kitchen concept. For me it is about 3.5 stars.
Very yummy Vietnamese food in the Bay Area! Banh mi, pho and BBQ pork dish were all amazing! The egg rolls were so yummy!
I got their iced coffee and it was SO good and STRONG. Went on a 7 mile hike came home and still had energy. Great place. I recommend the iced coffee. Delicious.

name: Shoreline Lake American Bistro
cuisine: Cafe, Food, Point Of Interest, Store, Establishment

reviews.comment:
A nice spot to have lunch or a drink and watch folks out on the small lake.
My wine country chicken and Brie toasted sandwich was quite good.
Prices seem reasonable given the location.

A cosy cafe with an awesome view and ambience! Just by the lake side.
The food wasn’t great though. We had a turkey club sandwich which was a little dry. Eggs Benedict was good. Chilli scramble wasn’t as tasty either.

4/1/2025

Clifford’s Chicken & Fish
699 Calderon Ave
Mountain View, CA 94041

I went there for a quick solo dinner on an early Tuesday evening.  It’s at the end of a small plaza a block north of ECR.  The parking lot was nearly full but turn over is fast.  There is some interior seating; a table and chair setup for about 14 people.  You order and pay at the counter from the menu board behind the counter.  I ordered the two piece dark meat, which came with a biscuit and fries.

My meal was brought to me shortly in a box with the biscuit in a bag.  The chicken had a crunchy breading and was very moist.  The fries were hot and crispy.  The biscuit was fall apart moist.  Every thing was tasty and a little salty.

A very good neighborhood chicken place with reasonable prices.  I went here when they first opened for the catfish, which had a “bottom of pond” taste and I wouldn’t recommend.  It’s repeatable for the chicken.

Very good fried chicken, a little too oily. The fries were delicious. Thea meals include a butter biscuit like a sweet bread.
2 meals each with 2 pieces, fries and biscuit, one juice and one beer —>37$

2/22/2025

Sizzling Lunch
1760 Miramonte Ave
Mountain View, CA 94040

I went there on a Saturday for lunch looking for Katsu Curry.  It's in the Blossom Valley mall next to the Safeway so lot's of parking.  It was a little less than half full and I was seated promptly.  You order by scanning the QR code on the table and launching the URL which opens the menu tab in the browser.  I tapped the Pork Katsu with Curry Sauce and placed my order.

The interior is contemporary bench and table seating with wood furniture.  It was very clean with staff frequently cleaning the tables and floor.

The curry sauce in a gravy boat came first.  My food was brought to my table in a searing hot cast iron plate on a wood tray.  The dish consisted of rice topped with corn and green onions, the breaded pork katsu, raw red onion and raw mushrooms on the sides.  Make sure you stir the rice and vegetables immediately or the bottom of your rice will burn.  I then poured the curry over my rice.  The katsu breading was crispy but the cutlet was uneven in thickness so the thin part was dry and chewy but the thick part was tender and moist.  The curry had good flavor and is not spicy.

I'll round up to 4 stars and forgive the uneven cutlet experience, I'd repeat.

Server is very friendly!  Order from tablet on table.
Kiddo impressed with the sizzling plate.  The cheese corn appetizer was yummy!
Beef cube taste better than the slice beef.

They had Dad eat free for Fathers day!

Got a carne asada bowl (just like a burrito but with no tortilla) and paid the $3.50 for extra meat.  Honestly, it was bland.
Maybe my expectations got too high after reading all the great reviews.
Good Mexican spot for food. Grabbed a late lunch. Decent staff, quick service. Food is good.

Best place to enjoy a good meal with family and friends. Service is amazing, food comes out fast and servers are very aware of your needs.

Diana and David are so friendly, they take great care of us and even remembers our orders. They are a great example of amazing customer service !

You get 2 hours for all you can eat and let me tell you . . It keeps going until you can’t eat anything anymore ! You leave full and satisfied for your k bbq needs.

A must try is their crazy sauce, you’ll be hooked! Stop by and try it, you won’t be disappointed.

This place stands out from the other Korean BBQ places I've been to. The atmosphere reminds me of a nightclub. Seating was spacious and comfortable. My preferred beer was out of stock, so they comped me some hot sake for the trouble. Staff went above and beyond to make sure we had everything we asked for. At the time of visit, they were swamped with guests and had us seated in less than 15min. Every cut of meat I tried was tender and of quality taste. I had just about all the beef and pork cuts I can order. Stop by if you're ready to eat mountains of great tasting food.

name: Happy Lamb Hot Pot | Mountain View

reviews.comment: This is a nice place at the end of Castro Street. The portions of meat and veggies are big, and the service is good. The Ribeye and Angus were especially tasty. The king oyster mushroom had a nice thick texture, which made it really good. The sauce bar was a little disappointing, with some sauces looking like they had been left out for too long, and it could use more variety. But overall, this is a solid place, and we will come back.

Went on 4pm before thanksgiving day.  Not busy and we were sat down right away.  Since this is our first time, the wait gave us a brief introduction and n how to order and the amount of food to order to avoid food waste.

Food was fresh.  The soup base was tasty.  This is not AYCE but the price was decent for each person.

Will visit again.

The food was good!
The titanic momos were amazing, the soya chap was excellent.
The chicken egg chowmein was also good, felt like home.
We didn’t enjoy the roti it was a little oily in my opinion. Everything else was good, the service was good and the place was cozy

One of the best momo I ever had! Enjoyed every bit of it. Must try their house special Titanic jhol chicken momo and their signature chicken chow mein. Staff was accommodating. The place has good vibes.

We came for dinner and were pretty disappointed.

My mom got the vegan bolognese and calling it bolognese was pretty generous. It was more like excess of pasta with a hint of tomato.

I got the the Korean wings which were pretty good along with the truffle fries.

Overall everything was very overpriced for what it was. The service was good with very friendly staff but the prices and food quality were a let down.

Quick Summary
Pretty solid brunch option, especially if you're a globalist with the free breakfast. Solid food, large portions, cool interior and patio seating options.

Food- 5 stars
It's a typical hotel restaurant which is slightly better than chain brunch spots. I very much enjoyed the free breakfast options here with their menu. Really can't go wrong with the standard options: eggs Benedict, omelettes, french toast, waffle. Tasted great and large portions

Service
I would say they are slightly understaffed here as we did have to flag our waiter down towards the middle/end of our meal. Otherwise, the service was pretty solid

Bottom Line
Good ambiance, good food and portions, and pretty good service. A good and reliable option if you're staying at the Hyatt Centric

Came here for dinner with my partner. It took a while to get seated but the wait was worth it! We had the fried shrimp basket with garlic fries and I believe one of the specials/combos with the house special sauce (mild). The house special sauce is just so delicious and especially paired with the lemons that they provide you. The seafood was fresh and seasoned beautifully. I loved the snap of the sausages. The fries and fried shrimp were seasoned well and were fried to crispy perfection. The cocktail sauce was perfect to counteract the oiliness of the fried food. I highly recommend the garlic fries as they are truly some of the best garlic fries I have ever had. Crispy, garlicky, buttery. They are divine. The service was impeccable and the food came out rather quickly. I highly recommend this place and I can't wait to come back!

The place is spacious.  Seating is very comfortable.  Staff is friendly and nice.

They have lunch specials during the week.  We ordered the friend oysters and soft-shell crabs.  Both fried dishes are very good.  Their french fries are better than sweet potato fries.

Garlic noodles are just so-so, not much flavor and the noodles were overcooked.

When it came to the seafood, we ordered the Signature Combo #2 with House Special sauce.  The sauce tastes good.  However the seafood wasn't cooked well.  Shrimps are not fresh and get mushy once shells were peeled.  The crab was overcooked.  Clams were the only items that were good.  It's very disappointing with the shrimps and crab.

name: 老高烧烤旧金山店GAO’s BBQ & Crab Milpitas

reviews.comment:
Everything is good quality and the vibes are right. They have good music playing and it’s a good place to enjoy a meal and beer. My favorite items are the Chinese cumin lamb and beef BBQ skewers, but any of the seafood dishes are really good too. The seafood tastes fresh at least and the sauces are great.

Shoutouts to Ken, our server. Now I know I can adjust the spicy level for the skewers.

Recommend it here!

4.6 stars
A variety of skewers with seafood boil to choose from. The flavor is authentic and I finally find the BBQ cold noodle in the bay!

My fav dishes are eggplant, cabbage and squid feet. Sometimes beef and chicken can be a bit harder to chew.

The environment is lively and waiter checks on you every once in a while. Recommend this place if you are finding the Chinese BBQ place

I believe this is the new location for Home Eat in the Great Mall’s food court!

Just like their other locations, you can order your box lunch or dinner, which you can also order from the menu for your order to be cooked on the spot for you!

The service is quick and easy, you can pay with cash or credit card. Just follow the instructions on the kiosk.

We ordered three dish but forgot to order some white rice. So when I try to make my second order just for rice, the lady just said she would give me two orders for free! What a nice surprise and service!

All three dishes are on the salty side of my liking, I will ask for less salt when I order the next time!

This store is like a Chinese authentic super version of panda. They have meal boxes but you can also order the Chinese way: shared plates. The price for shared plates are 30% lower than any Chinese restaurant out there, and the amount is astonishing. We spent $75 and get the food enough for 4 people to eat two meals. Highly recommend!

I tried the steam pot on a whim, and Xian did not disappoint! We got the set menu for 2-3 people which was so much food that it probably could have fed 4, but everything was fresh and delicious. It was a great combination of seafood, meat, and veggies with a great natural taste that wasn't too heavy. The chicken soup at the end of the meal was delicious as well!

Although it was our first time dining here, everything was very straightforward and staff was attentive to help cook our food and make sure everything ran smoothly.

I would definitely come back and recommend it to anyone looking for a high quality steam pot experience!

We've been frequenting Xian Steam Pot & Yakiniku lately and have consistently had wonderful experiences. The steamed dishes are not only healthy but also incredibly flavorful. I've enjoyed dining there both with large groups and in smaller settings. The prices are reasonable for the high-quality food.

Total Score: 6.22

Bathroom: N/A
Didn’t use bathroom

Customer Service: 3.75/5
Refilled our waters frequently and gave us a lighting show. Wish there were more napkins though.

Ambiance: 4/5
Korean restaurant vibes but cleaner and brighter

Food: 3.25/5
Pretty decent food! Kimchi pancake was good, so was bibimbap. Wished there was more meat in the bulgolgi bibimpap though. Highkey some of the rice cakes in the tteobboki were kinda hard and not chewy

Wow: 0/1
Normal korean restaurant.

Total Score = BR + CS + 2*AM + 5*FOOD + WOW

I always get the seafood pancake when I come here with my friend. The restaurant is nicely decorated, and the side dishes are tasty as well. The other dish that I liked was the pork belly bibimbap. There hasn't been a wait at all the last few times I've been, and the staff is attentive and nice.

Have dinner at this restaurant in order to explore more locations that serve Korean-style tofu soups. The results are satisfying and the added order of bulgogi is also great other than the price that is a bit high for the amount served. Overall, the service is great and the ambience is also nice and quiet. However, the price may be a turn-off for those who are price conscious.

Nice Korean cuisine.
The service is extremely well.
The regular dishes like tofu soup, bibimbap, seafood pancake are good.
But their most famous dishes is Korean BBQ.
The beef is really tender. I would recommend  marinated beef, that is something restaurant does better.

I would come here more often in the future.

Support small local businesses! Pho Love was amazing. The staff were friendly, the food was incredible, the service was fast, and the place was clean. I've found my new favorite pho restaurant to eat at and bring all my folks to. Also they have happy hour with discounted pricing on the menu. I can't recommend this place enough! Thank you Pho Love!

Food is amazing! I've been coming here at least once a week for the past three months.  The restaurant is clean, music is calm, and the staff is kind. Everything on the menu is great but I recommend the rib pho & pork sandwich.

Just visited this Yunnan restaurant in the Bay Area and was immediately impressed by the beautiful ambiance—it truly felt like I was back in China for a moment. The atmosphere is relaxing, and the staff are young and friendly. I heard they recently brought in a new head chef and updated the menu. Every dish that came out looked absolutely mouthwatering and full of creativity. I was genuinely amazed by the presentation and flavors. Can’t wait to come back again!

Hands down the best Yunnan-style food I’ve ever had. We tried a variety of dishes, and everything was absolutely delicious. My favorites were Yuma’s Street Home Fries, the Stir-Fried Assorted Wild Mushrooms, and the Rose Pu’erh Latte—each one packed with unique flavors.

Great mexican place to dine in Milpitas. They have old school decor which feels warm and welcoming. Service is great.

The portion sizes are huge, I always have to carry my left overs.

I got regular burrito which was pretty huge.

Highly recommend this place to dining in.

Vegetarian Taco: Expected a flavorful vegetarian taco, but it turned out to be quite average. We had specifically requested fajita veggies instead of meat, yet there were barely any vegetables inside—mostly just lettuce on the side. The lack of well-seasoned veggies made it underwhelming.

Chips & Salsa: The complimentary chips and salsa were a nice touch. The chips were crisp, not too oily, and had just the right amount of salt—better than what many other places serve.

Ambience: A decent setup with a comfortable dining space, nothing particularly special but good for a casual meal.

Service: The service was good, with staff being attentive and friendly throughout the visit.

Overall, the experience didn’t quite live up to the positive reviews, mainly due to the lackluster vegetarian taco.

name: Casa Azteca Restaurant
cuisine: Bar, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment:
I was here maybe more than a decade ago and I’m so glad that I visited again today!

We were greeted by the manager I believe with a big smile and seated us right away.

The waiter took our drink order and delivered within 5 minutes.

Then we played our order and also quickly brought to our table. The portion and the taste was amazing, I specifically love their carnitas, so sold and flavorful!

I will surely come back for more. They also have good size of space can accommodate large party and special events!

Thanks to our friends, we visited this amazing restaurant. My son was amazed with the name and kept thinking about the colonial era. He enjoyed the wall paintings. I would say, we all did as well. Beautiful!!!!

Let’s get to food. I ordered shrimp fajitas which was delicious and generous portion. The refried beans and tortillas were okay. For the first time, my daughter ordered Mexican pizza. Not sure, if she’ll ever order again. And to my surprise they had chicken wings on the menu. It’s a Mexican restaurant. My son ended up getting chicken wings but it had no Mexican flavors. My husband ordered pork fajitas however he found it dry.

Customer service was great. Yesterday was National Margarita Day. We did celebrate by ordering house Margarita’s which delicious. Totally recommending the margarita. And try the guacamole dip. You will love the crunchy chips.

Overall, awesome experience.

name: Kathmandu Cuisine
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: They offer plenty of vegetarian options. The chilli baby corn was just okay, but everything else tasted really good. If you love spicy food, be sure to ask them to make it extra spicy. It’s a great spot to hang out and enjoy some good food.

Every table packed on a Wednesday night, but the staff handled it like pros. They even offered me a chai tea while I waited for my takeout, bless their hearts. Got jhol buff momo (water buffalo dumplings) and enjoyed immensely—and I eat a lot of dumplings. Super juicy and fragrant with amazing jhol (sesame tomato sauce). Super cozy interior with a cute water buffalo plushie at the counter. Will be going back!!

It was our first time visiting Hansang Tofu restaurant. We ordered the Grilled Sea-Salted Mackerel and the Combination Tofu Soup. The mackerel was cooked perfectly. It’s crispy on the top and moist and soft on the bottom. The tofu was delicious. Service was attentive. The waitress asked if we’d like refills on the banchan, before we had a chance to ask for refills. Overall, we had a wonderful experience at Hansang Tofu and we will definitely return again.
