The bibimbap is delicious. It is at a perfect temperature to get the crispy burnt rice pieces. The other good thing here is the banchan; there's a good variety. However, we had to ask each time for the refills. They don't take initiative to keep it going. There are other places that don't offer a lot of service either but are efficient with replacing the banchan, which is more reminiscent of the places in Korea. They took forever in getting us the check too.

As for the other dishes, we felt the portion for the tofu soup was a bit small. The seafood pancake was crispy but didn't have much flavor or ingredients.
Love love looove Mikonos! Been taking my sons here for over a decade, never disappoints. We always get a souvlaki plates, always cooked to perfection. Their salad dressing is a must.
We had the best time at Mykonos Grill. The food was amazing as well as the service. We had the best time eating outside and they even set up the umbrella for us. 10/10 experience

Delicious Malaysian cuisine.  Have been dining here over the last couple of decades.  This place is usually crowded during lunch and dinner times.  Even so, we were seated within a short time.  Staff was attentive, and order turn around was fast.  Enjoyed the eggplant with shrimp paste, pineapple rice, chili pepper prawns.

Went for an early dinner with a couple of other people. Seated promptly.

This Malaysian restaurant had a very large selection of dishes, the roti pratha had a great curry gravy with decent heat. We also had the beef rendang,  penang lamb, and the curry laksa. They waiter who was very friendly and good. The main dished seem tamed it down a bit, wish we would have asked for it to be spicier. Very tasty though.

Overall, a great experience and highly recommend.

This all you can eat hotpot was good! You have 90 minutes and it includes a variety of meat, appetizer choices and a cold/salad bar that includes vegetables, mushrooms, seafood, noodles, and sauce options. What is not included in the AYCE price are drinks. We had good service and meat selection. The broth was good too. It was clean and efficient. It is recommended if you like hotpot, but I'm not a big fan of hotpot. It was good overall.

Wonderful location to eat Japanese hot pot. The variety of the beef available for the hot pot is good, the delivery of the meat upon a new order is quick and the staff are helpful and friendly. I also like the variety of side items available on the buffet counter to go along with the meat in the hot pot. I was very happy that we are able to eat continuously for the whole 90 mins available to each customer per visit. It is definitely a to-go place for those who like hot pots with meat, seafood and vegetables etc.

Impressed with the carefully and mindfully crafted menu. Great sake selection to pair with the food. Service was excellent. Every course was explained to us well. Ambience was great with non-intrusive music in the background

We were there to celebrate mom's 81st birthday. They played a nice version of "Happy Birthday" on their audio system for her! Totally unexpected

The service was very very good.  Food was good as expected.  We liked the uni/salmon roe nigiri, the special chawamushi, and grilled misi sea bass.  We celebrated a family member birthday there; enjoyed much.

In town on a work trip and decided to try this place out. We were so happy with the food that we went back a second night! Both nights the service was great and the food even better! Highly recommend!

Great service! It's hard to find restaurants with great service nowadays. We are vegetarian and this place had plenty of options from pasta, pizzas, calzone, soup and salad. Pretty family friendly.

Definitely give them a chance.

Been to quite a few korean fried chicken stores and this one was pretty solid overall.
Had three flavors and the soy garlic was the best sauce but the spicy original was pretty good with nice heat.
Pricing wise they aren't that off the norm so worth a try if your near by them.

I've never been to this place before. I had no idea of what I missed  because this restaurant is amazing. They have plenty of tables and seats inside with appealing decoration. No complaint about the service - the staff helping us at the counter was very friendly and helpful. I ordered soy garlic bone-in chicken which had a very good flavor and I like its crispiness and chicken was moist as well. The fries were perfect with super nice crunch. Pretty good first time impression. I'll definitely go back for this and try new flavors.

I visited the place twice while we were traveling in the States.  Whatever I ordered, the food amazed me so much.  The blended juice was awesome, too, even my 2 yo daughter liked it very much, and she could drink 2/3 of the juice all by herself.
I would definitely visit the restaurant again and again in the future.

Needed a quick bite before a concert and found this gem! Holy moly! I was blown away!

The food was amazing! Larger portions! Did I mention full bar?

The staff were super friendly and helpful!

Everything tasted fresh and came out hot. There was not a single plate that was not wiped clean.

Highly recommend!

Always busy and crowded. We (2 people) came here at 12:45pm and waited for about half an hour to be seated.
Ordered a lot of traditional dim sum that we will usually order at similar restaurants. The food is good but not that impressive. Some of the dishes are a bit too sweet for me.
The service is really efficient. And the portion size is big. For 2 people, 4 dishes are definitely enough.

Overall it is worth a visit.

Attended a banquet dinner last weekend. The food is delicious and very authentic Cantonese style. Always love their dishes and quality of food. The service team was great, frequently changing dishes throughout the night. Great restaurant for celebration and their dim sum is also very good. Highly recommend giving this restaurant a try if you are looking for good Cantonese style dishes.

I had an incredible dining experience at this Thai food restaurant! The flavors were authentic and vibrant, with each dish bursting with fresh ingredients and spices. The atmosphere was cozy, and the service was friendly and attentive. If you're a fan of Thai cuisine, this place is a must-visit for its delicious food and great ambiance!

During my recent visit to Thaibodia Bistro, I had the pleasure of trying their chicken satay, prawns crispy wrap, and pad see ew.

The chicken satay was grilled to perfection, with tender, juicy pieces complemented by a rich, flavorful peanut sauce. The accompanying cucumber relish added a refreshing contrast, enhancing the overall taste. Other 2 dishes were delicious.

The portion sizes were generous, offering great value for the price. The service was prompt and attentive, contributing to an overall pleasant dining experience.

Tong Sui has always been my goto spot when it comes to puddings. Their ube, black sesame, and signature flavors are absolutely next level.rich, creamy, n perfect. The prices are on the higher side, so I couldn’t try everything I wanted, but I did sample a few, and they were totally worth it. The coconut base is silky and smooth with subtle layers of flavor that really come through. If ur into unique flavorful desserts this place won’t disappoint

This cozy little spot in Canaveras Plaza shopping center is awesome for dessert and drink lovers! Although it’s a small space with just a couple of seats, the location is super convenient and easy to find, with plenty of parking available in the huge lot.

The staff is wonderful—always busy crafting adorable and delicious drinks, yet they’re smiling and friendly, making the experience even better. They also have a restroom, which is handy.

The menu offers great options, including low-sugar and low-calorie desserts and drinks, making it perfect for anyone with dietary preferences. I personally loved their taro drink and black sesame pudding and the taro ube sago I tried at another location was equally fantastic.

Their refreshing drinks are a perfect pick-me-up, and the plaza itself is great, with lots of restaurants, shops, a grocery store, and even a Goodwill nearby—perfect if you want to drop off donations before treating yourself to something sweet. Highly recommend this place for a mood-lifting treat!

The food wasn’t bad but wasn’t good also I’m have same issues to describe it. Because every restaurant and every chef have his own style but in this one particularly the food was in the dry side and that it’s was makes the difference.
They have a very extensive menu with so many Dishes that you can’t find in other Chinese restaurant.
Portion are very generous (to share) and price are reasonable.
We ordered: potstickers (pork) they are big and 6 in the portion, chicken mu shu very generous  for an appetizer ( you need to ask for extra sauce) ,beef chow main a lot of noodles almost no veggies and small portion of beef and honey-walnut prawns good but almost no sauce. We appreciate very much the mango pudding that was on the house, I think was the manager arrived to ours table with the dessert and was an unexpected surprise, very nice touch. THANK YOU VERY MUCH.
The service was very good and attentive just a bite difficult to understand for the accent and mask.
The ambience looks elegant in comparison to others Chinese restaurants but using inexpensive decors , lighting, table cloth ( I think are disposable) , chairs are confortable also it’s a big restaurant they have a lot of seating.
If you like to give a change remember, most of the dish’s are for share unless you have a big appetite or like to take home the leftover.
The lobster noodle, roasted duck, sauté Asian eggplant and beef Asian broccoli were wonderful!!!  Annnd the portions were huge!

Still one of my favorite diner, big portions and quality food.

The food ain't anything special, you can find similar menu at any diner across the bay, but for the price black bear gives the best quality and quantity. I'm a bigger guy and I appreciate their effort keeping the plates big, the salads are especially huge.

They have lots of lunch and dinner options as well, steak burgers etc. Highly recommend.

It was cracking for breakfast! Our waitress was the sweetest thing ever, even before 8AM. My coffee cup was always full, the yummy food came out fast, and they let us chill after we were finished eating for almost an hour talking. Very cool. Will be returning!

Summary： Simple ‘hole in the wall’ style Japanese restaurant with great price and quality

Food: solid.  Lunch special was only 11.99 for 2 6-pieces rolls.

Decor and service: Average but you get what you need.   Family cheap eats but not a place you want to bring your future in laws. ;).

For the price and quality, it is a solid 4.

Good value! This place is awesome. Portion size is really huge and the flavor is also sooo nice. We ordered black garlic ramen, sashimi bowl, and sushi rolls and thse are all good. Ramen has a rich garlic flavor. Sashimis are fresh and flavorful. I am willing to visit this place in the future!!

I've been coming here with my family for years.  This place is CASH ONLY.  Their salt and pepper calamari is so crunchy.  It's addicting.  We tried the salt and pork ribs are pretty good too.
Prices have definitely gone up.  I think the salt and pepper calamari was about $26 but the container is petty full.
The place itself is small.  You literally have enough space to just look at the menu and come back to pick up your order.  The lady seems mean but she doesn't play.

Ordered in-person and got Combination Fried Rice, Salt and Pepper Fish Fillet, and Mongolian Beef. Their meats are very flavorful, but the Salt and Pepper Fish Fillet had no seasoning, so I would not recommend the dish.

Overall, I would order the meat dishes here, but not the fish.

Wonderful things can be had here.  Chili Garden is wonderful (honey walnut prawns are the best).  Ranch 99 Market is wonderful.  Darda Seafood is very good as is the dim sum place, The Mayflower.   Parking lot is free and there's usually parking available.    Getting there on 237 can be a challenge during "rush" hours.
Many Asian restaurants, stores, a good-sized market, and other services. Very busy Mayflower restaurant serves a good selection of dim sum and delicious dishes for dinner.

name: Romano's Macaroni Grill
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
As soon as I walked in I was greeted, which makes a world of a difference to me. I was sat at my table and greeted again by my waitress. Lauren was very kind, great smile and outstanding customer service. The food choices that she recommended definitely shows she knows her stuff. The food came to the table hot and delicious, my drink was extremely tasty. The atmosphere is still very family oriented which I love. It’s over 5 years since I dine at a Macaroni Grill, only because it’s the place that my sister, nephew and I would eat together. I couldn’t bring myself to eat here after she passed from cancer. Today I couldn’t resist and I wrote this review tears came rolling down my face. Thank you Lauren and Macaroni Grill for the amazing customer service & great memories.

My only concern would be that  I wasn’t offer the soup or salad that should have come with the entrée.
Great place for nearly home cooked tasty Italian dishes and a fine spread of beverages and desserts. Excellent courteous service by the staff. My folks love to come here often.
Good food and reasonable prices is a great summary of The Kerala foods. The portions are good as well. it gave me enough food for two meals.

Editing the review, now that they addressed my concerns about food quality .

Service : 5 for their attitude and service , changed from 1

Food: 1 still not happy with parotta. Shrimp roast was fine . Averaging it out

Atmosphere: 5 ( you can not dine there , should be NA)

Old review

Tried porotta pollichathu
Had to go to local saw mill to cut the poratta, not fluffy and fresh I would say l.when you go to a Kerala restaurant and order porotta, you expect to me fluffy and soft . Such a disappointment

Went there for first time , no seating arrangement got in dine

You have to order online even if you are there at restaurant

I visited this lovely restaurant with a really cozy and welcoming ambiance. The staff were amiable and made me feel right at home. For lunch, I decided to try their Japanese-style chicken wings and mixed tempura. The mixed tempura was absolutely delicious, with a perfect light and crispy texture, but I was a bit disappointed with the chicken wings as they didn't quite meet my expectations.

Interestingly, my friends ordered different dishes, and we had a great time sharing and tasting each other's meals. Our opinions about the food varied - some loved their choices, while others felt they were just okay. Overall, in my opinion, I would give the restaurant a 4 out of 5, primarily because of the delightful mixed tempura that left a lasting impression on my taste buds.

My boyfriend and I come here for lunch sometimes. He enjoys getting the unadon.
Celeste has rang us up the past few times, she’s super friendly and chill.

A very good happy hour from 3 to 9. Started with chips and guacamole and the guacamole was delicious. Got the happy hour margarita, really good. Ordered the beef Birria tacos as well and those were also really good. Service wasn’t the best, drinks took way too long to get, only had one bartender and this place looks to get packed out enough they should have 2. Otherwise the atmosphere was nice and restaurant was clean.

I placed a takeout order for chicken fajitas because they looked so good on the online menu. Unfortunately, when I received my order, it looked nothing like the picture. I’m uploading both the photo from their website and what I actually received — I’ll let the pictures speak for themselves. I don’t expect the food to look exactly like the pictures in the menu but I’m pretty sure I got less than 1/4 of the portion they advertised. The food tasted good, but I only got three super thin slices of chicken in my plate, looked nothing like what was shown online. I had ordered two plates, and while the second plate had four slices instead of three, it was still disappointing.

I went with my Chinese friend, and it was absolutely incredible. The food was so good it blew my mind. We spent around $45, which included 1 pound of food (priced at $15 per pound) and two drinks. I loved being able to customize everything and pick all the ingredients I wanted—it made the experience even better.

I asked the staff about the spice levels, and they warned me that the extra spicy was really intense. As a Korean, I opted for the regular spicy this time, and honestly, it wasn’t very spicy at all—probably mild by Korean standards. Next time, I’m definitely trying the extra spicy!

The ingredients were super fresh, and there was plenty of parking, which was really convenient. The place seems pretty popular. We didn’t have to wait, but I can see there being a line during busy lunch hours.

Also, there’s a fantastic boba spot nearby! Grabbing a drink there after your meal is the perfect finishing touch. I’ll absolutely be going back—it was just that good!

Came here about maybe two weeks ago? Although the line for it was quite long, I do think it was worth the wait. I got the tomato broth and it was so savory and delicious. I actually prefer this tomato broth over the tomato broth in one of the other malatang places nearby. I also think their signature broth is quite delicious. Good selection of noodles, meats, and toppings. I really enjoyed dining here and despite the hectic dinner rush, the staff was pretty organized. I will come back again and recommend this place!

I was invited by my uncle and his wife to this restaurant for my grandmother's 83rd birthday. This restaurant is quite fancy for a place that serves ordinary Filipino food. I love how most items from the menu are displayed to see how they look like though they won't exactly replicate them being served to us, which is why I decided to take pictures of them.

The food is good though, but some food needs to be a bit warmed up like the pancit. Some tastes alright but they don't really stand out. Most of them taste like home since I grew up in a Filipino household. The portions of the entrees are appropriate for hosting a party. Desserts are amazing though!

I recommend going to this restaurant for friends and family if you're willing to try Filipino food in the Bay Area.
Our clinic staff is not Filipino at all, but we go there to eat very often. We are located in the same plaza. So,  after great dinner, we always get purple ice cream. So beautiful and so yummy!

Lunch time buffet is $20. There’s a ton of variety—Chinese food, dim sum, fried food section, sushi, desserts, etc. For the price and the quick service, it is pretty worth it in my opinion. There are also plenty of seats and customers coming in and out. They keep refilling the food section as well.
The food was amazing tables and other stuff r really clean I loved the service the boy who was serving was very nice I recommend it

name: Sevens Bar & Grill
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Super friendly server. Relaxed vibe. Mediocre food, especially for the price. However, if you're staying in the hotel and want classic American food without having to walk far, this is your only option.

We visited this place to watch the finals between golden state and Boston Celtics! The place wasn't busy when we reached but quickly got filled up. They had just two servers that day but they got very busy in the end.
We loved the food and the drinks here.
The chicken flatbread is a must try. They even customized it for my vegetarian friend. The chicken wings are SUPERB! Do try them.

All the hot food with burner under or sizzling plates are highly recommended.  Otherwise the other including bibimbap can skip.  Mine came without the egg too, not sure if it's because the egg price lately.  Ha.

The soup was overwhelmingly salty, making it hard to enjoy. On the other hand, the kalbi jjim was way too sweet, overpowering the rich, savory flavors I was expecting. The balance just wasn’t there. Disappointed, as I was hoping for a more well-rounded meal.

Use to love this place, not sure what's going on with this place and their burritos; new management or new cook ?.  The past two times I've ordered a carne asada burritos no beans I get a mostly rice burritos.  They use to put a lot of meat in their burritos  not anymore so I won't order burritos here anymore.

This taqueria came recommended by a friend, and did not disappoint!

I ordered two Birria tacos along with beans and rice a coke. They additionally have all you can eat chips with a salsa bar.

The Quesabirria tacos were cheesy and crisp and the au jus was not too salty, but added great flavor to the crispy tacos! The meat was tender and flavorful. The Birria tacos come with meat, cheese, onions, and cilantro.

I added onions, cilantro, and salsa to the rice, and ate the chips with the beans and the rice.

The various salsas are tasty and not too spicy.

All in all a good experience, I will definitely be coming back to try some of their other menu items.

Royal Thaali really lives up to its name. The thali was a perfect mix of flavors — from the spicy curries to the sweet desserts, everything was spot on. The service was warm and welcoming, and the ambience had a lovely traditional feel. Definitely coming back!

Went in before the rush soon after they open and found a table. Ordered weekend special unlimited thaali. They started serving after 10 minutes. Rotating servers bring different items. Kachori wasn’t fried properly. Gatta sabji was more like gatta kadi. There was also a plain kadi. Jalebi was cold. All curries were mild and taste was mediocre. Daal was tasty but baati was hard inside. Overall not worth the price and not anywhere close to authentic taste.

This place is very good overall.  They specialize in Steamed Vermicelli Roll Cantonese style.  But their menu is quite extensive.  I think their congee is better than most Chinese places I have been to because it came out burning hot which I like.  The place was busy so we were placed on waiting list for about 20 minutes.  You scan the QR code on your table to place your order.  I have 3 stars for the atmosphere because the place is small and not a fancy place.  You would come here for Southern Chinese food and not the ambience.  Price is reasonable.

This place is a cantonese classic restaurant that has some good rice noodle dishes. It also has some solid porridge and chinese doughnut

For two grown men we got 2 rice noodle dishes, one chinese doughnut, one porridge, one drink, and it came up to around $40 after tax and tip not too bad.

Overall restaurant is ur typical tight cantonese restaurant.

They take card and parking lot has small spots but still plenty

It was Valentine's, I wanted to take my wife to a nice French restaurant but one of the reservation failed through, luckily I remembered this place that I took my girlfriend (my wife) 22 years ago. We both remembered this place, we didn't know it's still there after all these years since we never came back after we got married and moved.
The Google booking system is amazing, we got our confirmation right away. My wife was happy to come back to our first date years ago.
The restaurant is small, plenty of parking spaces, we came early because we went straight after work, we found the parking right away.
This is called French VN fusion restaurant, it's kinda like our favorite Le Colonial in SF but closed after 26 years in business.
We've been in Paris and tried quite a few restaurant there, we like escargots, steaks and ducks, but we still think the fusion restaurants taste as good or better.
The service here is so attentive, pleasant and happy, we liked it right away after all these years. The decor is quite nice IMHO, quite simple and not very pretentious.
So, French restaurant the escargots are a must, this place doesn't use the whole snails instead using the out-of-shell meats, with a little bread in a cup, kinda different. The important thing is the tastes, the meat is quite soft and flavorful, we both liked them very much. The bread dipped in the sauce is quite tasty.
Everywhere we went, we love crispy calamari, and this place is excellent, the calamari is crispy but the meat is tender, the sauce are just plain tartar and cocktail sauce, they should make their own special sauce for this then it would be better. We finished these in a heartbeat.
The salad is included which is nice. The dressing is just right, I think it has a touch of fish sauce in it, very nice.
The main course, the #15 and #16 that we can hear people are ordering. we order both because we forgot what we ordered 22 years ago LOL. Actually both sauces are almost tasted the same, but my wife thought her pepper corn sauce tasted better than my Mushroom sauce. My wife likes the hot crunchy bread and butter instead of my red rice. They're both excellent eating with our sauces.
The steak is tender and does have texture, it's the sauce that counts.
The prices here are quite reasonable. We will come back here again to try different dishes when we're craving for another romantic outing event. It's not just the restaurant, it's how we love each other. When we're in love, everything is romantic and taste great LOL.

It has been a while since I last visited here. Seems the ownership changed again. So different than the original restruant. Food was just OK, I had the grilled pork chop vermicelli bowl, my cohort had a grilled pork chop with egg and rice. They were both OK, nothing special. The original owners had special menu items especially the beef onion rolls, not on the new menu.

name: Koong's
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: The service here was quick and friendly and the portions were great for family style. We ordered the green beans, wings, beef chow fun, sizzling rice soup. The beef chow fun and green beans could have been a bit more seasoned, but they were still delicious. Overall great experience!

After seeing the good reviews, I decided to grab some takeout from this place. I got the green beans, but I messed up and ordered them fried somehow. I also got the hot and sour soup + egg roll + fried rice add-on, and the fried chicken wings. The green beans were very well prepared and tasted okay, but they just weren't what I had in mind. I'm gonna go back and get them without the breading next time. They were VERY plentiful, though. The egg roll was much better than your typical one. The soup tasted like most other hot and sour soups, so it also wasn't my favorite. I'll try the won ton next time. The fried rice was much better than average. Finally, the chicken wings were some of the best I have had in a long time. Perfectly cooked, tasty, crunchy. I'd go there just for those any day. Finally, the venue was clean and the gentleman at the counter was very nice. I will be back.

name: Tequila Shots Bar and Grill
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Silver Dragon and Ma in the kitchen are the best. The bar tenders are very nice and good vibes. Especially Candy, I was real tired from work. Wanted to get the burrito and a beer. Burrito (barbacoa)so good. She noticed I was tired and she talked to me. Not trying to get tips. But a real conversation and genuinely was interesred in my day. That is rare in bars. I will always come here as long as she's there. Nobody talks to me. It was a real energizer. God bless you Candy. Patrons are welcoming and joyful. Folks that come here are great. Thanks for the dope environment.
Best prices in bay as far as food drinks are good atmosphere is great I come here also for the added Marriott points highly recommend and also super chill spot

⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
This Place Has A Total Nostalgic Vibe! 🏁🍒
Customer Service was Amazing !!!
When you stop by, ask for Irma to help you!
I ordered the Breakfast Burrito, and it did not disappoint Egg, ham, bacon, onion, tomato, and cheese with the house potatoes. 🔥🔥

Great cozy spot to have some time with friends or by yourself. Service was great and your coffee cup is never empty! Coffee could be a little better. Maybe a better quality perhaps but still good. Food was made to order..will come back with family and try the corn beef hash and pancakes or waffles! The owner did not say hello to me but said hello to the regulars/ other customers. I thought that was a bit odd but I was on my phone texting so maybe that was the reason. Maria was my server and she was phenomenal. Her service made my morning!

Today is New Year's Day, and there is a huge crowd of diners. After waiting for a long time, we finally got seated.  The Cantonese dim sum here is delicious and worth the wait, and the food is served very quickly. Although the price of each plate of dim sum is about one dollar higher than other similar restaurants, the chefs make it delicious and it is worth every penny.  This restaurant is very spacious and suitable for wedding banquets and similar banquets.

Today. Very disappointed meals. 1)Cold soup. 2) Great Pork Belly. 3) fish dish came with fish head and body bones.  4)egg tofu without egg tofu. 5)chicken up to the standard level. 6) lamb stew not soft enough, maybe because of not warm enough. 7) no wok hei氣。 8)hot water strong clorox taste
If cannot handle this class of restaurant, narrow down the customer numbers.
End up pack home to eat. 4 people at this price with this presentation. If excuse for busy New Year Eve, then only worth 40-50% price value without service fee.  Or redo this whole set to offer us to experience again. Item #1,3,4,6,7 were all our disappointed dishes.

Yoshi Sushi is an okay spot for sushi in Milpitas, but it doesn’t quite hit the mark for a great experience. The quality of the sushi is decent, but nothing outstanding. The rolls are pretty standard, and if you’re looking for authentic flavors or fresh, high-quality fish, this may not be the best choice.

Not the worst, but not worth recommending. If you’re craving sushi, there are better options around Milpitas.

The sushi boats are gone, and you order by scanning the QR code, but Yoshi sushi is still a solid choice if you want a nice Japanese lunch or dinner if you're in the area. Lots of locals like it.

The dancing dragon, caterpillar, and dinosaur rolls we ordered are on the sweet side. Maybe it's the sauce.

The sushi tasted fine. The high volume of customers ensures their fish is sold consistently.

The dining room  is medium-sized and might fill up quickly. Prepare to wait during busy periods.

Service is friendly and efficient, and parking should be fairly easy.
I
Clientele is diverse, meaning a mix of old and young. That said, the atmosphere is casual and not too noisy. Which allows  for conversation.

I’ve been seeing this establishment in malls and other shopping centers. I see that the food looks good based on what I saw on the menu and so, I decided to try here.

I wanted to get the Grandma Braised Chicken Rice since it’s much affordable costing only around $11. It’s a lot of ground meat and hearty ingredients filled in a bowl. It’s a very small place, which isn’t really good to dine-in in my opinion.

I was quite shocked with how quick the service is. I was expecting it to be a little longer though since prepping a meal like this seems to take long.

Decent place for traditional Taiwanese street snacks that are difficult to find, such as oyster noodles and oyster omelette. The popcorn chicken was also good. Please note that this is a take-out only location, so plan to eat the food elsewhere. Large free parking lot.
Excellent service! Outstanding and welcoming environment. Friendly and professional staff. Food is delicious. Highly recommend it.

I was here for a private event hosted by Mac Mall for New Year's Eve so unfortunately I didn't get to experience it on a day-to-day to know what the food is like. However with that being said I had an amazing time the venue was beautiful everybody was professional there was no incidents and I look forward to visiting again during their regular hours so I can leave a review on the food. 🎊🎊🎊🎊🎊🎊🎊🎊🎊🎊🎊🎊🎊

Great decor and atmosphere. Jazz music is fun and relaxing. Very spacious with the tables well spaced. I like ordering by QR code but even so, the service was friendly and appropriately attentive.

The two of us ordered three dishes - snowflake dumplings, beef wrap, and pork belly noodle soup. The dumplings and wraps were both excellent. The noodles were tasty and chewy. We didn’t care much for the pork belly, so we’ll try something else next time.

Loved the vibe with what is not expected in an Asian dine. Quite refreshing. We had soup dumplings, salty string beans, onion cake, crab soup dumplings, combo rice,broccoli beef. All relatively decent quality. The dumplings good , but slight behind the Din Din dumplings . As always post wherever, you end up especially if new to the establishment.

name: Erik's DeliCafé
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Store, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Awesome place 😎 great customer service, cool vibe and good music 👍🏼 perfect for a chill Sunday 😊 newbies today but we will be regulars

The workers who are full time are so lovely. It's nice to see the same faces when I visit once or twice a week. I'm vegetarian and I highly recommend the autumn squash soup and sweet beet salad or the light and tasty combo with small salad and cup of soup. I also enjoy the veggie sandwiches. I used to always order ahead and do takeout but the environment and free drink made me switch to eating in.

Miles Bistro offers an unforgettable taste of the Philippines. The highlight of our meal, the Kare-Kare, was simply delicious. The vegetables were fresh, not overcooked, retaining their texture and flavor. The peanut sauce was rich, not too thick, allowing the freshness of the ingredients to shine.

We started with lumpiang Shanghai, perfectly crisp and filled with savory meat. The Crispy Pata followed, living up to its name with a crispy exterior and juicy interior.

The Sisig, served sizzling, added an extra layer of excitement. Its balance of textures and flavors was spot on, with just the right amount of zing.

The family atmosphere combined with attentive service made our visit truly special. Miles Bistro is highly recommended for anyone seeking authentic Filipino cuisine.

I had lunch here with my Ate (older sister). We had dinuguan and the arroz caldo. The dinuguan was served on a sizzling hot pan and reminded me of what the dish would be like if it was dinguan sisig (style). As it turns out this is the best way to eat dinuguan. The blood is not too soupy and the consistency is great, and the flavors just pop with the added heat and subtle peppers.

The arroz caldo was not the highlight of the meal but still very good. I'm not sure if adding fried chicken inside the soup adds much to the dish (I would have preferred it to the side). On a cold day, it was warm, comforting, and not too salty.

Service was perfect. Got two takehome boxes and the food microwaved well. Ang sarap!

Nice comfortable indoor vibes. Will return with my sister soon.

Got to try many items on the menu and everything was really good.
We ordered Wraps, sandwiches, BHEL Puri, vada pav, puranpoli, falooda, thali and so much more but we were not dissapointed with any of the items.
Sabudana khichdi could've been better though.

Would recommend this place for some good Indian veg food!!

The service was very fast and placing the order online was very user friendly.

We ordered dahi puri raj kachori n paneer frankie, dagi puri was good . Raj kachori was actually a stuffed puri which we eat for breakfast and was not so great. Paneer frankie is 0.5 /5 , frankie was so oily that you can squeeze directly from it, would not recommend frankie at all

name: Tayyibaat
cuisine: Food, Point Of Interest, Store, Establishment

reviews.comment: ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Tayibaat Restaurant and butcher shop is a gem! Ordered the Wagyu brisket platter, and it was absolutely bomb—juicy, flavorful, and cooked to perfection. The portion was generous, and the sides complemented it perfectly. Amazing service and vibe too. Highly recommend!

The food was very good, even though the place looks very unassuming. They have something for everyone - kebobs, steaks, burgers etc. I will be back to this place to try some of their other menu items.

It was cool. Would try them again. Not often due to the price of a single slice. Otherwise, no real problems. It was a fresh pepperoni slice. Good crust too. Decor was also nice. Never been to NY but it seemed organically decorated and connected to their roots.

I recently started coming here, and since my first time a month ago, I keep going back!! Originally came for slices, they have pizza ready and quickly warm it up. One time they only had cheese slice and added pepperoni since that's what we wanted.
Slices can be expensive, two slices and two pops costs $18. I finally grew a brain and got a large half cheese half pepperoni which has 8 large slices for $33, so l recommend doing that. One thing that also made me want to order a full pizza is that the slices aren't evenly cut. One time I got a slice and it was huge another time I got a slice and it was smaller than the first one. Ordering a whole pizza is the way to go!
It's a no frills kinda place, seating on the inside, parm & red pepper shakers for you to bring back to your table.
Some TVs and a Statue of Liberty to remind you of NY hehe.
Overall, I love love love this place!!! I love how thin the crust is, it makes it so easy to eat, I ate up my portion of the cheese half no issue. Just writing this review is making me crave it so bad. Highly recommend this for NY thin pizza! Not doughy and you won't be weighed down after eating it!

A go to lunch spot. Would highly recommend their mini tiffin which is simple, filling, fresh, and delicious. Love the Vada - crispy on the outside, flavourful and light on the inside.

The sambar has had a lot of variations in taste each time. It tastes great but some days the salt and spice levels are higher.

The curd rice was however disappointing with no flavor (barely any curry leaves or white urad dal), extra extra salt and served with an even saltier pickle. The rice was clumped and there were large chunks of plain rice.

Overall great place and love the options of some ready to go curries, idly and dosa batter which have also been great so far.

No-nonsense honest to goodness take-out Indian Indian restaurant serving breakfast items and all the items that get your tummy and heart full.

Located conveniently in a strip mall off the busy commute highway, you could pick up lunch on your way to work, and their curry boxes hone for dinner. A few tables are available if you want to swallow that goodness and can’t wait to get home.

Taste is as trusty and consistent as ever. The Tatte idli is awesome and fluffy. The dosas crispy and the curries bring back the flavors of madras to your mouth and memories to your mind.

Staff is prom and proper and courteous without being performative.
Authentic Taiwanese cuisine.  Got two huge pork chops in my bento box. Good for two meals for me.

Came here for the first time cause i was craving something different and was pleasantly surprised. Good amount of food for the price with a drink included. Love the variety and quality of the food that the box came with.

I've been going here with my family for years.  This trip I was the chauffeur.  So many great eats here from cooked food, desserts, and frozen items to cook at home.  This place is clean and always busy.   There are all sorts of goodies everywhere you look.        This trip we bought:

1.  Laing:  My mom's favorite and go to.

2.  Karioka:  One of my favorite items here.   First bite brings me back to memories of my lola making this at home.   It tastes exactly the same.  The crunch with each bite and perfect amount of sweetness.  The only difference is this is a lot bigger than what my lola made, but so worth the trip.

3.  Turon:  Perfect size with perfect ratio of banana and langka.  This had the same crunchy and sweetness on the outside as the karioka.  It tasted like the panutsa that they use not the typical brown sugar or sugar coating.

4.  Kakanin sampler:  This is delicious.  My least favorite was the sapin sapin.  It was a little hard and the consistency wasn't ma kunat.  A certain kind of chewy texture that I don't know how to explain.

5.  Frozen tocino:  It seems a little pricey but more than enough to feed a family of 4.  This made the perfect tocilog at home.   I forgot to take a pic after it was cooked, but the color was perfect.

6.  Frozen longanisa:  Sadly, this was a little too sweet for us.  I'm not sure if it was just an off batch but I think I'll stay away from that for now.

We kept adding to our order because we would see something else that looked good.  The gentleman helping us was like,"Anything else?"  Thank you to him for being so patient with us lol.  I highly recommend this place and can't wait to come back sooner than later.

Their lechon is really good! They also have yummy authentic desserts! I love to stop by here when I’m in the area! Also Riz the young handsome kid is fun to converse with! I love to see young people helping their family’s business!

Ordered some chicken shrimp fried rice rice tasted like they made the rice 30min- 1hr ago than slapped some chicken on top from a different sauce pan on top of the rice and than for the shrimp as well from a different sauce pan and thrown on top. I expected it all to be cooked together like when I go to a Thai restaurant. Easily this is the most expensive dog food I have given my dog in a while first and last visit. Ironically enough it is a popular location so I must assume that their soups are what are good cause it feels like a sub par and over priced Panda Express. Unfortunate that my first experience was so bad I can’t give them a second chance.

Really bad experience with the service!!!!!
The soup was very  Blane and tasteless the meatballl was very chewy tasted like plastic, the shrimp wasn’t even cooked all the way. The mango smoothie was tasteless and it just tasted like ice. The egg rolls tasted like it was made was yesterday. Was not even in there for 10mins left the food there and the smoothie’s as shown in the pictures.
I’m never coming back here
“DO NOT RECOMMEND IT I REAPT “
“DO NOT RECOMMEND”

name: The Best Sandwiches
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Absolutely great sandwich’s here we had the carnitas torta and hot pastrami sandwich’s. Also had a coconut mojito it too was amazing. We shared so I actually had half of each sandwich loved doing it this way. Can’t wait to come back and try two more I would highly recommend.

Updating my rating as the quality of delivered sandwiches has significantly declined. The egg, bread, and salad sandwiches delivered today were far below acceptable standards. I ordered a couple of sandwiches, and they were stale—completely disappointing. This is not just about poor quality; it’s a serious risk to customers’ health. Proper food safety measures need to be ensured to prevent such issues.

Love the veggie bagel, egg salad sandwich and Eggs Benedict. The veggie sandwich and egg plant with goat cheese are also good.
This bowl of noodle soup is not fresh. Their menu has not been updated and the chef has changed. The taste is completely different from a last year. It's so unpalatable.
This is a Hong Kong casual fast food style restaurant.  If you just want something quick and simple and inexpensive, then it is OK.

I’ve been coming here for the soup and sugar cane juice, both of which I really enjoy, but today I left feeling pretty disappointed and a little upset. I ordered a large sugar cane juice, and when it was brought to me, the cup was only about three-quarters full. I asked the waiter why it wasn’t filled to the top, especially since I paid for a large. She told me that to get a full cup, I’d need to pay an extra dollar.

I then asked, isn’t the point of a larger drink to have a full cup? Her response was that I had asked for no ice, so that’s why the cup was not filled. I didn’t want to argue further, but I left feeling frustrated. Honestly, I didn’t want to risk anything happening to my food if I pushed the issue. It’s a shame because I really do like the place, but this left a bad taste in my mouth.

Pho 90 Degree in Milpitas offers delicious and authentic Vietnamese cuisine, especially their flavorful pho with rich broth and fresh ingredients. The restaurant has a casual ambiance, friendly staff, and prompt service, making it a great spot for a comforting meal.

name: Water Tower Kitchen
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: came here for a work dinner and was pretty impressed with the vegan options they had! love the lettuce wraps and the drinks! got an espresso martini and butterfly drink thing and both were so yum! the ambiance is bar/dinner like but friendly staff and a good time!

A very nice place to hang out with friends and family.  The service was fast  and pleasant. The atmosphere is inviting and modern.
The food was pretty good,  nothing super special, but suits everyone.
The size of the portions is good.
There is a varied Manu of cocktails and drinks.
Great prices.
Definitely will come again

name: Orchard City Kitchen
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
1st time🥇

Food:
10/10 Winter citrus salad 🍊 : celebrating citrus season with orange and grapefruit over radicchio. Bursting with fresh herbs and nuts.

6/10 Lamb riblets : these needed to be served at a hotter temp. That aside, I ate more of the pineapple, cucumber, onions than the lamb (and I LOVE lamb but not this).

7/10 Dumplings 🥟 : solid but not a standout (I don’t even remember what they taste like)

9/10 Bacon 🥓 Butter 🧈 Biscuits : the bacon and the BUTTER were the best parts. Candied thick-cut bacon. Whipped honey butter. The biscuits weren’t dry but still 1-2 minutes over.

Service: Service was friendly. They came back around to check on us regularly.

Atmosphere: Farmhouse style decor matched the farm-to-table menu. Very lively with music and people inside. We sat outside on the patio near a tree and a railing lined with flowers, even the patio was intentional. Table-height propane heaters kept us warm on a chilly day.

Today, I had the delightful experience of dining at OCK for the first time, and it was nothing short of fantastic! Every dish we ordered was expertly prepared and beautifully presented, with flavors and aromas that were simply irresistible. It felt like a delicious indulgence! In fact, it was the first time we didn’t even ask for boxes for our leftovers because we enjoyed everything so much. While the portions seemed small at first, they turned out to be perfect for sharing with family and friends. We walked in with empty stomachs and left feeling wonderfully satisfied—truly an experience to remember! I can’t wait to return!

name: Locanda Sorrento
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Lovely Italian place. The food and staff worth visiting. Make sure to ask for the bread. We had Insalita Liza and meatballs. The meatballs is big portions the steak was delicious and juicy. Lemon cake was delicious and high recommended

That a beautiful place, so warm and inviting.  The holiday decorations were perfect.

I really wanted to try their pizza and I’m glad I did, it was delicious.  Cooked just right !!  It was definitely more than 1 person can eat, but great size.

They had a special Ravioli with Salmon, it was awesome.  The ravioli itself was fresh and the salmon was flavorful.

I also tried the tartufo desert - first of all the presentation was amazing and the taste was out of this world.  It was great to pair this with a cafe latte ….

The staff was friendly and very knowledgeable- I will be back !!

Excellent service. Food is delicious. The pizza dough has a nice chewiness. The truffle fries are perfectly fried with a hint of truffle.  We always get the Doppio Zero pizza. Love that there's arugula to go with the prosciutto.

If you're a fan of Italian cuisine, this place is a must-visit! The food here is exceptional, with a wide variety of pastas and pizzas that are sure to impress. The calamari and prawn starters were perfectly cooked and absolutely delicious, setting the tone for a fantastic meal.

The atmosphere is warm and inviting, making it an ideal spot for both casual outings and special occasions. Whether you're craving a classic Margherita pizza or a creamy pasta dish, their menu has something for everyone. Highly recommend giving this place a try, you won't be disappointed!

My family and I first visited this place 7-9 years ago and have enjoyed it ever since, and we have recently came back for valentine’s dinner. modern ambience and excellent service made for a great dining experience. The dinner presentation was superb. The medium steak was juicy, and the Brussels sprouts were perfectly cooked. The poke with glazed sauce was outstanding, and the handmade bread was delightful. Don’t forget to remind the hosts if it’s a guest’s birthday for a free dessert.

We shared a wonderful pre Christmas dinner with family and friends. The food was fantastic, our server was good until he was pulled away for a large party near the end of our meal. The wine choices were good and the desserts were special.
The music selection was a bit loud. It was pop music which made it hard to hear and didn't give the right atmosphere in my opinion.

We came here for my daughter’s birthday dinner. Had a reservation for 730 pm but was not seated until 815 pm. Food itself was so-so. I ordered the ossobucco. It was not tender, and the sauce tasted like it was from a can. My wife ordered the steak special and was impressed by it. Wine selection was okay. For the price, the food and service are underwhelming.

Had dinner on a Sat night. Walked in and was seated immediately. The restaurant has a Fall menu. I ordered the same pappardelle pasta with lobster but had tiramisu for dessert. My friend had the lasagna. Food is consistently good at this restaurant.
___________________________________________________
Came to this restaurant at downtown Campbell on a Friday night prior to 8:30pm. The restaurant has a nice modern setting. Ordered the flaky pastry appetizer which has shredded vegetables between it, sitting on a cream sauce. I had the pappardelle pasta with lobster and my friend had the penne pasta with sausage. The food servings at this restaurant is generous compared to most Italian restaurants. I really like that my pasta was served fresh from the kitchen, pipping hot. There was also a generous amount of lobster that I was able to get a bite of lobster with every bite of the pappardelle. It was a huge serving but I finished every bit of it cos’ it was that delicious. For dessert, I ordered the tartufo in dark chocolate. It tasted like regular dark chocolate gelato to me, but my friend claimed that it was very rich and creamy. Overall, it is a very tasty meal on the pricier side, although I think the taste and quality of the fresh ingredients justify the price. Definitely recommend this restaurant if you want good and high quality italian food.

name: Opa! Campbell
cuisine: Bar, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Loved the food.  We had the opa sangria, flaming cheese,  spanikopata, chicken sliders, the Lamb burger and half chicken entree.

It was so good we decided to get the banana bread for dessert 😋

For the flaming cheese, be ready for fire at the table and a nice and loud opa! I took a video too late, I was so excited 😊

The patio seating is quite nice and well shaded.
I was disappointed in the food, maybe just had a poor experience but the gyro fries were childish and the fries tasted like they had been sitting out for a while. The same with the meat on them a bit cold. The lemon orzo wasn’t my cup of tea either.

The cheesesteak gyro was good and I was surprised that the salad did not have any leaves in it FYI was tasty. Mostly onion, pepper and tomato. Overall the food was 3/5 but the old tasting fries and meat bring me to 2/5. Maybe better next time 🤷‍♂️

name: Aqui Campbell
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Every single bite was delicious. The flavors blended well the presentation was good. The atmosphere is beautiful to look at. And the food came quickly. And lots of choices

This place use to be awesome about 15 years ago!! The Chicken Enchiladas were way better, the chips were better, and the red salsa wasn't so watered down as if they just added water to make it so thin!! $5.19 for chips and salsa? Should have skipped it! Never again!!

And oh, forgot to mention the soda fountain didn't work for any drinks! It just put out syrup and no soda for all drinks except water!!

We finally were able to try this smaller spot in Campbell and overall it was a very nice experience!  They have a very creative bar with some fun concoctions and the manager Kendrick was helpful in chosing.  The staff was attentive and interior decor was cool.  What blew us away were the taco plates! We ordered the Birria and Chicken Tinga  and both were fantastic.  We will definitely return to try other things.

Went on a Wednesday around 5:30 pm. We were seated right away. The inside seating area is just one small room and many tables and the bar area were already taken. The outside patio has heaters and you can enjoy the downtown feels.
Service was great! Our waitress was efficient and kind. The manager (assuming here) never stopped moving the whole evening. He was here and there and everywhere. Always making sure that everyone had what they needed, whether it was the staff or the patrons.
I felt like the cocktails we got were just so-so; a little bland, but pretty. The al pastor street tacos were better once adding the lime included. The crispy fish tacos needed the lime also, in my opinion.
Even though I'm only giving it a 3-star review, I think it has potential. It wasn't a bad experience at all. Perhaps if we would have sat outside and had different dishes it could have been a 4.

My friend and I had a blast here! Everything went well from the service, ordering process, the ambience to the freshness of the food and fantastic drink and dessert!

This Pacific Catch location is conveniently located in the Pruneyard, next to Marshall and Trader Joe’s side of the plaza. Parking was reasonably available.

We went there on a Monday night at 7pm and the place was pleasantly not crowded at all. We loved that we were greeted warmly and then seated promptly at one of the most beautiful places in the restaurant - in the heated patio and next to the cool blue-light “fireplace”. But honestly everywhere in this restaurant is pretty! I love the vaulted ceiling with statement rattan lights hanging off it.

Our server Zach was attentive yet gave us some space and time. He also gave us some suggestions on which drinks to order, which we appreciated. We opted for the Trio Sampler, which had original ahi tuna poke, Serrano ahi poke and Baja shrimp poke, and the West Coast style salmon.

We dived into our food as soon as they came out. The dishes were aesthetically presented. All the ingredients tasted so fresh and healthy. We were surprised to find the brown quinoa rice (which came with the grilled salmon dish) were soft and flavorful. The salmon was delicious with the right amount of moisture and flavorings.

The Trio Sampler also held a candle to the grilled salmon dish. We couldn’t decide which poke we loved the best as we finished them all LOL

Zach was smart to present the dessert menu to us in the middle of our meal so we knew to pace ourselves. After not much of the debate, my friend and I picked the Hula Brownie Sundae, which was another highlight of the night. The brownie was moist and had that night balance of bitterness of chocolate and sweetness from the cake. We loved how coconut shreds and macadamia nuts complemented each other nicely and made the entire dessert an epic.

Overall, we were very satisfied with our meals and the experience. We’ll definitely come back soon!

Food was exceptional! Great place for lunch!

Parking could be a struggle, as it's Pruneyard, but it's worth it!

Food and drinks were delicious, it was flavorful and fresh!

Pretty nice food and good selection. I am surprised to the quality of their pasta in particular. The place is a bit small and if you have things like stroller it is a challenge. Parking is also a bit tight around. The staff is very attentive and helpful.

We went to this place seeing great reviews.  However, it didn't meet the expectations.  The place is small and you can easily bump into servers and other diners.
The food was mostly okay.   Lobster tail pasta was good - seemed freshly made.  The red pepper soup wasn't as good as I have had before.  Disappointed with Tiramisu as it was extremely sweet and mostly cream.

name: Wild Rose Eatery and Bar
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
100000/10!
Great customer service, all staff were very nice and always checked on our table and make sure we were okay throughout the night without us even having to get up and get their attention. Kayla G did a great job she was our main server but her team were super great as well!

The food matches the aesthetics! Not only is the inside so nice but the food is incredible! Very tasty and doesn’t make you feel like that heavy full. Even the desert was great !

The ambiance is beautiful! Loved the dim lights (we went around 7pm), the interior design and decor was so pleasing to look at. Such a vibe !

Now the music, that playlist was slappin! R&B vibes all night and it was loud enough where you can have a great time but still have a conversation.

We went on a Thursday night for my bff bday dinner, when we walked in they added a special touch to the table decor to acknowledge her bday! So thoughtful and very much appreciated.

I brought my toddler (2 y/o) and had no problems! I will say maybe the weekend is not toddler friendly and a different vibe after 8pm since it closes late.

Clean and good smelling bathroom !

They have different options, high tables, regular tables, booths and lounge seating.

As you can see, this place was a hit !

We visited Wild Rose Eatery and Bar to celebrate my wife’s birthday, and the experience exceeded our expectations with its delectable cuisine, delightful cocktails, and exceptional service.

We have had the below food from their wide selection of options.

Fresh Oysters: A delightful start to the meal, these oysters were fresh and flavorful.

Noodles Fry: While the noodles were tasty, the cheese was a bit overpowering for our preference.

Calamari Fry: Perfectly cooked and seasoned, the calamari was a crowd-pleaser.

Edamame : The bone marrow was well marinated and literally melted in our mouth. Highly recommend

Steak: The steak was cooked to perfection—tender and juicy.

Service: The staff at Wild Rose Eatery and Bar went above and beyond to ensure a memorable dining experience. Their attention to detail and friendly demeanor made our celebration truly special.

Overall Impression :  We highly recommend Wild Rose Eatery and Bar for its delicious food and outstanding service. It’s the perfect place to celebrate a special occasion or enjoy a casual meal with friends and family.

name: Rock Bottom Restaurant & Brewery
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
The good: The beer was yummy, and the selection was decent.  The server was friendly, though I think they were understaffed.

The bad: They weren't quick on getting food out, so it sat a bit and wasn't hot.  Examples being Tater Tot Fondue, where cheese had developed the skin and the tots were not hot. Also, the Fried Pickles were over fried, and then also not hot. So that sucked. It had a great sauce though.

The fine: The Chicken Sandwich and Club were both fine, they had decent flavor.

I'd probably go back for a beer and a snack, but I wouldn't seek it out.

This place has hit rock bottom for sure. The restroom was dirty and aging and graffiti on the mirror, paper towels on the floor.  The service was good from the bartender, but that was all. Apparently, this establishment had been bought a couple of times by different entities.  The burbon blue cheese burger was sad, starting with the buns were just like flat bread with no fluff and tasteless, along with the plain flavor fries that were not even hot, just warm. Just go elsewhere like In N out for food and it'll also cost less. Trust me.

We had a good visit.  The place was very busy and yet we were seated immediatly.  Once seated we realized the place was extremley busy and it was Cinco De Mayo.  We walked into a large band playing traditional music.
The music was slightly too loud, but we were close to the band.... And trumpets are quite loud. Overall, the music was enjoyable.
I had the steak fajitas and they were delicious.  They were hot, and fresh and plenty of it.
The service was good, but not spectacular as they were busy, but everyone was trying their hardest.
I was never served my second Coke, but was charged for it.  I had to ask for it to be removed from the bill.
Because of the service this would normally been only a 4-star review but a manager (?) stopped by our table and replaced our nasty diet cola in a can with a bottle of Coke made with real sugar.  They do not serve fountain drinks so and that was kind of weird.
Overall we enjoyed our vusit and will visit here again.

Impressed by the great vibe this place offers. The wait time was surprisingly short, only about 10 minutes on a busy Saturday afternoon. The food was also enjoyable. What really stood out, though, was the inclusion of mocktails on the menu—a refreshing option that’s often hard to find elsewhere. Overall, it was a pleasant dining experience.

The best! I’m a local and proud to say this is my go to hang out spot. The staff is fantastic and always provides outstanding service. They make you feel like you are family and are always happy to see you. Food and drinks are always great! Nice happy hour too.

Pretty nice place. Lovely vibe and ambience, has a lounge like feel with a nice bar area and some good cocktails which my colleagues really liked. Would definitely recommend a stop in here especially for a cozy drink.
They have a pretty good happy hour for drinks.
I was not otherwise impressed with the food, which was presented well, however the flatbread was salty and other items not memorable (had the warm nuts, deviled eggs and hummus).
I think the highlights were the attentive staff and the alcoholic drinks. I would stop by again for sure!

Absolutely an incredible experience with just amazing food. The cocktails are all delicious and we tried multiple of them. I would have to recommend the American Smoke if you're a fan of whiskey sours. The crudos were both amazing but I think the hamachi fish was better while the salmon's miso sauce was better. The ricotta gnocchi were unlike any gnocchi I've had before and were absolutely amazing. The scallops and brown butter hummus was perfectly executed and delicious. The braised short rib was so filling it was a perfect finale to the meal. But of course we had room for the cheesecake which again was just divine. All in all an amazing experience made even better by the fact that Chef Tucker takes some time to walk around the dining room and talk to the guests. Cannot say enough good things about the restaurant.

We had an incredible dining experience at Lira by Chef Tucker in Campbell! From start to finish, every detail was thoughtful and elevated — it’s so exciting to have a creative and refined spot like this added to the South Bay dining scene.

We started with the sunchoke appetizer, which was absolutely delicious and beautifully plated. The flavors were rich and layered, and the presentation was stunning. We also had the hamachi crudo appetizer, which had the perfect balance of chili oil heat and coconut essence — such a creative combination that really worked. Each plate is designed to be shared and experienced, which made the meal feel interactive and fun. The variety on the menu is impressive — there’s truly something for everyone.

A major highlight were the short ribs— melt-in-your-mouth tender and packed with flavor — and the Dubai cheesecake was the perfect way to end the meal. It was light, creamy, and had such a unique flavor profile. I also had a beautifully crafted mocktail (I wish I could remember the name!), but it was so well-balanced and refreshing.

The vibrancy of each plate was remarkable — edible flowers and bright, fresh ingredients made every dish feel like a work of art. The atmosphere is modern and lively, making it a perfect spot for a date night or a night out with friends.

To top it all off, Chef Tucker herself stopped by our table to say hello. She was so warm and down-to-earth — it’s clear that her passion and creativity are reflected in every dish.

We’re already looking forward to coming back once brunch starts in a few weeks — if dinner is any indication, brunch is going to be incredible! Lira is such a gem, and I can’t wait to explore more of the menu soon.

Wonderful breakfast buffet.  Young lady working the area was very nice and helpful while she kept the place super clean.  Mostly standard fare but the chicken and peppers were great! It was comped for us so not sure of the price.

Night supervisor Alex and the bartender resolved an issue that needed attention and helped me out. And  the bartender went above and beyond to make sure I didn't leave empty-handed. Concerned employees who actually care are what every hilton should look like.

Also, shout out to Joseph,  the day supervisor, for upgrading my room.

Thank you to all the staff for being so kind. It made this long a** road trip so much better. We hope to stay here again in the future.
.. except for the person that made the creme

name: Naschmarkt Restaurant - Campbell
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Ok... I love it when you have high expectations of a place, and they meet and exceed them!  I got the scallops, beet salad and goulash... Each item a memorable moment.  But the goulash... it's perfection.  Your mouth wants for nothing...
Order it, you'll never be dissappointed... if you've had better, your Austrian Grand Mother must have been a wonderful cook!!!

Love the atmosphere and the industrial-y look of the interiors SO much! Service is great and food is good! Goulash and double roasted pork belly are super awesome. I always go for one of these two, so I have mo idea how’s the rest of the menu. I did try some of the sausage plates and cabbage roulade, both also very good. I give it 4 stars for food just because. This restaurant and this location is one of my favorite in Bay Area. Always happy to come here.

Ordered a couple of boba teas and the Big Vons pizza from the restaurant for takeaway during dinner hours. I like that there is even an option for zero percent sugar for the tea which is not available in many boba tea shops. Next, the selection of cuisines available for ordering is also a pleasant surprise when even dim sum cuisine from Koi Palace is shown as an option. Also, the Big Vons pizza is very yummy but it is a bit oily for me. Finally, I like their big display on the Wall which shows the progress of each order from the customer. A very nice place to warrant a second or third visit.

Note: Add some photos after my second visit today.
Everything was great. We had a large order and they didn’t miss a single item. The atmosphere is fine, it’s just nothing fancy. The food was great though

name: Effie's Restaurant & Bar
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
This place is a hidden gem! I’ve been to this restaurant many times, and every visit has been nothing short of fantastic! The food is consistently delicious, the service is friendly and fast, and the portions are very generous for a very reasonable price.

I’ve tried several dishes, and each one has impressed me. I’ve had their carne asada tacos, philly cheese chicken, patty melt, smashed burger, nachos, clubhouse, prawn cocktail and chicken tortellini soup.

Their desserts are truly next level! The pistachio cake is so light and flavorful, the chocolate temptation cake is so rich, but the real showstopper is their crème brûlée. It’s served inside a fresh pineapple. The top is the classic crème brûlée and the bottom has a layer of caramelized pineapple. It’s absolutely amazing!
I highly recommend this place.

We stopped by for brunch. A California omelet and a customized veggie omelet with Italian sausage & cheddar cheese added and an order of apple pancakes. Everything was prepared wonderfully! We got to sit outside and were accommodated with a heater. Very clean restaurant.
We plan to be frequent customers.

Had a blast celebrating a double birthday here with a big group – they totally hooked us up with the table setup. The bone marrow and burrata appetizers were killer, and those Porterhouse and Mega-Hawk Chop steaks? Cooked perfect. Plus, they even surprised us with free Baked Alaska! Our servers were awesome all night. Seriously good experience

We’ve eaten here half dozen times, with mixed results; but have always had an enjoyable time. The latest time was for a friend’s birthday. The servers went out of their way to answer questions, and even brought us something that wasn’t officially back on the menu, yet.
They have been seasoning the steaks appropriately. There was a misunderstanding with the ordering, but we were too full anyway eating another dish.

We ordered the focaccia bread with balsamic & olive oil, watermelon juice, blazing bird and date delight added chicken.
We were the only ones that had lots of tables to choose from. Outdoor seating as well.

Love their salads! We ordered
Steak supreme
And create your
Own and it’s always spot on! I highly recommend.

Too many places to choose from when your in the Bay area, nonetheless I decided on Brew City Grill.

Staff was super friendly and the ambience was very relaxing and laid back. They definitely did not mind that we were still killing time before we checked into our hotel.

Ana was our waitress and she was super friendly and helpful.

Our food was great from the variety of beers on tap, to the sides and burgers and pizza. Everything was flavorful and high quality. Well worth the price.

Came for pliney the younger, got lunch to soak it up. All together a good experience. Food and service were both good, great beer selection too. It was just a bit pricey for relatively small portions.

name: Capers Eat & Drink
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
The service was outstanding.  Super friendly and accommodating but not hovering at all.  I like the decor and organization.  Roomy yet cozy.  We went for lunch but I imagine evenings are a lot of fun.
The food was good.  It's hard to tell much from soup and sandwiches, but the meatball sub was really tasty and the mushroom soup very good.  Friends at table raved about the tomato garlic soup.

Tap beer for $10 what a rip off. Might get more customers if they weren't so pricey and the food was surprisingly even worse. I don't think the head chef realizes he's not that great. Tables were sticky and the bathrooms were not kept very clean. Very disappointed overall and will not recommend this place to my friends and other people.

name: Cedar Room
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Great selection of draft beers. We stopped here after Captain America Brave New World (Great movie!) Service was great, attentive but not intrusive. The reggae music added to the ambiance.

This is a great bar and music venue that is part of the Pruneyard theatres.  The staff were all friendly and helpful. It was a friendly, welcoming crowd at the bar. The bartenders were professional and fun to watch mix drinks. I just had a burger, but it was a good one!

We had lunch in here celebrating Valentine's Day,  I have to say it was really excellent I like everything I ordered. I ordered everything with red hearts on the menu，I recommend giving it a try. I visited Angkor Wat in Cambodia ten years ago.this restaurant brings back good memories!!!! We’d be back

Excellent ambiance and quiet place to sit and have a meal. Great for people who want to avoid noisy crowds. The food was well portioned, well priced, and one of the most delicious meals I’ve had. The chef and owner is friendly and welcoming to our party of 6. She accommodated us very well and I would definitely return for meals and takeout.

Decent spot with room for improvement

Tried El Guapo recently and had a mixed experience. The ambiance is fun and lively, great for casual hangouts or a night out with friends. The service was friendly, though a bit slow during peak hours. As for the food, some dishes were flavorful—especially the tacos—but others felt a bit underwhelming for the price. Drinks were solid, especially the margaritas. Overall, not a bad place, but there's definitely potential for a more consistent experience. Lastly we ordered spicy pineapple cocktail which was great
Fish Taco was nice and delicious chicken tacos were ok in taste , it can be better ..

El Guapo’s is an ok restaraunt in Campbell downtown. While the ambiance was phenomenal as they had plenty of outdoor and indoor seating as well as a bar, the food was unfortunately extremely mediocre.

I got the Quesabirria tacos and the food came out in a reasonable time. The tacos themselves were extremely wet already with some grease and they were just soggy and had no crunch to them making it some kind of tortilla soup which I didn’t enjoy. While the meat(beef) was tender, it had little to no actual flavor. The consome which is what is supposed to be the highlight of Quesabirria tacos was unfortunately underwhelming as it too had no flavor. The chips and salsa for me were really good though, as the salsa and chips tasted fresh. The tomatillo salsa was my favorite.

El guapo’s was extremely cheap for a nice restaurant in downtown as my dish which was sufficient for my whole dinner was only about $11 with tax which was great! Overall, while I would not come back to el guapo’s again due to their mediocre food I would recommend this joint to others because of its affordability and prime location!

Went in on a Sunday around 12:30pm. As soon as we went went inside a table for 4 was immediately available.

No problems with parking outside before walking to the place. Though i can see how it might be tougher on busier days

Food was excellent. Ordered the following:

Spicy Miso Ramen - bonito & seaweed soup base with chicken & pork oil, along with chashu pork and bamboo shoots

Hinodeya Ramen - dashi & scallop soup base with scallop & pork oil, along with charsiu pork and bamboo shoots

Beef Bowl - sukiyaki beef, soft boiled egg, teriyaki sauce, seaweed and rice

Chashu Bowl - chashu pork, soft boiled egg, mayo sauce, seaweed and rice

Sweet Chili chicken Bowl - fried chicken, soft boiled egg, sweet chili sauce, seaweed and rice

Service was also excellent, Tom checked in with us onnour specific requests, if any, everything was served well

Atmostphere was lovely, excellent for conversations.

This was one of the first ramen places I tried when I moved to the bay area, and it still holds up 2 years later. Had a great birthday dinner here last month. The ramen broth is quite flavorful with a good amount of spice, and the food tastes fresh. One of my favorites.  Limited parking is the only issue with the location, I would recommend skipping the lot entirely and finding somewhere else to park.

Cute pub in the San Jose area serving various food. Seems like a nice hang out /social spot for the older crowd. The fries and wings were ok, but it could be spicier and have more flavor.

We also got extra carrots for .50 cents 🥕

It seemed like there was additional items off the menu if you ask (like quesadilla)

Definitely a better spot if you’re a more social person than we are and like sports.

I’m originally from Chicago and this is hands down the best pizza in the South Bay. Their dough is soft and ingredient are always very fresh.

I recommend everyone trying their “the Combo” pizza. Keep up the good work team!

name: La Pizzeria Italian Pizza and Bar
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Being local to downtown Campbell, this is one of my favorite go-to restaurants.  I often bring visitors and suggest it to friends. When going with groups, I love to order the antipasto, caprese, garlic bread with the mozzarella, and a salad to start. Then a pasta and pizza or two depending on the group size. You can't go wrong with a classic Margherita, but I also recommend both the Quattro Stagioni and Formaggio, as well as the Prosuitto Arugula. When it comes to dessert, I've had them all and you can't go wrong. They all hit the spot in their own way. And if you have a guest little or otherwise, they can do a simple butter pasta as well.

Food taste really good here. I was very happy with the food. The waiter is also friendly. Price I wish is cheaper to eat out now - this cost me $60+ after tax and tips. Added $5 sausage for the 4 cheese penne.

name: Sushi Confidential - Campbell
cuisine: Bar, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment:
I’d heard a lot of good things about this place, so we went in with some expectations. It was a Sunday night, and the restaurant was nearly empty—no wait for a table, which was nice.

We started with sweet potato fries, which came out quickly. Then we ordered three rolls of vegan sushi and some baos. As vegetarians, we appreciated that they had decent plant-based options with tofu. But despite the restaurant not being busy, the service was really slow. The baos took forever to arrive, and even the sushi took longer than expected. We had our 8-year-old kids with us, and they were getting restless waiting for food.

Since the portions weren’t very filling, we ordered sizzling vegetables with tofu, and—surprise—it also took ages to come out. While the food itself was great, the wait times were frustrating.

To top it off, they automatically added a 20% gratuity for our party of six (four adults, two kids). The prices were already insanely high—both appetizers and entrees felt way overpriced. We ended up with a $200 bill, which just didn’t feel justified given the service.

Their sushi is good, no doubt, but they really need to step up their service if they’re going to charge those prices and demand a 20% tip. Not sure I’d go back with this kind of experience.

First time here. All the sushi rolls were excellent. Large rolls but a little pricey. Excellent service. My son's birthday was why we were here. Our server comps is a lava cake that we shared. He and his colleague both sang Happy Birthday for my son. Parking is a little difficult during the weekends. We didn't have to wait like some of the other restaurants in the area. Definitely a place to come back and eat!
