Sorelle’s is a nice Italian restaurant serving delicious home style authentic Italian dishes in your neighborhood.
Every dish I have tried is hearty, delicious and tastes just like Italy. I always make room for the desserts also, as they are phenomenal.
One side note is that there is always a line on the weekends and there is a longer wait for serve times when they are busy.

Sorrelle Italian Bistro is a terrific neighborhood favorite of our’s. The food is scrumptious, always fresh & tasty - both their regular menu items and specials. The personnel are on top of their game - friendly welcome as you stroll in, great service at the table, quick delivery and attention from their entire team throughout our meal. We are so happy to see a vibrant local business do so well. Thank You Sorrelle!

name: Kyoto Palace Japanese Steakhouse
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Considering there arent many Teppanyaki places to eat at in San Jose. This would be the best recommended. I definitely prefer it over Benihanas.  The aromas you smell before getting to the door are fantastic. As you dine in the Chefs cooking at your table make it a entertaining and fun experience. The Food is just as great as the smell. I highly recommend The Chicken, Steak, or Lobster, paired with some shrimp, fried rice and vegetables.

Next time I go ill be sure to get a picture of my plate before its all gone..

This review is for the bar only. We did not eat full dinner in the dining room. But we love getting some appetizers or sushi and sitting at the bar for drinks! The cocktail menu is so inventive and delicious. The food is only ok but the drinks and fun bartenders make up for that. We will be back. Thank you for a great evening!

Tried a different location of this chain before but did try they're newest items today.

Upgrading a side to the brussel sprouts are well worth it. As far as fast food goes it was pretty nice. The chicken was very samey but it's not bad.

Worth a try for sure at their prices.

Generally good food in a nice spot at the Pruneyard but their new Chicken Parm sandwich 100% for NOT match their advertised picture of it. A total mess that's difficult to eat and it has an odd sweetness to it that's not very pleasant or fitting.

I like the place. I like the salads here. I completely regret ordering a sandwich.

Pancakes are the best thing on the menu (surprise!) the other items I found underwhelming. The place can get busy on the weekends, it’s nicely located next to the farmers market on Saturday so you can stroll if there is a wait.

Banana macadamia coconut pancake is bomb!!
Breakfast sandwich is meh.

Fantastic service! Fantastic Food. I sat outside. Had the grass fed beef burger with grilled mushrooms and raw onions, and fries. It came with a side salad and a little fruit cup, that was delightful. The burger was one of the best I've had. The fries are shoestring fries. Everything was grilled and cooked to perfection. It's going to be my go to.

If you're looking for some bomb gyro wraps, you have to check out Yiasso in Campbell. I went on a Friday night, there were people eating but no line at the register. You order at the register & they bring you the food. We got 2 gyro wraps, each wrap costs about 13$, an order of fries to share, loukoumades, and a piece of baklava. All in all is was about 43$
The gyro wraps were a hefty size and loaded with meat and other ingredients. I would definitely get it again. Gyro was perfectly thinly sliced and the tzatziki was incredible!
The fries were eh, straight from the freezer fries and we all know fresh cut is the best. I would still get them again tho lol
Loukoumades (like little greek donuts if you don't know) were so incredible! I feel like it's a rare find so when I saw them on the menu, I knew I had to get and they were delish, crunchy on the outside and chewy in the middle!
Baklava was incredible too.
We went on a Friday night and it was chilly, but they have outdoor seating with fire heaters going which I appreciated. If it was a bit warmer, I would've sat outside!
Seating on the inside is standard. All in all, this will be a repeat meal for me!

Extremely disappointed with the “greek fries” ….I mean…look at this picture. Does it even look like real feta cheese??? So disappointing. Do better. Use real feta, not this stuff. Make the cheese more prominent. This picture on the cheese front is well, pathetic. I paid almost $3 extra for this over the regular fries. Is this $3 worth of feta??? No. Is it even real feta??? Skeptical. Possible, but who shreds feta (my advice—use a “crumbled” type of feta).  Lamb Gyro was decent, used real lamb as opposed to the typical “gyro” meat you may be accustomed to.

My initial dislike of this place was the pricing.  I saw $39.99 for chicken parmesean and almost left... but decided to stay because we already had our drinks.  When the meal arrived, I was amazed by the 3 large portions of chicken parmesean. I then realized the meal is meant to be shared as it is served with platter utensils to serve others.
The chicken tasted pretty good, but I tasted nothing in the marinara that was special or even tasty.
The service was absolutely nothing to praise.  We were not offered any bread until it was requested. Our waitress walked past our table 4X before I flagged down a waiter that had passed my table twice for a drink refill.
The building and decor are dated and well worn.  The bathroom was also well worn but was clean.  The cushions in our booth seating literally had springs pushing up and should have been replaced years ago.  The poop stains on the toilet seat were gross.

I could see coming here if I had to feed the visiting grandkids or the like as the portion sizes make this place very economical when feeding (paying for) a group.
Overall, I did not come with a group as it was just the two of us on a date. Since we eat out often, this place was a dud.
We did not visit here to forfeit flavor for portion size.  The mediocre (flat) flavor, combined with poor service and a very run-down facility, make this a disappointing visit.
And what's with the head on the lazy-susan with the bust of a Pope?

This restaurant has a warm and cozy atmosphere for large parties.

However, the quality of the food is an insult, not only to the diners, but to the standards of Italian cuisine. The best I can say is that it's filling for those who eat the food.

For a party of 12, we had a huge pile of spaghetti which was topped with an insufficient amount of cheap grocery store sauce. The lasagna was dry. How does that happen? The Chicken Parm was decent, even though the chicken was dry and under seasoned. Oh, and it was no surprise to see "Kraft" parmesan cheese in a shaker on the table. The food may be a feast for the eyes, but not for the palate.
Great little restaurant that has been here for 20 years.  Decor is ok, but you don't come here for atmosphere.  Jalisco is all about the food and the service.  Try this place, it won't disappoint.

3 stars for very Nice customer service. Ok quesadilla plate... so much cheese in what seemed to be a homemade tortilla. The  Taco salad was ok but would have been better with beans in it. For almost 16 bucks,
it should have had beans in it! Chile Verde for almost $19 was overpriced and the meat did not taste good at all. It was big chucks of meat that tasted "gamey". Got a different plate of what should have been a chicken enchilada but it tasted more like chicken and mole. All together the 3 of us felt it was a little overpriced for $60+ dollars and no refund for the bad chile verde. Got a lesser priced plate in return.
The refried beans were yum. The rice on our plates was mushy and overcooked. We did not eat too much of it.  This restaurant was rated like a 4+ star on yelp and google... it was our first time and we didn't feel that rating ...wanted to give only 2 stars for the food (sadly the pictures look better than the food actually was)...but like I said, the cashier man and the young lady at the bar gave nice service to us.
Lequy in Campbell, CA offers a cozy dining experience. The clay pot rice is absolutely phenomenal—worth every bite. While the other dishes are just okay, this standout dish makes it a must-try spot!

UPDATED REVIEW 2024/09
they moved to a new location where is right next to Grocery Outlet, just a few steps away from the original place. There’s a 20% discount for dining in to the end of September, kind of celebration of the opening. Unfortunately I have to downgrade on this second visit (though it’s my first time at the new location) because the food quality is just average. I had beef stew with rice today thanks to the accommodating staff who let me swap the egg noodles for rice. The soup tastes a bit too sweet, with nothing much else going on. You can't really taste the freshness of the ingredients. The beef is cut way too square, like it came straight from a factory. The pork has that gamey flavor and wasn’t properly sliced before serving on the plate. The rice isn't wet or sticky and tastes great, but some were clumped together, which is a bit disappointing.

ORIGINAL REVIEW
The restaurant has excellent natural light, and the vintage booth seating by the wall is very cozy and welcoming. We enjoy eating BBQ pork slices and BBQ chicken rice plates there. Delicious food, super comforting with everything in a decent portion size. Solid for the price. Service is speedy. We’ll certainly have to come back when we’re in the area again.

Such a cute little spot with delicious seafood! Every dish was unique and beautifully presented, but the real standouts were the miso cod and the blue prawns. The cod was perfectly seasoned with a melt-in-your-mouth tenderness unlike any cooked fish I’ve ever had before. The prawns were incredibly succulent with an aromatic curry flavor. Overall, the food was excellent!

The only miss for me was the oysters — they had a noticeably fishy aftertaste and didn’t seem particularly fresh. I also wasn’t a fan of the sweet prickly pear sauce they were served with. However, all the other dishes were so delicious that it’s still 5 stars from me.

One Fish Raw Bar is a culinary experience you won't want to miss. Each dish showcases the vision with which One Fish's menu has been crafted, with creative combinations and inspired pairings for both food and drink. I would highly recommend the 5 course family style meal, it takes you through a great variety of foods that are all delicious. There are dishes that will surprise you, awe you, and give you a sense of fun, all the while being extremely tasty of course.

The hospitality is also top tier, it's clear that the staff care about making sure you enjoy your time there. Each time I have been (which isn't nearly enough times since I found out about One Fish) I have always had a wonderful experience. Thanks very much to Josh and the rest of the One Fish crew for such a great time there every time!

This place was a waste of money. We ordered the chicken souvlaki, a falafel wrap and a gyro bowl. The falafels were completely undercooked. While the outside was crispy, inside it was still raw and pasty.
The rice was also undercooked and hard. It took them more than 20mins to get the food ready, which is fine if the food was worth the wait. It was just terrible, and we couldn’t finish what we ordered. How does a Greek place not get their falafels right? The only thing decent was the chicken gyro. Not recommended

had the privilege of visiting El Greco Grill again, my absolute favorite Greek restaurant in California. Every time I’m in San Jose for a fencing tournament, it is a must-visit for me. Once again, they exceeded my expectations.

This time, I enjoyed an incredible meal featuring a Greek salad, French fries, pork gyro, and chicken gyro, all while watching the Super Bowl. The flavors were authentic, fresh, and just as fantastic as I remembered.

The staff were amazing, even better than ever. What made this visit even more special was that the owner himself prepared the meal. It was such a blessing and the perfect way to end a long day after a tough fencing tournament.

El Greco Grill truly feels like a taste of home. Representing Greece 🇬🇷 with every bite!

name: Tessora's Barra di Vino.. As of Jan 16, 2025 Tessoras is under new management
cuisine: Bar, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment: Great place for wine tasting and small family get together, they also accept small parties and can close place for you to make it private.  Service is fantastic and food tastes great from small appetizers to a meat and pizza. Thank you for making it very delicious and special.

New owners, they just opened this week and I stopped in to see the updates.

Summary: Absolutely incredible.  Food was TASTY, wine selection was great, but best of all was the service.

Angeline went so far out of her way to make sure everyone was having a great time and enjoying the atmosphere. It’s clear the new owners want to make something unique out of Tessora. Can’t recommend it enough

Had friends tell me how good this chain was so went to try it.

Overall it was pretty solid, I did give them five stars but it's closer to four and a half.

Nothing I tried was bad and the beef Jamaican patty was great but it's hype isn't that justified.

Still for the pricing and what they offer they are unique and is worth a try if you like chicken.

Second location I have been to. I came back for the oxtails as they are delicious and the portions (which include rice and plantains) are great for the price. My husband stuck to the jerk chicken breast and love it as well. Their Jamaican patties are also delicious! I will continue to visit any Back-a-yard restaurant as the consistency is spot on!

name: Kirk's Steakburgers
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Meal Delivery, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: I love that Kirk's was able to take over the old Grill Em building, as it creates a great atmosphere for both groups and families with the indoor and outdoor seating. This is a counter order, deliver to your table establishment which is great for groups, since you don't have to worry about split checks. The serving sizes are plentiful and there is a ton of variety. Their shakes are delicious, but you can also order a soda or something from the bar. There tons of side options, I love the Cajun fries! I'm determined to keep going back ordering something new off the menu every time. 😉🤣

Kirk’s Steakhouse is our go-to spot after a hike, and for a good reason! The spot is old fashioned and serve some of the best burgers in town. We tried the Steak Burger Bowl, which was a great (and healthier) option if you’re watching your diet. We also had the Blue Cheese Burger, Jalapeño Cheddar, and Mushroom Swiss Burger, and every single one was fantastic. The flavors were spot on, the ingredients fresh, and the burgers cooked to perfection.

Their fries are fantastic too! We got both sweet potato fries and regular fries, and they were crispy and delicious. Plus, their prices are fair and not expensive, making this spot even better.

If you’re craving a great burger and fries, this is the place to be! Highly recommend!

name: Best Taste Chinese Restaurant
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment:
A wonderful Experience at this place. The food was delicious with various options to choose from.
As a first timer my wife and I got:
●Szechwan beef (unfried)
●Chow mein (shrimp)
●Fried rice (combination)
●Bread Pudding (Desert)
●Teriyaki Chicken Bento Box
-Teriyaki Chicken
-egg roll (x1)
-salad
-California Rolls (x4 pieces)

I will say it's not often you find a great restaurant like this that has Szechwan sauce and great tasting meat and vegan choices.

I personally recommend the Chicken and beef as main course options if your looking to try this place out.

I always have a great experience at Best Taste Chinese Restaurant! The atmosphere is cozy, newly remodeled and inviting. I have ordered food to go from here several times and it's always delicious, well packaged and they never forget condiments and utensils. It's so nice to be greeted with a smile and a warm welcome. I definitely plan to stay and eat one day soon when I'm in the area and I have more time!

Went today for my birthday! I had the Mama Chen’s Chinese chicken salad and I'd  say it was pretty good! Unfortunately (I know this'll sound weird) the fork's texture was very disagreeable and bugged me throughout the whole meal. If you're sensitive to different metals in cutlery, I'd keep this in mind!

Besides that, the portion was huge, which was great! But I also would've appreciated a bit of more protein. Service was super nice too. Overall; decent place!

This sandwich spot knows how to pack a punch of flavor - whether you’re a meat lover or all about the vegan life  - this place is a must-visit! My vegan Banh Mi sandwich had fresh ingredients and creative combinations that made me rethink what a sandwich can be. The sweet potato soup was smooth and velvety with a touch of savory depth. Every Thursday, kids eat free, making this not just a great place for a meal but a welcoming space for families. Plus, they throw in crayons and coloring pages to keep the little ones entertained. Friendly staff and generous portions - this is the kind of spot that keeps you coming back.

Such good food and experience.

Good parking, easy to spot in the square.

1 restroom that is unisex.

Fast service, large menu with diverse meats (and not).

Hope to return to try more dishes.

Wow! This place really looks nice inside. I saw their restaurant name sign outside and seems like they haven’t changed it since they opened, which is a bout a decade ago. Anyways, you can see that there are plenty of decorations inside and it’s mostly about sports. It also gives you a good vibe of living in the Philippines since the environment of that place tends to be like.

Let’s talk about the food. I am quite impressed that they serve us food in more cultural plates with a leaf sticking at the top. The food is also delicious and authentic. Really great choice of seasonings especially on the garlic rice and pork sisig! No wonder this place is so popular especially on Yelp.

It’s also great that they leave utensils out there unlike most restaurants where you have to ask them for extra. Honestly wish that they have more individual plates options in the menu, but that’s fine. I came here for breakfast and popularity of it anyways!

name: Blue Line Pizza
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: It's been a long time since I visited, and I think it's better. You can choose the pizza you want from various thick dough options. Today, I chose wild mushrooms and truffle sauce. It was better because it was cloudy and early lunchtime, and there were no people. I recommend you to go!

Visited here since I wanted to try Chicago style pizza and overall it was solid.

Their wings are also good but a bit overpriced.
Pizza was fine, it's a different style but if you like pizza you'll enjoy this too.

Overall for the price it's fair. Would give them a try.

Pros: clean outdoor seating, many food options, different seating options, soft meat and large pieces. Fresh vegetables, friendly staff, clean environment and clean bathroom.
Cons: paper plates that easily tears apart from food’d moist and cutting with knife, bathroom was missing essentials like seat cover and towel, food presentation was very bad and dirty

This is a cheerful little eatery, which was delightfully done up for Halloween. We had ordered a burrito bowl, and chicken fajita. The burrito bowl had generous portions of chicken, rice, beans, and salsa, and the chicken fajita contained a lot of spicy chicken strips. The restaurant filled up quickly while we were there, and I could see why. By the end of our meal we knew that we would visit again.
Latin Asian fusion kitchen catered my grand opening party, and it was spectacular! They did an amazing job with the good and presentation. Everybody was taking about how delicious everything was!

It was a very nice evening, the kitchen time was easy and basic with fresh ingredients.   We started on time and were the only ones in the kitchen which was nice.  A group of 6 was at our table and they started after us which gave us the kitchen without a rush.  Something to ask about, they looked crowded,  Overall, a very nice evening, but make sure you ask pricing on wine.    We picked a $10-12 bottle of wine we knew, and we’re charged $75.00.   Our fault for not confirming the upcharge 100%… but that was a bit of a buzz kill after paying for the event $$$ and then the wine$$$$,  but still a nice evening

name: Out of the Barrel
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Don't really do reviews unless some stood out to me. Went there for an afternoon drink today. Love the selection of beers. The redheaded bartender was pretty rude. I tried to ask a few questions about the other breweries. Made me feel unwelcomed. Sorry that the speaker is right over the bar so it was hard to hear me.
Great place for a beer and they have a generous selection. The only downside is they have limited seating so it can get crowded very quickly

Wonderful service, it's a pleasure when the family of the restaurant take real good care of you and service if real good.  It was a little of everything we ordered and they brought out the hot sauces and the platters were all delicious.  Keep up the good work.

We had lunch at this nice Vietnamese restaurant on Sunday. It looked like the kind of place you go for real Vietnamese food, and it was almost there . We hoped for something amazing, but the food was just  good - simple and tasty. Sometimes that's enough, right?
We really liked the appetizer mix, especially the steamed meatloaf. The wonton soup was great too - fresh, warm, and full of dumplings. The banh mi sandwich was alright; the chicken was steamed, not grilled, so it was a bit soft, but still okay. What made our visit special was the service - everyone was super nice and quick. It was a good place to eat, with a friendly vibe.

Came here for the second time before a movie.
The pizza is pretty good. We got a veggie pizza and added jalapeno's. The toppings are ample, and the crust is nice. If we were to order again, we would request extra crispy as the center was watery.
We got the chicken pesto, and it was average. Not a strong pesto flavor, but the portion is good size. I wouldn't order chicken again. It was small cubed pieces that seemed as if they might have been frozen at some point.
The garlic bread is probably their strongest contender. Soft and tasty.
My biggest problem and why I would only get takeout is they were cleaning the kitchen while we were eating and the cleaner was so strong, I had to get out asap. It was making me physically ill and on the edge of vomiting. :( Even if I didn't have sensitivity to odors, I don't think anyone likes to smell chemicals while they are eating. It doesn't allow you to taste the food at all.
I guess the positive is that the place is probably clean, but I can't risk getting a migraine or getting ill from it.
It is very loud in the place even with only a few people and the kitchen staff going back and forth with a cart of dishes clanking as he goes over the carpet (3 times in the 40 minutes we were there) was less than pleasant.
The place is very old school and very 'rough around the edges'. You grab your own forks, plastic plates, and super thin napkins. It's a good place for families. I'm sure because of the portion sizes and prices, just know what you're getting into when going.
They seem very nice, so I'm torn with a not so great review, but I think honesty is the only way restaurants can know opinions and try to retain customers.
A typical small, local Italian spot with a cozy, unpretentious vibe. The pizza is decent, though the pastas are just average. The host is warm and welcoming, and the service is attentive.

Absolutely loved my experience! We ordered two quesadillas, a noodle bowl, and the Tiki Tofu, and everything was incredibly fresh and flavorful. It's so refreshing to find a health food restaurant where the food doesn't sacrifice taste. The ingredients tasted high-quality, and the dishes were well-prepared. Even the quesadillas felt light and satisfying. The Tiki Tofu was a standout – delicious and perfectly cooked. Highly recommend for anyone looking for a healthy and delicious meal.

I recently enjoyed a meal here at World Wrapps, where the friendly, attentive service truly stood out—a rarity these days. I ordered the Argentina chimichurri wrap, bursting with fresh, healthy flavors. As a vegan, I appreciated the thoughtfully crafted menu with clearly labeled allergen-friendly options. Dining outside in a quiet, relaxing ambiance made for a perfect experience

During my recent visit to Tostadas in Campbell, I was thoroughly impressed by the vibrant atmosphere and exceptional culinary offerings. The restaurant exudes a lively and inviting ambiance, making it an ideal spot for both casual gatherings and special occasions.

We began our meal with the Guacamole, artfully presented in a traditional stone molcajete and accompanied by fresh salsa. The guacamole was rich and flavorful, perfectly complemented by the salsa’s zest. The accompanying chips, though slightly firm, provided a satisfying crunch that paired well with the creamy dip.

For the main course, we opted for the Birria Tacos, featuring tender, slow-braised beef enveloped in warm tortillas. The depth of flavor in the birria was remarkable, and the dish was elevated by the addition of fresh cilantro and onions, graciously provided upon request by our attentive waitress.

Desiring a take-home treat, I ordered the Birria Pizzadilla to go. This innovative fusion dish combines the savory essence of birria with the cheesy indulgence of a quesadilla, all packaged thoughtfully with extra condiments to enhance the experience at home.

To accompany our meal, I indulged in a vibrant blue cocktail, the LaToxica, which offered a delightful medley of fruity flavors and a refreshing finish. The drink menu at Tostadas is extensive, featuring a variety of creative cocktails that cater to diverse palates.

Overall, Tostadas delivers a memorable dining experience with its dynamic atmosphere, courteous service, and delectable dishes. I eagerly anticipate my next visit to explore more of their enticing menu offerings.

When I rate a restaurant, there are three factors: quality of Salsa/ chips, the main plate, and the drink itself.

Different categories within those three.

Is the salsa unique? Are the chips fresh or too oily? Is the plate warm? The value of the plate vs volume?  Is the margarita well mixed? Is the margarita "syrup" or feels hand crafted? Size of drink vs alcohol content vs price.

Bonus pts for atmosphere cleanliness and the overall "Vibe"

The atmosphere here is beautiful but I tend to find that shows as an increases in price.

The salsa didn't have enough flavor or kick to it. The chips were too oily IMO.

The plate I ordered, I did not care for the style of sausage, but honestly was pretty tasty, could use a larger portion of has browns, which were cooked amazingly 🍳👌

The mimosa came out a bit "sad" IMO. It wasn't full enough for $12. It only needed a few more ounces.

On the service level, the gentlemen was friendly, yet soon forgot about me once my plate was out. No one came by for 25 min and I was ready for the check. Still polite, I thanked them for their time.

I do plan to return, as their happy hour of M-F 9@? To 12pm is intriguing.

Time will tell.

This place has good burgers. But ordering for delivery isn’t great because they don’t pay attention to the details. Sauce requests are important and they forgot ours. We called to notify and the person on the phone said ‘thanks for letting us know, is there anything else we can do for you’. No offer to correct the situation. We live in Campbell and likely won’t choose this again. I’d expect great service all around. In store and delivery packaging. Ordered on 4/30 around 6pm.

Pretty fantastic burger joint. Burgers are very tasty with a great beefy flavor. The few burger variations we've tried have all been delicious. Fries and especially the onion rings are top quality. They've got a few craft beers on tap. There's a happy hour special afternoon Monday thru Thursday. Can't wait to come back soon!
Really like the food there and everything, first time visiting the states as well really nice store nothing like it back home god bless
Not bad, I've had better. quick service.

name: Taco Bravo
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Ate here 3days in a row. The first day was the first time I tried this place. I drove from Mt. View 3 consecutive mornings, ate till I'm full. Yeah, it's THAT delicious, and totally worth every penny. This place is a local gem, family owned, all ingredients freshly prepared every day, most delicious and much healthier option compared to any other taco shops (I usually get sick after one meal at other taco shops). No wonder why they are the local fav for 40+ year. Will comback to try every menu. Thank you 🙏 Taco Bravo!! 👏👏👏😁😁😁

Taco Bravo has been unchanged for decades, thank you. Tacos have huge amounts of beef and cheese.  You think you can eat maybe 4 or 5 soft tacos at the big Bell place?  Just two soft tacos here is way plenty. Also get some hot sauce. It seems homemade and unique. Spicy, but not stupid hot. Bravo!!! 🌮🌮🌮

We cannot say enough good things about Casa Lupe! The food is delicious and the service is so friendly, we feel like family when we dine here. After moving away and only returning every year or so, Al still greets us warmly at the door and Margarita knows exactly what we want to eat.
The fajitas are served sizzling and piled high with seasoned meat and perfectly cooked veggies. The burritos are well filled and the chips are crispy, served with spicy salsa and pico de gallo.
Be sure to have a margarita when you visit!

Just okay. The food has always been on the bland side of the scale. I have never had a spicy dish served to me so I ask for a hot salsa when I feel the need for a good burn.  Otherwise Casa Lupe serves the standard Tex-Mex cuisine. Portions are good. Price seems a little high but this is Silicon Valley, so who knows.

The chicken is pretty good. But it’s a little spicy so it needs a dipping sauce. I got four chicken strips, not chicken nuggets, chicken strips, and one very small packet of dipping sauce. They’ve also changed the type of dipping sauce so it’s much smaller and I’m sure they get a better deal on it but they would only give one small packet for four chicken strips not sure I’ll come back probably not

So they saved five cents on not giving me a second dipping sauce and it cost them future sales.  Makes zero sense.

I added a photo so you can tell that I’m not just a complainer. It’s very small packet of sauce with four large chicken strips..it was over $9.00.  You would think you’d be able to have two sauces

Fried chicken at a gas station..... Sounds horrible, right? Please keep thinking that way so I can have more of it. The chicken is insanely good, the biscuits are moist and sweet, the fries are bomb. This is the most unlikely place to get dinner for the family, but I do it and everyone loves it. Service and atmosphere are what you would expect....it's a gas station.

After a good start to our birthday dinner things took a wrong direction with the bone in ribeye being undercooked. But Alan the GM saved the day. Comp’d our meal and gave us delicious desserts and a twist on a two shot espresso with a lemon twist and it was so good on the palette..and our server Erick came through with bomb whipped cream! We’ll be back guys!

Great service.  The steak was nicely cooked topped with truffle butter.  My go to drink "Old Fashioned" was perfectly done.  Nice atmosphere, parking can be a premium, but can't hold that against them. Will come back for the high quality food they serve.

name: Bella Saratoga
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
This is a really nice Italian restaurant in an old Victorian home. We've eaten here several times over the years. The food is very good! They have an outdoor dining area, and I believe that they still have live music during weekend brunch and weekend evenings.
I usually have Italian entrées but this time for lunch we had the Bella burger which was really big and tasty with fries that were very good. I was really full after lunch. Also posted a few pics of more food that we've eaten.
Latest update:
Sat at the bar yesterday, and Wendy and Ben, the bartenders were really nice and made really good drinks! Started with a Negroni and then some wine. To eat, we started with the crab cakes, then for entrees, Eggplant Parmesan and Linguine Bolognese. For dessert we shared the Pecan Turtle pie. Everything was delicious! With  dessert, also had an Expresso martini and Expresso.

Seated upstairs. Great service.
Tried the mussels and clams appetizer with olive oil instead of butter and the pasta primavera with a red sauce. The bread is homemade and also very good.
My wife tried the Halibut special and my son the fettuccine Bolognese.
The appetizer was excellent, the wine sauce was delicious. My pasta was OK, a little over done even for fresh pasta. The red sauce was good.
The Bolognese was also excellent and the pasta was better. The Halibut was yummy.

We've been talking about trying Goga for a while now and am I glad we did! We were their first OpenTable reservation :) we showed up and did to a glitch they didn't have us on the books, but no worries at all.. they shifted some tables around and we were seated.

This was a prefix menu, which made ordering super easy.. and much to our surprise.. such an amazing choices of flavors and textures. We started with a duck appetizer salad, followed by cod (OMG sooooo good) topped with lamb. Honestly, it was all made to perfection.

There is a wine and beer menu available.. minimal choice. We were recommended pinot with dinner.. it was fine.. not amazing as the food.

Dessert was simple and delicious!! I could've had two 😁

The staff were attentive enough (i.e. not annoying) and very nice. Our water was consistently filled, utensils changed between meals, etc.

The ambiance of the restaurant is fine. Would be so much better with better, warmer lighting. Although the kitchen is semi open to the space, there wasn't too much noise nor smell to be distracting.

Overall, gem of a find.. must try!! We'll be back for sure!!

The restaurant only offered a set menu, and while it’s a small family-run establishment with friendly owners, the food and service were slower than expected due to limited staff. The clam chowder soup was delicious, but unfortunately, the rest of the dishes didn’t live up to expectations. The beef portion was disappointing, as it was mostly fat and tendons with little actual meat, and the cut I received was already small to begin with. For dessert, I received a tiny slice, much smaller compared to what other customers were served.
Staff was very attentive. Unfortunately, I was not too impressed with my meal. It was tasteless and bland. The bread served before the meal, though it was very yummy. Crab cakes were okay.

We had multiple family dinners while staying in Saratoga. This place is somewhat hidden between other restaurants, but definitely worth coming. Great pasta and pizza. Amazing service and everyone was very friendly and welcoming.

name: Plumed Horse
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Been here a couple of time but my most recent was celebrating my birthday at The Plumed Horse, and it was truly an unforgettable experience.
The ambiance of the restaurant is both elegant and refined making it the perfect place to celebrate a special occasion. The lighting and decor are sophisticated and warm. Service was exceptional.

The food is nothing short of extraordinary. Every course was a masterpiece - beautifully presented, bursting with flavor, and perfectly paired with wines recommended by the knowledgeable sommelier. The tasting menu was an absolute highlight, offering a delightful variety of innovative dishes that left us both amazed and satisfied. Each bite felt like a new culinary adventure, and the attention to detail was impeccable

We went here to celebrate and it was an exquisite experience from beginning to end.  I highly recommend coming here if you've got something special to celebrate and enjoy.

The four course meal left me very full and very satisfied.  The granny smith dessert was divine  and I would order it again in a heartbeat.

I found the pork more enjoyable than the ribeye, but that could just be me.  The way the beans blended with the savory meat was awesome.

The house version of an old fashioned was very drinkable and I probably shouldn't have ordered  so many.

My favorite restaurant ever because the fondue is so delicious and made with quality ingredients. We live 3 hours away now and STILL drive back to go here. Great date night spot or for special occasions. Takes a few hours to enjoy the full meal experience. Oh, they also have great cocktails, and I always get a white chocolate mocha with the chocolate fondue. So yummy!

I made a reservation for 4.27 at 615 for a party of 3, got caught up in traffic, was running late. Called the restaurant, the man who answered the phone was really nice and offered to push our reservation 15 mins forward. Once we arrived, we realized we would prefer patio seating and asked if that was possible. The host was also very nice, polite and accommodating. We got seated in the patio with a minimal wait time.

The highlight of our reservation (besides the yummy food of course) had to be our amazing server, Julian. He was super attentive, very friendly and highly knowledgeable about the menu, suggesting what paired well with what (for my 2 friends, it was their first time eating here and they had lots of questions). I really want to commend Julian for providing outstanding service despite being really busy taking care of multiple tables. We had a great time, my friends loved the restaurant and the food was delicious. Thank you Julian for being awesome! :)

Overall, highly recommend this restaurant!

Wow! We came here for our anniversary on a Tuesday and they knocked it out of the park! Alex was an outstanding waiter and paced our meal out perfectly. I definitely recommend popping in on a weekday. It was busy, but not enough to affect our conversation. For the price, wasn’t disappointed. Plating was beautiful. Will come back! Cheers!

Katelyn L was excellent as our server last night. She was consistently attentive but not intrusive. She had the right balance of friendliness and respected our privacy. She made suggestions and did not interfere in our selection. Her service was so memorable that I almost forget to mention that the special Spring menu - duck breast with risotto, Alaskan key lime pie - was also super!

This brunch spot is a delightful find, offering both style and substance. The food is a feast for the eyes, with beautifully designed dishes that look almost too good to eat. Fortunately, the flavors match the presentation—every bite is as satisfying as it is visually appealing.

A standout feature is their kid-friendly menu, making it a great choice for families. It’s always a relief to find a place that caters to young diners without compromising on quality or creativity.

The seating options are versatile, with both indoor and outdoor spaces available. Whether you prefer a cozy corner indoors or a breezy patio experience, this spot has you covered.

One of the best parts? It’s not overly crowded. You can enjoy your meal in a relaxed atmosphere without feeling rushed or cramped, even during typical brunch hours.

With its combination of delicious food, thoughtful design, and a welcoming ambiance, this place is a must-visit for brunch lovers. Whether you’re dining solo, with friends, or bringing the kids along, it’s a spot that caters to everyone.

If the restaurant did not offer discount and complementary waffle, I’d rated as 1 star. Super slow food and not delicious at all. The house Benedict “fusion” with a crispy kale and it took half the space of the plate. And the stem of it is not chewable at all, don’t get the point of this dish. The loco moco was also weird and took waaaaay tooo long to come, that’s also why they offered the discount and free waffle. The loco moco also doesn’t look like the other one we use to have and had a huge portion of rice.

To really find some positive things: bacon in my Benedict tasktes food and the place is clean.

name: Mangia Mornings
cuisine: Cafe, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: New place in Saratoga, we drove by recently and tried it out now. We had a very pleasant breakfast. The food looked very nice and was tasty. The space is simple and clean. The service was fantastic. Very friendly and helpful. We didn’t like one of things we ordered (just personal preference) and were immediately offered to choose something else.

We enjoyed our coffee and meal here. The bomboloni was delicious (my husband is Italian and he approved) Hoping to try the sfogliatella next time if they got it since we haven’t had one since we were living in NYC! This place is cute and service is great. My eggs Benedict was good, but not a fan of the hashbrowns. Other than that, we’re def looking forward to trying other menu items.

name: Pisco Bar
cuisine: Bar, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment: I had the most amazing meal and experience here. The service was impeccable. We were served by Eduardo the manager and he was amazing. He gave great recommendations, service was on point. I really dislike when we people bring out apps and food way too fast so I asked him to stagger it and he timed everything so perfectly! I loved the ceviche pisco was soooooo good! The Loma saltado had great flavor. The empanadas were so good too. The ahi tuna app was so tender, I wish it was a little less sweet but it was delicious. The whole experience was so enjoyable. The music was really good. The pisco passionfruit drink was great and I especially loved the passionfruit mojito was to die for. Thank you Eduardo, you were such a delight!

Stopped in for a quick drink. We got 2 pisco flights, tried 6 different flavors of piscos. They were delicious but our favorites were the maracuja & cucumber! The bartender took a lot of care whilst making the drinks & you could tell. They were pretty & yummy! I’d like to come back to try the food. The salsa that came with the chips was really really good so it gives me high hopes for the plates there!

name: Big Basin Cafe
cuisine: Bakery, Cafe, Store, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Had a nice breakfast and latte at this coffee shop! They have the best coffee on Saratoga Avenue. The lavender latte was smooth and the avocado toast was fine. They also have different board games to play with! Would like to try their ice cream next time!

This place gets quite busy during peak hours especially with the bikers coming in. Good vibes with indoor and outdoor seating and dog friendly. The food was not amazing though but portion size was definitely decent.

Great burger joint that really shows just how good a burger joint can be.

They've got all kinds of options for your burger here and they're all pretty good but you won't go wrong even if you just get the most basic one. The atmosphere is casual and lively but clean and nice. You could be a teenage high school student,  or a CEO and feel right at home at the tables here either way.

There's a bar with all kinds of craft brews on tap, too. Would be a nice low-key spot to catch a taste with a few friends in the evening or get wasted at lunchtime watching your team lose the game.

All in all, this is a burger joint with great burgers and if that isn't what's beautiful about America I don't know what is.
The food is fine cuisines for sure. It's not a regular burger spot. Must try!! 5 star service and quality foods. The team working is also providing an excellent experience.

Definitely avoid  Fried rice was so salty could not eat. What do you do? I don’t return food.  These people are very money minded. I got a small cup of chicken curry for $22. No rice. Small would be an understatement. Husband owner charged me $1 for hot sauce after all payment. The chicken curry was actually delicious. But also very salty. I think she mistook spicy request for salty.

We arrived at almost 5 p.m. for dinner on Saturday evening and were so glad that we made a reservation as the restaurant was already packed. We were greeted and seated with warmth welcome. All the food dishes come out promptly and delicious.
Po Tak were delicious with a great blend of spicy and sour combination. Spicy Lamb was delicious and goes great with all the meals on the table.
Will come back for all this yummy food again!

Jake's of Saratoga is a nice find when I was in the Saratoga area. I came in because I was interested to see how a place that sells pizza, burgers and sandwiches makes a pizza. I really love my pizza, but I dislike it when the pizza is too oily or soggy from too many toppings. The "combo" pizza has a great deal of toppings, it makes the pizza look heavy, but to my surprise the crust was nice and crispy, there was not too much oil and all the toppings were fully cooked. The extra cheese on top is also a nice addition as well.

Its a bit empty and spacious at 3 pm. This goes for both indoor and outdoor seating. Outdoor seating was especially pleasant with the 70 degree weather.

My only qualm with Jake's of Saratoga is the outdoor seating states no pets on the patio. So unfortunately you may not be able to bring man's best friend here.

Great place for gatherings.
Decent selection of beers on tap and something on the menu for everyone. Burgers, salads, sandwiches, and pizza are their specialties. The combination pizza is piled high and very satisfying.
Booths, tables, and outdoor seating options.
Several TVs with a variety of games on, but the volume is not too loud so you can still have a conversation.
Everyone who works there is personable and cares about the customer experience.

name: Bell Tower Café
cuisine: Cafe, Meal Takeaway, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Was expecting more and better from them.The food was good ,but after they made a few mistakes with 2 out of 3 of our orders. The service was lacking, and they were short staffed and very unorganized . They even charged us wrong and had to tell them.The food looked and tasted good, but was very disappointed.  .... tbd.
Our server was sweet and did try her best to correct things and apologized. Might or might not go back.

My wife and I had breakfast and it was terrific. My chicken fried steak was cook to perfection as was eggs. The pancakes were fluffy. A great little place to have a quick or relaxing meal at. The menu has several things I wished I could’ve ordered.

Came here for lunch on a weekday after spending some time admiring cherry blossoms at nearby Hakone garden. We were greeted by the friendly gorgeous owner. We ordered three appertizers and two entrees. Food came quick and they are all tasty. The baked seafood supreme is so delicious. We left full and satisfied. The bill was just $65 for all the fresh seafood and tasty lamp chop. Strongly recommend.

Absolutely exceptional. This restaurant is as much about the excellent food as it is about the experience. Hands down some of the best food I have ever had the privilege of indulging in. The owner personally came to our table and, upon learning it was our first time at her establishment, proceeded to grant us a personal tour of her distinguished, personally arranged formal dining room. She spoke with an air of loving pride about the hand-picked chandelier from Prague and the marvelous painting by a local patron which represents many important people in her life. We watched as she interacted with the other diners as well. It was a tremendous gift to have chosen this place to dine. Every single morsel, from the French Onion Soup and Seafood Crepe to the fresh bread and Chicken Forestiere, was a showcase in beautiful culinary execution. All that we experienced was provided for an extremely reasonable price (much more so than many “cookie cutter” chain restaurants) and delivered with a superior standard of quality. Many thanks for reminding your guests of what life-memory dining is really about. If you like this review, let me know with a thumbs up :)

Went here on a Friday night. It was pretty free, not much crowd.

The staff were extremely polite and friendly. They catered to all our needs. The vibe was great with nice music.

We ordered the hummus with chicken which  i definitely recommend. Chicken was juicy and tender. The hummus was the OG kind. Mediterranean pasta wasn’t the best, I’ve had better.

Finally, the show stopper was the lamb ribblets!! Absolutely tasty and tender with the mansaf sauce. I would definitely recommend this place for a nice dinner or even a date night.

We  was a group of 6 , went with high expectations but all went bad.
We ordered 6 samplers and falafel for appetizer and It was good for main course 3 seared salmon , 1 Bronzino , 1 lamb kebab and mansaf .
Seared salmon were okay but the resoto they served were weird taste feels like the cheese they used expired.
Then the bronzino fish was too salty and couldn’t eat .
The main thing is mansaf, am eating mansaf after 11 years and still I have the carving and taste if the fish in my mind I ate last time . Meat for mansaf need to cook in aged yoghurt sauce and served with rice and pine nuts but the items they served not come closers to any where. Never come back and ever recommend

name: Anchors Fish & Chips And Seafood Grill

reviews.comment: It was our first time here and could say that overall we were pleased. The fish and chips batter was different from what Im used to, but good. The Dungeness crab sandwich was also tasty and well portioned. It was early in the evening so the place was quiet and the service was great.

Fish n chips were very good with generous portions, but a bit oily and seemed slightly under done. The fries were nothing special, and again slightly under done. The po'boy was excellent. Better than the one we had in New Orleans. We will definitely go back for more.

The service was friendly and accommodating.

Be aware: there is an extra charge to use your credit card. The menu prices are for cash only.

I've been a loyal customer of Hong's for years, and it's high time I shared my positive experiences.  This is my go-to spot whenever I'm craving delicious food.  Honestly, you can't go wrong with anything on their menu. My personal favorites are the Emerald Chili Chicken and the salt and pepper fish—they are absolutely divine! The staff is incredibly friendly and welcoming, creating a warm atmosphere.  The recent renovations have also made the space even more beautiful.  I highly recommend Hong's if you have the opportunity to visit.

I've been going to Hong's for 10 years now and I've seen the evolution of this place over the years. Food was high quality and really good 10 years ago, had some rough patches during the covid years but I'm glad to say it's picked up and gotten better since 10 years ago. New, better service. Online QR code ordering. Lots of new improvements

My husband and I recently dined at this Thai restaurant on a Saturday for lunch and were highly impressed with the variety of dishes offered. The restaurant provides a separate vegetarian menu, which was a welcome addition.

We began our meal with Fresh Sesame Rolls and Fried Tofu as appetizers, along with a rich and aromatic coconut milk soup. The soup was not only generously portioned but also expertly seasoned and well-balanced in flavor. While I typically enjoy tofu but do not consider it a favorite, the Fried Tofu at this restaurant was outstanding—one of the best appetizers I have ever had. For the main course, we opted for Pineapple Fried Rice and Panang Curry. The fried rice was fragrant, slightly sweet, and loaded with fresh ingredients, while the Panang Curry was a perfect harmony of rich, creamy coconut milk and bold, aromatic spices. Together, they created a beautifully balanced and deeply satisfying meal.

Beyond the excellent cuisine, the restaurant had a warm ambience and a welcoming staff, making for an enjoyable visit. If you appreciate authentic Thai cuisine, I highly recommend this restaurant.

Have not been back to Mint Leaf for a few years now.  We met family there last night and loved it.  The atmosphere is authentic Thai.  The food was very good but we needed our chili 🌶️ sauce as we like our Thai food spicy.  The presentation of each of their dishes was the best we have ever seen. Beautiful.  No corkage is an extra plus as we love to take our own wines to restaurants.  .

Grilled Chicken Burrito was good, but a lot less chicken inside the burrito than I expected there would be. Staff are very nice and welcoming. Chips and salsa -- OMG, their green salsa was outstanding!!😋I had to buy some to go, it was so yummy.😋 I recommend this place to check out for sure.

Small Mexican restaurant that serves delicious Mexican dishes.

This is one of family spots for quick authentic Mexican food. We always order takeout because the restaurant is small and is packed. During busy times, they get tons of orders and sometimes don’t pick up.

Recommend:
Enchiladas
Seafood Chile Relleno
Shrimp Quesadillas
Tacos
Horchatas / Agua Frescas

name: Zeni
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: There are very few ethiopian restaurants in bay area and this place is the only one that stands out. They have a whole vegetarian friendly menu options. The food was flavorful, perfectly spiced. Went with family for very late lunch and there was no line, got the table and service was fast.

Our first experience with Ethiopian food. We had no expectations but full of curiosity

We ordered Vegetarian Combo and stir fry beef. The Vegetarian Combo was excellent with various lentils with different spices. The beef was rather tough and hard to chew, but it had a good flavor. Next time we'll try chicken.

I had the pleasure of dining at 575 Miishien, and it was an experience unlike any other. Specializing in miishien, a type of Yunnan-style rice noodle, this spot offers a rich and flavorful dive into Chinese regional cuisine that’s both comforting and exciting.
The star of the show was the Wagyu Beef Cross-Bridge Miishien – incredibly tender slices of wagyu beef paired with a savory broth that had clearly been simmered to perfection. The broth had layers of flavor, and the noodles had that perfect silky-chewy texture. For those who love a little heat, the Small Pot Spicy Ground Pork Miishien hits the spot without overwhelming your palate.

I had a great experience at this Yunnan rice noodle restaurant! The broth was flavorful and rich, and the rice noodles had the perfect texture—soft but not mushy. The ingredients were fresh, and the portion size was just right. I especially loved the pickled vegetables and the variety of toppings available. The staff were friendly and the service was fast. I’ll definitely come back again!

👍👍 updated 2/7/2025.Back for more! Always a plus - no wait, good prices, and friendly service. Just double-check your order!

2/5/2025
If you're looking for amazing fried calamari, look no further! This restaurant nails it. Big portions, good service, and the calamari was perfectly cooked. The wedge salad was also a tasty side. Definitely coming back!

Came in for lunch on a Saturday and got seated fairly quickly.  Orders were taken not too long after that.  Overall the experience and the food were both great.  We had 2 kids with us (2 and a 5 year old) and they were pretty happy with the food as well. Pictured are the macaroni and cheese classic, fish and chips, kids chicken tenders and a kids hot dog.  Pretty straightforward menu of American food and a good vibe inside.  Will definitely be bringing the family back

name: The Bywater
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Came here for a weekend lunch. Had high hope for the quality of food due to pretty good rating on google map. We were so disappointed with the fried chicken and waffle. Chicken was dry and the waffle is tasteless. Scone is alright but not that tasty. Pull pork - hm… has it better somewhere else….. anyhow, they have a full bar there, maybe it’s good to drink here instead, and order some food along with it.

We decided to stop here a day after returning from New Orleans because we missed the flavors.

We got Gumbo, which tasted like it was cooked with three day old seafood that was left out. It had such an unsavory taste to it.

I got the Muffuletta, which was okay hence the two stars.

The Charbroiled oysters came out to the size of one oyster I’d get in New Orleans and with 1/10 the flavor and sauciness…$18???? what a rip off. I can get a dozen oysters there for $25. If I were them I’d cut the pricing down to $10 . I can get an oyster for $2 each from my local seafood store and they taste great. At local Oyster bars around here we get 4-6 for less than $18 dollars

The beignets and here is what really made me decide I just had to leave a review. I’ve eaten beignets all over New Orleans, and I tell you what, if people were served these there, this restaurant would be shut down.

Service was mid and they forgot we even wanted beignets when they were about to hand us the check, even though they asked us if the beignets should come after the main course and we said yes

They were soggy and undercooked, and in fact were so bad I decided to book a trip back to New Orleans to cleanse my pallet with authentic beignets.

We used to come here often after hikes.  Today’s lunch was very disappointing.  The tofu salad was terrible! and they used firm tofu instead of silken.  And the sauce wasn’t good either.   My sashimi was cut in huge chunks.  After bringing the food, the waitress never showed up to check on us.
The plus side… the restaurant is in a nice court yard and we can bring our dog with us.
Finally when she brought us the bill, we told her about the tofu salad, she was rude and told me we were the first one to complain about the tofu.  So I removed one star from the service.

Perfect little gateway to delicious rolls, tempura and more. Slightly hidden away, but a perfect place to wind down in the evening, with some crisp beer, and some good Sushi. We thoroughly enjoyed ourselves, and were happy with both the food, as well as the service.

The time to deliver our order was between 20 mins to 30 mins. The fire wings were good with a little sweet taste. We didn't find any difference between Sriracha wings and Buffalo stampede wings. They both tasted the same. The wings were crispy and non smelly ( wings we buy from Costco smell raw even after cooking). The tables were very sticky .Plenty of parking available in the shopping complex.

I wish I could leave a negative star review. every single time these idiots get my online order wrong. as if this is rocket science- simple order of 10 wings and they can't get it right. I foresee this branch closing soon. it is never clean to eat there and they stop serving 45 minutes before closing because they are simply LAZY- their pick up is a mess. don't bother - better luck going to Wing stop- dont' waste your money

name: VinoVero Los Gatos
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Exceptional service. At the start of our meal Michael asked everyone seated if we had any food allergies and then crafted all of our dishes around that. Every dish was presented with dedicated beauty and integrity to the food. Delicious food happens here 💖💖

This was a great place, my wife and I had a wonderful time with beautiful wine and solid food. This makes for a cute date spot and has vibrant energy, but I would recommend making a reservation as it fills up well.

I’m rating 3 stars as a warning though for any future diners to not get bullied like we did. Our server added things to our tab that we didn’t order, but did so in a way that made it seem as though it was complimentary. So this is just a heads up to not be foolish like me who blindly paid without looking and check the tab.

The focaccia was wonderful though!

Good selection of traditional Japanese dishes that aren't sushi (though there is some sashimi pf course). Try the rice biwls (Donburi) or the stone pot rice combinations (Meshi) for a fulfilling, crackling delicious meal. Yes there can be a little wait on a busy weekend evening, just know that.

We stopped by on a chilly evening, thinking about the ochazuke we had a long time ago, but we waited for over 40 minutes. The strange thing was that many customers were leaving after finishing their meals, and there were many empty seats, but they didn't let the waiting customers in. After a couple who were in waiting group went in, my husband checked again, and the male staff member said that the only tables left were bar tables and guided us to them. There were a few groups of people who arrived just before we went in, and it was unpleasant to see them all being guided to their tables. The meal wasn't bad, but among them, the green tea chicken was the worst.  I don't think I'll visit again.

I've been coming here for months now, and it's one of my favourite places in the area. The service is incredibly good, always welcoming and friendly. The atmosphere inside is also very nice, with dark furniture that give a cozy atmosphere even with many people inside. It's a great place for an authentic taste of China for a good price. I'm a noodle soup person, so my personal recommendation is their pork belly noodles; even the smell of that soup can make my mouth water! Bring your friends to share a generous pot of hot chrysanthemum tea to wash it all down.
We came here for lunch. I feel like the items here were not as flavorful as other locations of Special Noodle, and it kinda felt like they skimmed out on the toppings.

We had the nanjing roasted duck and the duck blood vermicelli soup. Both had very large portions and both were really tasty! We kinda wished that there could be more customized seasoning for the soup but it tasted good. We ordered half a duck but there were two legs! Very rare to see when we order half, but very nice and generous of this restaurant!

The restaurant itself was small and seats were limited. Not too many people were inside but servers were nice and attentive. Will come back

The food was all very tasty, especially the fried stinky tofu, and the pig ears. It was surprising to see so many choices for a small restaurant. The portions are very decent. All the staff were friendly and made sure to accommodate our dietary restrictions and requests.

Food was high quality. Portions minuscule, prices high. Barely fed myself for $100. The table was sticky and not clean. The air was thick with burned food smoke. No ventilation…

Servers were kind. But They charged for water?! Overall very disappointed. Would not return for any reason.

They were very nice though…………. But still not coming back.

This is an Omikaze which is a boiled dish restaurant. The emphasis is on a light cuisine and sashimi. There is an open kitchen view; you can sit at the counter or at a table. The atmosphere is supposed to have a local and small-community feel. The restaurant gave us a Midnight Diner (on Netflix) aura.

You have the option of choosing your own courses or try a Kaiseki which are a set series of dishes that the Chef has chosen to tell a story with particularly paired flavor profiles.

We chose our own dishes:
Pork Belly with Black Vinegar (highly recommend, so flavorful that I ordered seconds), Box Sushi with Salmon (Chef Suzuki swapped in a fatty salmon because my girlfriend had frequented the restaurant before), Mushroom select soup (very light), Chazuke Rice in Broth with Scorched Rice and Sauteed Konbu Kelp (leathery kelp that has a great consistency and mouth feel) with Spinach. We also tried the Beef Gyoza which was also very flavorful with the right amount of crisp.

I also had a nice imported Japanese beer and a lemony dessert sake.

Carbs/fried options are recommended to go at the end because they fill you up and take away from the flavor profile of other dishes if you fill yourself up first.

It can be a bit pricey, but that is expected with rampant inflation and price gouging across the United States. Also, their choice of ingredients and imported alcohol is not incredibly cheap.

Despite some of the overly critical and pretentious reviews that I have seen of this place, I would recommend at least trying it out, being nice and respectful (that goes a long way), and having an open mind about the chef’s approach, history, storytelling, and journey.

Chef Suzuki and staff were explicitly kind and accommodating to us even with 3 other tables while we were there. If you come enough times and get to know him, then you will have a chance to write on the wall and have a specially prepared meal in the back room with him. See the attached picture of the art on the wall that Chef Suzuki did himself.

name: Tasting House
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Wow! What an amazing gem this place is. Friendly welcoming professional tidy service with a flare of art and style. And I just used their bathroom..... After I used the bathroom and washed my hands, i noticed they have a lovely basket with rolled up white cloths to dry your hands with, and I could have sworn they were heated. What!!!!!!!?!? amazing next level. I will definitely be making a reservation to come back and really experience this wonderful spot. Jazz music playing in the corner. Low dim lights, friendly servers. Wow, just wow.

Excellent dining option! The small menu has a wine pairing suggestion for each dish, the plates are really well executed and presented. The service is really good and so the ambience. They do have a piano and a singer some days, which really is a pleasant experience. The wine list has variety from grapes and countries, totally an enjoyable Dining experience.

Bold broth flavor of pork and bonito in the Tonkotsu Udon. On the salty side.  Like the thick springy noodles which also had the nice amount of chewy consistency.
The chashu pork in it were soft and had a slight sweet flavor.  Also fave a whole seasoned egg and a shrimp tempura in it.  The egg had a sweet jelly yolk.
If you prefer a sweeter Udon dish the Beef Sukiyaki  Udon would be the a good choice.
The Assorted Tempura had 3 shrimp, and 4 different veg and a squid tempura.  Sauce was light with traditional soy sweet flavor.
Price was reasonable for the quality of ingredients.
Food came out quickly.  Staff were attentive.

Have dinner with a friend at this Udon Speciality restaurant on a Friday night. Was pleased that there are indeed many varieties of Udon to choose from including curry-based or nabe-based selections. However, for me, the presentation of the yaki onigiri is the best among all the dishes that we have ordered.

name: The Heid
cuisine: Bar, Lodging, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Such a quaint location to enjoy a drink and food. It’s right by a creek with lush trees all around. Indoor is also nice and quiet.
Good place to have a drink.

Bar tender was very nice and made us feel comfortable. The outside area is my favorite part of this bar and why I will definitely make a point to stop by again. Food was not being served when we went by which was disappointing but not the end of the world.

When I found this restaurant online, I described it to my husband as "a step up from Denny's," and I wasn't too far off! It was a very cute and cozy American diner with all-day breakfast items and quick service. We're thinking about returning to try their other menu items sometime.

Note: Warm and cold. Bring clothes for both. It was better in Cupertino.

We came in around lunchtime for the $29.99 two meal deal. Store was clean, staff were nice. It was not very busy.
Food was pretty good but it did take a while to get it prepared, which I put down to the lack of other patrons, they had to make the food rather than having items ready to go.
Overall, we like the food and would definitely consider stopping by again.  It makes a change from McDonalds across the way especially since their prices have gone up.

Good wings- tried mango habanero, original, Korean bbq, atomic.
Service was exceptional- Josh at the billing counter and guy inside

name: Liuyishou Hot Pot (San Jose) 刘一手(圣何塞)

reviews.comment: Excellent gastronomical experience at this hotpot. I went there with my children. They are vegetarian so we tried both the mushroom-based as well as the tomato-based broth. I thought they were very mild, and that was perfect for our youngest as she is not too keen on spicy food. In the end, I end up using the tomato-based to cook a bunch of seafood items. The abalone was fantastic and so was the shrimp paste. The oysters and scallops were also very tasty and fresh. From the veggie sides, the fried tofu and the oyster mushrooms were my favorites. My children loved all they ate. Next time I plan to come here and try the non-veggie broths with a selection of meats. Great service and ambiance as well.

Favorite hotpot place in the area! I love this restaurant so much. Everything is so authentic (as a Chinese person!) and I also love the vibes. They have a self-serve station with all kinds of sauces and condiments, side dishes, fruits, and even deserts. If you aren’t used to eating spicy foods I would recommend the Pork Bone broth, but if you are a Chinese Mala enjoyer I definitely recommend their signature spicy soup base. The meat is high quality and delicious as well as all the other ingredients we ordered. Highly recommend!

Quick and friendly service! My first time trying this California classic, and I wasn't disappointed. I loved their potato salad especially!

I got their seasonal special, which was the Winter Citrus & Goat Cheese Salad. This was SUPER YUMMY! I asked for the the dressing to be tossed in and it was very well flavored/distributed. Ingredients were fresh and the oranges were SO SWEET!

Can't wait to try out more from their menu :)

Located in the quiet corner of Westgate Plaza. Some of the other Mendocino Farms are in crowded shopping complexes where even doing curbside makes one feel guilty.

The food is consistent with the other locations. The decor is the same too with the standard blue cow and grass seats.

The most horrible thing is that they discontinued all the good salads on the menu like Save Drake's Salad 🥗 and Impossible Taco Salad. Not this particular chains fault but it does bring their food taste down to a 4-star. I tried two of their other salads and they are a solid 3 stars.

The hummus wrap was delightful though. The tortilla was perfectly chewy.

We enjoyed our Friday lunch here. Good food and service, not crowded. Perhaps too much wine for lunch, but that’s entirely my fault. Delicious Brussels sprouts for an appetizer. My stake was made to order. Ravioli were also pretty good.

Ambiance: 4 - Made a reservation on Valentine's day and the first thing the host said to us was that we have 1hr and 15mins. The main room was so noisy but we thankfully got seated in the back room. Cute homey feel inside
Service: 4 - Attentive and friendly staffs
Food: 3 - Maybe my expectations were high but it fell short. Don't get me wrong, the Hush Puppies were scrumptious! Crunchy exterior with grittiness of the corn meal - sauce on the bottom and some sort of butter? Yes, please. The Short Rib Bites were also tender but it was too little. 😬 The Fried Chicken Sando was where it fell short. We got cut in half and I somehow ended up with all of the breading, which wasn't crispy one bit and just sloppy
Drink: 4.5 - Would come back to try other drinks once the menu is rotated

Would I come back? It wouldn't be my first option but maybe for the drinks. ;)

On my birthday, I came here for a meal, and as soon as I entered the restaurant, I could smell the aroma of natural wood, creating a very comfortable atmosphere. Every dish was fresh, with many ingredients sourced from Japan. Particularly delightful was the fresh and sweet sea urchin imported from Japan. Each course provided both visual and gustatory enjoyment, and we had a delightful dining experience. Since it was my birthday, they even presented a beautiful plate with exquisite desserts – a thoughtful gesture that made the experience truly fantastic! It’s indeed a remarkable Kaiseki restaurant.

This place is the real deal - they've got servers rocking kimonos that'll transport you straight to Edo-era Japan. Book on OpenTable to snag a spot.
📍14417 Big Basin Way, Saratoga
This was actually my second time here - first time was back when they were in Burlingame. Gotta say, I preferred the OG spot. More food, longer experience, you know how it is.
🍶Every time I do omakase or kaiseki, I swear it's like a spa day for my taste buds. Perfect recharge after traveling!
Highlights:
Jw5 aperitif sake to kick things off
ODash appetizer soup served in a wine glass - looks like white wine but packs a punch with that 5-year aged broth
Sakizuke tofu with fish roe - silky smooth tofu + salty roe = happy mouth
Otsukuri sashimi - fresh but nothing mind-blowing
YakiMono grilled eel - salt-cured eel with morels was 👌
SunoMono seafood jelly salad - my fave! Creamy yam, shrimp, uni, edible flowers. Texture for days.
Seasonal Gohan - Hokkaido A5 wagyu over rice. Tiny portion but that certificate-worthy beef tho!
Desserts were on point - loved the caramel mochi cake with soy milk powder
Overall, presentation was fire and the vibe was transporting. Wish there was a bit more food and some bolder flavors, but still a solid kaiseki experience. Who's ready for their omakase fix?

name: Campo di Bocce of Los Gatos
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Fun place! Unique with indoor and outdoor bocce courts. Full bar. Full food and beverage service. Great for a team event and dinner. Had fun. Highly recommend!
What a cool place and a fun time!!  Food far exceeded expectations.  Get the lamb chops...! Wow!

I really like the beef huoshao here! Inside is juicy but soup isn't spilling out, outside is flaky. The lamb and 3 flavor dumplings were also good. I like how it's hot but not so hot I immediately burn my mouth. You can almost eat it immediately. The lamb soup was flavorful too if you like lamb. In general I'd come back again, it's a small little shop with very nice staff.

The dumplings are all handmade and fresh!!!
As a huge fan of dumpling, this place is definitely authentic!
We don’t favor the seaweed but everything else are all soooooo good!

name: Gardenia
cuisine: Cafe, Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Store, Establishment

reviews.comment: This gorgeous location has seen many, many restaurants come & go over the decades. The large outside dining perimeter is a special touch since most Los Gatos restaurants are lucky to even have sidewalk space for outdoor tables. The old Victorian building is charming, iconic & drips with "high tea" interior decor... perfect for a weekend brunch. The music is lively, the bar area is comfortable with several chic sofas to lounge on. The service is good but slow. The food...it was divine (incredible quality & presentation)! And the coffee menu, well let's just say this coffee snob was fervently impressed! Well done, Gardenia.

Visited for the first time and stopped by for a quick lunch early afternoon on Saturday. Liked the old Victorian ambiance (great for photos!) in the restaurant, and the creative coffee and tea options. The menu options, however, were limited to mostly brunch menus. The service was sweet but inefficient. May revisit for coffees but not for the food.

Had a nice dinner here after a long time. We love Mediterranean cuisine and have been going to Evvia for years and recently to Meyhouse, Barbayani and their sister restaurant Antolian Kitchen. The mesquite grilled dishes at Dio Deka are particularly good. We have their lamb chops before but this time we had the Branzino and the Wagyu short ribs. Baklava for desert and chicken kebabs and the pita play for appetizers

Went for a birthday dinner, thought we'd class it up a bit and go for some fine Greek dining at Dio Deka, which didn't disappoint. A couple of us had the Arni Youvetsi "lamb volcano shank", which was delicious and a sizeable portion. We also had the lobster pasta, which was great as well (as long as you don't mind looking at a lobster head 😋 ); rich and creamy sauce. Marco was an amazing server and gave great guidance on both food and drink.
I haven't been here for a few years, but I have to come back sooner.

Absolutely loved this place! As an Iranian, I can say the food was authentic and delicious. The kabob was incredibly juicy and flavorful—just like home. The service was warm and attentive, and everything from start to finish was top-notch. Highly recommended for anyone looking for high-quality Persian cuisine!

A nice and cozy restaurant. The staff was very friendly and attentive. The serving portions were HUMONGOUS, and the flavor profile didn’t disappoint. The chicken kabobs and koobideh was very moist and juicy. They know how to cook their meat well. This place deserves more love, go check it out.

ASA is a Michelin guide recommended restaurant with cozy romantic vibes throughout.
Food was delicious and they were able to accommodate dietary restrictions such as pescatarian, alcohol free and gluten free.

Highly recommend their scallops and seafood dishes as that is what I ordered whereas the rest of the table enjoyed their meat dishes.

I'm not a fancy food guy, but everything here is incredible. For LG, the prices are super reasonable and you get real, high quality food with decent portions too. It's one of those rare restaurants where you can go casual or fancy and not be out of place. And the staff is amazing, too!

I wish I could write a better review.
The food was plain, lacked salt and flavors. Bloody marry most likely had no alcohol at all. A water glass was really dirty, the cups were chipped.
On a positive side: the service was quick.

I've driven by many times. May a point to try them. I had know idea of what type of food they serve. Today Sunday morning, I ordered just biscuits and gravy "take out",🤣 Call me weird, (country Boy Inside)A restaurant with biscuits and gravy on there menu. I have to try it and it's good/great. I'm coming back for sure. Can't wait to experience other dishes on their menu.

name: Italian Brothers Restaurant | ITB | Dining & Delivery | Catering for Events & Weddings

reviews.comment:
We decided to visit this restaurant and try their dishes. We ordered

Fried Calamari
Margarita Pizza
Sceriffo non Perdona
American
Crema Catalana

In the beginning we were very impressed with the efficiency of the service, we got our appetizer, bread, pizza, pasta, American very less waiting time.
