My husband enjoyed the pizza, while I didn't enjoy the tomato sauce much - I thought it wasn't the classic style of the margarita flavor. I enjoyed the one I ordered, though. There's a hint of spiciness, the creaminess of the yolks is great, and the pancetta and the rest of the ingredients went along with the overall flavor. We thought the fried calamari was too greasy, but we really liked the lightly battered style. The intensity of the coffee was excellent, and even though we ordered Americano, we asked the server to make it with less water so that we could still taste the intensity and boldness of the coffee.

When it came to our dessert, this was the longest one we had to wait for, perhaps around 10 minutes. Even though it wasn't that busy, the server told us they were pretty packed, which caused the delay. Despite that, we enjoyed the creaminess and smooth texture of the crema, melting smoothly in our mouth - just that it was not warm anymore when it was served to us.

Overall, we’re pleased with the professionalism of the staff and the taste of their dishes, coffee, and dessert. We're happy to visit again and try other things on their menu.

Cute restaurant,  nice and pleasant atmosphere.
The food was good
The pizza was mediocre
The gnocchi was insanely delicious and also the Alfredo.
Cute dessert, good coffee.
The service was nice and friendly.
Prices are a bit high
Service is pretty quick and friendly. They have Indo Chinese vegetarian options and Indian curries. Food was oily and lacked flavor.

Delicious food and excellent service. Location is great too - plenty parking. I have taken quite a few friends here, and it is always a hit. Authentic food with honest ingredients that is truly enjoyed and appreciated by guests of various backgrounds, cultures and ethnicities. This is always a great sign of quality AND hospitality to me. Also many repeat customers, and the staff remembers you!

name: Shepherd & Sims
cuisine: Night Club, Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
There are many positive reviews so I don’t know if we ate here on an off night or what.

I do like the restaurant atmosphere. It has quite nice decor, a cool blend of hip with a touch of modern rustic class.

But service was slow and we felt unattended all evening. From ordering to food to water to the bill. When the waitress WAS with us, she was quite nice and attentive though. But still, wasn’t expecting an hour and a half dinner on a Monday.

Food was hit or miss. Oysters, risotto scallops, and octopus were good. Chicken liver mousse was an odd combination of flavors IMO. The sweetness overpowered the savory pate characteristic. The burger was average at best. I’ve had the same at my favorite restaurant (Forthright, now closed) which used to be a sister place to here. Seemed better there. And the seafood bucatini noodles were really undercooked. Not even al dente but kind of doughy. I dunno, I was expecting so much more for the price and since they are related to Forthright.

We thoroughly enjoyed every dish we ordered!
Started with Oysters & a shot, followed  by Scallops Risotto, Mussle Curry, Pistachio Dessert. Our Server was especially kind answering all our questions. We found out the owner / chef was cooking that night and clearly puts a lot of love and care into his ingredients.

We had dinner here on a Saturday at 7 and it was packed! We got seated quickly (reservations) and the staff were great throughout our whole meal. We tried the dragon balls (special of the night), octopus, beef skewers, pan con tomate and the torrija for dessert. The food was good but didn’t blow us away. We were happy with everything we ordered.

Beautiful restaurant with solid service and good food. The tapas are great, and the number of choices large but not overwhelming. Good drink selection as well. Like many tapas places and like most things Los Gatos, the prices are elevated, but still a great spot for a date and special occasion. Note: the menu is from Aug 2024

Came here for a mid-week lunch and was surprised to see it so empty. We were greeted kindly and were given the option for indoor or outdoor seating. The weather was favorable so we opted for outdoor in the semi-covered patio. Things we liked about the food & drink: lovely amuse-bouche lentil soup, varied wine list and choices by the glass, moist-cooked grilled meats, lovely sauces and dips. The one improvement would be for the dessert. (Lots of honey but not a strong pistachio flavor) Service was truly acting as host of a home, educating us on the owners, their intention and vibe. I can just picture this being a great dinner hangout.  I would like to return for dinner.

Saturday evening nightcap with my 4 legged companion in downtown Los Gatos.  We sat outside in their heated patio and enjoyed the evening with complimentary wifi. Thank You for wifi password Dar Restaurant and Thank YOU! to their bartender that night for the perfect espresso martini.  We started with lamb riblets and finished with chocolate mousse.  Restaurant was quit busy when we arrived and continued to stay busy as we left.

name: Oak & Rye
cuisine: Bar, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment:
We stopped past here while visiting Los Gatos. The menu is very creative with plenty to choose from. We had a couple of non-alcoholic beers, which is nice to see amongst the other drinks.

The staff were attentive and we had a table outside overlooking the street. In a strange coincidence, we commented on how similar the menu, pizza choices and actual pizza was similar to State of Mind in Los Altos. Turns out the owners know one another.

Thoroughly enjoyed our lunch and look forward to returning. 🍕🍻🥗

This is gonna be the best pizza establishment in the entire Bay Area Peninsula. They offer absolutely delicious, woodfired pizza, amazing cocktails, and a great experience all around. The highlight here is definitely the pizza and the location is in downtown Los Gatos. There is some beautiful outdoor and indoor seating as well.

The pizza was absolutely amazing. We ended up getting a barbecue chicken pizza which had a sauce that was made out of a mustard and barbecue base. It was incredible. We chopped it off with the draft beer, and I got an oak and rye cocktail, which was absolutely to die for.

The prices here are fair and the service is fast. From the moment we sat down we were served in about three minutes and our food came out in about 15. We had enough time to drink, relax, and wait for the amazing food.

The service was friendly, we were able to find seats very easily, and it was just an overall good experience.

I’m I’m adding this to my list of the best pizza in the Bay Area by far

name: Centonove
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: We have been here a few times.  Fantastic food and great service too. We have tried their bruschetta, pesto pizza, pizza pera, fungi pizza so far. All have been excellent. They have great quality burrata and bread.

This is officially my new favorite restaurant! The food is fantastic, and they can accommodate food allergies, and gluten intolerance very well. The gluten-free bread and pizza is so delicious. The service is excellent and the staff is friendly and welcoming. I love sitting outside on their little patio. I brought my husband the second time I went back and he also was very happy. This is our new go to place when we want to go out to a local dinner spot.

name: Loma Brewing Company
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Loma Brewing Company in Los Gatos is a must-visit! Their craft beers are exceptional, with standouts like the refreshing Youks Kölsch and the flavorful Hazy IPA. The food menu complements the brews perfectly; the dishes are delicious and thoughtfully prepared. The atmosphere is lively and welcoming, making it a great spot to relax with friends or family. The staff is friendly and knowledgeable, enhancing the overall experience. Whether you’re a beer enthusiast or just looking for a great place to dine, Loma Brewing Company delivers on all fronts! ￼

Loma Brewing is a great spot for late-night beer cravings—we went around 9 PM and loved the vibe. The IPAs were the highlight, with excellent flavor, and the Oktoberfest Lager was also really good! However, we weren’t fans of the Cougar Juice, as it lacked taste. While the drinks were great, the food is definitely pricey—$15 for a pretzel feels like a whole meal price. Overall, a nice place for good beer and vibes, but be prepared for higher food costs.

name: Wine Cellar Restaurant
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: At this restaurant, you'll find a mix of familiar American and Italian dishes. It's the kind of place that sticks to the basics—think fries, Caesar salad, a nicely cooked steak, and grilled fish. The food is reliably good, though it doesn't offer much in the way of surprises or culinary innovation. If you're after a meal that's comforting and straightforward, this spot will do the trick. Just don't expect to be wowed by any bold flavors or unique dishes. In short, it's a decent option for a simple, no-frills dining experience.

Came in for lunch. Ordered a fondue starter and a wine. Took about 35 minutes for both to arrive at the same time. Cheese was already mostly cooled by then. There's enough cheese to cover the bread and two apples they provided. There were some vegetables but again, not enough cheese

Restaurant wasn't overly busy but the service was glacial.

It was a little strange at the time that our waiter didn't take main course orders when we were first ordering. Glad he didn't.

One fondue appetizer and a single serving of wine $45 before tip.

Another oddity was the service. There was a male host downstairs that helped us out and was very nice. Upstairs there was a lady who was maybe a host but ignored us until we walked around and found someone to help. That same lady was greeting local/regular customers, seating them and seemed to have an entirely different quality of service for people she knew. These customers were getting food and drinks really quickly.

name: Enoteca La Storia
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: The food at this restaurant is very delicious, but according to their official website, it’s described as American-style Italian cuisine. So, whether it’s authentic Italian food is uncertain. The location is tucked away in an unassuming corner surrounded by outdoor decorations, making it easy to miss if not recommended by someone. Personally, I really enjoyed their Cacio e Pepe (I might have misspelled it). Their appetizer sampler is also highly recommended.

I’ve come here a few times and the food & wine don’t disappoint! The staff is friendly but sometimes slow. There are a lot of regulars here so they tend to be very chatty with them and it’s hard to get their attention. But other than that, this place is great to sit at the bar and enjoy a glass of wine and some meats and cheeses.

We found this place while searching for our weekend meal. This place is far from us in beautiful Los Gatos but we had to try it. We travel for good food. There is plenty of parking in the back. The inside interior is beautiful and great for a date.

I love their Iced Coconut Vietnamese coffee! It has fresh shredded coconut on top. I wish it was a bigger size for the price though. We also tried their Banh Xeo tacos. It's pretty good size for one person each.  It comes with good sauce.  We had their Loco Moco which was good. We also liked their Pho Poutine which was beef with  curly steak like fries. We had a dessert to complete our meal. The Coconut Pandan Pann Cotta was excellent and smooth. Not too sweet either.

Service was great as well as the food. I would definitely come back to try their additional dishes especially their Ube Pancakes. I would recommend this place to try if you're in the area.

This had been on our list for a while, then we moved away. We found an opportunity to visit for breakfast bright and early, 8AM on a Sunday. We were the first party there. By the time 9AM rolled around, there were only two other parties.

The decor is very nice and classy. We ordered the pho poutine, the resting brunch face (chicken and waffles) and the pork belly fried rice. The poutine was such a large serving for it to be a starter! We ended up eating so much poutine we barely touched our mains. The chicken for the chicken and waffles were saltier than I would like, but the pandan waffle was nice. We were disappointed the orange juice wasn’t fresh squeezed.

Not sure we would make a dedicated trip out here, but definitely worth a stop if driving by!

My go to Mexican restaurant! The chicken fajitas, chips and guacamole are my fave! The guacamole is so fresh and delicious. The bartenders make a mean margarita and they have good tequila and beer selections.
The manager and the servers are friendly and knowledgeable.
I celebrated my birthday there this year and it was incredible!
Highly recommend!

We had a pleasant experience at this restaurant, and the food was quite good. The highlight for me was the medical salad. It featured very crispy iceberg lettuce topped with grilled chicken, blue cheese dressing, cucumber slices, and boiled eggs. The presentation was also quite inviting, adding to the overall appeal of the dish.

The kids had a great time with their meals too. They enjoyed both the chicken and steak tacos, which were tasty and well-prepared. The guacamole was made to order and tasted very fresh, which we all appreciated.

In summary, it’s a nice spot for Mexican food near downtown Los Gatos. While it didn't blow us away, it was still a good experience, and we’ll likely visit again.

This may have been the best meal I've ever had. I know the crescent cake with vanilla ice cream was the best thing I have ever eaten ever in my life.

Update: while Manresa has closed, the staff of Ritual at Manresa keep the dream alive. Every month a new chef brings their creativity and excellence to share their specialty with those lucky enough to reserve. We've attended two of the recent meals and were amazed by both, but I was completely blown away by tonight's trout and wine pairing. Absolutely sublime pairing.

If you get a chance and want to really treat yourself or that special someone, reserve a meal here. You won't be disappointed .

The dinner I bought tickets to was advertised as an Alex Atala dinner. A Michelin 2-star chef. I believed, like other dinners of this caliber I might take a photo with the chef, give him a gift, and possibly have him sign something. I paid $1,000 per person.
I was very upset to learn that Chef Alex was in Brazil. He is/was not present at the restaurant for his whole last week at Ritual. It’s like buying Taylor Swift concert tickets and her understudy’s understudy performs. It’s not the same, it’s false advertising. His sous chef was the one who was responsible for our meal.
I even asked to switch to a meal he was cooking, and was turned down.

My family and I had a delightful dining experience at Kamakura Japanese Restaurant in Los Gatos, and we were particularly impressed with the cleanliness of the establishment. The dining area was spotless, with tables and chairs meticulously arranged and free of any debris. The floors were well-maintained, and the overall ambiance was inviting and comfortable. The restrooms were also exceptionally clean, which added to our positive experience.

The staff at Kamakura took great care in ensuring that all surfaces were regularly sanitized, and we noticed them frequently cleaning high-touch areas. This attention to detail made us feel safe and well-cared for during our visit. The presentation of the food was also impeccable, with each dish served on clean and attractive tableware. The overall cleanliness of the restaurant contributed significantly to our enjoyment of the meal.

In addition to the cleanliness, the quality of the food and the friendly service made our visit to Kamakura a memorable one. We highly recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a clean and welcoming dining environment with delicious Japanese cuisine.

Best sushi we’ve had in years. Fresh, generous slices, delicious, beautiful presentation. And rolls made with real crab. (No overbearing sauces.) These lovely people deserve to feel proud of this quiet restaurant. Friendly comfortable casual outdoor seating. We were there on a weekday. The waiter brought a bowl of water for the nice dog sitting at the next table. Thank you!

If you’ve been searching for genuine authentic Italian food, look no further than Gardinos. I believe this place is overlooked due to the bar, but the restaurant portion of the establishment is truly phenomenal. Come here if you’re looking to be fulfilled and satisfied with your meal, there has not been one time so far that I have had a bad experience with the food or attentive people that work here. I truly appreciate the environment that makes up the inside of the place, lots of awesome memorabilia of Italian portrayal. I typically go in the morning generally around when they open for business, it’s laid back and relaxing to enjoy such a delicious meal. The owner Pete is always so kind and makes sure we’re satisfied with what we have received. Jeff the waiter is also attentive, kind, and super responsive. This place is truly a hole in the wall amongst the many restaurants along the strip, make sure to come here!
Sunday early evening exelent place to spend on your boring Sunday afternoon, not only great service, the food is so fresh and autentic the atmosphere is great!!!! Totally recommended

name: Andale Mexican Kitchen and Bar Patio

reviews.comment:
I always enjoy eating here, usually with my dog outside.  The chili relleno is great.  My mole chicken enchiladas were tasty and the sangria is a fav.
Since we ate inside without the dog recently I got to admire some of the details in the mural along the wall.  I liked the lamp integrated into the mural.
Not in my photo, but look for Wile E Coyote somewhere nearby.

World's BEST Salad:  Mesquite Chicken Salad at Andale.  Crisp selection of lettuces with a wonderful, light dressing.  Generous warm slices of delicious grilled chicken atop.  Chunks of avocado, creamy feta cheese, tomatoes round out the ingredients.  My wife and I drive 30 minutes each way weekly to enjoy a lunch or dinner salad.  You can also try their scrumptious grilled chicken torta (sandwich) on a perfect roll and a side of the aforementioned salad.  Their chips and homemade salsas are outstanding.  Wonderful fresh fruit drinks and made-to-order churros rounds out what is always a great meal!  The Andale mother ship is based in Los Gatos, but you can also find outlets at both the SF and Oakland airports.

I bought my friends out for their first time trying Thai food and even as a Thai person myself it’s my first time to Coup de Thai and I’m so glad we made a good choice! The food was great, Nam, our server was incredibly friendly and had great suggestions. The restaurant itself had a nice atmosphere, not too loud or over stimulating, clean and well decorated. Definitely recommend!

Amazing food and environment. Made it in there for happy hour. Enjoyed happy hour menu items. Tom Kha soup was super tasty with layers of flavor. The chicken satay served on a qtr pineapple that was pre sliced to eat after. Joseph was an amazing server and host. Super attentive and great conversation. Will definitely be returning. Can't wait to try the rest of the menu.

Stumbled upon this place on Google maps and happy we did! My wife has celiacs so going out to eat just isn’t in the cards until we found this place! It’s a small space and we didn’t have a reservation but luckily they were able to seat us at the bar. The food was all amazing and the owner and waitress were a delight to talk to. We will 1000% be coming back for our next date night.

Delicious gluten free Italian food (delicious even if you’re not gluten free). We had the lemon ricotta pancakes and the arancini di riso (fried risotto balls) and both were great. Service was friendly and food came out quickly.

The food was solid and full of flavor, and the cocktails were crafted with care — balanced, bold, and on point. Service was attentive without being overbearing. The interior decor? Stunning. Thoughtfully designed with a clear attention to ambiance.

That said, we were seated outside despite having a reservation. The outdoor area lacked the same charm and atmosphere as the inside, making the experience feel like a noticeable downgrade. It’s a place worth visiting, but make sure your table matches the vibe you came for.

went on a Thursday evening. we were surprised by how quiet it was. The food is great. if you are looking for a bunch of delish small plates this is the place for you. Loved the chicken egg roll, which tastes surprisingly light and clean as egg rolls. My partner got a great Hendrick Martini and I asked for a Roku Gin Sour, which is not on the menu, and the bartender crafted both of them perfectly. Brandon, our waiter, was very pleasant and attentive. we had a lovely time and will return.

name: Épernay Bistro | Los Gatos
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
I recently had the pleasure of dining at this charming French bistro and champagne bar, and it was an absolute delight from start to finish. The cozy atmosphere is perfect for an intimate dinner or a fun evening with friends, and the adorable little patio area adds to its appeal. The food is outstanding—each dish beautifully crafted with fresh, high-quality ingredients—and paired perfectly with an impressive selection of champagne and wine. The service is beyond friendly, making you feel right at home.

Since taking over two years ago, the new owners, D’Avonny and Adam, have truly transformed this place into a gem. Their attention to detail and warm hospitality shines through in every aspect. Whether you're looking for a lovely night out or a venue for a future event, this bistro is an excellent choice. Highly recommend!

The best restaurant I've been to in years, and the service was so excellent, my friend and I felt as though we'd been invited to a friend's home. Excellent French onion soup, amazing beignets w salted caramel sauce. Truly, a memorable experience!

What an amazing restaurant! The food is absolutely fantastic! Every dish we had was packed with flavor and cooked to perfection. It seems like they change their menu often — I don’t remember the exact names of what we ordered, and I totally forgot to snap a photo of the menu… haha! The staff was super friendly, and everything was served quickly and right on time.

I’m definitely coming back! Highly recommend! 🎉🍴

One of the more memorable restaurants we've been to lately. Josh seemed genuinely happy to take care of us. Our outdoor table was comfortably heated on a cold rainy evening.

Started with a couple of cocktails and an appetizer. Anchovies with buttered crostini was something new and loved it. Barraco's pappardelle with mushroom ragu was very good. Olive breadcrumbs added a nice texture to the dish. Now the salmon, which I'm very particular about, was the best salmon I'd ever had (even better than mine). The skin was crispy and seasoned perfectly. The meat was medium-rare and just melted in my mouth. The sauce brought all the flavors together. We were also happy with the Pavlova, of which I'm also particular. The pastry chef came to our table to discuss the details of his creation.

Can't wait to go back for more.

Pros: beautiful and clean atmosphere, good variety of food options, food was yummy
Cons: our server was optimizing for a greater tip: offering (you read pushing) for more orders and more expensive items, at the time of getting the check he agreed to give us separate checks but we ended up getting one check because he didn’t want to lose the extra tip for 6+ people in the group! We suggested to pay the same amount of tip he didn’t do that. Even for paying with multiple cards we had to discuss a lot!
The signs and guides on the menu were not very correct: biryani was not marked as spicy while it was very spicy.

Called ahead to check if they had outdoor seating for our dog, and they did! Also had big heaters which helped us stay warm on a cooler than expected night. Service was great! The food was beautifully laid out in tasteful serve ware, and tasted great. They brought out papad and dips to start, and then we got the chili paneer appetizer which was delicious. For our mains we got mango chicken, chicken tikka masala and rice. We tried the Asiago pesto naan just for fun since it’s pretty unusual to see that on a menu, and it was good although I enjoyed my lachha paratha a lot more. For dessert I tried the Himalayan khuwa, which I’ve only eaten a handful of times before and it was good. We had a lovely evening.

name: Double D's Sports Grille
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: So good! Tons of TV’s, a great bar and really good food. A perfect place to watch some college football. It was awesome that they asked what games we wanted to watch before we were even seated. Really loved the Double D BLT & E - plenty of bacon and great taste. We will definitely come back.

Tired of restaurants adding deceptive 4% "living wage" fees. Stop complicating our lives and simply adjust your menu prices to properly pay your staff.
I had chicken with rice and vegetables and the rice had uncooked kernels in it. 20% tip was automatically added so with tax and fees my $12 beer became a $16 beer. I had their featherweight entre (a piece of chicken, a little bit of rice, and a little mixed vegetables) and one beer and my bill was $47. I left still hungry.

name: Out of the Barrel
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
This is such an amazing beer experience, that I would definitely recommend this as one of the best places to grab beer if you have some time on a weekend. This is more like a taproom, and they have beer from a variety of different local breweries. You can even buy beer to go. Hi Lou recommended especially if you’re going to be doing Los Gatos for a day, we started here and ended up walking up the street to try different places.

There’s not a lot of seating, but there’s enough to accommodate most people. There’s indoor and outdoor seating. We ended up sitting outdoor and this was pretty cool because we could see all the traffic going into Los Gatos and got to people watch while drinking beer. It was a kinda nice experience.

The service was extremely friendly and super knowledgeable about all the different beer that they had to offer. There’s something for everyone here. They have ciders, IPAs, loggers, and other offerings.

Highly recommend recommended. We just came here for a beer, but I could easily see me returning and grabbing a few more.
No food here, but great selection of craft beer on rotating taps. And don’t be fooled by the Untappd menu. There are multiple fridges that are not listed! Go here!

This was the first time that we've eaten here in a few years. We didn't have reservations, so we sat at the bar. The bartenders were excellent and extremely nice. Zach, who we knew in the past, remembered us and Mark  V., there was one more, but unfortunately, I don't remember his name.
We started with the Portobello Mushroom & Garlic Tart that was delicious, followed by French Onion Soup that was very good. For our entree's, we had the Australian Lobster Tail so delicious and Steak & Australian Lobster Tail. The steak was very good. I don't recall the name of the dessert.

The food was wonderful and excellently prepared. We were there for a birthday celebration and they even had special versions of the menu for our event. For the quality of the food, the prices were very reasonable. The dining room is quite noisy, however.
Loved the basil pasta. The apple and Gorgonzola pizza sandwich was new and tasted good. Loved the mole cola

This place was amazing. It was so clean and well maintained .. it appeared as if it was brand new. However they have been open for a while now.

The staff was great and we got seated during lunch right away. We ordered the garlic cheese, the salad was amazing and the pasta was super fresh. Cute little place in the area and I am happy to come here again anytime with friends and family.

The place recently opened. The interior is warm, cozy, and classy all at once. You’ll find a rich variety of Mediterranean dishes on the menu. We started with the Brussels sprouts, followed by the Firenze salad, which included strawberries, dates, and arugula leaves. For our entrée, we had the Icnik (lamb shank), which was incredibly tender and delicious, served with a side of barley that had a pleasant, whey-like sourness. The cherry on top of our dinner was the Ekmek Kadayifi with ice cream—a true masterpiece. The cream inside the toasted bread was rich, buttery, and perfectly sweetened. Our server, Karina, was very polite and friendly, and we trusted her food suggestions completely.

Great food, great decor and ambiance. However, the owner needs to recognize that he is playing his music WAY TOO LOUD!. When your place is small, and you play your music too loud, then all your diners are going to have to raise their voices and suddenly it's so loud that the experience can be unpleasant. Secondly, I would have asked to be seated outside for a more pleasant experience as the place had many tables available, however, they only had one space heater for the entire outdoor seating. That didn't make sense to me because they were packed/full inside, and more tables could have been booked for a cozy experience outside. Invest in space heaters, you will fill the tables.

name: Willow Street Wood-Fired Pizza
cuisine: Store, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
What a fantastic place! My team and I came here to celebrate, and we couldn’t have been happier with the food and service. We sat outside, and the atmosphere was absolutely lovely—perfect for a relaxed and enjoyable evening.

Our server was quick, attentive, and super friendly, making the experience even better. We started with two appetizers, followed by three incredible pizzas: Margherita, Vegetable Pesto, and Mediterranean. Each one was absolutely delicious, with fresh ingredients and amazing flavors!

This place is a true gem, and I can’t recommend it enough. We’ll definitely be back! 🍕

We often go to Willow Street Pizza. They have a great pizza oven, and the kids enjoy the kids' menu. Their favorite is the salmon and noodles. I really like the Thai pizza. The service is always friendly, and it’s best to reserve a table on weekends.

Finally the first Korean restaurant in downtown Los Gatos opened!! The first impression of the restaurant was modern and clean, the food was so delicious and the presentation was beautiful. I loved their traditional but modern gold dishes and gold lightings. The servers were very friendly and I can't wait to go back to try other dishes.

Danbi is a delightful new addition to the downtown neighborhood that just did a "soft launch" less than a week ago. They don't have signage or interior design completed yet, but they DO have delicious, authentic Korean fare under the careful eye of owner/operator and deliberate chef, Sunny. She claimed it was "just simple fare", but we very much appreciated the thought and careful consideration of all her choices.

We tried the seafood pancake and basic fried chicken with a pot of jasmine green tea and were pleasantly surprised by the variety of flavors and textures. The pancake was out of this world - thick and hearty in the middle, loaded with seafood and absolute crunchy perfection on the outside. The chicken was also so sharply crispy all over and super moist in the middle. You might think two fried dishes would leave us feeling heavy, but the ultra fresh fermented or barely-blanched veggie banchan left us with such cleansed palates that we felt great even after eating all the generous portions. The dressings and sauces were spiced and salted *just right*, so it didn't leave us feeling like we had overeaten or had a post-salt thirst. The spices never overpowered the flavor of the ingredients, allowing us to really experience the freshness of everything in each dish.

Small details also made a big difference - the fried foods and cold dishes are served in hollow, insulated stainless steel plates, so the crispy fried foods remained piping hot even seated next to an open door on this blustery, stormy day. It wasn't a race against time to get to all the hot food first because it just ...stayed hot and crispy... which wouldn't be the case if it were served in standard stoneware. What a delight. Clearly this is just second nature to her and she takes her own fine taste for granted.

We can't wait for other neighbors to try out this new spot and get to know more of the beautiful creations on her menu, especially as the weather warms up and she's able to open the patio soon.

Thank you Sunny for sharing your own bright spot in the heart of town!

There are monitors in the front, you enter your order, pay and then take a seat for dine-in or wait for takeout.

I had the SOB (Sweet Onion Burger),  adding lettuce and tomato. ICooked just right with their semi-sweet SOB sauce as a side.

We also ordered the grilled cheese  - tasty triple cheese, layered  and toasted just right.

Fries were good.

Our order came fast (10 minutes) and was brought to our table.
Atmosphere is clean and comfortable.

Honestly my order was pretty straightforward. I did take out not dine in. The app was really easy to use. Once I chose my food, it took me maybe two minutes to pay and have the order go through. Even though it said it would be 15 to 30 minutes, it only took what felt like 5 to 7 minutes to be ready. Since I was taking out, I didn't have a lengthy exchange with any staff, but the young man who did greet me seemed friendly and happy. Furthermore, the chicken tenders were some of the best I've had. The meat maybe wasn't super seasoned, but it tasted like good quality chicken, and most of all the breading had a really nice texture. It was super crispy but not dry. I love that it was more similar to a fish and chips batter. Everything tasted fresh and I would happily eat there again :-)

I was pleasantly surprised with Tsing Tao. They started me off with hot tea and a plate of kimchi. The kimchi was done of the best I've ever had and figured it had to be homemade due to texture and freshness of the cabbage. I asked a server, and she confirmed it was homemade. The soup was very good.  But I was very impressed with the beef and broccoli.  The broccoli was cooked perfectly al dente and hot as it should be ! The beef was tender and flavorful.  The chow mein was very good and flavorful for just being a vegetable chow mein. Everything was very good,  if you live in this area make sure you come eat here !! I love in Gilroy, so it's a ways for me to drive.

This place serves great portions for a decent price. The shrimp fried rice is particularly good. The chili prawn is a little too sweet, and can be mistaken for a dessert. The hot and sour soup is a harmonious blend of spicy and tangy flavors. They also offer free jasmine tea with meals. The place is well lit, and service is great.

name: Zona Rosa
cuisine: Bar, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Great location, pretty good food. Very pleasant outdoor seating. Took a while to be seated but we were able to get a table Saturday night without reservations, so major plus!

We tried the guacamole. The chips were pretty oily,  the guacamole was good, but not very tasty and a bit too mushy. The tortilla soup was very hearty and flavorful. Prefect for a meal. The enchilada was tasty and a good portion.

Founding and Establishment: Zona Rosa was established in 2012 by owner Alvaro Alvarez. He expanded the business to Los Gatos in 2023. His goal was to offer a modern take on Mexican cuisine, emphasizing fresh, handmade dishes and innovative flavors while staying rooted in traditional tastes. Operating as a scratch kitchen, Zona Rosa prides itself on crafting every dish by hand, from salsas to tortillas. The menu includes vegan, vegetarian, and gluten-free options alongside classic dishes. Signature items include highly regarded tacos, such as blackened salmon tacos and tostadas atun ahi (ahi tuna), and handcrafted cocktails like hibiscus margaritas.

Very good tapas place! Everything we had was great. Recommend the fig bacons, the shrimp, the cheese plate. Pretty much everything was great except maybe the octopus which was just OK. Since these are small plates, I suggest you also get the lamb chops - served with their wonderfully crispy fries! They only have one dessert (I think) but it too was great. Service was wonderful - the waitress took the time to explain every single thing on the menu, and service was prompt and attentive. Highly recommend.

PintxPote is one of the best hidden gems that you can find in a town like Los Gatos. They are friendly. They love the food that they make, which you can taste in every bite.  Sometimes if you become a regular you can ask one or two weeks in advance to see if chef Hector is willing to make one hit of his amazing paellas. These are not on the menu so you definitely would have to reserve in advance. Otherwise the menu is always absolutely fantastic. Try the pinchos. Try the main dishes such as lamb or beef or octopus. When peppers are on the menu try those as well.

Specials are on the menu when there is something in season or chef Hector is moved to try out a new dish. Come regularly to see what's new.

Personal favorites include the house made potato chips that are served with the meat dishes, huevos con jamon, and Spanish tortillas.

If you enjoy wine, they have quite a nice selection of Spanish wines, including cavas and tempranillos. They are always willing to discuss your princes and see how well they can match your preferred wine.

I don't usually write this kind of review and recommendation because I always want to make sure that whoever comes to what I recommend will have the kind of experience that I describe. In this case, I cannot recommend highly enough. If you love this type of Spanish food, this is the place to go.

Hands down some of the best contemporary Mexican food in the Bay Area if not California. Pedro’s wasn’t exactly a dining destination before they re-opened last year, but the new ownership and Chef has reinvented the place and the food is definitely worth driving out of the way for. You can taste the high-quality ingredients and the care in the cooking and presentation. Can’t wait to go back and try more!

Restaurant has a very nice Mexican decor and vibe. Bar section is separate and rest of the restaurant has plenty of tables. Food was very delicious and flavorful. FYI, the portion are very large so 1 order will be plenty for 2 because they give chips to begin with and that fill your stomach🙂 plenty of parking spaces outside. Staff is very friendly. They do have few veg option in main course.

name: Los Gatos Tavern
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Great atmosphere, kid friendly, and great food

name: The Happy Hound of Los Gatos

reviews.comment: The fries were my favorite, so make sure to get some, I haven’t had fries this good in a while. I got a chicken sandwich, and my boyfriend had the double burger. He literally loved his meal. I liked mine, but it was a bit plain. I would definitely come back, but I’d probably try something different next time

I eat here on a fairly regular basis and I can confirm that the hot dogs are delectable. I particularly enjoy the default dog and the chili cheese dog. I can also confirm that the malts are delicious. The fries are great too. I cannot say anything about the burgers because I haven’t tried them. I like the old style vibes of the interior as well.

name: Los Gatos Soda Works
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: This place is awesome! I've been when they have Christmas theme but didn't know they were doing Halloween. It's their first year doing it and I hope they continue this because it's amazing. The drinks are delicious and really cool. I tried almost everything and it's well worth the price. A super nice accommodating staff as well.

We showed up without reservation and were seated at the lowtop bar.. not the best seat in the house, but we didn't plan, so that's on us.

The drinks are AMAZING!!! Perfect balance, beautiful, delicious!!! Yummmm!

The menu is limited but we enjoyed the couple of things we tried. I'll be back to try more of the drink menu 😋

name: Aldo's Ristorante & Bar
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Drove by and saw this place, looked nice. My husband and I love Italian food and I was thinking this could be a great place for us to enjoy for a future date night. I went inside to check it out and use the restroom since I traveled from almost an hour away. Someone who worked there asked “can I help you? I said yes, where is the restroom please? He said it was a private event and I couldn’t use it. No big deal however what really left a bad taste in my mouth was that he looked me up and down before saying no. Seriously? Very judgmental. If he would have left it at this is a private event, I would have had no problems leaving but you had to be rude. Disgusting. Be better. Costs $0 to be kind dude.

We went there for my friend birthday, it was an amazing evening, we took my mom, she makes the best ñoquis aka Gnocchis, so she is not to kin to eat out, but she was amazed on how good they were. We will come back, we order the calamari(ok, miss the tentacles, those are my fav, but they don't serve them anymore), we also got the artichokes , WOW, delish, and the birthday boy order the GOLFO, what an amazing place.
We closed the night with a great teramisu and cappuchino.
We will be back. Specially on the 29th as it is our custom to eat ñoqui aka Gnocchi on every 29th of the month.

name: Andalé Mexican Kitchen To Go Location

reviews.comment: Located in downtown Los Gatos, this is a nice Mexican restaurant. Service was good. We had a pitcher of the Cadillac Margarita which comes with a nacho plate (not on the main menu). This was enough appetizer for 5 and there were options for veg and non veg. It was very good. Cheesy. For dinner we had the chipotle burrito, mole enchilada, tacos and chili verde plate. Burrito was ok with not much flavor. However the rest of the food was good. Service was prompt. The back patio is quieter with heat lamps.

Andale in Los Gatos is a clear winner. I had never made arrangements for a group of 30 before, and the manager, Carlos, helped curate a special, economical dinner which felt quite grand and elegant. I was excited to tell people where we celebrating.

We walked in to the patio to find a lovely, green space. The table was set with specially printed menus and people were able to pick their starter and main course and enjoy aqua fresca and/or iced tea/lemonade and dessert. I was expecting buffet trays but everyone got beautifully plated dishes, which made the dinner more formal. People LOVED the food. I got the salmon and it was incredibly flavorful and a great portion size - I need to return for more salmon.

The amazing food, drinks, set-up, service,  and the lovely patio space made the evening feel perfect and elegant. This is a great place to make fond memories for important occasions.

name: Southern Kitchen Los Gatos
cuisine: Cafe, Store, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Sunday breakfast dine-in :(~ 7 am)

- Walk-in, got seated immediately(went before their busy time), such a lovely vibe inside and out. The place was reasonably priced.

Pro-tip: Walk across the street, to stroll on Los Gatos creek trail next to water stream after breakfast, stay healthy.

- Ordered Banana Nutella (Churro) Waffle, replaced the Churro waffle with a regular one

- The waffle was perfect, not soggy, the bananas were fresh and they didn’t overdo the Nutella. Comes with a hot syrup on the side, great combo, makes the waffle less dry and tasty. I needed an extra of syrup, provided at not extra cost.

- They don’t have freshly squeezed regular fruit juice which was a bummer. They have ‘Juiced’ combo vegetable and fruit juices if you’re interested.

Breakfast at this spot was absolutely fantastic! The food arrived in no time and was delicious, and the friendly staff made us feel right at home. I couldn't have asked for a more welcoming atmosphere to start the day!

As a fan of diners and the 80s vibe, this place made me happy.

I enjoyed the breakfast and coffee. Got myself an eggs benedict and with bacon, link sausages, biscuits and gravy. It was loaded with cheese - best way to start your sunday!

The waiters were kind too. I recommend this place for brunch or breakfast.

We were very excited to go eat at this diner but it was raining and we couldn’t dine in with our dog since the outdoor area was closed. Instead we got take out - I got the Kentucky hash and house omelet. The hash came with eggs made how you like them, grilled spinach and tomatoes, and biscuit & gravy. The gravy and biscuits were delicious, and the food was flavorful we really enjoyed it.

Wow. The food is delicious. We ate here before dinner service began so the menu had small cafe size dishes that we shared and got filled up on. The prices were so reasonable. We did wait for dinner to order dinner plates to again share. The staff is so friendly and accommodating. Bathrooms are a must to try out. Very clean, stylish and warm. The covered patio seating was comfortable  and a bit cozy but it was good for our large noisy group.

Quick service and large portions. The food was good but not great.

- The cinnamon roll is fun.
- Our soufflé eggs weren’t very flavorful.
- The potatoes were the real standout for food! Potatoes get 5 stars.

I went on Thursday evening to celebrate my friend's birthday. They had live Jazz music performances that created a relaxing atmosphere that went so well with their beautiful and delicious dishes. The server was very nice and friendly. I highly recommend this place and will definitely be back soon!

Loved the brunch on rainy Saturday. It was cozy inside, bread and butter was yummy  and food came out quickly.

We had French onion soup, crepe benedict and croque monsieur. We loved all of them!

They serve great burgers! If you're ordering halal, just double-check that they leave out the bacon and any other non-halal ingredients. Fortunately, the cook asked me about the bacon, so it was taken care of.

There are not many burger places that offer gluten free buns and halal burgers!
Main Street offers a variety of burger options that can accommodate different dietary restrictions and they are one of our go tos for halal burgers.
The location is nicely situated in downtown Los Gatos and whenever there are city events, you can get a good view sitting in their outdoor seating area.

I like their salmon salad also when I’m not feeling up to a burger and they have really nice milkshakes. Their garlic fries are a must and last we went, they fry it in a separate fryer.

We used to frequent the Willow Glen location until they closed down. Loved the lobster rolls they had there.

name: The Garret Station
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Great food! Great background music & TV shows. Friendly and attentive staff members.

So we ordered garlic fries, a pizza, a fish sandwhich, and some chilli. I really dont recommend the garlic fries honestly... Probably some of the worst fries I've had. They were very stale and also they were so overly greasy and just...wet, from the garlic paste that kind of looks like it was just lazely splatted in the middle. The garlic paste was way too strong, or like garlicky but not in a good way, tasted like minced garlic straight from the jar that you'd get at the grocery store or something, lol. The fish burger also was alright. It was a little bland and just didn't really have anything too special about it, but it was still good. The two things I think were really good though were the chili and especially the pizza. The chili wasnt too spicy or anything and i think had a really good savory meaty flavor and it was nice. The pizza was also super yummy, probably some of the best pizza Ive had actually, the crust was a little crispy yet still soft and moist in some places, and the cheese was really stretchy and melty! I feel there was a nice balance between the tomato sauce and the cheese, and it was just all around really good. This place can definitely get a little bit loud, it was kind of hard to hear what the people on the other side of our table were saying. They do have a fun little arcade area with claw machines and other stuff that could be fun for the kids. Food didn't take too long to come out either. So yah If you come here, they do have good pizza, but Id probably just STICK to the pizza, lol.

name: Los Gatos Cafe
cuisine: Cafe, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: One of the best brunch in the area. Portions are big and there are plenty of options. The eggs Benedict with blue cheese is my go to, but the omelets and herb potatoes are good too. Usually have new items every week.
Stopped in for breakfast on our way to San Francisco and had a wonderful experience! Our server Laura was absolutely amazing and the food was delicious. 10/10 experience, would definitely come back.

Sashimi lunch was super fresh, properly cut into same-sized pieces not too small, only minus was it didn't come with shiso leaf/leaves. Service was good. Depicted is sashimi lunch special,  which also had rice on the side, March 2025 price about $27.
Placed a to go order and loved it. The owners here were so sweet. I came here with my 5 year old and they gave her a small treat. So nice! The sushi tasted very fresh too.

Good juicy burger with tangy burger sauce. Sundays get busy at lunch with all the kids coming after games and whatnot but a good spot. Service is pretty quick too. Nice benches outside to sit at or inside.

Yum! Oh how I love this Restaurant the the food it serves, so glad to have discovered it when I was in SF one day. Only for it to open more locations in the East Bay Area that were closer for me to visit.

Like in the reviews I've written for other locations, the food here is good, tasty, juicy and they serve grass fed beef, along with a multitude of other organic ingredients! Love it! Makes it that much easier to want to have it.

And like all the other locations, the homemade pickles are deeeelicious! Hmmmmm, mmmmm, mmmm.

For this visit, my cousin was kind and generous enough to treat me to a meal AND drive me too! So considerate of her, and good company too.

This location is a pretty large size, plenty of space and seems to be pretty easy to find a spot to sit down and eat. There is also a foozball table, in case, someone needs to work up their appetite a little more before inhaling their yummy meal! IT's a nice little additive to the rest of the typical restaurant feel.

One little drawback I found was parking seemed to be a little tight not scarce, just tight spaces, but it could have just seemed that way, b/c it was dark and hard to see.

name: The Cats
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: The service was a little slow, but they were crowded, so understandable. We got the pork ribs and they were amazing!!!! Gladly took leftovers home. After dinner we moved to the bar section to listen to the band and get dessert. We enjoyed ourselves.
Just had a great meal while listening to a friend perform. We'll be back, loved the Filipino barbecue.

The price and taste are good overall, but there are a few issues with the food. The tortilla wasn’t fully cooked, and the tamale shell was much too thick. I also tried the chicken taco, and while the flavor was decent, the meat was a bit dry.

Nina’s Taqueria is one of my go-to spots in Los Gatos. It’s nothing fancy, and that’s exactly why I love it. The food is always fresh and flavorful—burritos, tacos, whatever I’m in the mood for, it always delivers. It’s the kind of place where you know what you’re getting, and it’s always solid.

It’s super popular with local families, and you can definitely feel that neighborhood energy—especially right after school when it gets packed with kids and parents grabbing a quick bite. I usually try to go just before the rush.

It’s become a comfort spot for me—reliable, unfussy, and just genuinely good food. Definitely one of those places you miss when you’re out of town.

I visited this place for the first time, and I was absolutely fascinated! The food was incredible—every bite was bursting with flavor. We started with the cauliflower florets as an appetizer, and they were perfectly crispy and seasoned. For the main course, we tried the beef kebab and the pita beef kebab, and both were absolutely delicious!

A special shoutout to our server, Dante, who was not only friendly but also made the whole dining experience even better with his amazing service. He truly went above and beyond!

This place has everything: fantastic food, top-notch service, and a great atmosphere. I’ll definitely be coming back! Highly recommend! 👌🍴✨

We came on a Monday a little before six and there were only a few other customers.  The space is well lit and modern, perhaps a bit too bright.
Service was friendly, but they forgot to bring our water and it took a bit to get the bill.
We got the sampler of dips with pitas and the lamb kebab.  Both were tasty, but not quite my ideal versions of those dishes.

name: 107 Bistro & Wine Bar
cuisine: Bar, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Team dinner here on a Thursday evening. I love the ambiance. It's high in the woody part of Los Gatos and the lights strung around the winery, grounds, and restaurant are beautiful at night. Super picturesque. Even saw a family of deer in the middle of the road.

The table service was also quite attentive and good. Friendly. Clear the silverware between apps and meals. Food came for everyone all at once but it took quite some time after ordering even with hardly anyone else in the place.

The food selection was a little sparse. I was hoping they'd have steak. Since not, I had the pork chop which was quite succulent and tasty with the onions and other garnishing. The burgers and pizza all looked ok but the menu wasn’t special. My vegetarian friend was not able to find anything he liked. Felt sorry for him.

Too full for dessert and anyway, it took so long for the main course we didn't have time for it.

Best quality and tasting food in Mt. Shasta area! The fried calamari starters can also be extra spicy upon request! The carrot ginger soup is amazing! There are always wonderful specials, too! The fish and chips are too quality, the burgers and salads are amazing!! Our favorites are the ahi salad and the Thai chicken salad. All of the desserts are wonderful. Few places does your server hold two Masters in Science! Both regulars and tourists love this place - EVERYONE is welcome!!

Solid Chinese food, some Cantonese classics like HK crispy noodles and potstickers with handmade dough. The onion pancake was different than I had before - more like a stuffed pancake so the scallions weren't visible from the outside. Our friends enjoyed the fried rice, wonton soup, etc. The sizzling black pepper lamb was also delicious and tender. Well prepared food and attentive service, would recommend!

Great place! The service is prompt and cordial. We requested to skip adding bean sprouts, after some minutes of ordering. The server went in and interrupted the cook from adding that.
Food was tasty and tasted good. The decor is nice: there is a giant image that will draw your interest.

Perfect spot for lunch or dinner. They have daily specials and a great menu. They seem to really care about their food quality and creativity in their cuisine offerings. They also have outdoor seating. If sitting outdoors please be mindful of the proximity of the main street flowing through downtown Morgan Hill which could be loud due to motorcycles and loud car engines which could make the dining experience disappointing.

Upscale restaurant, you're going to pay above average prices but you're getting phenomenal food. I got the beef wellington im going to have to say it's one of the best I've had. Nice thin flaky crust, very savory flavor will definitely be back

Was down in Morgan hill on  Sunday . We wanted to get brunch,but needed a dog friendly place. Didn't realize that a huge farmers market is right next door. There's only street parking,so we had to walk a bit. Our fault for not doing better research. We were told it would be a while since we needed outside seating. Only ended up waiting 15 minutes. Once seated it took a while for the waiter to appear. It's seems that the brunch menu is cheaper than the regular menu. We ended up ordering a croissant sandwich and a loco moco. Once it arrived the presentation looked great. Alas the taste didn't match the look. My loco moco was bland. The gravy had no flavor at all . The burger was just as bland. No salt or seasonings. My wife's sandwich was just as disappointing. Stale croissant, not really that great. They do have a great patio. We may try it again just to see if it was a off day.

Good spot to try after hiking Uvas Canyon.
The wait can be long and there isn’t anywhere to sit. If it’s not too cold you can walk around the local vendors market. Service is good, it can get busy though. It’s lively, coffee shop inside with fresh press juice options. Good for groups, families or dates. Good vibes. The food was good. The fried Brussel sprouts were 🔥🔥

Had an amazing experience today at Odeum. Decided to have some Ribeye and Tomahawk and everything was delicious (rich in flavor and amazing textures). The servers were very attentive and quickly responded to our requests as well as Salvatore!

Overall, 5 star experience. No complaints.

We were greeted at the door by Presley. She was very welcoming walked us immediately to a table. I noticed that the ambience of the restaurant perfect. I was going to give a three star review due to the fact of our server Steven but decided to give four instead. I ordered the 8 ounce fillet, which was delicious. My wife ordered the skirt steak which also was delicious. We also ordered the Louisiana butter cake and I have to stay the food. Here was delicious. The only reason why they didn’t get five stars is because our server Steven only showed up to the table to take our order and that was it. When I did inquire about our server, and if he could come to the table, I was told he was busy, but Presley stepped up to the plate and make sure that our table was taken care of and we got everything we needed. We will definitely be coming back.

Azeem’s, Morgan Hill’s newest Indian restaurant, recently opened for takeout, catering, and private parties during their soft opening. They informed me they will offer table service in the coming weeks. Although I’m not an expert on Indian cuisine, I’m a huge fan and thrilled to have another option in town.

For my first visit, I opted for their takeout Chicken Biryani. It was incredibly delicious! The spiced rice was generous, and the three pieces of chicken were perfectly cooked. I’ve only had biryani a few times before, but Azeem’s version was truly a delight.

I’ll definitely be adding Azeem’s to my list of go-to takeout restaurants. I can’t wait to try their in-house dining experience as well.

The dishes were very authentic and extremely flavorful! We had the Vegetable Biryani and Butter Chicken. Wow, what a surprise!
The Biryani was very authentic and one of best I have ever had. Part of the masala has medium sized fruit seeds (pits) that add to the flavor ( you don’t eat that ) which really gives a fullness to the flavor along with the other spices. The Butter Chicken (halal preparation) which I personally pour over the Biryani, was equally amazing with a homemade butter sauce that just opens up your flavor buds with a deep mild spice that was just perfect. We also ordered the appetizer Chicken Samosas with the mint chutney that was likely one of the best Samosas I’ve had in the entire Bay Area. To wash it all down I couldn’t resist the Mango Lassi of course.
Fun, stylish cafe with desserts, appetizers, coffee and drinks. There’s an attached floral design studio and event planning space.

hard to find parking. there is a parking garage near but you need to walk

alfredo is lacking some flavor. their pizza is very good though. staff is nice. bathroom is nice.
The food was amazing! I had raviolis with sausage and bolognese sauce with 2 sausages! My husband had the lasagna. Both were so good, some of the best Italian food we have had.

Very nice atmosphere and great service. Food is good but they charge high for such a small menu selection.

Food is healthy and tasteful. Roasted eggplant sandwich definitely worth a try without breaking the bank.

Good experience but it's not my style. Perfect place for business conversations and casual get-togethers but for fine dining id go nextdoor

Great experience overall, high quality food with great flavors, the red wine came at perfect temperature, the royal mojito was the cherry on top. Will go back to check out the next set of art in the gallery that belongs to the place.

name: Rosy's At The Beach
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: $20 for two of the smallest crab cakes in the world and below average taste. The coleslaw was super sweet and not edible. Fries were unsalted. My mom got a Caesar salad - very average tasting, like one you get in a bag at the grocery store. Service was good, but I will definitely not be returning.

The loaded Clam Chowder bread🍞 bowl was phenomenal🤤, presentation was on point 😁. The level of temperature could use some help 😕.
Mine was a tad under heated and also heard others complain that it was cold. So just ask them to make sure it's piping hot 🔥. I'd rather wait for it to cool down then ask them to reheat it. 😩
Tried the crab🦀 cakes which can be hit or miss.... It was a hit!🎯
I definitely wanted to try the the 🦑calamari but that'll be another time.

The atmosphere was clean and neat!
Looked very fancy🤵‍♂️ and welcoming. I went in the morning 🌅 when they opened and we're the 1st one there with a few friends.
We all ordered the tik Tok sensation that is going viral haha, I found it on IG.

Server was super polite and jokingly friendly which made us relaxed. I will say,  the staff do deal with some very prissy people which you can't do much about other customers but does ruin the vibe🤙. Guess that comes with the territory of a somewhat high scale looking place 🤷‍♂️

I will be back and looking forward to the other items on the menu.

Oh and the mango 🥭 iced tea wasnt super sweet which I loved 😍

Highly recommend if you haven't, it does get busy here so find that time to visit.

Parking 🚗 can be found in the back parking🚘 lot, and there's more parking 🅿️ if it gets full, just have to keep going to the next parking lot if there's nothing available up front or on the side street. Use the back entrance 🚪 if you do park in the back.

name: Noah's Bar & Bistro
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Service was great food was good, pricy for Italian food I did enjoy my visit just wish I'd have the option to tip accordingly. Was a slow night and we were a party of 6

First time here and came with a group. I was able to make a reservation via the website. We went on a Tuesday at 6:30 and we had the place to ourselves. Waitress was very kind and attentive. Everyone got drinks and we shared appetizers. Everyone ordered different entrees including salads, pastas, and burgers. They were all pretty tasty. I wanted the Beets & Goat Cheese Arugula Salad but they unfortunately were out of goat cheese so I got the Southwest instead. It was our friends birthday and they offered her a free dessert and we bought another. Good service and will come back to try something different.

Absolutely incredible bar!
I visited from out of state and heard about it while eating at the restaurant owned by the same people. Glad I stopped in as the drinks were great, the food was amazing, and the atmosphere was to die for!!
A friendly environment great for everything from solo drinking to catching up with friends. My wife and I had a blast. Wish I lived closer so I could come more often.

My girlfriends and I popped in for a drink and light bites here last week. We each got a drink and shared the French dip and chicken baguette. I asked for a mocktail version of one of the drinks and the bartender asked if I was set on that because she had other recs for a mocktail. She ended up making me a drink that was not on the menu which was super fun and I really enjoyed 🤩 My other friends got the Negroni and the Clover Club and liked both of those. The interior was beautifully designed and there was lots of seating to choose from. We enjoyed the round booth seating where we were at. Towards the end of our time there the music got really really loud and it became kind of hard to hear one another so that was when we decided to wrap up. I am so happy Morgan Hill now has a cocktail bar like this now. I can’t wait for my next visit!

name: Craft Roots
cuisine: Bar, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment: Great place for vegans and vegetarians. A lot of delicious food and even larger selection of beers. The service is very nice and they can advise what is best to choose. Everything can be made gluten free which is always great!

Amazing vegan food. I’m a lifelong vegetarian and never had jambalaya like that! The Japanese BBQ cauliflower was perfectly crisped but what made us memorable was the aioli. The Animal Lover pizza tasted original and the crust was perfect. Had the Alameda Cola soda which is how all great drinks should taste. This is now our official Morgan Hill spot!
Great little restaurant in Morgan hill…. Food was great and service as well…. Nice set up lived the table cloths and the place is very nice

We ordered the bruschetta and veg pesto pasta, olive oil pasta and desserts. we got our food quickly and it was absolutely delicious. Very friendly and welcoming staff. Great quantity. Loved their Pasta and dessert . Several options for vegetarians. Wonderful experience.

name: ENCINA
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Lessy is hands down one of the best bartenders I’ve had the pleasure of meeting! From the moment I walked in, she set the tone with her warm personality and effortless charm. She genuinely made the night better with her conversation and attention to detail, even when the bar got busier. Her drinks were spot-on every time, and she never missed a beat—except for her salted lemon drop!

Shoutout to Brandon for handling a tricky situation with the town weirdo—he acted quickly and professionally to keep the chill vibe intact. Overall, the bar’s atmosphere was fantastic, and the service from both Lexi and Brandon made it a top-notch experience.

Updating review. The food is very good. Love the butter chicken waffle fries, but a recent change in their menu has made me decide not to go there again. I don't drink alcohol and have enjoyed a soda at the bar. Soda   was pricey... $5.00, but it was unlimited soda. Been that way since it opened and up to a few weeks ago.  Tonight I went there had their delicious butter chicken waffle fries and ordered a coke zero... later on in the evening I asked for a refill. When I got my bill... my bill came to $38!  The Butter Chicken was $18.... Turns out they charge $6.00 per drink now for soda!! No refills. At that price I've decided to stop going there. One thing to charge for refills, another thing to make a change without notifying customers.  When I asked the waitress why the prices increased so much,  without any notice she said... "Inflation"... Nope.. inflation didn't raise the price of soda up to $6.00/glass. I'd been there several times in the past couple of months. It was a good run. But, I won't return...
The food and the service were great. The staff was very attentive. The restaurant is small and tables are set close yet the seating still felt intimate and not overly noisy. We will be back!

We went to celebrate a birthday, and everything tasted quite good! I personally loved their Bistecca Quattro Formaggio and the Tortellini con Prosciutto. The appetizers were pretty amazing too.

The Calamari Fritti with lemon, sweet basil syrup, and spicy tomato sauce were delicious and well-portioned. The Burrata con Prosciutto, with fresh burrata cheese, prosciutto, sun-dried tomato pesto, and crostini, was a delightful start to the meal.

Of all the pastas we tried, the Fettuccine al Pescatore was just ok compared to the others, so I'd skip this one. However, the Tortellini con Prosciutto, cheese-filled tortellini with mushrooms, prosciutto, spinach, and cream sauce was absolutely fantastic!

The Bistecca Quattro Formaggio was another standout, with a rich, creamy flavor that was simply irresistible.

As soon as we walked in, I knew it was the right choice to celebrate a birthday on a Monday afternoon.

Everyone here was all smiles.
The bartender was outstanding!

My loaded potato was loaded, ha! I enjoyed every bite I took of bacon, cheese, and sour cream. It was delicious.

There were two other people at the bar and we got the party started and sang happy birthday.
I love the happy vibes we got from everyone here.

In addition to our wonderful meal and service, they brought us a special birthday dessert. How awesome are they?!

They sure know how to make a girl feel fabulous on her birthday :)

They also have a live DJ every Thursday, Friday, and Saturday from 6:30-9:30 PM.

Excellent food, drinks, and service at the Willard Hicks location in beautiful downtown Morgan Hill.  The best place to get your espresso martinis.  The bartenders are attentive and the restaurant has a great vibe to unwind after your day.  Their signature burger on menu was amazing and perfectly cooked medium rare.  Thank you team at WH for being great and consistent.

name: Mama Mia's Mediterranean & Italian Cuisine - Morgan Hill

reviews.comment:
We had the eggplant scaloppini and lobster ravioli with minestrone and clam chowder. The chowder was excellent, the eggplant and minestrone were good.

Overall, the ravioli was good as I could see and taste the shrimp, the green onions. The shrimp had the expected texture.

However, the ravioli filling had neither the texture nor the taste of lobster, so I was disappointed.

The outdoor patio's waterfall was working and added to the ambiance of our dining experience. We were looking for a venue for our 50th anniversary and are considering this location. See attached pictures.

Solid food and options.  Had the salmon risotto and Gorgonzola salad with shrimp.  The salad was very large and shrimp juicy.  The salmon was tasty but just slightly overcooked.  Overall good comfort food.   Service was great.  We came 1/2 hour to closing and they were very accommodating.

I’d highly recommend this place if you’re looking for authentic Oaxacan cuisine.

Their menu has different options and aguas frescas.

The shrimp tacos were delicious.
My partner and daughter ate birria tacos and couldn’t get enough.

This place has karaoke and music. Come on the weekends if you want to have a Sunday Funday.

We also got an Aqua de piña- they offer free refills.

They have a Oaxacan sample and other typical Oaxacan dishes.

Awful food experience. We ordered two entrees of chile verde, the first sign that it was not going to taste good was the look of it which resembled cold gravy but green. I tasted a tiny amount and didn't touch the rest of the plate. One small burrito was consumed by my spouse from his entree. This was mentioned to them as we were paying the bill and we proceeded to be charged for both. Within 20 minutes my husband was not feeling well and got sick.

Roman is amazing! He makes everyone feel welcome. He is an expert mixologist and the cocktails he makes are amazing. The food is high-quality and prepared to order. They have daily specials and happy hour specials that are budget friendly. The atmosphere is pleasant and relaxing.The restaurant is clean and in good repair. The brunch is the best in Town. You will not be disappointed come and enjoy this wonderful place.  I love it!

HIGHLY recommend stopping by if you’re in the area - especially for happy hour, but I’m sure everything on the dinner menu will also be well worth the price. Leo and Maria were wonderful!!

I had the Pork Parmesan and New York steak during happy hour and I was blown away by the quality and the portion size! For $14 I expected the happy hour “bites” to be small, so I ordered two - a mistake but also a blessing in disguise since I am now fully convinced that this place is a real gem. The pasta that came with the parm was cooked to perfection, a truly perfect chew which I haven’t experienced in more than a few years. The potato cake that came with the steak was also excellent.

They can prepare almost every pasta as gluten free, as well as their pizza and multiple desserts. My wife who is gluten-free also enjoyed her meal immensely.

What a wonderful restaurant. Service was also excellent and went above and beyond, so friendly and helpful. The whole experience really made my day!

name: Cochi’s Kitchen
cuisine: Bakery, Food, Point Of Interest, Store, Establishment

reviews.comment:
I recently had the pleasure of visiting Cochi Kitchen, and I couldn’t be more impressed. The Godfather I ordered was simply delicious—perfectly balanced flavors, fresh ingredients, with just the right amount of pesto.

The customer service was another highlight of my visit. Gabby the owner was kind, friendly, attentive, and genuinely cared about making my dining experience enjoyable.

Located in the heart of Morgan Hill, this establishment boasts a fantastic ambiance and easy accessibility with plenty of parking. It’s a great spot to enjoy a meal with friends or just relax and have a cup of coffee with some of their amazing homemade pastries.

I highly recommend the delicious food, outstanding customer service, and a great location. I can’t wait to return and try more of their menu!

Thank You!

Great local spot for breakfast and lunch. Love the Guido Sandwich (menu item) and the Tri-Tip Sandwich (special only). Reuben's Uncle, Ezra is also excellent especially if you sub the Swiss cheese for habanero jack. Breakfast burritos and house made salsa are awesome as well. A whole glass case full of delicious scones & pastries to finish off your experience. Shout out to Traci. the weekend counter  lady who is friendly and helpful.

Had a fantastic brunch at Stacks in Morgan Hill this past Saturday. Food was amazingly delicious. I had the crab crepe and my wife had the corned beef hash. Others in our party had pancake stacks. Lots of variety so this is not a typical pancake house. The even have an extensive gluten free menu. Don’t forget to order a tasty mimosa.
It was very crowded when we arrived at 11:20. The wait time was 20 minutes which is acceptable. The noise level was very loud and distracting, so much so that we had difficulty hearing our own conversations. Our server was wonderful and took really good care of our needs. You will love it here!! Oh and you can dine inside or outside!!

A little late, but came to finally check out this place. Place is a little small inside, but it looked nice. The wife and I ordered breakfast. I ordered the triple berry pancakes, since I love pancakes,  and they didn't disappoint. The wife had the bacon avocado omelet which she said was pretty good & came w/hashbrowns. The son went the lunch route and had the basic burger w/cheese and fries. He loved the fries but said he didn't like the burger because it was too juicy....make it make sense son!!! Overall a cool spot to check out.

From the very first visit, the restaurant pleasantly surprised me — they served a delicious miso soup as a complimentary dish from the chef.

Pros:
1.	Extremely fresh fish
2.	Delicious rice
3.	Outstanding sushi
4.	Steamed gyoza — great dough and tasty filling
5.	Very fast order delivery — just 4–5 minutes even with 30% of tables occupied and active delivery orders
6.	Quick check presentation
7.	Clean restroom
8.	Authentic Japanese chefs
9.	Nice background music

Cons:
Found none.

It’s a pity the restaurant is far from where I live — I would love to visit much more often.
Left a good tip.
Wishing you lots of great customers!

FOOD
honestly food isnt that good— it is okay, but there are definitely better places outside of morgan hill. not very authentic and very pricy. i think if you want to try japanese cuisine i recommend traveling to somewhere like ippudo in cupertino or somewhere more authentic— but creasian is an okay option. overall prices are pricy and food is okay.

SERVICE
servers are nice, but failed to provide a set of utensils for my brother (7).
This place never disappoints and you will enjoy the food. We got a dozen oyster and they were delicious!! Clam chowder and fish and chips is very good. Highly recommend this place.

We got a shrimp cocktail, salmon, key lime pie, fish tacos, salad, linguine with mussels and clams. The shrimp cocktail was good, but everything else was bland. It seems like they have good fish and chips. Based on the reviews, I should have gotten that. I definitely will not be returning to find out.
Update: I had given a 3-star based on the flavor, but after eating the linguini with multiple broken shells, I am just super disappointed. This dinner was an order in for a birthday. Please be careful eating this. At least the seafood quantity was good, and after adding oregano, basil, chili flakes, and some other seasonings, the flavor wasn't terrible. Please do better City Fish.

When I got to Chapala I was not sure what to expect. The place looks new and is very clean. Not the hole in the wall spots I am used to: There were some of my favorites like a seafood molcajete, Mojarra frita, and tacos de tripa. So we decided on those items except the Mojarra was a la diabla. As a spicy food lover with most places not at all touching my spice limits the Mojarra was the best I've ever had. The tacos de tripa were very good but with the red sauce on the side there a complexity of flavors I have never tasted for such a simple dish. The seafood molcajete was yet another homerun. The sauces here are one of a kind. They are rich, savory, and spicy. I will be coming back again… and again… and again. Also, this is at 810 Tennant Station not Tennant Ave. Right next to the theater in the Safeway parking lot. Directions on your phone may lead you behind a church.

I recently dined at this new Mexican restaurant, and it was a fantastic experience from start to finish! The atmosphere was warm and inviting, with a vibrant yet cozy ambiance that made for the perfect dining setting.
