The food was absolutely delicious—starting with the fresh, crispy chips and flavorful salsa that had just the right amount of kick. I ordered the molcajete, and it was a showstopper! The sizzling mix of meats, vegetables, and rich, savory sauce was packed with bold flavors and served in a traditional stone bowl that kept everything hot and delicious.

To complement the meal, I had a sangria margarita, and it was the perfect balance of sweet, tangy, and refreshing. The service was attentive and friendly, making the whole experience even more enjoyable.

If you're looking for authentic Mexican flavors with great drinks and a welcoming atmosphere, this spot is definitely worth a visit!

I ordered a queso birria and it was so good I ordered another one to go so I could have it the next day. Every time we go to La Hacienda, the food is perfect and the service is great. They always have plenty of room so there is never a wait. The drive from San Jose to Morgan Hill is worth it!

We stopped by here on a complete whim while passing through. We were so happily surprised to find lightning fast and cheerful service, delicious food, and a fab Grand Margarita. Service was truly excellent! From sitting to getting drinks and food was less than 10 minutes. All wait staff were bustling and smiling. Place was packed, deservedly so. Thanks for such a happy accidental discovery!

I would not bring a group more than 4 people as it's pretty small.

The takoyaki was great, very generous with the flakes.

The karaage was a bit overcooked so it was tougher than I'd like.

Their choice of bowls makes it look like there's barely any food, but it's actually pretty deep so I think it's the same amount compared to other ramen places. Reminds me of a street Cafe in Japan.

The waitress was very nice.

The donburi was fine, the curry was fine, the ramen was great.

They just opened so people need to have some patience. The portions are relatively smaller than other ramen places, less meat too like only 2 slices of pork. Broth is well-seasoned. Just wish they had more ramen selection or oils (black garlic oil please!) Hopefully they’ll expand. Liked the katsu-don a lot.

I wouldn’t say it’s a restaurant where I’d bring a group of friends to socialize - definitely more of a “I’m craving a quick bite before work” vibe. Very small joint next to the Poke place. However, for the convenience of not having to drive 15+ miles for ramen, the food’s pretty good. I’ve also gotten doordash delivery from them before and I appreciate the packaging.

name: Bubbles & Brew
cuisine: Bar, Store, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Nice relaxing outdoor seating with live music on the weekends. Good small plate selection.
Great little restaurant. Happy hour 3-6pm. Good menu for food and great wine and beer options.
First time here. Calm and quiet. Service was great! Food was delicious specially lemon chicken.

Consistently good Greek food and solid drinks (get the Grand Opa Sangria). Zucchini Chips and the Opa! Lettuce Wraps are can’t miss dishes. My mom loves the meatloaf but it’s too much food for me. You’ll need a take home bag for the meatloaf. I’m partial to Lamb or Beef Souvlaki (medium rare) with Opa fries. There’s a lot of good food on this menu so if you’re like, “I don’t know what to eat tonight,” go to Opa! because you’ll find something and it’ll be good.

name: MIMOSAS GOURMET MORGAN HILL
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
The food is pretty good. The serving sizes are enormous! The wait staff is good. It is a very good breakfast place. If you like oatmeal, theirs is great!
The music they play is too loud. It interferes with table conversations.
They have nice big televisions for watching games...but you cannot hear them...close captioning would be a nice touch.

Friendliest service people ever - they are quick, efficient and bend over backwards to make you happy.
The place itself is fairly big, open and clean - has both booths and tables- lot of windows/lighting great.
Big menu, both breakfast and lunch.
Like their other location, (pearl, south SJ) not crazy about the food/ spices.
The food quality is great, it just doesn’t add up. To my taste. I honestly think others might match up better.
Good crowd, kid friendly

Ohh- giant shared alcoholic drinks!!

name: Trail Dust BBQ
cuisine: Meal Takeaway, Liquor Store, Bar, Store, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment: The breakfast tacos are outstanding. I enjoy the brisket with scrambled eggs and barbecue sauce holding the jalapenos.  What deal at $5.73 with tax.  They are doggies friendly too.

I wish I had better things to say about my most recent experience here. The food was better 6 mo. - 1 yr. ago, but even then, it was really just the meats that made it worth the money.  The sides are all pretty disappointing...rubbery garlic bread, bland beans, slaw with no flavor and Mac and cheese that somehow manages to be too dry/chewy and too wet/mushy simultaneously. If the flavor was good, it might make up for this, but nope.
When I arrived to pick up my order, I stood there for 5 minutes, but there were no other customers except one table getting ready to leave.
I spent $75 to feed 2 people.
Maybe I'll go back eventually to see if any improvements have been made, but probably not for a long time.

FOOD
non dessert items are lacking in flavor. the portion sizes are VERY big. everyone had to take home leftovers so i recommend sharing one item per two people or something like that. dessert (waffle, crepe, pancake) was good though.

ENVIRONMENT
there was food all over the floor. the tables were too small to fit our plates—again portion sizes is very big so i recommend sharing to also save table space. there is also a lot of people so there may or may not be a wait/line

PARKING
very busy so it is hard to find parking. you may have to drive around for a while to find an open spot.

First time here and we will be back. I wanted to try the Waffles and also ordered the Joe Omelette which was splendid. The facility used to be a Sizzlers Restaurant, and they had to close down because of the nasty COVID back in 2019. Reyna was our waitress, and she was excellent and professional and courteous in her service. The coffee was nice and hot. The Blue Berry waffle was yum yum! ¡¡Muy Bueno!! The pancakes were also a hit with my lady. She enjoyed the fluffy and consistency in the batter made the pancakes proper for the belly and the palate. The facility was nice and big inside. A lot of room and they even had an extra room in the back section for private parties or meetings for any companies that wanted this restaurant as a company event. The place is in Morgan Hill California 18 miles south of San Jose and enjoyed finding something different in another town. They close at 2pm so they are open for breakfast and lunch. The food was EXCELLENT!!

This was the worst “Thai” food I have ever had! About 10 years ago I ate at Siam Morgan Hill and it was good. It is definitely not the same food! The Pad Thai was stuck together like glue and shaped as the to go container. The Pineapple Rice was horrible and super yellow I have never had pineapple fried rice like it. The “Crab”Rangoon was mainly all cream cheese barely any imitation crab. For the $64 I spent it was not worth it, this place is more like fast food. Don’t recommend it.

Siam Thai Restaurant in the Morgan Hill area offers a decent experience, though there are a few dishes that didn’t quite impress.

Drunken Noodles: The Drunken Noodles were pretty disappointing. The dish lacked the depth of flavor I was expecting and felt somewhat bland. The noodles were a bit too chewy, and the overall combination didn’t live up to the hype. I wouldn’t recommend this dish if you’re looking for something flavorful.

Panang Curry: On the other hand, the Panang Curry was much better. It had a decent flavor, and it paired really well with rice. The curry itself was rich and savory, with just the right amount of spice. If you’re going to Siam Thai, I’d definitely recommend ordering the curries over the noodles.

Service: The service was good. The staff were accommodating and attentive, making sure our needs were met throughout the meal. They were friendly and helped make the experience a bit more enjoyable.

Ambience: The ambience was pleasant overall. The restaurant has a nice, comfortable vibe, and the outdoor patio area is particularly pleasing to the eyes. It’s a relaxing spot to enjoy a meal, especially on a nice day when you can sit outside.

Overall, Siam Thai Restaurant is a decent option in Morgan Hill, with the curries standing out as the highlight of the menu. The service and ambience are good, but some dishes, like the Drunken Noodles, could use some improvement.

I lelf a review on this business almost a year ago. It was a mistake that I didn't  notice untill recently and it was negative, It was not ment for this restaurant it was ment for China Palace another restaurant in town that has been in the community for a very long time that has gone downhill, but this is not about them.  So I want to apologize, and leave a review for this restaurant that it deserves.
This restaurant has been a staple in Morgan Hill for as long as I can remember. I have lived in morgan hill since nineteen eighty nine. Im a bit of an O.G. The food here is delicious and consistent. I had not been here in a few years but once I realized that I left the sense deleted negative review. I had to come and show my support, and it is just as I remember, wonderful. Wonderful food and wonderful service. My parents have been come here for there for their anniversarys for going on 35 years, partly   because it's tradition, but also because they serve a unique menu of Japanese inspired cuisine with an American twist.  My grandparents alos used to also frequent offend. So if you haven't tried moon's kitchen, or if you just haven't been in a while  you really should make a vist this weekend.

They're friendly :) their service is excellent.
I’ve been here once and had an excellent experience. It was my partner's first time and he enjoyed the food. He even liked the salad here! Lol
Good mom n pops, a must have in morgan hill. Service was fast and dishes were prepared well.

Great food, easy to pick something from menu, and fast. Service was quick and efficient but a bit loud. Very much like a diner atmosphere. Would return to try other items then I might change my rating. So far so good.

Ordered to go 2 days ago. Both the large chicken phao had extremely hard chicken very hard to chew. Also the order of the Shaking beef we got had steak that was soo tough to chew, definitely not filet mignon like stated on menu. Very disappointed, usually quality is much better.

Ordered pho. The price was good. The spring role had seasoned bbq ( like teriyaki pork? ). It was interesting flavor.
The pho was good. I wish the soup was little more hot. I would visit this place again if i come this area.

BTW, i hope they remove the spider web in the restroom.

name: Margarita's Bar & Grill
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
Was recommended this place by friends and I'm so glad we went! We were all extremely happy with the food- everything tasted delicious 🤤 and very fresh.  Excellent salsa and warm chips. Everyone ordered off the Happy Hour menu and the meal was extremely affordable- especially for the size of the portions! Enough for leftovers later. The drinks were tasty and enormous as well... and effective!
Our waitress (and everyone else) was friendly and food and drinks came extremely fast. The decor is cool too- creative and unique. Lots of art everywhere- lots to look at while you're waiting if you're bored of the talk at your table (or if you're adhd like i am). I dig the living plants as well.

Great experience. 🤩🤩🤩🤩🤩

We'll definitely be back!

First timers. Services was great. The wait between table visit were just right. Food was yummy. Table salsa was really good. Decor was really nice and clean. Items were well priced. Will be back for sure!

PERFECT SPOT FOR DATE NIGHT!. It's your classic sushi restaurant that you can count on to hit the spot. Fish was SO fresh and everything we ordered was super tasty and delicious. The restaurant was clean and the servers were nice-- what more can you ask for from a restaurant??

We ordered:
Edamame- your standard salted edamame, a delightful snack for my kids

Toro on the rock- 10/10 recommend this! So fresh, melt in your mouth and it's topped with fresh wasabi. It's perfect!!

Jalapeño Hamachi- I love yellowtail, so this is a must for me

Kayla Roll- 10/10 the best role IMO.

Goku roll- also very delicious with a nice crunch!

Shrimp tempura roll- for my sister who doesn't eat anything raw. She enjoyed this!

Hamachi Kama- so so sooooo good and meaty!! Nice sized portion!

Spicy pork lunch plate- LOVED everything on the plate! It’s perfect for those who don’t eat raw. Perfect portion for me.

Salmon belly nigiri- the BEST! Melts in your mouth and I love the fresh wasabi

Goku Sushi was pretty good. The decor is quite charming with a mix of a traditional Japanese storefront facade inside and more modern characters scattered around.

The sushi was inventive and tasty.

We would recommend the Goku Special for most anyone (not pictured).

Came in today excited to order some carne asada fries and found out they sold papusas I wanted to give it a try but sadly was extremely disappointed with my food. During the wait for the food I overheard them talking about my papusa as if they had run out of certain supplies it seemed and kept staring over at me and my partner I felt something had went wrong and considered going to ask if something was wrong but I trusted them but they failed to communicate with me the whole time .I ordered a papusa queso & chicharon when I got home I found there was absolutely no meat and the carne asada fries had extremely poor presentation , the avocado was very bruised with gray and black markings only 4 literal pieces of jalapeños. I had to drive all the way back to ask for a full refund and while already being very frustrated with the food the lady helping me made matters worse she greeted me with attitude and was very condescending, she kept rambling on to me about how I looked young and insisted that I listened to “her advice “  ive worked in customer service for 4  years now of course i deal with angry customers from time to time or deal with a refund and the way she handled it was very immature and unprofessional I only asked for a full refund because of how unappetizing the food was and paid 6$ for basically a quesadilla. She was very difficult trying to show me her unopened avacados to show me “how fresh they were “ the interaction lasted almost 10 minutes because of how much she kept trying to lecture me overall very disappointed and unsatisfied with this place and visit , I was hoping to keep supporting this place but after the way I was treated today trust I will not be back and don’t recommend to anyone unless you want to pay for overpriced unsatisfying unappetizing food . I wish I had taken a picture of the food to share but I’ve seen similar reviews already saying they also had no meat in they’re orders

The Super Burrito without pico was great and the Quesabirria was also delicious. Will be coming back, plus they sell beer. Sure they'll only get better with time give it a try and review it yourself.

Their salsas are also pretty good the green was my favorite

name: The Running Shop and Hops
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Family & Pet Friendly place to grab a beer and just hang out. They have a huge selection of beers from different Northern California Breweries. Their first come first serve indoor & outdoor space provides a chill, relaxing, & fun environment. They have a small game room area & local food trucks - check their instagram schedule. The staff was great; attentive & helpful when deciding what beer to order. I’m coming back soon!
Lots of draft beer selections from Bay Area breweries. Family and pet friendly—a great place to hang out! Plus, they have some arcade machines on site, which is a big bonus.

name: A Jay's Cheese Steaks of Morgan Hill

reviews.comment: Decent cheese steaks and salads. Everything felt fresh. No real place to sit inside unfortunately.

Fish and Chip Review
7/10
Chips and fish are great. Both well fried and crispy, salt is just right. Lack of homemade tartar sauce, vinegar, and slaw make it the score it is.

Otherwise the sandwiches are GREAT. Can swap out the bread for other types.

I heard this place was family owned and local so I wanted to try.

They let me choose my own seating and were prompt. Their customer service was great.

Ambiance was fine. Their prices are pretty amazing and competitive.

They were so accommodating towards my baby’s plate. She liked her Flautas, which is always a plus!
My enchiladas were good. I was so impressed with their serving of food.

There is parking in the back.

The only thing I didn't like/ appreciate is that they gave my baby a lollipop without asking me for permission.
Other than that, give this place a try.

Just not my taste. It's certainly not bad, I know others like it a lot, but not me. Enchiladas Verdes didn't have a good Verde flavor. Fish tacos were a little fishy to me and flakes of fish as opposed to a fried piece of fish. Asada tacos were the best part and they were just okay. Rice was not bad but the beans were tasteless.  Won't be back but you might like it because everyone's taste is different.

I ordered Togo. Walnut prawns were delicious, large and tender. Lemon orange chicken and spicy honey chicken were okay, the chicken was a bit dry which I read on other reviews. The chicken fried rice was really flavorful, combo chow mein was okay the pork in it was overcooked, dry, I preferred the rice. Egg rolls were good, hot and sour sauce could have been spicier.

Phenomenal authentic Chinese food! Used to be Peking Palace, Kitchen of Grace has gone through a facelift and provides the same mouth watering dishes,, my dad’s favorite Chinese restaurant in Morgan Hill.  Excellent service!

I hadn't been here before. The service is great. Everyone is friendly. We had the shrimp appetizer with guacamole, and that was delicious. I got the chimichanga (I wanted something fried!) and my husband the chile colorado. We both thought the dishes were just ok. They weren't bad by any means but we've had tastier. The food did look good. I think the dishes can be a hit or miss. The place is popular, so they're doing something right.

I used to love Sinaloa. Man has this place gone down hill. Service was terrible. Waiter ignored us and was on his phone the whole time. The food was dry and seemed old. We had to ask for silverware. The waiter messed up our order and never came back. To top it off, we had to ask another waiter where our waiter went and for the bill. Don’t waste your time coming here!

name: Teresa's Morgan Hill Café
cuisine: Cafe, Meal Takeaway, Bakery, Store, Point Of Interest, Food, Establishment

reviews.comment: What a small, lovely business. We ordered to go via their online system. The order was ready at the time specified. One of the items we ordered wasn't out of stock , Crystal called me to find out what we'd like as a substitute. The two ladies working were very kind and welcoming. The food was delicious ! We enjoyed the tamale pie, Birra tacos, and Thai coconut soup. All were made from very fresh ingredients and were tasty. We ordered our meal to go.  I asked her to include napkins and utensils,  and she gave us plenty. It was nice that she included the condiments for the soup and wrote on the outside of the bag where the condiments were to be used.

only one person working behind the counter and we were a big group. she handled it well and service was great. food was lacking a bit of flavor though. the cafe js also hidden away in an obscure place. kind of hard to find

Saw this place was opening up in Morgan Hill and heard good things about it,  so came to check it out. It was a little bit of a wait, but we finally were sat down. It looked nicer inside then when it was Yolked. The wife ordered the Popeye omelet. She said it was ok. I ordered the chocolate chip pancakes...it was a bit busier than I expected....a lot of stuff going on on top of them, so I didn't enjoy them as much as other chocolate chip pancakes I've had elsewhere. The son had chicken tenders and fries. The  chicken tenders didn't look very appetizing. Similar to what you would throw in the microwave and warm up. Our food choices weren't the best, but we'd go back to try other things. Ambiance and service was pretty good.
Very cute, chic new breakfast spot. The serving sizes are a significant portion. The Georgia Peach mimosa was sooo good. The food and service was great too, I would definitely go back.

name: Chili's Grill & Bar
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: I recently decided to try this place after reading some glowing reviews, and it truly lived up to the hype! Heidi’s exceptional service turned what I planned as a quick bite and beer into a much longer, thoroughly enjoyable afternoon. Her attention and hospitality made all the difference, and the food exceeded my expectations, perfectly complementing the inviting atmosphere. Whether you're stopping by for a casual drink or a full meal, this spot delivers on all fronts. I’ll definitely be back for more!

My buddy and I went to Chili's for a late night dinner.  I got the 3 for me steak dinner. It's a perfect combo. 6oz steak with broccoli and mashed potaoes.potatoes. it also included my drink and a salad for like $16. It was very good and we also got chips and salsa (that I love). We sat at the bar and my buddy knew the bartender, that gave us great service ! We will be back.

If I could give zero stars, I would. I ordered ahead and my order was still somehow 20 minutes late and they proceeded to get every single part of it wrong. The only part of my order that was correct was a part that I was in charge of and that was my soda. This place is being run like a defunct zoo.
It was pretty good fresh just wish I had gotten my cheese sauce when I order the game day but I did get more wings then accounted for so if it makes up for that

I had the 2 piece chicken with potato salad and coleslaw and it came with garlic bread. The chicken was dry, but I give them the benefit of the doubt, it was slow, probably because of the rainy weather. If it was busier, the food might be fresher. The slaw and potato salad was good, and they had some fresh hot peppers and  delicious hot orange sauce in addition to the standard BBQ sauce. Surprisingly, the highlight for me was the garlic bread. It was very flavorful and perfectly soft on the inside and crunchy on the outside. Delicious. I will be coming back.
Great service and delicious food! Owners are super friendly! Highly recommended.

I’ve been here twice and the food has been phenomenal each time. As someone who doesn’t eat seafood I think their veggie rolls are great, the salted plum and cucumber roll is so unique and fun. Everyone that eats seafood that I’ve gone with loved their rolls too. Everything tastes high quality and fresh. Service is good too! Knowledgeable, friendly, accommodating with my toddler as well. Prices are fair for the quality and portions!

They have indoor dining now, plus take out, no delivery. Food is still delicious and fresh.
Update 4/30/2022: Very busy because the food is delicious! Good service. Definitely recommend! Update 8/27/2022: Vegetarian Yakisoba Noodles fantastic. California Roll fantastic. Tempura, Gyoza, Chicken Katsu fantastic.

Super authentic birria de chivo. Normally it can taste gamey and be very greasy but
this restaurant mastered it. As soon as I walked in I knew we had made the right decision. Don't let the location fool you. The servers are super nice and attentive! We will be returning!
1st time here the food was delicious I ordered a enchilada & beef taco this comes with beans ,rice waiters were great we also had a large group come for dinner

name: Boxseat Sports Grill
cuisine: Bar, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment:
I had an amazing experience at The Boxseat Sports Grill! The staff was friendly, attentive, and made me feel right at home from the moment I walked in. The interior is incredibly unique and well-decorated, with a giant boxing ring set right in the center of the restaurant, which adds a really fun and cool vibe. It’s a perfect spot for any sports fan, with pool tables, foosball, and TVs showing all the major games.

I ordered the Warrior Burger with garlic fries, and they were absolutely delicious! The burger was cooked perfectly—juicy and full of flavor, and the garlic fries had just the right amount of seasoning. Whether you’re there to catch a game, enjoy a good meal, or hang out with friends over some pool, this place has it all. Highly recommend!
Came in during a trip out to California, great food, great staff! Would recommend to anyone

name: Grinds Vines and Automobilia Cafe (GVA Cafe)
cuisine: Cafe, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Came for a lunch meeting and was greeted by amicable staff. It was very warm inside for a nice, chilly day outside. Ambiance for our door seating was good, next to main Street, not too noisy but bustling with cars. Chai tea latte was great (a little on the sweeter side) and the turkey sandwich on sourdough hit the spot. The prices are also very competitive and economically friendly for proportion. Quick service too!
Unfortunately the Staff wasn’t friendly (the girls ) it seemed like they didn’t get along with each other and they didn’t want to be working .food was delicious.

Yummy veggie burrito with fajitas was super fresh! Service is so friendly and fast. I’m from Sacramento and highly recommend to all if you haven’t tried it yet. Once you do, it is sure to be your favorite, too, in MoHi!!

Food is not good.  Ordered the super burrito al pastor.  First 10 bites just wet pinto beans.  Then a couple pieces of nasty boiled pork no sauce, no flavor, overcooked, not al pastor.  Then more wet beans.  Friend had carne asada tacos.  Also very bland, no flavor.  Would not visit again.

Really great spot for Vietnamese food. The food was fresh and cooked to perfection with no issues. The staff was very friendly and quick. I loved the number 25. It had a great flavor and very well cooked beef. The spring rolls were also very fresh and had a great thick peanut sauce.

I highly recommend the crab noodle soup (bún riêu), mì quảng (noodle dish from Central Vietnam). The food here is great in general. The coffee is good but I'll see if I can order less sweet next time. The good thing is they can speak English.

name: Chocotellacrepes
cuisine: Store, Food, Point Of Interest, Establishment

reviews.comment: Great place, also  great seating . from the savory to the sweets and best of all Santa Cruz coffee !!!! Am glade everything is locally sourced. Also fresh!!!  It’s great to know a local place makes açaí bowls. None of the fake stuff I loved my paradise bowl. Topped it with mixed very smoothie  my afternoon was fruitful.

Nice quiet breakfast (or anytime, they have heaters) Morgan Hill eatery. I had the savory sunrise crepe. It was light and tasty , which is what I was looking for. My wife had straw-nana crepe. It was very tasty. Fruit in every bite with Nutella on top. Yummm!

I was super impressed with the service when I went in with my SO to order for carry out. The servers were attentive, ensuring I didn’t need help deciphering menu items and ordering. We ended up getting the crab won tons, and I must mention that the crab is real, not imitation. Salt and pepper spareribs with little bits of hot peppers and green onion, giving it texture and spice. We also got the pot stickers and the seafood and beef noodle soup. Did I mention the dough is made fresh and that the potstickers and wontons are made by hand? I do not usually eat fried food, but everything was a hit. This is a new local go-to. Also, while we waited, the server brought us some snacks. I will be a repeat customer. I wish more businesses had this kind of customer service and quality food. I love this place!!!

I’ve been a loyal customer of Taste of China for over 25 years, and their Mongolian beef, honey walnut shrimp, and orange chicken have always been my favorites. Unfortunately, the original owner retired, and the restaurant closed four years ago, leaving a hole in my heart for their amazing food.

But the good news is, I recently discovered that Taste of China had reopened a new location just 25 miles from my home! I couldn’t believe it when I saw the familiar menu items listed on Google. When we arrived, I was beyond thrilled to find that the owner was there, and it felt like a reunion.

Not only did we get to enjoy all the incredible dishes I’ve missed for so long, but the owner, ever gracious and kind, treated us with extra dishes on the house, as a token of appreciation for being a loyal customer. The food was just as delicious as I remembered, and it’s clear the passion for great cooking hasn’t faded.

Thank you so much for bringing back these amazing flavors, and I wish you all the best with this new chapter. Welcome back, Taste of China – you've truly been missed!

name: Lawson's Bakery
cuisine: Bakery, Food, Point Of Interest, Store, Establishment

reviews.comment: We drove down to try the burnt almond cake. It is a small bakery that has a small but very good breakfast menu. The cake was very good. As per another person telling me. I let the cake sit out for about an hour to let the frosting get soft. This helps it stick to the cake . Be sure to slow down or you will drive right by it. It's a large white building right before the apartments. There's a large patio to enjoy the food.
First time here. Noisy place, considering small area. I ordered 2 eggs breakfast and latte. Wait time for food was over 25 min. Eggs were delicious 😋. Overall 4 stars. Could be faster service)

The food was delicious. We had the samosas, mango lassi, garlic & butter naan, chicken masala, and shrimp vindaloo. Service was great. The price was reasonable. The portions were good. The place is clean and neat . Even the restroom was clean. Definitely coming back.
Fresh and delicious food! Very nice clean and relax place. Very good service!
